d with Tina Noronha\r\n<h2><strong>Abhishek Banerjee Early life and Education:</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Banerjee was born in a Bengali family and he was an introverted child. He received his higher education from Delhi. Abhishek completed his graduation from Kirari Mal College, University of Delhi, and was a member of Kirori Mal\'s dramatics society. He completed his schooling at Kendriya Vidyalaya, Andrews Ganj in Delhi.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One day, after playing the role of Lord Rama in one of his school plays, he decided to make his career in acting. After completing his studies in Delhi he shifted to Mumbai to pursue his dream of becoming an actor.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1108 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/abhishek-banerjee-rajkumar-roathe-tv-freak.jpg\" alt=\"Early life and education | Abhishek Banerjee\" width=\"800\" height=\"576\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In an interview with PTI ( Press Trust Of India), he told something interesting. Abhishek said, “ When I came to Mumbai to act and it didn’t work out for me for a few years\". \"I thought I will go back to the training and the casting Room has been a great training space for me.”, he added.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Abhishek Banerjee As a Casting Director:</span></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In 2010 at the age of 23, he began his career as a casting associate with the Bollywood Movie </span><b><i>Once Upon A Time In Mumbai</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> where he worked with Ajay Devgan and Emraan Hashmi. <img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1100 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/abhishek-banerjee-in-once-upon-a-time-in-mumbai-the-tv-freak.jpg\" alt=\"Once upon time in Mumbai\" width=\"800\" height=\"560\" /></span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After seeing his work in the film \'Once Upon A Time In Mumbai (2010)” </span><b>Milan Luthria</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, the Hindi Film director offered him the job of a casting director. Abhishek Banerjee accepted the offer and became a casting director at the age of 24.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His first Hindi film as a casting director was,\' The Dirty Picture\' (2011). Then he continued to work in Hindi films.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He appeared in the YouTube Channel Screen Patti\'s comedy video Daaru Pe Charcha- Vijay Maal Legaya along with the famous youtube actor </span><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/jitendra-kumar-life-biography-and-bollywood-journey/\"><b>Jitendra Kumar</b></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Aka Jeetu Bhaiyaa. </span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As a casting director, he has worked on many blockbuster films. In 2017, he opened a casting company, </span><b>\'Casting Bay</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\' along with his partner Anmol Ahuja. In the same year, Abhishek was featured in the film \'Ajji\' along with \'Sadiya Siddiqui, Vikas Kumar, Smita Tambe, Sudhir Pandey, and others.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As an actor, he rose to fame with meatier characters in films like Phillauri (2017), Stree(2018), Dreamgirl (2019), and Bala (2019). <img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1101 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/abhishek-banerjee-in-phillauri-the-tv-freak.jpg\" alt=\"Pillauri- Abhishek Banerjee\" width=\"800\" height=\"576\" /></span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It was the impactful roles in the web series that earned him praise and recognition for good work.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>Film Career of Abhishek Banerjee:</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Abhishek Banerjee has showcased his many talents in Bollywood movies. He made his acting debut in </span><b>Rang De Basanti </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">in the year 2006 he played a college guy in this film.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After this, he acted in </span><b>Soul of Sand</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in the In 2010 he played the role of Daya. </span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the year 2012, Banerjee appeared in a short film</span><b> What Happened When</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Wherein in 2015, he acted in another short film </span><b>\'Fuddu Boys\'</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> he played the role of Lambu. </span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It was in 2015, he appeared in TVF Pitchers – a tv mini-series in 2015 and he played Bhati in one episode.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Agli Baar</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Abhishek played Mahindra in 2015. In 2017 in the Bollywood movie</span><b> \' Phillauri\' </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">he played the role of Soma. In </span><b>“Inside Edge”</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> he played a Drug Dealer role.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>Abhishek Banerjee Versatility as an actor:</strong></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Palatal Lok: </span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Paatal Lok now has become the talk of the town. Abhishek Banerjee portrays the role of a stone- blooded serial killer Hathoda Tyagi, to perfection. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Without saying much Abhishek managed to express a lot, making everyone a fan of their acting abilities. Hathoda Tyagi has brought the spotlight on him.<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1102 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/abhishek-banerjee-in-pataal-lok-the-tv-freak.jpg\" alt=\"Paatal lok\" width=\"800\" height=\"560\" /></span>\r\n<h3><strong>STREE: </strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In this film, Abhishek plays Rajkumar Rao\'s best friend Jana, who can be best described as an innocent and helpless romantic. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, when he is possessed by the Stree, he turns into a bloodthirsty monster and gives her nightmares with his growls and bloodlust.<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1103 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/abhishek-banerjee-in-stree-the-tv-freak.jpg\" alt=\"Stree\" width=\"800\" height=\"560\" /></span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">MIRZAPUR SEASON 2:</span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">While Paatal lol was successfully able to divert us for a while from our wait for Mirzapur\'s season two, it reminds us of the show in a lot of ways. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In Mirzapur season 2, Abhishek Banerjee seems to have released his potential for a dark role as in Mirzapur he plays the role of Munna Bhaiya\'s right-hand man co-founder. His job is basically arranging for anything and everything wrong that Munna Bhaiya\'s heart desires. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">While he still didn’t give us chills as he did in Paatal Lok, watching Divyendu and Abhishek Banerjee in the same frame was a delight.<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1104 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/abhishek-banerjee-in-mirzapur-the-tv-freak.jpg\" alt=\"MIrzapur season 2\" width=\"800\" height=\"560\" /></span>\r\n<h3><strong>BALA:</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There is the only thing that we will always remember about this Bollywood movie. That thing is what Ayushmann Khurrana\'s looked like when he was bald and those cringe Tik Toks.<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1107 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/abhishek-banerjee-the-tv-freak-in-bala.jpg\" alt=\"Bala\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" /> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However one of the performances that you may have missed out on Abhishek Banerjee, who played the role of Bala\'s Barber. Abhishek played the role of Ajju with colored hair and Jazzy outfits.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Dream Girl:</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another film, in which Abhishek Banerjee Shared Screen Space with Ayushman is Dream Girl. In this romcom, Banerjee plays the role of a cabinet leader who is also the elder brother of Ayushmann\'s love interest. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First, he falls in love with Ayushman Khurrana\'s Pooja, then insists on meeting her, but also marrying her and breaking his vow of celibacy just for her. But little does he know that his love interest is his soon to be brother in law.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>TVF PITCHERS:</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This series was among the early web series that garnered a lot of talk around it. The viral fever put together a story of four unlikely men, who quit their job to run a start-up.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1106 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/abhishek-banerjee-in-humurously-the-tv-freak.jpg\" alt=\"Banerjee - TVF pictures\" width=\"700\" height=\"700\" />\r\n<h2><strong>As a writer:</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Abhishek Banerjee did two films as a writer one is a very famous <strong>new Hindi movie</strong> of Anushka Sharma Pari which </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">was released in 2018 another was a Bengali movie Aashbo Aarek Din (come another day) in the year 2013. He got some special appearances in two films like The Twist. The Laila Manju(2018).</span>\r\n<h2>Read Some Other Stories and Bio:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/shweta-tripathi-biography-tv-shows-movies-and-commercial-ads/\">Struggling story of Shweta Tripathi</a></li>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/pankaj-tripathi-biography-movies-tv-and-awards/\">How did Manoj Bajpai\'s life make Pankaj Tiwari work in movies?</a></li>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/gulabo-sitabo-movie-2020/\">Gulabo Sitabo Movie (2020) | Trailer and Story</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>','Abhishek Banerjee Casting Director and Acting Journey','','publish','open','open','','abhishek-banerjee-casting-director-and-acting-journey','','https://www.thetvfreak.com/shweta-tripathi-biography-tv-shows-movies-and-commercial-ads/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/pankaj-tripathi-biography-movies-tv-and-awards/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/gulabo-sitabo-movie-2020/','2020-12-26 13:32:54','2020-12-26 08:02:54','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=1097',0,'post','',0),(1142,1,'2020-06-30 19:06:41','2020-06-30 13:36:41','<div align=\"justify\">\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When it comes to building up hype and expectation, no other place can beat the lush green hillside of Los Angeles named <strong>Hollywood</strong>. For decades Hollywood has produced numbers of sequels of successful movies. Sometimes winning praise and accolades, sometimes showering the audience with sheer disappointment. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It is not easy to pick a handful from this vast wilderness of motion pictures. Here we’ve selected the top ten. This selection is in accordance with a cult fan base. Each of these films introduced a whole new genre in the history of Hollywood.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>10. Fast &amp; Furious Hollywood Movie:</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1119 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/