e.com/watch?v=D4kTFf9qOwQ[/embedyt]\r\n<div align=\"justify\">\r\n<h2><strong>8. Jurassic Park Hollywood movie:</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1139 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Jurasic-park-min.jpg\" alt=\"Jurasic park\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This Sci-fi adventure series makes the top ten largely because of its portrayal of dinosaurs in humanistic posture, unlike its predecessor productions where they were only monsters. Largely thanks to Steven Spielberg for the unique conceptual development and a clear scientific explanation to back up the storyline. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Though the series saw a decline when Spielberg left the franchise and the general audience almost saw the end of it, surprisingly saw the revival with changing the name to Jurassic World in 2015 and since then successfully carrying on with a worldwide appeal.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1126 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Jurassic-world-movie-min.jpg\" alt=\"Jurassic world\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gjIaV6CU0wA[/embedyt]\r\n<h3>Watch Latest Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aJJrkyHas78[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>7. Dark Knight trilogy:</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1132 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/the-dark-night-trilogy-min.jpg\" alt=\"the dark night\" width=\"600\" height=\"432\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Who thought a fictional character from a comic can claim a position in Academy awards? None I bet. Until Dark Knight. Christopher Nolan got an already dead and mummified superhero with a hideous reputation in the box office (watch Batman Forever or Batman &amp; Robin if you dare) team up with Christian Bale, yet to