" width=\"740\" height=\"481\" />\r\n<div align=\"justify\">\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A very underrated actor of Bollywood, Abhay Deol likes to remain in the shadows. Although being a nephew of superstar Dharmendra, Abhay Deol never really flaunted his “filmy” background. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Also, he earned his spot in the acting circuit on his own. Though he has “Deol” as a surname, he didn’t take any help from his uncle Dharmendra to pursue an acting career. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This would come as a shocker to everyone as it was usually thought that he is another product of nepotism.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Abhay School Days &amp; Debut</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1992 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/1-min.jpg\" alt=\"abhay Deol young\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Since his school days, Abhay was fascinated by the world of characters and acting. He took up acting classes and soon joined theatre. He did many plays from his school and later college. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hence, he was a theatre artist first, before becoming a Bollywood star. He often stated in many interviews that he chose the acting career himself. He wasn’t pushed into it by his father or uncle.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Abhay Deol genuinely liked acting on stage in theatres and wanted to follow his passion and make a career out of it. In his school days, he learned dancing as well as karate to keep himself fit. He also refused to eat junk food as he knew it would de-shape his body and it would affect him later to land leading roles in movies.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1993 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/2-min.jpg\" alt=\"Abhay deol Socha na tha\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Soon his talent was spotted by<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Imtiaz_Ali_(director)\" rel=\"nofollow\"> Imtiaz Ali</a> in theatre workshops. After a long casting process, Abhay Deol was finalized as a lead in ‘Socha Na Tha’. Abhay Deol starred against Ayesha Takiya. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His performance was appreciated in the film. The movie was average in terms of box office collections. It was directed by then lesser-known director Imtiaz Ali, who later produced gems like Jab We Met and Rockstar. Both the actor and director received praise for their noteworthy performances. </span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1994 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-min.jpg\" alt=\"Abhay deol honnymoon\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Abhay tasted his first success in ‘Honeymoon Travels Pvt. Ltd (IMDb: 6.1) released in 2007. This gave a huge boost to Abhay’s career and he also gained a lot of confidence in himself after this film. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film showcased the story of six couples who traveled to Goa to celebrate their honeymoon. The film was produced by Farhaan Akhtar, who later collaborated with Abhay Deol in one of his career-best movies ‘Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara’.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Abhay Rise to Prominence</b></h2>\r\n<h3>Beginning in the Industry:</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The year 2007 saw Abhay in prime light. After tasting commercial and raw success in ‘Honeymoon Travels’, he went on to do two of <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-movies-of-abhay-deol/\">Abhay Deol\'s best movies</a>. ‘Ek Chalis Ki Last Local’ was a crime film set in the fast-paced city of Mumbai. It showcased the struggles of a common man and his journey on the path of crime and destruction.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1995 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/4-min.jpg\" alt=\"‘Ek Chalis Ki Last Local’\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It was followed by a thriller ‘Manorama Six Feet Under’. The later, ‘Manorama Six Feet Under’ is considered one of his best works of all time. Also, the movie is one of the best-underrated Bollywood movies of all time. ‘Manorama’, if you haven’t seen it, is a must-watch and we highly recommend you to watch it. basically, the plot is in Rajasthan and has some shocking twists which makings it an engaging <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/best-crime-movies-based-on-true-life-stories/\">crime-thriller</a>. </span>\r\n<h3>Now Time for the best contribution:</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1989 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/6-min.jpg\" alt=\"Oye Lucky Lucky Oye\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Abhay went on to do many prominent roles later on. His film, Oye Lucky Lucky Oye in 2008 was a black comedy. Usually black-comedies bomb at the box and get negative responses. But surprisingly, this film received high critical acclaim and even today is a delight to watch. But it was a disaster at the box office because it released a day after the 26/11 terror attacks in Mumbai. Not one person dared to step out and go in public places as the terrorist attacks shook the whole country. Hence the makers of this brilliant film lost their money, alas, to terrorism. </span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1990 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/7-min.jpg\" alt=\"Dev D\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His first major stardom moment came in 2009 when he accepted the movie ‘DevD’ directed by Anurag Kashyap. Devdas had been already made into a movie two times earlier. But DevD brought in a whole new angle to the classic and discussed modern-day problems of youth.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ATZB8mwU3M0[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It also took a stand on drugs, alcohol, and abusive problems of the youth nowadays. The film was highly praised for its experimental and noteworthy soundtrack and exceptional narrative. Abhay Deol’s performance as modern-day Dev struck a chord with the masses and was gladly remarkable in that role. It felt as if the actor was at ease in his character and only he was to play it.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1784 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/14-min.jpg\" alt=\"Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara(2011) Abhay Deol\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is one of the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-15-movies-on-friendship-that-you-must-watch/\">best movies on friendship</a> you should watch of all time. The year 2011 brought Abhay his first nomination in the Filmfare Awards as Best Supporting Actor. His decision to take on the role of Kabir in ‘Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara’ was spot on and changed his life. The movie is considered a modern classic and <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">best Bollywood movies</a> ever made. Abhay Deol was in a lead role alongside Farhaan Akhtar and Hritik Roshan. The film also had Kalki Koechlin, Katrina Kaif, and Naseeruddin Shah in supporting roles.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch the trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FJrpcDgC3zU[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> ZNMD earned more than 1.53 Billion rupees worldwide and went on to break the record of Dhoom 2 at the box-office. The location of this film was primarily in Spain. Abhay Deol gave him 100% for the film. He took training from professionals to be a deep-sea diver, just to be comfortable while filming it for the diving sequence in the film. </span>\r\n<h2><b>Abhay Deol Controversies</b></h2>\r\n<h3><b>Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara awards nominations</b>:</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1991 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/8-min.jpg\" alt=\"Abhay Deol \" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\nAfter the suicide of <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/sushant-singh-rajput-facts-journey-to-bollywood/\">Shushant Singh Rajput</a>, he said something big.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Abhay sparked a controversy regarding Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara when he slammed B-town for considering him as a supporting actor in the movie. The film has 3 main leads, played by Abhay, Hritik, and Farhaan. But the nomination was only for Hritik Roshan in Best Actor category in various award functions including the Filmfare.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Abhay Deol and Farhaan Akhtar were in the Best Supporting Actor nomination category. And this clearly showed that the industry award functions were ignoring them as potential leads for the film. This made Abhay furious and criticized the functions. Later Farhaan clarified that he didn’t feel bad about it and gladly accepted being in that category.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vmUI0esRvWA[/embedyt]\r\n<h3>Abhay Deol A<strong>t MAMI festival:</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">People were also trolling him when he spoke openly at the MAMI festival in Mumbai about banning the Pakistani actors and filmmakers. He said that if we are banning Pakistanis, then the import-export trade, goods, and other things also should be banned, and not just artists. Though many thought he was fearless in his opinions, some trolled him for raising voice in support of Paki actors and also called him anti-national. </span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kP5dIHo9NTA[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What do you think about Abhay’s personality and his ability as an actor? Which of his films do you think is the best work ever done by Abhay Deol? </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Let us know your thoughts about his life and journey in the comment section below!</span>\r\n\r\n</div>','Abhay Deol | Personal life, Movies and Controversies','','publish','open','open','','abhay-deol-personal-life-movies-and-controversies','','https://www.thetvfreak.com/best-crime-movies-based-on-true-life-stories/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-movies-of-abhay-deol/','2020-12-26 12:38:07','2020-12-26 07:08:07','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=1987',0,'post','',1),(2004,3,'2020-08-08 22:55:47','2020-08-08 17:25:47','<div align=\"justify\">\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/abhay-deol-personal-life-movies-and-controversies/\">Abhay Deol</a> is one of the most underrated actors of the Bollywood industry. The man is known for taking unconventional roles and flashing his cute dimples. Although many consider him to be a <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/nepotism-and-favouritism-in-bollywood-star-kids-vs-outsiders/\">product of nepotism</a>, he clarifies that he did not receive any help from his uncle, Dharmendra in landing roles in movies. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This career-path was totally his choice after he started taking interest in theatre. Here is a comprehensive list of the best movies of Abhay Deol which are must-watch. We have included a wide variety of genres which were seen in his movies so that you can pick your interest and watch it, to enjoy the brilliance of the actor in these movies. </span>\r\n<h2><b>10) Honeymoon Travels Pvt Ltd (2007)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 6.1</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Reema Kagti</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Abhay Deol, Minissha Lamba, Boman Irani </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2010 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-min-min.jpg\" alt=\"Honeymoon Travels Pvt Ltd (2007) Abhay Deol\" width=\"600\" height=\"384\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Produced by Farhaan Akhtar, this travel film is full of fun and romantic moments. Six couples travel together to celebrate their honeymoon in Goa. They all meet randomly after they hire the same travel agency, ‘Honeymoon Travels’. What follows is fun moments between all the couples as they try to coordinate with each other. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film is a great one time watch, and Abhay Deol stands out with his performance. The soundtrack of this movie is really good and the song ‘Sajna ji Vari Vari’ was an outrage when the film was released. </span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4lRBmxsdmHM[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>9) Ek Chalis Ki Last Local (2007)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.3</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sanjay_Khanduri\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sanjay M. Khanduri </a></span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Abhay Deol, Neha Dhupia, Amit Mistry</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2011 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/4-min-min.jpg\" alt=\"Ek Chalis Ki Last Local (2007) Abhay Deol\" width=\"600\" height=\"384\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Have you ever missed your train? Or as they say in Maharashtra, your local? What difficulties can one go through if he/she misses out on the last train of the day? The plot of this film is the same. Two individuals miss the last local-train at 1:40 am at night. What follows is a fast-paced crime-thriller that will keep you engaged through-out the movie’s running minutes. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Abhay Deol and Neha Dhupia do a commendable job in taking the movie forward and keep you guessing what’s going to happen next.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yKVxfUjjT_A[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>8) Socha Na Tha (2005)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.4</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Imtiaz Ali</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Abhay Deol, Ayesha Takia, Ayesha Jhulka</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2008 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/2-min-min.jpg\" alt=\"Abhay Deol \" width=\"600\" height=\"384\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Written and directed by Imtiaz Ali, this movie is typical of the director’s genre. A light-hearted <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-romantic-comedies-that-are-forever-in-our-hearts/\">romantic comedy</a>. Socha Na Tha was the debut film of Abhay Deol. Imtiaz Ali had spotted his acting talents after watching him act in theatre plays and undoubtedly thought of offering him the lead role in his film. The plot is pretty straight-forward.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Abhay meets Ayesha Takia for an arranged marriage. But they reject each other and opt to be friends. Later when they get engaged to different partners, they realize the love for each other. The movie did average business at the box office, but enough for Abhay to kickstart his career.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5k0CDfpTb30[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>7) Raanjhanaa (2013)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.6</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Aanand L. Rai</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Dhanush, Sonam Kapoor, Abhay Deol</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2006 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/1-min-1.jpg\" alt=\"Raanjhanaa (2013) Abhay Deol\" width=\"600\" height=\"384\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Before directing the Tannu Weds Mannu franchise, Aanand L. Rai directed this superb romantic drama. It follows the story of a young couple who fight against society for their love to be accepted. This movie was the debut of south superstar Dhanush in the Bollywood industry. Surprisingly, the performance of Sonam Kapoor was also appreciated in the film. Abhay Deol plays the role of a young politician who aims to lead the rally against the ruling party. His short role in the film is the film’s highlight.</span>\r\n\r\nSo this is one of Abhay Deol Movies in which he has shown to the audience the best action in very little time and dialogues.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ER9vmhxFucg[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>6) Chakravyuh (2012)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 6.9</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Prakash Jha</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Arjun Rampal, Abhay Deol, Manoj Bajpayee</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2007 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/2-min-1.jpg\" alt=\"Abhay Deol \" width=\"600\" height=\"384\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another brilliant crime drama by Prakash Jha. Chakravyuh follows the story of two IPS officers, who take on the task of fighting the Naxal community in Jharkhand. The story of this film is somewhat similar to the Hollywood classic ‘The Departed’ where a police undercover joins the mafia to help the police catch them. Abhay Deol plays the rat who joins the Naxals and informs the police about their whereabouts. The film is shot in a very realistic way, as all Prakash Jha films are. That makes it an authentic viewing experience.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OnamEA8iLGY[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>5) Shanghai (2012)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.2</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Dibakar Banerjee</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Emraan Hashmi, Abhay Deol, Prasenjit Chatterjee</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2009 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-min-1.jpg\" alt=\"Shanghai (2012)\" width=\"600\" height=\"384\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Directed by Dibakar Banerjee, this political crime drama will leave you in awe. The performances in the film are exceptionally great. The on-screen chemistry between Emraan and Abhay as friends will leave you wanting for more. Both are showing their extreme acting talents in this one. Especially Emraan. He nailed his role to perfection.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xNbGmjD2_qQ[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>4) Oye Lucky Lucky Oye (2008)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.7</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Dibakar Banerjee</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Abhay Deol, Paresh Rawal, Neetu Chandra </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2013 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/6-min-min.jpg\" alt=\"Oye Lucky Lucky Oye (2008)\" width=\"600\" height=\"384\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dibakar Banerjee is known to make underrated gems. Oye Lucky Lucky Oye is a black comedy crime movie that has an interesting plot. The story revolves around Lucky who is a thief. The media goes on to make him a star as they debug his burglaries trying to figure out how he carried out the crimes. This one will make you roll with laughter. Although a disaster at the box office, this film is highly rated by the critics.</span>\r\n\r\nSo if you want to watch a strange comedy than this is one of the best Abhay Deol Movies.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3paPF30NJhg[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>3) DevD (2009)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 8.0</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Anurag Kashyap</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Abhay Deol, Mahie Gill, Kalki Koechlin</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2014 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/7-min-min.jpg\" alt=\"DevD (2009)\" width=\"600\" height=\"384\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When the news broke out in 2009 that Anurag Kashyap was making the remake of Devdas, everyone was sceptical about it. Especially after Sanjay Leela Bhansali nailed it in his version of the classic, with the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/successful-self-made-bollywood-stars-who-had-no-root-in-industry/\">star cast of Shah Rukh, Aishwarya and Madhuri</a>. But little did people expect DevD to turn out so well. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Initially, people were negative about Abhay Deol playing the title role of Dev, which was previously played by Bollywood superstar Shah Rukh Khan. But when the movie came out, everyone only had praises for the actor and director Anurag Kashyap. The film talks about modern-day youth problems and their take on drugs and prostitution. Career-best performance of Abhay Deol in a lead role. You surely don’t want to miss this one!</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9UVZprrlvtw[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>2) Manorama Six Feet Under (2007)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.7</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Navdeep Singh</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Abhay Deol, Gul Panag, Raima Sen</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2012 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/5-min-min.jpg\" alt=\"Manorama Six Feet Under (2007) Abhay Deol\" width=\"600\" height=\"384\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of the best-underrated thrillers of not only Abhay Deol but of Bollywood itself. The film when released was very under-appreciated. The critics rated it highly, but the audience was not ready to appreciate art cinema back then. The movie came to light recently when people started watching art cinema and underrated gems.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It took 13 years for people to understand the quality and brilliance of the plot Navdeep Singh presented through this film. Even though the first half is all build-up, it may feel a bit lagged. But the second half of the movie will leave you craving for more! Had it been a commercial success back then, it could have easily made it into a detective franchise. </span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Qjzr3bBHuho[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>1) Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara (2011)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 8.1</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Zoya Akhtar</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Hrithik Roshan, Farhan Akhtar, Abhay Deol</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2015 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/8-min-min.jpg\" alt=\"Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara (2011) Abhay Deol\" width=\"600\" height=\"384\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Who can say that this modern-day classic is the directorial debut of Zoya Akhtar? This masterpiece was an outrage in 2011, earning more than 1.53 billion rs worldwide. The story of three friends who decide to tour Spain by road and do adventure sports. A simple one-line plot, but the film depicts a thousand emotions.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The direction, acting, music, and locations everything is just spot on in the film. One of the all-time classics you can watch any time and enjoy! This film will never let you down in expectations and would leave you awestruck every time you watch it! </span>So, the list of Abhay Deol Movies can not be completed without this one.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FJrpcDgC3zU[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hope you liked our list of best movies by Abhay Deol. Which of the mentioned movies is your favorite? Which film according to you is the best acting performance of Abhay Deol? Do let us know in the comments section below!</span>\r\n\r\n</div>','Top 10 Movies of Abhay Deol | You Must See','','publish','open','open','','top-10-movies-of-abhay-deol','','https://www.thetvfreak.com/successful-self-made-bollywood-stars-who-had-no-root-in-industry/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/abhay-deol-personal-life-movies-and-controversies/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/nepotism-and-favouritism-in-bollywood-star-kids-vs-outsiders/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-romantic-comedies-that-are-forever-in-our-hearts/','2020-12-26 12:44:16','2020-12-26 07:14:16','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=2004',0,'post','',0),(2076,4,'2020-08-11 18:43:39','2020-08-11 13:13:39','<div align=\"justify\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2079 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/1-min-4.jpg\" alt=\"zaira wasim\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The young star of modern times, who found her fame when she starred in the 2016 <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-sports-movies-based-on-real-life-stories/\">biographical sports movie</a>, Dangal. A face which then everyone started to recognize with her wonderful acting ability | Zaira Wasim. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The young actress of Kashmiri background born at the turn of the century in the year 2000. Her short career has a lot of stories to be told as well. </span>From starring in one of the most successful movies of modern times to winning numerous awards to controversy about what she says publicly, Zaira Wasim has had a confusing career.\r\n\r\nSo what are the significant stories that have been a part of this young up and rising star? Read on ahead to find out more about her!\r\n<h2><strong>Zaira Wasim Start and Beginning:</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2080 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/2-min-4.jpg\" alt=\"zaira parents\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The upcoming superstar had a difficult time convincing her parents when she began her career, she always had a love for the big screen. With her parents strongly in opposition to her acting career. They needed convincing from her aunt and her school principal to allow her to pursue her acting career. With her Islamic background and so many other factors playing a part, her rise came with her struggle to achieve her dreams as well.</span>\r\n<h2><strong> Zaira Wasim Breakthrough Movie:</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2081 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-min-4.jpg\" alt=\" Dangal\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In 2016 director Nitin Tiwari then signed her up to star in the Sports Biography Dangal to star alongside a star as big as Aamir Khan. Battling through <strong>17,000 other applicants</strong> she won the signing and was a star of the movie. The movie told the story of the wrestler <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mahavir_Singh_Phogat\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mahavir Singh Phogat</a> and his daughters Geeta and Babita and his determination of making them world champions. With Zaira Wasim starring as a young Geeta Phogat, she had to show the determination of a young wrestler. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She underwent a bodybuilding phase that was quite tough on her in order to be perfect for the role. She practiced and learned swimming as well in order to be able to carry out the role as well as she could.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2083 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/5-min-3.jpg\" alt=\"Modeling\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dangal went on to become the highest-grossing Bollywood movie of all time and her rise to fame came along with it. She found appreciation for her work everywhere with critics applauding her performance. She won several awards as well which included the National Film Award for best supporting actress. Zaira also got the nominations for a Filmfare award as well for Best Female Debut.</span>\r\n\r\nShe also received the National Child Award for Exceptional Achievement from Mr. president.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2082 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/4-min-3.jpg\" alt=\"zaira wasim award president\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n<h2><strong>Rise To Stardom</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2084 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/6-min-3.jpg\" alt=\"zaira secret superstar\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Her next film also had the influence of <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/laal-singh-chaddha-2020-based-on-forrest-gump/\">Aamir Khan</a> when she played a lead character in <strong>Secret Superstar</strong>. Secret Superstar was released in 2017. Her rise did not stop at Dangal with Secret Superstar proving to be a hit as well, becoming the third highest-grossing Indian movie worldwide. It also became the highest ever grossing Indian movie with a female in the lead role.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">That is the quality of an Actor/ Actress. They just need a chance to prove themselves and that’s it. The movie Dangal has given her a chance to show her potential and now she is a Superstar.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She took on the role of a young 15-year-old. The girl wanted to be a singer but society and family stood in the way of her achieving her dreams. The awards kept coming for her winning the Filmfare Critics choice for Best Actress and received a nomination for Best Actress at the Filmfare Awards as well. </span>\r\n<h2><strong>Controversy Time</strong></h2>\r\n<h3><strong>Trimmed hair While Shooting Dangal:</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2085 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/7-min-3.jpg\" alt=\"zaira haircut\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It all began when she started shooting for Dangal. With her role requiring her to have small trimmed hair, the photos soon circulated on the internet with her getting criticism about it. Some said that she was going against her Islamic religion by taking an acting career. Being of Kashmiri background, when she met Chief Minister Mehbooba Mufti, she was again at the end of criticism and questioning. Her then public apology on social media which was deleted soon after found a lot of attention as well. It went as far as the young star receiving death threats.</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sexual Harassment On Flight:</span></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2086 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/8-min-3.jpg\" alt=\"Sexual Harassment On Flight\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Then in 2017, another story came about her in which she accused a man of sexual harassment on a flight on which she was. The airline she was traveling by apologized to her and arrested the accused and charged for the same. But when the accused and his wife narrated a different story to the public and found attention. The story became much more complicated. </span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2087 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/9-min-2.jpg\" alt=\" Sexual Harassment On Flight\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The public took two sides with Zaira becoming the victim of intense trolling as well from the internet. So far so that the Mumbai police intervened tweeting about how every victim of sexual harassment has the right to stand up when she has been harassed in such a manner. Ahead then in 2020, the accused was sentenced to 3 years in jail on molestation charges. The case then went to a higher court where the verdict is still pending. </span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yDmHykViXKA[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><strong>Big Announcement of Quitting Industry:</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another story in which the media focus was on her was in the middle of 2019 when the young actress took to social media to announce that she would be quitting film and not be acting in any movies anymore. She said that her decision was in order to protect her faith. </span>In a lengthy social media post she spoke of how while she may fit in Bollywood, she did not belong there.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2088 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/10-min-2.jpg\" alt=\"zaira wasim raveena tandon\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\nShe said that she had realized how it interfered with her connection with God and doesn’t want to lose that, and as a result would be cutting off all her ties to cinema and movie making. She insisted that the industry brought her a lot of fame, love, and affection. But she believed that she kept convincing herself that what she was doing was okay. But eventually, she said that she didn’t want it interfering with her relationship with God and decided to take this decision.\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Where is Zaira Wasim now?</span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Her last movie was ‘The Sky is Pink’. In this, she played a young motivational speaker character who narrates the love story of her parents over the years. She starred alongside a cast of Priyanka Chopra and Farhan Akhtar and yet caught the attention of so many. Again she received a nomination for awards and the public and world continued to love her work. Although she has now taken the decision to step away from the industry and would not be acting again.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What did you think of the rise of the star of Zaira Wasim? What have been your favourite roles of hers? Tell us about your favourite movies that she has starred in. Do you think she was right to leave the industry and will she return? Let us know about it all in the comment section below!</span>\r\n\r\n</div>','Zaira Wasim | Life, Movies, Stardom and Controversies','','publish','open','open','','zaira-wasim-life-movies-stardom-and-controversies','','https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-sports-movies-based-on-real-life-stories/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/laal-singh-chaddha-2020-based-on-forrest-gump/','2020-12-26 12:50:06','2020-12-26 07:20:06','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=2076',0,'post','',0),(2097,4,'2020-08-12 21:42:29','2020-08-12 16:12:29','<div align=\"justify\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2101 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/1-min-5.jpg\" alt=\"sanya malhotra\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This young Indian actress Sanya Malhotra has started to gain the fans that she so very deserves in today’s times. The Delhi born star who was the daughter of a middle-class couple found her own way into the industry. With an engineer father and housewife mother, Sanya learned dancing and found her interests remained in the acting industry as she grew up. Born into a middle-class Punjabi family, she was just as regular as the rest of us. So what is her story? Read ahead to find out the story of this<a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/successful-self-made-bollywood-stars-who-had-no-root-in-industry/\"> self-made star in this time of nepotism.</a></span>\r\n\r\nBirthday: 25 February 1992\r\nInstagram: @sanyamalhotra_\r\nTwitter: @sanyamalhotra07\r\nHeight: 1.52 m or 5\' 0\"\r\nFigure Measurement (approx): 32-26-32\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Sanya Malhotra Humble Beginnings</strong> </span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sanya Malhotra as we mentioned, did not come from any film background. Her story is that of a young girl who had big dreams. She became a trained dancer early in life and started competing in various competitions. Being trained in contemporary and ballet her dancing ability did not go unnoticed eventually being spotted and selected for the Dance India Dance reality TV show competition.</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Her Struggle for a Good Chance:</span></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2104 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/4-min-4.jpg\" alt=\"sanya malhotra\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She rose through there, with her dancing ability shining reaching the top 100 of the competition. After which she realized her true goals and moved to Mumbai in order to pursue her dreams. She then started auditioning for roles and advertisements but did not find much progress that easy to make. She even did some advertisements paying as little as 5000/- rupees but did them for the sake of exposure.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>The Big Break</strong></h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Big Competition:</span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Then she found the break that she was looking for when she auditioned for the Wrestling Biographical movie Dangal. Alongside <strong>Fatima Sanaa Shaikh</strong> who was a relative newcomer herself, Sanya underwent several rounds of this tough competition.  Competing against 10,000 other women who wanted the role as well before she finally landed the role in the movie.</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First Big Movie:</span></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2103 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-min-5.jpg\" alt=\"sanya malhotra dangal\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When she was signed on for the Nitin Tiwari Movie, she admitted that she did not know much about wrestling herself. But remained determined to be the best version of herself for the role. The wrestling based movie, in which she starred as the older <strong>Babita Kumari</strong> daughter of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mahavir_Singh_Phogat\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>Mahavir Singh Phogat</strong></a> played by Mr, Perfectionist <strong>Aamir Khan</strong> himself. The role of the daughter whom Mahavir had big dreams for, she did the role exceptionally.</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dangal Time:</span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Knowing little about wrestling, she did her research about the characteristics of a wrestler. She also researched their walking style, body language among so many other things, and trained to the best of her ability in order to be ready for the role. The hard work was rewarded as Dangal went on to be one of the highest-grossing movies ever made in India. </span>\r\n<h2><strong>Sanya Malhotra Controversies?</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Most stars in modern days have been a part of multiple controversies, with questions about what they say or the actions that they take. The other child actress from the same movie Dangal, <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/zaira-wasim-life-movies-stardom-and-controversies/\">Zaira Wasim was stuck in some big Controversies and finally, she has to left the industry</a>. They are always being watched and being a star in today’s times is a difficult job on its own. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">But Sanya Malhotra in her young career has not been a part of any significant controversies. As difficult as it is to imagine and believe, her young career has not been questioned by any such controversial decisions and choices on her part.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The young actress comes from a middle-class family and mainly keeps to herself while living in Mumbai. She is fairly outgoing but doesn’t involve what she doesn’t want to. With her, as an example, it is good to see the level headed and calm stars that are getting good roles along with her being a self-made star as well.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2102 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/2-min-5.jpg\" alt=\"Daniel Radcliffe form Harry Porter, wisted Sanya Malhotra on her Birthday\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\nWe are sure that you know about Daniel Radcliffe from Harry Porter, wisted Sanya Malhotra on her Birthday. Yes, you read it right Mr. Porter gave her his wishes on Instagram.\r\n<blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" style=\"background: #FFF; border: 0; border-radius: 3px; box-shadow: 0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width: 540px; min-width: 326px; padding: 0; width: calc(100% - 2px);\" data-instgrm-captioned=\"\" data-instgrm-permalink=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/B8_A80LhR1p/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" data-instgrm-version=\"12\">\r\n<div style=\"padding: 16px;\">\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; align-items: center;\">\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #f4f4f4; border-radius: 50%; flex-grow: 0; height: 40px; margin-right: 14px; width: 40px;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: column; flex-grow: 1; justify-content: center;\">\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #f4f4f4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; margin-bottom: 6px; width: 100px;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #f4f4f4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; width: 60px;\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"padding: 19% 0;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"display: block; height: 50px; margin: 0 auto 12px; width: 50px;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"padding-top: 8px;\">\r\n<div style=\"color: #3897f0; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 550; line-height: 18px;\">View this post on Instagram</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"padding: 12.5% 0;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; margin-bottom: 14px; align-items: center;\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #f4f4f4; border-radius: 50%; height: 12.5px; width: 12.5px;