-min-5.jpg\" alt=\"The Avengers (2012)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Who would’ve thought Marvel could make a talking tree as popular as it became? But ‘I am Groot’ because as common dialogue as it could be. With a grand bunch of unlikely heroes, these likeable bunch of misfits became the heroes we didn’t expect them to be. One of the must-watch Marvel movies that you definitely cannot miss out on!</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d96cjJhvlMA[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">12. Guardians of the Galaxy Vol 2 (2017)</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2395 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/12-min-4.jpg\" alt=\"Guardians of the Galaxy Vol 2 (2017)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Taking place fairly early after the first part, Volume 2 brought back the likeable misfits we loved so very much. A new dynamic and a new story based on the past of some. It remained just as loveable and enjoyable as the first one.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2cv2ueYnKjg[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">13. Avengers: Age of Ultron (2015)</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2396 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/13-min-3.jpg\" alt=\". Avengers: Age of Ultron (2015)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The second big crossover in the Marvel Cinematic Universe. This second installment of the Avengers brought out the fears of so many of the members and Tony Starks in particular. With Ultron being a manifestation of the fear that lived within Tony to become a threat to all of mankind. With the introduction of new characters, the Avengers must now rise.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u1OKBqHICMQ[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">14. Ant-Man (2015)</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2397 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/14-min-2.jpg\" alt=\"marvel movies in chronological order 2020\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Paul Rudd plays the ever so likeable thief Scott Lang who seemingly stumbles upon becoming the Ant-Man. The name as literal as the superhero, it would not be smart to underestimate his ability to resize himself as the Ant-Man along with his allies who are, yes you guessed it, Ants.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QfOZWGLT1JM[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">15. Captain America: Civil War (2016)</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2399 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/16-min-1.jpg\" alt=\"Captain America: Civil War (2016) marvel movies in chronological order 2020\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The next Captain America Movie was here, and with it, the after-effects of Age of Ultron remained. Although a Captain America movie, it is safe to say it was as good as another Avengers movie, with the main Avengers all returning for this one. With the conflicts between the members as high as ever, they now fight one other for their ideals. And oh, Spiderman is finally here in the MCU.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dKrVegVI0Us[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">16. Spiderman: Homecoming (2017)</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2400 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/17-min-1.jpg\" alt=\"Spiderman: Homecoming (2017)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After being introduced in the Captain America Movie, the young Tony Stark prodigy as made to be in the MCU, Peter Parker is here as Spiderman. The young kid returning from the high of being an Avenger, battles between what his priorities in life are as a young kid.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WWfz3Yri_o4[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">17. Doctor Strange (2016)</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2414 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/doctor-strange-min-1.jpg\" alt=\"marvel movies in chronological order 2020\" width=\"717\" height=\"477\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Oh, what would we do without Doctor Stephen Strange? A sceptical man about the world of magic goes on to be the greatest sorcerer around. Played by the wonderful Benedict Cumberbatch (Yes, we’ve spelt it right) the charisma and practicality along with the wonderful storytelling make it a very important movie in the universe. When watching the movies in chronological order in 2020 it is very important to watch this movie for story purposes.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=h7gvFravm4A[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">18. Black Panther (2018)</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2401 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/18-min.jpg\" alt=\"Black Panther (2018)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A game-changer with the movie about another character that was introduced in the Civil War alongside Spiderman. Black Panther was absolutely loved by audiences and critics, with the movie reaching the Oscars as well and being the only Marvel movie to reach those heights. About a seemingly third-world country Wakanda which has hidden its advancement from the world, Black Panther was a complete game-changer in the Marvel Universe.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xjDjIWPwcPU[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">19. Thor: Ragnarock (2017)</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2402 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/19-min.jpg\" alt=\"Thor: Ragnarock (2017)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Oh, Chris Hemsworth, how all of us love you. And along with it, we have Tom Hiddleston playing Loki which is another heartbreak on its own. Arguably the best Thor movie made out of the trilogy, the humour and storytelling are wonderful and the music is absolutely magnificent. The God of Thunder has to fight the battle that has come to haunt him from his father\'s past.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JBxQ_XYQJhc[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">20. Ant-Man and the Wasp (2018)</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2403 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/20-min.jpg\" alt=\"Ant-Man and the Wasp (2018)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Scott Lang returns and with him comes to the Wasp as well. The second installment of the Ant-Man brings more light-hearted comedic timing and a twist at the end in the post-credits which is not something you expect in the slightest.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UUkn-enk2RU[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">21. Black Widow (Unreleased)</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2404 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/21-min.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Finally, the much-awaited<a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/black-widow-2020-film/\"> Black Widow</a> movie that has been a very long time coming. Scheduled to be released in 2020, it is based before Avengers: Infinity War and finally after so many years of waiting gives Natasha Romanoff her own movie and story to be told. With her character just appearing in other movies until now it is very welcome to see her get her own movie.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_1eykFE1fSA[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">22. Avengers: Infinity War (2018)</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2416 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/post-750X480-3-min.jpg\" alt=\"marvel\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The first part of the brilliant, popular, and heartbreaking Franchise comes to an end with this and the next movie. Infinity War and Endgame brought about the end of Phase 1 of the Marvel Cinematic Universe. With the Avengers not on good terms and on the run, the biggest threat to the Universe Thanos has come along and is destroying everything in his path. And this time it isn’t just Earth\'s mightiest heroes, it is the Universe’s mightiest heroes that have to come together to fight this big and unstoppable threat.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QwievZ1Tx-8[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">23. Avengers: Endgame (2019)</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2406 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/23-min.jpg\" alt=\"marvel movies in chronological order 2020\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The heroes find out in Infinity War just how unstoppable Thanos is, and the aftermath of Thanos would remain for a very long time. But the Avengers are the Avengers for a good reason.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">They must rise and find a way to fix the mistakes and losses that the world has to bear. The guilt haunting them and the world in mourning, our Heroes must rise as one and take down this threat and end it for once and for all.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TcMBFSGVi1c[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Endgame completes phase 1 of the Marvel Cinematic Universe. For any person watching the MCU in chronological order, it is an absolute must to end the series with this movie. And the fans of Captain America has seen a lot in it. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Captain America uses Thor Hammer in this movie and that scene was awesome. It creates a big question, <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/how-powerful-is-captain-america-marvel/\">is Captain America is the strongest superhero</a>. With the excitement levels on record highs and constant screaming in the theatres, all we can say is “Avengers Assemble”. The only question that is unexplained in this movie is, <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/will-iron-man-return-after-death-in-endgame/\">will Iron Man return after death in Endgame</a>.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">24. Spiderman: Far From Home (2019)</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2407 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/24-min.jpg\" alt=\"marvel movies in chronological order 2020\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Spiderman begins the next phase of the Marvel Cinematic Universe and begins it in style. Another must-see movie that is as eye-catching and mesmerizing as the previous. Peter Parker is his own man now and Spiderman his own hero. With the limelight all on him and the expectation to rise up to Iron Man’s legacy, he must realize his true capabilities and believe in himself to be the star that everyone knows he can be.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LFoz8ZJWmPs[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What are your favourite Marvel movies that have ever been made? Do you think we have the order wrong? What would you like to see in the next phase of the Marvel Cinematic Universe? Let us know all your thoughts and beliefs in the comment section below!</span>','The Chronological order of the Marvel Cinematic Universe','','publish','open','open','','the-chronological-order-of-the-marvel-cinematic-universe','','https://www.thetvfreak.com/how-powerful-is-captain-america-marvel/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/black-widow-2020-film/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/will-iron-man-return-after-death-in-endgame/','2021-01-15 17:21:21','2021-01-15 11:51:21','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=2252',0,'post','',0),(2279,6,'2020-08-18 22:40:29','2020-08-18 17:10:29','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2288 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/1-min-12.jpg\" alt=\"Amrita Puri birthday \" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Born on 20th August 2020 Amrita Puri is a well-known face in the Bollywood industry. She is a sort of on and off a character on the screen. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After completing her post-graduation in Mass Communication, she always wanted to be a Bollywood actress.</span>\r\n\r\nAmrita Puri Instagram: @amupuri\r\nHer Twitter Account: @_amrita_puri\r\nAmrita puri age: 36\r\nAmrita Puri Birthday: 20 Aug 1983\r\n<h2><b>Journey to Bollywood</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">‘Kai Po Che’ actress Amrita Puri\'s Journey was a roller coaster ride for her with the starting push being the hardest one. Now when we say starting push what do you think it would be? </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You might be thinking that it is a breakthrough in Bollywood. No, my friend, you are wrong-it’s the struggle that started from her home.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mf97nknAtz4[/embedyt]\r\n<h2>Amrita Puri Struggle Story at TedX:</h2>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ii5nBm79WHs[/embedyt]\r\n<h3>What She Revealed:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MH9cUwIRcd0[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Family Issues</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You might be amazed to know that Amrita Puri is the Daughter of none other than </span><b>Aditya Puri (MD, HDFC Bank-India)</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You know that it becomes very hard for an Indian Family whose roots are in business and administration to send their child to Bollywood Industry. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">They do get surprised by their child’s decision to join the Industry.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2289 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/2-min-13.jpg\" alt=\"Amrita Puri family\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Initially, every parent whenever they listen to the phrase “Mama-Papa I want to become an actor or actress” the first answer is No. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">That too was the case with Mr. Puri. It is not that he didn’t want his daughter Amrita to be Successful but yes he had fear because of all sorts of news he heard about the Bollywood Industry. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">But believe it or not Today he is proud of his Daughter.</span>\r\n<h2>What does she think when signing a movie?</h2>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=crpVluja2C0[/embedyt]\r\n<h2>Struggle for a Big Role</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Initially, Amrita used to work for an advertising agency as a copywriter and later as a freelancer for a lifestyle magazine. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She sometimes said that if my father would have supported me in my initial days then I would have done graduation in acting rather than doing my honors in English.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nNekk07Qt2g[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Because doing an acting course gives the foundation and also takes you a step ahead from the other contenders who are in the race to become an actor.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now as soon as her graduation and post-graduation completed she jumped on to auditions. She used to audition for every ad-film and motion picture.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After a lot of Hustle, she got her first ad in the company </span><b>Kotex </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">and later she became the face of many brands such as </span><b>People’s First</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, </span><b>L’Oreal</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, and many more.</span>\r\n<h2>Amrita Puri Movies And TV Shows:</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She has done a TV serial <a title=\"Stories by Rabindranath Tagore\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stories_by_Rabindranath_Tagore\" rel=\"nofollow\"><i>Stories by Rabindranath Tagore</i></a> (2015) in which she played the character of Charulata. This Tv Serial has 26 Episodes. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Later in 2016, she appeared in Indian political thriller television series <i>P.O.W. - Bandi Yuddh Ke</i>. After This, in 2019 she did a web series  <i>Four More Shots Please!</i> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This became a famous series and liked by the audience so much. Basically, this was on friendship and oriented on women. She also did \"Made in Heaven\" in the same year.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2291 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/post-750X480-2-min-1.jpg\" alt=\"Amrita Puri FOur more shots please\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\nFor now, Amrita Puri Movies are very few in numbers but she is the leading star and would appear in more quality movies in the future.\r\n\r\nYou know maximum Amrita Puri movies are with Bollywood most Famous actors like Abhay Deol in Aisha, Rajkumar Rao &amp; Shushant Singh Rajput in Kai Po Che and Kangana Ranaut in Judgemental Hai Kya.\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>\r\n<h3><b>Aisha(2010)</b></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2287 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/4-min-12.jpg\" alt=\"Amrita Puri aisha\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She worked as a model for two years but did not get any film offer. So her confidence was getting down. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She was even thinking that if anything did not work then she might have to turn down copywriting again. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">But at that moment she got the role of Shefali Thakur (supporting actor)in the Bollywood movie </span><b>Aisha</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In Aisha, she had to work a lot, especially on the Haryanvi Ascent.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> And it was quite a tough job for Amrita as she belonged to Mumbai. Nevertheless, she fulfilled the role and was also </span><b>nominated for a Filmfare Award</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in the Best Debut Actor(Female) Category. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">But she was not satisfied with it as she wanted a role in which she would be introduced as a lead. And finally, she gets it- Look down the heading below.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>\r\n<h3><b>Kai Po Che (2013)</b></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2290 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-min-13.jpg\" alt=\"Amrita Puri aisha Kai Po che\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You would be amazed at how Amrita got the role of Vidya for this Bollywood movie. It goes like this when Abishek wrote the role of the character he wanted an actress with a fresh face and he auditioned various girls but to his hard luck, he never found one. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So on a fine party night, he goes on to meet Amrita and share a short story of the movie with her.</span>\r\n\r\nThis was the only Amrita Puri <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/sushant-singh-rajput-facts-journey-to-bollywood/\">Sushant Singh Rajpoot</a> movie. It was the best opportunity for both and Amrita and Sushant did it very well.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Amrita tried in the Auditions in the coming days with her dressing look being somehow connected to the character of the movie. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Director Abishek Kapoor finally came up to the conclusion that she would be the best personality for this lead role. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So a long journey of getting the lead role in a movie comes to an end.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>\r\n<h3><b>Blood Money (2012) &amp; Judgemental Hai Kya (2019)</b></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Amrita has also done a lead role in Blood Money(2012) where she was cast opposite Kunal Khemu. Her work was appreciated by her fans. Also, she played a handy role as Meghna Kumar in the movie Judgemental hai kya.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>\r\n<h3><b>83 </b><b>(2020)</b><b>: Upcoming Amrita Puri Movie </b></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Amrita is going to play Miss Vidya Srikkanth in her upcoming movie 83( Based on the INDIAN cricket team\'s world cup winning story in 1983) which showcases  Ranveer Singh as Kapil Dev. The poster released of the movie has already made a pinpoint in the heart of all the INDIANS.</span>\r\n<h2>Her Personal Life</h2>\r\nAmrita Puri Husband, Imrun Sethi <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Restauranter. He launched a new European Restaurant launch in Mumbai. They got married on Nov 11, 2017. But in January there was some news about her marriage.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It was said in an entertainment portal that is <a href=\"https://n