\">In a reply to which Farhan Akhtar wrote that he strongly denies her conspiracy theories though her anger is justified. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sajid’s sister Farah Khan also wrote that it’s hard to believe that his brother has misconduct of behaviour and she does not entertain this type of Behaviour and also stands aside with every woman who has been hurt with this type of misconduct. </span>\r\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">I deeply resent your insinuation that me or my family knew of his behaviour yet did nothing. Your anger is justified. Your conspiracy theories not. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/_Amrita_Puri?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@_Amrita_Puri</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/MCLptZioWR\">https://t.co/MCLptZioWR</a></p>\r\n— Farhan Akhtar (@FarOutAkhtar) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/FarOutAkhtar/status/1051000652741132288?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 13, 2018</a></blockquote>\r\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\r\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">This is a heartbreaking time for my family.We have to work through some very difficult issues. If my brother has behaved in this manner he has a lot to atone for.I don’t in any way endorse this behavior and Stand in solidarity with any woman who has been hurt.</p>\r\n— Farah Khan (@TheFarahKhan) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/TheFarahKhan/status/1050695932017295360?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">October 12, 2018</a></blockquote>\r\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At last Amrita Puri wrote an apology tweet to Mr.Farhan Akhtar saying it was not directed to him. And the matter finally settles down.</span>\r\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">My tweet was not directed to you. Are you related? Pardon my ignorance. Also it’s not fair to generalise as I did.