cent, Randeep gave many stellar performances throughout his acting career. Highly interested in making a career in sports, Randeep studied at Motilal Nehru School of Sports.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It was during his school days when he realized his passion for acting. He joined the theatre production of his school and actively participated in the theatre plays. Here are some of his best movies on Randeep Hooda birthday, you can select any one of them which you had not seen and enjoy. This is a comprehensive list of the top 10 movies of Randeep Hooda. </span>\r\n<h2><b>10) Once Upon A Time In Mumbaai (2010)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.4</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Milan Luthria</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Ajay Devgn, Emraan Hashmi, Kangana Ranaut, Randeep Hooda</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Firstly the film that truly marked the rise of the stellar career of Randeep Hooda was the Milan Luthria directed ‘Once Upon A Time In Mumbaai’. The Hindi film showcased the underworld rulings of Haji Mastaan and Dawood Ibrahim. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Set on the happenings of 1993 Mumbai blasts, the film follows the rise of one of the most dreaded gangsters of all time. Although the film is fictional, it has a close resemblance to the real-life Underworld wars that shock not only Mumbai but the whole of the country.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2314 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/11-min-min.jpg\" alt=\"randeep hooda hit movies\" width=\"840\" height=\"520\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Secondly, the film was welcomed by high praise by both the audience as well as the critics. Only after it’s one week of a run at the box office, the film was declared as a hit.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> And no doubt that Ajay Devgan and Emraan Hashmi had done wonderful work here. Critics love them for this one. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Emraan probably gave his career-best performance in this film.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is one of Randeep Hooda Films in which he played ACP of the crime branch in the Hindi film, and his narration is what makes the film forward. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Even in less screen time offered, Randeep gave one of the memorable performances of his career. The actor also won the Best Supporting Actor award at the Lions Gold Awards for his graceful performance in the film.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5Tk4DtG_iEs[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>9) Saheb Biwi Aur Gangster (2011)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.2</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Tigmanshu Dhulia</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Jimmy Sheirgill, Mahie Gill, Randeep Hooda</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tigmanshu Dhulia is known for directing under-rated gems. One of such gems is Saheb Biwi Aur Gangster. It is the initial part of the Saheb Biwi series. It has all the aspects one can ask for in a thriller drama movie. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film is filled with ambition, betrayal, passion, and loyalty. The title and the basic theme of the movie were inspired by the 1962 flick ‘Saheb Biwi Aur Gulam’.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2322 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/10-min-min.jpg\" alt=\"Saheb Biwi Aur Gangster (2011) randeep hooda films\" width=\"840\" height=\"520\" /></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film gained a high appreciation and applaud from the critics. All the top critics were impressed by Tigmanshu’s direction and were blown away by the performance of Randeep Hooda. This contribution to Randeep Hooda movies list is unpredictable and well satisfying. And it is marked the rise of Randeep as a bankable actor.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tigmanshu Dhulia won the Best Director award in the Stardust Awards. Randeep Hooda also earned his first nomination in the IIFA awards in the category of Best Supporting Actor Male.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xFyQTtD6BzM[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>8) Monsoon Wedding (2001)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.3</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Mira Nair</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Randeep Hooda, Naseeruddin Shah, Lillete Dubey, Shefali Shah </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Very less is known or talked about this masterpiece by Mira Nair. This film marked the debut of Randeep Hooda. And what a stellar debut it was! The film was nominated as the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-romantic-comedies-that-are-forever-in-our-hearts/\">best romantic movie</a> of the 21st century by IndieWire. And yet, no one noticed the film, let alone watching it!</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2319 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/5-min-min-1.jpg\" alt=\"randeep hooda film\" width=\"840\" height=\"520\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Hindi film captures the highs and lows of a Punjabi Hindu wedding in New Delhi. The romance building up in the various characters is beautifully captured in the movie. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film was a successful international collaboration between production houses from India, the US, Italy, France, and Germany. The film was highly received in film festivals across the world. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Monsoon Wedding won the Golden Lion award as the best feature film. Later the cast and crew were on the seventh heaven when the film received a nomination at the Golden Globes Awards. The soundtrack of the film was so wonderful that it received a separate feature in 2014 at Broadway.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sjQjw-UyAX0[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>7) Sultan (2016)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.0</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ali_Abbas_Zafar\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ali Abbas Zafar</a></span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Salman Khan, Amit Sadh, Randeep Hooda, Anushka Sharma</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of the top 5 highest-grossing and earring Indian Bollywood <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">Hindi movies</a> ever, Sultan earned 623.33 crores worldwide. The Salman Khan starrer was a complete rage in 2016. It was produced under the YRF banner and also featured Anushka Sharma in the lead role. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The story followed a fictional wrestler who takes on the journey to become a world champion. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2318 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/4-min-min-1.jpg\" alt=\"Top 10 movies of Randeep Hooda\" width=\"840\" height=\"520\" /></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Randeep Hooda played the role of Sultan’s trainer and coach. He was at first criticized as fans couldn’t accept their favourite superstar being trained by a noobie actor. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">But Randeep let his acting skills do all the talking. He spent months training hard to make his body built as big as Salman’s to fit for the role. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His hard work was rewarded when each and everyone leaving the theatre praised the actor’s short but long-lasting role. </span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wPxqcq6Byq0[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>6) Rang Rasiya-Colours of Passion (2008)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.1</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Ketan Mehta</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Randeep Hooda, Nandana Sen, Paresh Rawal</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The career of Randeep Hooda is full of underrated and under-appreciated gems. One such choice of his is Rang Rasiya. This Randeep Hooda film is a biopic on Raja Ravi Varma, a painter of the 19th century.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2320 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-min-min-2.jpg\" alt=\"randeep hooda movies list\" width=\"840\" height=\"520\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You may ask, what’s so special in the life of a painter that a whole feature film is about him! Well, he was the painter who first gave us the painting of Mother India. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">Bollywood movie</a> is exceptionally great in handling topics such as nudism, sexism, and nationalism. Randeep Hooda fit perfectly into the character of the painter and did a commendable job. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Though the Hindi film was ignored by the masses, critics still consider it a win for cinema that such a great story could see the light of the day in theatres.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_TC8o690ns0[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>5) Bombay Talkies (2013)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 6.7</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Zoya Akhtar, Dibakar Banerjee</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Rani Mukerji, Randeep Hooda, Saqib Saleem</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">An Anthology of some sort, Bombay Talkies was the much talked about collaborative project of Bollywood industry in 2013. It consisted of four short stories, or rather short <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">Hindi films</a>, directed by cults like Karan Johar, Dibakar Banerjee, Zoya Akhtar, and Anurag Kashyap.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2315 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/2-min-min-1.jpg\" alt=\"Bombay Talkies (2013)\" width=\"840\" height=\"520\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Bollywood movie marked the celebration of 100 years of Indian Cinema. It also celebrated the beginning of the modern era in Indian Cinema and hence this collaborative project took place to uphold the spirit of cinema. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Randeep Hooda was seen in the short film directed by Karan Johar which was first in the anthology. He played the character of Dev and shared the screen-space with Rani Mukharjee. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film very delicately showcased the life of homosexual people. It also had a brilliant message about marriage and life. The film and the actor received high praise all over the country and many critics cited the project as a must-watch.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=njzTBH8mZLU[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>4) Do Lafzon Ki Kahani (2016)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 6.5</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Deepak Tijori</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Kajal Aggarwal, Anil George, Randeep Hooda</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">An official remake of the Korean film ‘Always’, Do Lafzon Ki Kahani is a romantic drama and is one of the best Randeep Hooda films. Although the film bombed at the box-office, the reason we included the Hindi film in the top 10 movies of Randeep Hooda is purely based on his acting skills.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2325 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/earn-more.-20-min-1-1.jpg\" alt=\"randeep hooda movies\" width=\"840\" height=\"440\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The way he has portrayed the romantic lead is truly exceptional and believable. Very rarely you can feel the strong bond between the leads, and this film can make you strongly believe that the two actors are in love. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Randeep Hooda, who previously had not done the role of such kind, gave one of his best performances. Surely if you haven’t watched the film, we recommend you to give it a go!</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1ZuGVyVNVAY[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>3) Sarbjit (2016)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.3</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Omung Kumar</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Randeep Hooda, Aishwarya Rai Bachchan, Richa Chadha </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The year 2016 saw Randeep Hooda deliver gems like Laal Rang, Sultan, Do Lafzon Ki Kahani, and finally Sarbjit. Directed by Omung Kumar, Sarbjit marked the comeback of Aishwarya Rai Bachchan on the big screen.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2316 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/9-min-min.jpg\" alt=\"Sarbjit (2016) randeep hooda films\" width=\"840\" height=\"520\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film is a biopic on a man Sarbjit Singh. He was an Indian, who faced charges of terrorism and spying in Pakistan. In 1991, Sarbjit was being declared a terrorist and was sentenced to death by the Supreme Court of Pakistan. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film became one of Randeep Hooda hit movies after earning more than 50 crores at the box-office. The production cost was a mere 15 crores for the movie and hence it turned out to be a profitable venture for the producers. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Randeep Hooda as Sarbjit leaves a lasting impression and makes us root for the man who faced so much injustice in his life.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Aishwarya Rai Bachchan graced the role of Sarbjit’s sister and was effective as always on the silver screen. At first, nobody knows about Aishwarya that she will play the lead’s sister. But after the screening of the movie, everyone was happy with the performance that the actress did a commendable job in playing a 22-year-old, as well as a 60-year-old in the same movie. Critics loved this movie and the performance of the characters. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">These kinds of Randeep Hooda films again proves that Randeep is a bankable actor to carry the movie on his own shoulders.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q1kYpWU7apI[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>2) Highway (2014)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.6</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Imtiaz Ali</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Alia Bhatt, Randeep Hooda, Durgesh Kumar</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A total masterpiece by Imtiaz Ali, Highway is a grand package. The film has outstanding music, great direction, mindblowing performances, and a twist, no one sees coming. This Bollywood movie became the highlight of 2014 and both Randeep as well as Alia’s career. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A very lesser known fact of the movie is that it is based on an episode from Zee TV series called Rishtey. The episode was with the same name as the movie. Imtiaz Ali himself wrote and directed it.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2323 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/8-min-min-min.jpg\" alt=\"randeep films\" width=\"672\" height=\"416\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film showcases the story of a girl, who discovers freedom after she has been kidnapped. Also, most of the movie is a travel journey. You will this movie more interesting than the details are in the trailer.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hence we can see lots of beautiful sceneries, and soulful places in India we didn’t know existed. Also, we see the country so superbly in the film. And Imtiaz did his career-best work while directing the film. Another highlight of this movie is the brilliant music, none other than the legend himself, A R Rehman. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Randeep Hooda bagged his first Stardust Award in the category of Best Actor. On the same night, Imtiaz Ali also received an award for the Best Director. Randeep Hooda also received nominations for Most Entertaining Actor in a Social - Drama Film - Male category in the BIG Star Entertainment Awards and Best Actor in a leading role at the Star Guild Awards.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Don’t be misguided by the IMDB rating for this one! The film is one of the modern gems of Indian Cinema!</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LSrDD52bx4A[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>1) Extraction (2020)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 6.7</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Sam Hargrave</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Chris Hemsworth, Bryon Lerum, Ryder Lerum, Randeep Hooda</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Netflix special Extraction marked the Hollywood debut of Randeep Hooda. Yet again, Randeep plays the badass gangster who tries to save<a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/pankaj-tripathi-biography-movies-tv-and-awards/\"> Pankaj Tripathi</a>\'s son who is being kidnapped by the rival gang.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2321 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/7-min-min-1.jpg\" alt=\"Top 10 movies of Randeep Hooda\" width=\"840\" height=\"520\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The highlight of the movie is Chris Hemsworth of course, who gives us yet another action-packed gem of a movie. This is the only movie in Randeep Hooda <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/a-top-10-pick-of-hollywood-franchises-you-should-watch/\">Hollywood movies list</a> but in the future, we will surely get more.\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The action in the film will make you stir in your seats. From the opening scene to the climax of the film, each and every frame is just awesome. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film features chase sequences,<a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-13-war-movies-based-on-real-stories/\"> fist-fights, gunfights</a>, and even a few of the bazookas flying around. All the efforts, just to save a little kid.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L6P3nI6VnlY[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Bonus Movie:</b></h2>\r\n<h2><b>Laal Rang (2016)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 8.0</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Syed Ahmad Afzal</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Randeep Hooda, Akshay Oberoi, Rajniesh Duggall  </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/best-crime-movies-based-on-true-life-stories/\">Crime and action</a> suites Randeep Hooda. The reason why the movie gained a high rating is because of the direction and performances. Set in Haryana, the film is a total festival for those who love <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/best-crime-movies-based-on-true-life-stories/\">crime thrillers</a>.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2317 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/6-min-min-1.jpg\" alt=\"Laal Rang (2016) randeep hooda films\" width=\"840\" height=\"520\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Randeep Hooda is exceptionally great in portraying the role of a criminal who runs an illegal blood bank. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Although this Bollywood movie failed at the box office and received harsh reviews from critics, it is one of the best performances by Randeep Hooda. The film does have a shade of grey, which is why it is a bit darker than the usual crime thrillers.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KzWsMbLwZ1M[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hope you liked our list of top 10 best movies of Randeep Hooda. Which of the mentioned Hindi movies is your favourite? </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Which film according to you is the best acting performance of Randeep Hooda? Do you think we missed any of his best work? </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do let us know in the comments section below!</span>\r\n<h3><b>ALSO READ:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-sports-movies-based-on-real-life-stories/\">Top sports movies based on true stories.</a></li>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-rated-movies-you-should-watch/\">Best rated movie of all time.</a></li>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/historical-fiction-movies-based-on-books/\">Watch these Novel based and real incident movies today</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Randeep Hooda Movies List | Must Watch These Top 10','','publish','open','open','','randeep-hooda-movies-list-must-watch-these-top-10','','https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-13-war-movies-based-on-real-stories/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-romantic-comedies-that-are-forever-in-our-hearts/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/a-top-10-pick-of-hollywood-franchises-you-should-watch/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/pankaj-tripathi-biography-movies-tv-and-awards/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/best-crime-movies-based-on-true-life-stories/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/top-sports-movies-based-on-real-life-stories/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/randeep-hooda-biography-career-and-struggles-in-film-industry/','2020-12-26 12:21:49','2020-12-26 06:51:49','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=2302',0,'post','',1),(2353,4,'2020-08-25 22:31:54','2020-08-25 17:01:54','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2358 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/1-min-15.jpg\" alt=\"jitender kumar actor\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The list of <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/successful-self-made-bollywood-stars-who-had-no-root-in-industry/\">underrated and unknown Indian actors</a> is quite long and arguably at the top of this list would be Jitendra Kumar. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another student of Engineering who never really fit in spite of his high marks and success. Tired of the 9 to 5 like so many of us, he decided to pursue his true love, acting.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In spite of making his debut on relatively unknown platforms and shows without a huge audience. He has developed into a wonderful actor. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">H</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">e has shown the country why he should be taken more seriously as an actor. So, if you are not familiar with him or do and want to know more about him, read on ahead to find out how he developed from being irrelevant to being the underrated start that he is today.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2359 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/2-min-15.jpg\" alt=\"Jitendra Kumar\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A Similar but Different Beginning</span></h2>\r\n<h3>The Beginning:</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jitendra Kumar like so many others was a young smart kid who was pursuing Engineering. As we know being an Engineer in India is the equivalent of being a drop in the ocean. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He went to IIT Kharagpur which is as prestigious as it sounds but at the same time not as much as well. As so many do, he decided to be a part of the stage acting. That would happen there in which he did quite well earning a name for himself within his campus. </span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2360 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/3-min-15.jpg\" alt=\"Jitendra Kumar kota\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He kept acting within the college and outside of it. Travelling with other artists and winning awards everywhere he acted outside as well. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He admitted that the recognition outside of the college, which came from veteran theatre actors meant a lot and gave him reassurances. Not many know this but he even had the small role of a Taxi Driver in the <strong>Naseeruddin Shah</strong> movie <strong>‘A Wednesday’</strong>.</span>\r\n<h3>The Big Decision:</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Like so many others, after Engineering he found himself in a remote town in Karnataka, working hours that did not let him breathe. No friends, no family, and a social life that did not exist. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The days were very hard on Jitendra. One day, he snapped and screamed at his superiors. The Japanese MNC he worked at gave him no peace, long hours, and humiliation at every turn. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His snap came as a shock throughout the company and he left his job tired of it. He mentions how it was quite a low point in his life, living there gave him his worst birthday ever with no calls from friends and a few from family.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2363 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/5-min-10.jpg\" alt=\"Jitendra Kumar tvf\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His snap and throwing away of a job did not go down in his family well. He tried to reassure his parents but they refused to listen with his father not speaking to him for a while. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With a heavy heart, he moved to Mumbai. Where he was invited by his old Senior living there pursuing a writing career. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He mentions how he asked if he will be paid, his friend tells him that he won’t be paid but he will get to act. And that has Jitendra sold and he moves to Mumbai to help his friend with a start-up which we all now know as ‘The Viral Fever Videos’ or ‘TVF’.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Acting Freedom</span></h2>\r\n<h3>TVF, The Famous Youtube Channel:</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCNJcSUSzUeFm8W9P7UUlSeQ\" rel=\"nofollow\">TVF</a> took off soon after with Jitendra Kumar having an important role in the acting part. The Youtube channel found attention all over the country. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With Jitendra being the heart of so many roles that he took on, it grew exponentially. The struggle was immense early in his days, with Jitendra admitting that he would live with money worries.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2362 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/4-min-14.jpg\" alt=\"Jitendra Kumar\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Watching the rickshaw meter hoping he had enough money as he went to auditions were a part of his everyday life. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Soon enough the auditions did not work out. But his natural acting skills were on display on their up and rising Youtube channel. The small work continued with him doing IIT coaching up to three times a week hoping for some financial stability. </span>\r\n<h3><strong>PITCHERS</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Then came Pitchers. Eventually, they made something that took everyone by storm. A show about a group of people who have their own startup. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">To understand better, you must understand that this show was before the days of Netflix, Amazon prime shows. This show was something that Indians had not seen before and loved the fact that there was so much quality from something so low budget. </span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2365 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/7-min-10.jpg\" alt=\"Jitendra Kumar tvf pitchers\" width=\"750\" height=\"421\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pitchers was a huge hit, with crowds gathering every time they visited colleges and the people shouting dialogues. Huge cheers and internet popularity was what they now had achieved. They continued to make more shows and Jitendra who was now known as ‘Jeetu’ gathered more fame. His name with his roles ahead including a show called ‘Kota Factory’, in which he went from ‘Jeetu’ to ‘Jeetu Bhaiya’.</span>\r\n<h3>The Big Hit<strong> \"Panchayat\":</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His rise continued and he eventually got an Amazon Prime show called ‘Panchayat’ in which he was the lead. The show was an immense hit and had a parallel to the life he lived so many years ago when he got a job after IIT Kharagpur. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The remote location, the lack of social life, and the difficulties he faced allowed him to understand the role he took on so much better. </span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2366 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/8-min-8.jpg\" alt=\"Jitendra Kumar panchayat\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It was not the first time, he had showcased something from his life onto the screen. When in a show he re-enacted the scene that took place when he confronted his father about his resigning from the job. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The frustration and ranting that he expressed with the emotion of the kid finding his way in life and the strict father looking to make sure his son would not be struggling for such a long time in life was something loved by everyone.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2370 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/39cbe2a3-a69b-43ba-9ddb-58e62179a9d0-1.jpg\" alt=\"jitendra kumar ayushman\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\" />\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Final Thoughts? </span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He is a wonderful actor and he has shown that he is very good with so many examples. Jitendra keeps adding to his resume and acting profile with wonderful work. He keeps doing and we hope he keeps doing such work ahead as well.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What has been your favourite Jeetu Bhaiya work? From the rants about Chemistry to the young man stuck in a dead town. Tell us about your favourite scenes from Jitendra Kumar. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you don’t know about him let us know if you will be watching his work now. Tell us all your thoughts in the comment section below!</span>','Jitendra Kumar | Life, Biography and Bollywood Journey','','publish','open','open','','jitendra-kumar-life-biography-and-bollywood-journey','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/successful-self-made-bollywood-stars-who-had-no-root-in-industry/','2021-01-24 17:07:59','2021-01-24 11:37:59','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=2353',0,'post','',0);
