etvfreak.com/top-10-romantic-comedies-that-are-forever-in-our-hearts/','2020-12-26 12:00:41','2020-12-26 06:30:41','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=2425',0,'post','',0),(2565,4,'2020-09-01 21:52:21','2020-09-01 16:22:21','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Love you 3000! A very strong yet emotional quote left by Tony Stark after his demise in the Avengers Endgame. It all started with Robert. It all ended with Robert. A beautiful journey of Tony Stark comes to an end. But the actor kept reinventing himself from time to time with various different projects. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">These projects were beyond his work at Marvel Studios and established himself as a Hollywood A-lister.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Here are some of the best movies by Robert Downey Jr which are a must-watch! This list does not contain any MCU movie, and sites upon the Robert Downey Jr <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">best movies</a> which he acted in.</span>\r\n<h2><b>10) Charlie Bartlett (2007)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.0</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Jon Poll</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Anton Yelchin, Robert Downey Jr., Hope Davis</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2567 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/3-min.jpg\" alt=\"rdj Charlie Bartlett (2007)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Can you imagine dating the daughter of your college’s principle? Especially when the principle is a cocky guy. Someone like Robert Downey Jr himself? The 2007 release has been ignored by many, but RDJ fans can never stop adoring his performance as the cocky principle in Charlie Barlett. This coming to age story is filled with emotions, funny scenes, and the ever good-looking Robert Downey Jr!</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b_DVwLq0wn0[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>9) </b><b>Bowfinger </b><b>(1999)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 6.4</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Frank Oz</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Steve Martin, Eddie Murphy, Robert Downey Jr</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2568 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/4-min.jpg\" alt=\"rdj Bowfinger (1999)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Naturally gifted with comic timing, Robert Downey Jr gives a memorable performance in Bowfinger. His funny approach to the role of a film producer will keep you wanting for more. Although the screen presence is very less, RDJ makes the most out of each and every frame. The film is never talked about and is usually overshadowed by his other works. But during his early days as an actor, delivering such class performance is something which only Robert Downey Jr can do!</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SkbHfeWfxHw[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>8) The Soloist (2009)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 6.7</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Joe Wright</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jamie_Foxx\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Jamie Foxx</a>, Robert Downey Jr., Catherine Keener</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2569 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/5-min.jpg\" alt=\"robert downey jr The Soloist (2009)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What happens when you cast two great actors in a film? You get a masterpiece! Joe Wright was bang on target in casting Jamie Foxx and Robert Downey Jr for The Soloist. This biopic will move your soul. The performances by both veterans are just outstanding.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The biopic focuses on the journey of a soloist from his days from being poor and homeless to becoming a successful musician. It showcases the heart-melting story of <strong>friendship</strong> and <strong>humanity</strong>. The Soloist is one of the best movies of Robert Downey Jr and his performance in the drama category is undoubtedly one of his personal best.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E_Spu2nO0jw[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>7) Zodiac (2007)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.7</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: F. Gary Gray</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Jake Gyllenhaal, Robert Downey Jr., Mark Ruffalo</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-2570 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/6-min.jpg\" alt=\"Zodiac (2007)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another movie inspired by true events and stories is the 2007 release Zodiac. One look at the cast and any idiot can say for sure that this is a Marvel film. Only to contradict the fact that it is not a Marvel film! This is one of <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/best-crime-movies-based-on-true-life-stories/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">the best Crime Movies Based on True Life Stories</a>. Zodiac managed to bring such an ensemble cast together and presented us with one of the most horrific incidents of serial killings.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The story focuses on the Zodiac Killings which took place in America during the 60s and 70s. A fellow cartoonist is determined to play detective in order to catch hold of the criminal. This is considered to be a modern classic in the genre of suspense thrillers. No list can ever be made of the best movies by Robert Downey Jr without mentioning Zodiac at least once!</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yNncHPl1UXg[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>6) The Judge (2014)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.4</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: David Dobkin</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Robert Downey Jr., Robert Duvall, Vera Farmiga</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2571 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/7-min.jpg\" alt=\"The Judge (2014)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are very few movies of Robert Downey Jr where his role has been totally serious. This is one of those movies. This movie is also one of <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/courtroom-movies-based-on-real-life-stories/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">the best courtroom movies based on true stories</a>.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A fantastic performance by the cast, RDJ as usual blows away your mind. Each and every single frame in which RDJ is seen; is just brilliant. He plays a father and a son. The film explores the relationship of a father with his son, at the same time handling the bitter relationship with his own father.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Keep all th