e. Although, a considerable star cast and wonderful acting all around, it struggles to stay afloat and may not be the best of a lot of movies with Chris Evans.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VxJsGKn2kyA[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>7) The Iceman (2012)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 6.8</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Ariel Vromen</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Michael Shannon, Chris Evans, Winona Ryder, Ray Liotta</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2586 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/6-min-1.jpg\" alt=\"The Iceman (2012)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Based on a true story about the Hitman Richard Kulinski. The notorious Hitman had escaped capturing for years before he was finally caught. WIth Michael Shannon in the lead role supported by a wonderful cast with Chris Evans and Winona Ryder as well. The acting skills in the movie was never in doubt, yet the scriptwriting and directing left a lot to be needed in the movie. There were several doubts and problems over the movie, with it unable to capture the emotion from the audience that was needed. But in spite of that, if you are a Chris Evans fan and want to either follow him or know about this cold-hearted Hitman, this is the movie to watch for you.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CJIXOx2-GZ8[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>6) The Gifted (2017)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.6</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Mark Webb</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast: </b><sp