ion of a comic by Vertigo. This movie shows a team of Elite Special forces unit who is out for revenge on the betrayal that they had to go through.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QSEM-hJF_vM[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>4) Sunshine (2007)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.2</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Danny Boyle</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Cillian Murphy, Chris Evans, Rosa Byrne </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2588 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/4-min-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A Sci-fi/Horror/Thriller made by Danny Boyle. Danny Boyle attempts to master yet another genre with this future based movie. With the year 2057 and the earth colder than warmer, a group of scientists is given the task of attempting to restart the sun. Yes, you read that right, the dying star has to be restarted and things do not go according to the plan. Not an action flick, Danny Boyle masters the direction with a wonderfully scary movie that should definitely be seen by Sci-Fi fans.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r8BSlqHAhuY[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>3) Scott Pilgrim vs the World (2010)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.5</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Edgar White</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Michael Cera, Mary Elizabeth Winstead, Chris Evans, Aubrey Plaza</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2587 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/3-min-1.jpg\" alt=\"Scott Pilgrim vs the World (2010)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Action and Comedy. What a combination right? But that is exactly what Scott Pilgrim and his adventure bring to the table. Scott Pilgrim falls in love but the minor problem about falling in love with Romano is all of her exes. In order to woo her, he has to get through all of her exes. Based on Bryan Lee O’Malley’s comic book of the same name, the infectious happy-sad humour is enjoyable and loved by most people that watch this movie.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7wd5KEaOtm4[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>2) Snowpiercer (2013)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.1</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Bong Joon-Ho</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Chris Evans, Tilda Swinton, Ed Harris, John Hurt</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2585 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2-min.jpg\" alt=\"Snowpiercer (2013)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Yet another Sci-fi movie which stars Chris Evans. Although, this one is completely different. The Earth has its second Ice Age and the survivors are not so many. Everyone is aboard a luxury train that moves through the snow and ice ploughing through ahead. And just like so many parts of the present world, there is a separation between the rich and poor. Until the poor decide to revolt and rise and attempt to take over the Engine Room. Chris Evans is wonderful throughout and is a must-watch movie for any fan.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r6UmqNuMdY4[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>1) Knives Out (2019)</b>