 style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/willsmith/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Will Smith</a>, Martin Lawrence, Lisa Boyle</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2640 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2-min-3.jpg\" alt=\"Action-Comedy Movies and tv shows \" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Nobody thought that cop-buddy movies would be a thing in Hollywood. Although it didn’t set a trend, Bad Boys did enough damage to be declared as a classic! </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film is full of larger than life Will Smith and circumstantial comedy, as two cops try to find their way out in a crime-filled city. The budding days of Will Smith as an action star are a treat to witness.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xm12NSa8jsM[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>8) The Hitman’s Bodyguard (2017)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 6.9</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patrick_Hughes_(director)\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Patrick Hughes</a></span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Ryan Reynolds, Samuel L. Jackson, Gary Oldman </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2641 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/3-min-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We can’t keep Ryan Reynolds out of this list, can we? Another action-comedy movie and great Reynold action flick with a bunch of comic scenes you will not regret watching. Pair the great Ryan with Samuel L. Jackson, and you get probably the most amazing action-comedy ever! </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We are uncertain when Nick Fury and Deadpool will face each other, but we got a small trailer of that moment throughout the film! The action sequences are pretty slick and comic timings by both the actors are phenomenal! Easily one of the best action-comedy movies in the modern ear!</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F4Afusxc2SM[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>7) Shazam! (2019)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.1</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: David F. Sandberg</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Zachary Levi, Mark Strong, Asher Angel</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2642 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/4-min-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When Fox and Marvel got a huge success with trying out comedy in the superhero genre, it was about time for DC to follow. And they chose Shazam to make the audience laugh. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Although the movie is more kid-centric and focused more to entertain kids, it does have pretty good action sequences. Even if Shazam is connected to the DCEU, it is a standalone film and is not related to any previous DC film. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">That’s what makes it such a good watch as it is free from the previous failures of the Justice League. The kids will surely love this action-comedy movie!</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uilJZZ_iVwY[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>6) 21 Jump Street (2012)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.2</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Phil Lord, Christopher Miller</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Jonah Hill, Channing Tatum, Ice Cube</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2643 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/5-min-3.jpg\" alt=\"21 Jump Street (2012)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cop-buddy films have more or less always followed the trend of cross blending action and comedy genre. Some follow the usual drill, by pairing up African-American with an American or putting an outsider in the case. But 21 Jump Street is something you can never think of. A more comedy than action, the film focuses on two failed cops who try to reinvent their career by taking on a secret undercover mission. Guess what the mission is? To go back to high school again. Yes, you read it right! Now go and watch the masterpiece!</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RLoKtb4c4W0[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>5) Beverly Hills Cop (1984)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.3</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Martin Brest</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Eddie Murphy, Judge Reinhold, John Ashton</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2644 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/6-min-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of the earliest movies showcased cross-blending the two genres. It also followed the trend of the cop-buddy plot. Beverly Hills Cop is a classic and will always remain so. The performance of Eddie Murphy is simply outstanding and the circumstantial comedy will drive you nuts. If you are a fan of classic old movies, this movie is a must to check out!</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oc3sPICXZLs[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>4) Kiss Kiss Bang Bang (2005)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.5</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Shane Black</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Robert Downey Jr., Val Kilmer, Michelle Monaghan</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2645 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/7-min-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A perfect black comedy of all sorts, the film has it all! A mindblowing cast, perfect setup, engaging suspense, and on top of everything, Robert Downey Jr.! </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The man is capable of pulling off almost anything. The film follows a thief, who due to his circumstances lands himself in a movie production house as an actor, and gets caught in double murders. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What follows is a bizarre tale of stupidness which will make you laugh so hard and leave you wanting for more!</span>\r\n\r\nYou can also check <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/best-movies-of-robert-downey-jr-except-mcu/\">the best movie of <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Robert Downey Jr to watch on Netflix.</span></a>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/best-movies-of-robert-downey-jr-except-mcu/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=__PnD1HWXSo[/embedyt]</span></a>\r\n<h2><b>3) Kick Ass (2010)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.6</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Matthew Vaughn</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Aaron Taylor-Johnson, Nicolas Cage, Chloë Grace Moretz </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2646 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/8-min-2.jpg\" alt=\"hollywood comedy movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">While focusing on the Marvel Cinematic Universe, Marvel Studios decided to venture a bit more into filmmaking. They decided to make movies, but couldn’t decide on the genre. Kick-Ass is a multi-genre film focusing primarily on the superhero, comedy, and action-adventure genres. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film showcased a world where everyone was obsessed with wearing a cape and acting like a superhero, but few people actually standing up against crime. The film is brutal to watch as the violence in the film is just as raw as the language used in the film. Just as the title suggests, this film is surely going to kick some major asses!</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2rpXHqnGDXo[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>2) Kingsman: The Secret Service (2014)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.7</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Matthew Vaughn</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Colin Firth, Taron Egerton, Samuel L. Jackson </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2647 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/9-min-2.jpg\" alt=\"Kingsman: The Secret Service (2014)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another venture by Marvel Studios under the 