inly a part of the Bengali movie and television industry, Rajesh Sharma has been a part of the Hindi film industry for a while now as well. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With a career that has been longer than 20 years in film and television shows making, many recognize him by his face rather than his name. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So what has been his career trajectory and story? Do you want to know more about this actor and his story? </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Read on ahead to find out all that you can about the <strong>life and career of Rajesh Sharma.</strong></span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Career</span></h2>\r\n<h3>Rajesh Sharma First movie Maachis:</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rajesh started his career in the Hindi film industry long before being in the Bengali filming industry. In 1996, as a young man, he landed his first role in the political thriller <em><strong>Maachis</strong></em> which was made by <strong>Gulzar</strong> and starred significant actors such as <em>Jimmy Shergil, Om Puri,</em> and <em>Tabu</em>. The movie was based on the Sikh insurgency which rose in the 80s in India. The movie was a huge commercial hit. It garnered widespread applause for the quality of film making including winning awards as well. </span>\r\n<h3>Rajesh Sharma in Bengali Movies:</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Even though he did get a taste for the film industry, Sharma took a break from filming for the next four years. He returned but he did not return in the Hindi film industry, he made his return in the Bengali film industry with the movie<em><strong> ‘Paromitar Ek Din’</strong></em> in which Aparna Sen was the director as well as writer of the movie.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2709 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/5-min-4.jpg\" alt=\" Rajesh Sharma hit films\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Having a career that spanned across 3 decades, Rajesh Sharma is credited with nearly 100 movies which by itself is considerably impressive. He continued to make movies in Bengali as well starring in movies such as<em><strong> ‘Sathi’, ‘Shubho Muharat’, ‘Bye Bye Bangkok’ </strong></em>and <em><strong>‘Kagojer Nouka’.</strong></em> </span>\r\n<h3>His Big year of Film Industry</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rajesh has always made a large number of movies in any given year, having as many as 11 movies releasing within a year as well, which includes both the Hindi and Bengali movies that he would be making. While some people focus on just one industry at a time, Rajesh made his name in both the Hindi and Bengali film Industry. And comparatively, probably made a bigger name in the Bengali film industry considering the number of movies that he has made over there. </span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2711 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2-min-5.jpg\" alt=\"Rajesh Sharma paatal lok\" width=\"940\" height=\"788\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We must also consider that while he is a very talented and bright actor, he never had any prominent enough roles at least in the Hindi film industry. Very often you can see Rajesh in a supposed ‘negative’ as we like to call it in Bollywood. While he has been a part of many great movies with many of them being all-time great movies as well. It is interesting to note that his role has always been one of a supporting character. The fact that his roles were so minimal in so many movies probably helped him be a part of such a high number of movies year on year. But he received such roles constantly because he is a very good actor as well.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Several Hits</span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Even in the Hindi film industry, he has been a part of several hits. <em><strong>Parineeta in 2005</strong></em>, was his return to Bollywood after his first movie which as we mentioned was in 1996. This movie had a rich cast of Sanjay Dutt, Vidya Balan, and Saif Ali Khan. Parineeta was based on a Bengali Nouvella and had Rajesh Sharma in his return to Bollywood.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2712 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/3-min-5.jpg\" alt=\" Rajesh Sharma web series\" width=\"940\" height=\"788\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As his career progressed his name grew in the industry and he started receiving more movies in Bollywood as well. With 2019 probably being his most popular year in the Hindi Film Industry. He has done so many big movies like <em><strong>‘22 yards’</strong></em>, ‘<em><strong>Super 30’</strong></em> which starred Hrithik Roshan. He also did ‘<em><strong>Mardaani 2</strong></em>’ and as well as ‘<em><strong>Dabbang 3</strong></em>’ in which he was a Minister.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Personal Life</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2710 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1-min-5.jpg\" alt=\"Rajesh Sharma biographi\" width=\"940\" height=\"788\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Born in Ludhiana, Punjab Rajesh has always had the aim of acting in films and taking on acting as a career. He did dramas and worked in a drama group in Kolkota. He is also a graduate of the National School of Drama which is in New Delhi. Rajesh was initially married to <strong>Sudipta Chakraborty</strong> in 2005. They separated from her in 2009. He got married again in 2011 to <strong>Sangeeta Sharma.</strong> He has led a happily married life ever since. </span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What is happening now?</span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rajesh Sharma continues to make <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">movies and now TV shows</a> as well. Starring in the hit<a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/paatal-lok-review-story-actor-director/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong> ‘Pataal Lok’</strong> </a>which was released on Amazon Prime Video in 2020. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His career will continue in the manner in which it has. His smaller roles allowing him to make a large number of movies across a year. We hope for such a quality actor to receive more roles and hopefully larger ones as well. </span>\r\n\r\nHe is also an outsider in the film industry. He is not having a hero\'s face but with his talent, he is not considered in negative roles.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What have been your favourite movies that have had Rajesh Sharma in it? Do you think he should have received any bigger roles in movies up until now? </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Let us know all your thoughts in the comment section below!</span>','Rajesh Sharma | Personal Life, Career, Movies and Web Series','','publish','open','open','','rajesh-sharma-personal-life-career-movies-and-web-series','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/paatal-lok-review-story-actor-director/','2021-01-24 17:16:25','2021-01-24 11:46:25','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=2676',0,'post','',0),(2688,4,'2020-09-15 20:11:30','2020-09-15 14:41:30','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Boxing movies are absolute gems in the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">film</a> making industry. The range of a boxing movie provides is rare and amazing. To go from the raw emotion and feelings to the pain and commitment a boxer or fighter shows in the ring. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pain is known to be one of the most difficult parts of acting and to show it in such an accurate manner becomes important as well. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So what are the best boxing movies that have ever been made? Read on ahead to find out all about them and which of them you have missed out on.</span>\r\n<h2><b>10) Girlfight (2000)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 6.7</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Karyn Kusama</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/mrodofficial/?hl=en\" rel=\"nofollow\">Michelle Rodriguez</a>, Santiago Douglas, Jaime Tirelli</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2724 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1-min-6.jpg\" alt=\"Girlfight (2000)\" width=\"580\" height=\"450\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Not necessarily the most popular boxing movie around but an important one none the less. Diana who is played by the talented Michelle Rodriguez has decided that she is going to learn boxing. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She even convinces a coach Hector to teach her for as little as 10$ a session. But with a deteriorating relationship with her father, Diane has to overcome a lot in order to pursue her dream.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=an7-gDMOe4s[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>9) </b><b>Tyson (2008)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.5</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: James Toback</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Mike Tyson, Tyrell Biggs, Monica Turner</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2715 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2-min-1-1.jpg\" alt=\"Tyson (2008)\" width=\"580\" height=\"450\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Who does not know about Mike Tyson? The former heavyweight champion of the world has had a life and career which had a lot of controversies. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With incidents both inside and outside the ring, Tyson threw away a lot of the reputation that he had earned during his successful years. V</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">olatile and destroying relationships, this documentary follows the fall, rise, and popularity of such a big sports personality.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-mKf4k8VLi8[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>8) The Fighter (2010)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.8</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: David O. Russell</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Christian Bale, Mark Wahlberg, Amy Adams</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2716 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/3-min-6.jpg\" alt=\"The Fighter (2010)\" width=\"580\" height=\"450\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Before you read the description we would suggest that you read the star cast first. If there ever was a movie that had a star cast it is this one. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Star-studded and a boxing movie. Micky is a boxer with a career in the fall who decides to team up with his brother who is an addict to get his career back on track.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LRIZ4mCi5Ps[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>7) Creed (2015)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.6</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Ryan Coogler</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Michael B. Jordan, Sylvester Stallone, Tessa Thompson</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2717 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/4-min-6.jpg\" alt=\"Creed (2015)\" width=\"580\" height=\"450\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Remember Rocky Balboa? Remember him and the rivalry with Adonis Creed. Well, I am here to tell you that this movie is about the son of Rocky’s greatest rival Adonis Creed’s son. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With Michael Jordan as Apollo Creed, Rocky has to train his former rivals son to help him reach the boxing levels that he wishes and believes he can.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Uv554B7YHk4[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>6) Knuckle (2011)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 6.8</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Ian Palmer</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Ian Palmer, James Quinn McDonough</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2718 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/5-min-5.jpg\" alt=\"Knuckle (2011)\" width=\"580\" height=\"450\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The quote ‘ Let’s settle this like men’ mean anything to you? This documentary about two Irish families who absolutely do not get along need to find a middle ground. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So many differences between them that they decide to settle it the old-fashioned away. With bare-knuckle boxing. Yes, you heard that right, now go on and find out more about them by watching this movie.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZX8qcOWFr-w[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>5) Cinderella Man (2005)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 8.0</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Ron Howard</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Russel Crowe, Renee Zellweger</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2719 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/6-min-4.jpg\" alt=\"Cinderella Man (2005)\" width=\"580\" height=\"450\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Think you can imagine Russel Crowe as a boxer? Well, you do not have to because you can watch him as one in the story named Cinderella Man because of the rags to riches story of the protagonist. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After being given a chance to fight a one time match, a former fighter who worked daily wages has the opportunity to be much bigger and he definitely is not letting this chance go.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3R01CGX2ubw[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>4) Million Dollar Baby (2004)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 8.1</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Clint Eastwood</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Clint Eastwood, Hillary Swank, Morgan Freeman, Jay Baruchel</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2720 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/7-min-4.jpg\" alt=\"Million Dollar Baby (2004)\" width=\"580\" height=\"450\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A movie directed by Clint Eastwood stars Clint Eastwood along with Hilary Swank and Morgan Freeman just to name a few? Oh, I need to watch this one all over again now. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We can dare not question the quality of a movie that won the Academy Award for Best Picture. If you want to know what is a must-watch movie, this is the one.</span>\r\n\r