580\" height=\"450\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A movie that is not for the emotionally weak. An absolutely magnificent movie that breaks emotion while telling the story of two boxers with such a different path in life. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The story of families, love, and priorities. It is just as much a boxing movies as it is the rest of what I have mentioned. A battle between two underdogs as a former marine finds his own brother in the ring as well. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mind-blowing movie with a wonderful cast and we would like to note the great music as well.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kY7HcUACs58[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>1) Fight Club (1999)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 8.8</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: David Fincher</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Bradd Pitt, Edward Norton, Helena Bonham Carter</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2723 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/10-min-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"580\" height=\"450\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A movie that absolutely deserves a re-watch. Not many movies can say that when you rewatch it you are going to have a completely different experience but this one is definitely one of those. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Telling the story of a man who meets Tyler Durden, a man tired of the capitalistic lifestyle of the world, and wants to bring it down. It all starts as an underground fight club which grows into something so large in scale that even the creator does not realize what he is doing and has created.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qtRKdVHc-cE[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-wei