strong>Dialogue</strong> -<em><strong>Pathan aur Sardar ke Jodi Baki sb Lil Lil ghodi.</strong></em></span>\r\n<h4>Interesting Fact:-</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The most adorable moment of Ajay Devgan in the movie was when he tried to run out of the house. And at the exit gate, he throws a pillow to check whether anybody is outside or not. Just after throwing everyone jumps on the pillow and cut it into pieces. At last Ajay Devgan tries to cover the situation telling him to be a tiger.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>1. Dabangg</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Dialogue</strong>- <em><strong>Chedi Singh Hm tume itne ched krenge ke confuse ho jaoge ki sas Kahan se le aur padein Kahan se.</strong></em></span>\r\n<h4>Interesting Fact:-</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie is the debut of Sonakshi Sinha. And this movie’s songs such as Fevicol se and the Chedi Singh dialogue written above is famous for all.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hope you like the content - <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">The Tv Freak</a></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do comment down below on which dialogue you like the most of Salman Khan.</span>\r\n<blockquote><b>By- S.Mohan Kumar</b></blockquote>\r\n<strong>Also Read:</strong>\r\n<h3 class=\"entry-title\"><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/radhe-your-most-wanted-bhai-2020/\">Radhe: Your Most Wanted Bhai (2020) | Salman Khan Upcoming Movie</a></h3>','List of Top 10 Most Popular Salman Khan Dialogues Ever','','publish','open','open','','list-of-top-10-most-popular-salman-khan-dialogues-ever','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/bollywood-industry-slammed-by-the-virus/','2020-12-25 17:48:53','2020-12-25 12:18:53','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=2779',0,'post','',0),(2786,10,'2020-09-21 00:01:31','2020-09-20 18:31:31','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Firstly, we would like to tell you that Entrepreneurs are always looking for motivation in someplace or the other. And what a better way to pump yourself up to other than watching inspiring Entrepreneursmovies. Secondly, We bring Bollywood’s finest movies based on Entrepreneurs, which will make your inner self bubbled with motivation.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So finally, here are our top 9 best Bollywood Films and Series for Entrepreneurs.</span>\r\n<h2><b>10) Sui Dhaaga: Made in India (2018)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 6.8</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Sharat Katariya1</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Anushka Sharma, Varun Dhawan, Namit Das </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2793 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/3-min-8.jpg\" alt=\"Sui Dhaaga: Made in India (2018)\" width=\"600\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Famous for gifting memers excellent quality content, Sui Dhaaga was primarily renowned for its content in 2018.  The crying sequence of Anushka Sharma went viral like the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/bollywood-industry-slammed-by-the-virus/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">CoronaVirus</a>, and till now is popular meme content. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Of course, t</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">he Entrepreneurs movies had an average outing at the box-office but boasted of a very good rooted made in India story every entrepreneur can dream of!</span>\r\n<h2><b>9) Baazaar (2018)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 6.6</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Gauravv K. Chawla</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Radhika Apte, Saif Ali Khan, Denzil Smith</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2795 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/5-min-7.jpg\" alt=\"Baazaar (2018)\" width=\"600\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Baazaar showcases the shrewd side of the business. With literally ‘business’ in its title, the movie delivers and stands on your expectations. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Powerful performances by <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/saif-ali-khan-said-about-his-autobiography-reactions-on-twitter/\">Saif Ali Khan</a> and Radhika Apte keep you on the edge of your seat. The story is the only weakness of the film, and hence it makes the movie a one time watch. </span>\r\n<h2><b>8) Corporate (2006)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 6.5</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Madhur Bhandarkar</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Bipasha Basu, Kay Kay Menon, Raj Babbar</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2796 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/6-min-6.jpg\" alt=\"Corporate (2006)\" width=\"600\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Firstly, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madhur_Bhandarkar\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Madhur Bhandarkar</a> is known for making dark, compelling, and realistic movies. Corporate is also one of them. Maybe the only cynical film on this list, Corporate narrates you the dark side of corporates and businesses. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Secondly, The two-faced people, over gained powers, misuse of money, and violence are common aspects of the corporate world. The film teaches us how to avoid such situations and how bad the world really can be. Kay Kay Menon is a surprise package in this one! </span>\r\n<h2><b>7) Made in China (2019)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 6.2</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Mikhil Musale</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Rajkummar Rao, Boman Irani, Mouni Roy</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2799 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/9-min-5.jpg\" alt=\"Made in China (2019)\" width=\"600\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Made in China is a clear struggle of a genius mind to try out his luck in business. After failing in almost everything, he finally comes across a brilliant idea. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A thing which we all can learn from this movie. The biggest takeaway is that always look to solve the problems in your society.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you address new problems and come up with our unique solutions, you are destined to be successful. This movie also talks about the same by combining the infertility problem in men and the idea of a shrewd businessman. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Excellent performances by Rajkumar Rao and Boman Irani and a great cameo by Paresh Rawal make Made in China an interesting one time watch</span>\r\n<h2><b>6) TVF PITCHERS (2015)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 9.1</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Arunabh Kumar</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Naveen Kasturia, Arunabh Kumar, Jitendra Kumar </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2801 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/TVF-PITCHERS-2015.jpg\" alt=\"TVF PITCHERS (2015)\" width=\"512\" height=\"395\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Although the only series on the list, this TVF product is pure gold. The IMDb ratings speak for itself and hence makes it the highest-rated Indian Web-series ever! Directed by <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arunabh_Kumar\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Arunabh Kumar</a>, TVF Pitchers talks about a group of entrepreneurs trying to make it big with their dreams.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The series takes a comic angle and sarcastically shows the life of young entrepreneurs in India. The series is very realistic, raw, and straightforward in its approach. A must watch for all, primarily if you aim to go for a start-up!</span>\r\n<h2><b>5) Harishchandrachi Factory (2009)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 8.4</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Paresh Mokashi</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Nandu Madhav, Vibhawari Deshpande, Atharva Karve</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2791 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1-min-8.jpg\" alt=\"Harishchandrachi Factory (2009)\" width=\"600\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The story we all are familiar with, but no one knows in detail, is the story of Harishchandra, also known as the Father of Indian Cinema. Initially made in Marathi, this movie is also available in Hindi Dub. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A fantastic take on the life of Harishchandra, and how he started his filmmaking career, which created the second largest film producing industry in the world!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The direction of Paresh Mokashi is a perfect blend in the mix, and Nandu Madhav as Harshichandra is a cherry on the cake. </span>\r\n<h2><b>4) Padman (2018)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.9</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: R. Balki</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Akshay Kumar, Radhika Apte, Sonam Kapoor</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2792 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2-min-7.jpg\" alt=\"Padman (2018)\" width=\"600\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2018 was a year for motivation. Padman is just a milestone and torchbearer of inspirational movies. Made on a rather delicate topic, the film showcases the menstrual issue beautifully throughout its running minutes. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As we know, Akshay Kumar never disappoints with his film choices, and Padman proved to be one of the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">best films</a> of his career.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie is about a man on an incredible journey to promote the awareness of menstruation and making economical sanitary pads which can be easily affordable by the rural women of India. The film is based on a true story, and hence every entrepreneur should have it on his to-Entrepreneurs Movies watch list!</span>\r\n<h2><b>3) Badmash Company (2010)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 6.0</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Parmeet Sethi</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Shahid Kapoor, <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/anushkasharma/\">Anushka Sharma</a>, Meiyang Chang</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2797 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/7-min-6.jpg\" alt=\"Badmash Company (2010)\" width=\"600\" height=\"480\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Photo Source: Hamara Photos</em></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">While IMDb has underrated the gem of a movie, we surely understand its true potential. Perfect for entrepreneurs to learn and look for different ideas, the film showcases the story of a young start-up between friends brilliantly and how it can go wrong in many ways.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Although the film loses its track in between by showcasing their personal life, it gets going in the second half. A brilliant business idea, a stable revenue model, a team of hard-working entrepreneurs, and a dream to make it big. This Entrepreneurs Movies are undoubtedly one of the underrated gems Bollywood has ever produced.</span>\r\n<h2><b>2) Rocket Singh: Salesman of the Year (2009)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.5</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Shimit Amin</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Ranbir Kapoor, Prem Chopra, Mukesh Bhatt</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2798 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/8-min-5.jpg\" alt=\"Rocket Singh: Salesman of the Year (2009)\" width=\"600\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Speaking of underrated movies, Rocket Singh is another tremendous potential project which flew under the radar. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With Ranbir Kapoor in his budding stage, the film blew at the box office, and the audience didn’t appreciate it at that time. Later, to everyone’s surprise, it was the audience itself that took this movie to hights and made it aware for the whole world to appreciate.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A catchy yet straightforward story of a salesman who aims to grow finds a way out to build his own office inside an office he is already working! This film, even though unethically, teaches you a lot and urges you to do something in your life!</span>\r\n<h2><b>1) Guru (2007)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.7</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Mani Ratnam</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Abhishek Bachchan, Aishwarya Rai Bachchan, Mithun Chakraborty</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2800 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/10-min-4.jpg\" alt=\"Guru (2007)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What could be better than learning from the life story of India’s most celebrated businessman ever? Guru is loosely based on the life of Dhirubhai Ambani, and his rise in the world of business. Today the Ambanis stand tall being among the top 10 wealthiest people in the world.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It all started with a basic idea and some really excellent entrepreneurial skills. Directed by veteran director Mani Ratnam, the star cast boasts of Abhishek Bacchan, Aishwarya Rai, Vidya Balan, and R. Madhavan. A.R. Rehman composed the music of this movie. If you are looking for some high energy motivation, Guru is definitely a must-watch! </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Which Entrepreneurs Movies out of the list do you prefer watching first? What e