eight: 400;\">Food always brings people together. What better way to show how it does so than a documentary which is based on the truth. A story based on 3 restaurants and the lives of the people who are the heart of each of this restaurant, shows us all the love and importance of food and the joy it brings to our lives.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PPHaLkd4J28[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>4) Chocolat (2000)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.2</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Lasse Hallstrom</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Juliette Binoche, Johnny Depp</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2822 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/7-min-7.jpg\" alt=\"Chocolat (2000)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At the heart of this french tale is a backward French town. And to the annoyance of this small town came a nomadic daughter and her mother and with them came a small shop. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A small shop that brought along the love of chocolate. The story is about how this mother and daughter duo win over this small town. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Apart from the only nuance of this movie that being of the french accents, it is wonderfully made and one of the best movies that have been made around.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=32x33l2sLe8[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>3) Chef (2014)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 7.3</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Jon Favreau</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 