te>','Are You Food Lover? Must Watch these 9 Best Food based Movies','','publish','open','open','','are-you-food-lover-must-watch-these-9-best-food-based-movies','','','2020-12-25 17:46:17','2020-12-25 12:16:17','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=2812',0,'post','',0),(2832,3,'2020-09-29 10:01:40','2020-09-29 04:31:40','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Have you wondered why Bollywood is so keen to make the best Hindi biopics? The answer is simple. Biopic <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">movies</a> give the producers a massive amount of revenue, and the project is a sure do best at the box-office. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The audience just loves Bollywood biopics, and hence we decided to note the best Hindi biopic movies for you to binge-watch! </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Here is the comprehensive list of Bollywood biopic movies and a peek into upcoming biopic movies in 2020.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The selection of these movies is not based on any parameter but the popularity and huge expectations were there. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Basically, these are the most awaited movies based on a real-life story in the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/bollywood/\">Bollywood industry</a>. After some time you will also get a complete list of the best Bollywood movies based on real incidents.  </span>\r\n<h2><b>Dangal</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Produced by none other than Mr. Perfectionist himself, this Amir Khan film is the best biopic Bollywood has ever produced. Dangal focuses on the story of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phogat_sisters\" rel=\"nofollow\">Geeta and Babita Phogat</a>. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Biopic covers the journey of the Phogat family to win Commonwealth Games and bring the gold medal for our country in 2010. Geeta and Babita went on to become India’s first world-class female wrestlers.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2834 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1-min-9.jpg\" alt=\"Dangal BIOPIC movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The biopic did so well that it went on to be a ground-breaking film in the history of Bollywood. It became the highest-earning movie as well as the highest-earning biopic of Bollywood. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Producing with a budget of mere 70 crores, the biopic bagged 2100 crores from the box-office worldwide.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Sanju</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This 2018 biopic was just as controversial as the title. The biopic was based on Sanjay Dutt’s life and the allegations of him being involved with Mumbai Underworld. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film was made by the veteran director Raj Kumar Hirani and produced by his dear friend, Vidhu Vinod Chopra.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2835 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2-min-9.jpg\" alt=\"SANJU BIOPIC movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film became a smashing hit as soon as it opened in theatres. Ranbir Kapoor played Sanjay Dutt and almost went on to perform his lifetime. His acting and efforts for the role were appreciated all across the country.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film received backlash due to its portrayal of the character. Many believed that the biopic glorified the mistakes made by the Bollywood actor Sanjay Dutt and the biopic was just a reason to clear his name in some very horrific incidents in Mumbai. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">These include the 1993 bombings in the city as well as two A.K. riffles found with Sanjay Dutt liking him directly to terrorism.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Bhag Milkha Bhag</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you are wondering at which point Bollywood fell in love with making biopics look no further. Bhag Milkha Bhag was the first biopic of Bollywood which left a lasting impression on the audience back in 2013. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The biopic was based on the novel ‘The Race of My Life’, by Milkha Singh.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2836 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/3-min-10.jpg\" alt=\"Bhag Milkha Bhag BIOPIC movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film beautifully captures the journey of India’s most celebrated athlete and the ups and downs in his life. He was entitled as the flying Sikh, based on his blistering speed and mind-blowing pace.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Farhan Akhtar did a tremendous job and cemented his position as a lead actor in Bollywood. The transformation he did for the part was just outstanding. Rakeysh Omprakash Mehra directed the biopic.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Super 30</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Speaking about transformations, this Hritik Roshan film will leave you speechless. Hritik plays the celebrated Anand Kumar in this biopic. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Not only Hritik underwent a body transformation, but he also changed his dialect and accent for the biopic. He took lessons for the Bihari language and soon after, gave a performance that left everyone dazzled.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2837 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/4-min-1-1.jpg\" alt=\"Super 30\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The biopic focuses on Anand Kumar, a brilliant yet poor teacher who started a free coaching institute for I.I.T. in Patna. He selected 30 students every year who were from poor families and taught them for free. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">And the big and good news came for him. All the 30 students cleared the exam and join the top engineering institute of India.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Their struggle and hard work are shown correctly in the film, and for those who think something is impossible, this movie is a must-watch!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Overall I would like to say that if you are looking for any motivation and feeling demoralized in any industry then this is the best stuff for you. How you and go to Hundred from zero. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You only have an idea with desire and so much dedication, only then you can achieve the goal that is so unachievable for you.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Padman</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Akshay Kumar seems to have cracked the mantra of doing successful movies over a period of time. His new mantra, however, is targeting as many as biopics as possible. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He did back-to-back hits of biopics in Bollywood, and it all started with the 2018 box-office super-hit biopic Padman.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2792 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2-min-7.jpg\" alt=\"Padman (2018)\" width=\"600\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film is loosely based on the true story of Arunachalam Muruganantham, a social entrepreneur from Tamil Nadu. Arunachalam started to make sanitary pads for women at a very low-cost rate. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At times were one sanitary pad was for 10 rs, his pads were for only 2 rs, and were as efficient as the branded ones. Soon his social activities were noticed, and he received substantial funding for his start-up after which he became a widely-known entrepreneur.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now that we have covered the top 5 best Bollywood biopics, here are some <strong>upcoming biopics in 2020</strong> which will leave you hooked to the screens.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Shershah</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2838 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/5-min-1-1.jpg\" alt=\"sHERSHAH\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Siddharth Malhotra will do a double role in this war biopic. This upcoming biopic is based on Indian Army hero and martyr Vikram Batra who died in combat during the Kargil War on 7th July 1999. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Vikram Batra was awarded Param Vir Chakra, which is the highest honor of the Indian Military.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The character was also famously portrayed by Abhishek Bachchan in the Kargil War movie and biopic, L.O.C. Kargil.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Bhuj: The Pride of India</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2843 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Untitled-design-1.jpg\" alt=\"Bhuj: The Pride of India\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another war-action biopic on the list, Bhuj: The Pride of India will see Ajay Devgan in the lead role. The biopic will be based on the 1971 Pakistan War and the Indian Air Force Squadron Leader Vijay Karnik. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film focuses on the sheer hard work of his team and 300 local women who reconstructed the airbase. Along with Ajay Devgan, the biopic will boast of the star cast of the likes of Sanjay Dutt, Sonakshi Sinha, and Nora Fatehi.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Recently, it came up that this movie will come on the O.T.T. platform of Disney+ Hotstar and will have a worldwide release.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Shakuntala Devi -The Human Computer</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2839 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/6-min-8.jpg\" alt=\"Shakuntala Devi -The Human Computer\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Releasing on Amazon Prime Video on 31st July, Shakuntala Devi will see Vidya Balan in the title role. Shakuntala Devi gained worldwide fame due to her mathematical skills. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Bangalore-born was also entitled as the human-computer, and her calculations were even faster than an electronic calculator. She had received the Guinness World Record in 1982. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Later she was known to pioneer the study of homosexuality in India.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Gangubai Kathiawadi</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2840 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/7-min-8.jpg\" alt=\"Gangubai Kathiawadi BIOPIC movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Alia Bhatt will be back on silver-screen with this smashing biopic Gangubai Kathiawadi. Sanjay Leela Bhansali will direct this movie. It would be set in the 60s, and based on Gangubai who ruled the Bombay Underworld in that era. She was a feared don and also a brothel owner.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Gangubai, from a very young age, was forced into prostitution and later rose significantly in the drug trade. Alia is getting used to the abusive slang of the sex-workers. Ranveer Singh will also be seen in a prominent cameo in this biopic movie.</span>\r\n<h2><b>83</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2841 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/8-min-1-1.jpg\" alt=\"83 BIOPIC movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Speaking about Ranveer Singh, the nation is waiting patiently to witness the historical and magical moment of India lifting the Cricket World Cup for the first time. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ranveer will play the legend Kapil Dev in this upcoming and most awaited Bollywood biopic, ‘83. Great sports film, Chak De India\'s Director Kabir Khan is directing this movie. Most of the scenes of this biopic were in London, including famous stadiums such as Lords and Oval.</span>','List of Bollywood Biopics and Upcoming Biopic movies in 2020','','publish','open','open','','list-of-bollywood-biopics-and-upcoming-biopic-movies-in-2020','','','2020-12-25 17:44:54','2020-12-25 12:14:54','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=2832',0,'post','',1),(2850,6,'2020-09-29 13:20:55','2020-09-29 07:50:55','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When it comes to a name who has rocked the Gujrati Film Industry and</span><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hindi Film Industry</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. One name which pops out is Darshan Jariwala. So let us see his filmy career and see his journey till now on the occasion of his Birthday.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2856 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1-min-1-2.jpg\" alt=\"Darshan Jariwala birthday\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First, we should start with the starting of his life, Born in Bombay on 29th September 1958. Darshan Jariwala is an Indian Film Actor who has his roots in Gujrat. Jariwala was born to a Gujarati actress Leela Jariwala, who herself has acted in many Gujarati and Hindi films.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Darshan Jariwala Television Career</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Darshan started his Television career in the year 1997 from Kya Baat Hai. In that serial, he played Ram Daya Mehta. You know, he also appeared in the Hindi TV serial “</span><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saas_Bina_Sasural\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Saas Bina Saasural</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">” in the year 2010.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In this movie, he played Chedilal Chaturvedi and he was very much appreciated for his character.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Darshan Jariwala Filmy Career</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Darshan Jariwala started his film career very late in his life. He started his film career with the movie Style in the year 2001. He played the role of Principal Sardesai in the movie.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Gujrati Filmy Career</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He first started in Gujrati Film Industry. And also had made an appearance in several Gujarati plays. Some of the popular films in which he appeared are Haatheli pe Baadbaki, Patro Mitro, Andhalo Pato, and many more. One of his famous Gujrati movies is Oxygen which was released in 2018</span>\r\n<h3><b>Hindi Filmy Career</b></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2855 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2-min-3-2.jpg\" alt=\"Happy birthday Darshan Jariwala\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When it comes to Bollywood he has made several Appearances. Some of his famous</span><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/bollywood/\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bollywood movies</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are Ajab Prem Ki Gajab Kahani, Phata Poster Nikala Hero, Commando, F.A.L.T.U, Rajneeti, Aaja Nachle, Aarakshan, Gandhi-My father, and many more. The most loved movie of his was Gandhi-My Father.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Marathi Films and Plays</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mr. Jariwala made his Marathi debut with Swarajya in the year 2011. The movie is under the banner name of Raj Lashkariya Productions. He was appreciated by all the Marathi fans for his performance. Darshan has also acted in many Marathi plays such as Junngli Kabutarr and Dhaandevaik.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Darshan Jariwala English Play and His Company</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mr.Jariwala has a company of his which is named Leela Theatres. Leela Theatres has produced an</span><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/hollywood/\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">English Theatre and English Play</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. The name of the English Play is Salt &amp; Pepper. Also, the name of the English theatre is Your Place or Mine?.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Being on the International level</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2857 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/3-min-3-1.jpg\" alt=\"Darshan Jariwala movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the year 2007. Mr.Jariwala did a movie named Gandi -My Father. For this movie, he gets theNational Award.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The award was given in the field of Best Supporting Award. But it is said that his being in the character of Gandhiji was a great achievement in itself.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He also said that it was a great task physically. But it required more emotional contribution than physical. He had to lose a few kilos in order to be perfectly fit in the character.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Also, he wanted to keep the character to be neutral. Performing this character he made a great impact on the global platforms.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Darshan Jariwala Personal Front</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He tied knots with Television Personality Apaara Mehta in the year 1981. And they have a single daughter too.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">But he lives separately without his wife. Though they are not officially divorced.Though he says on this that when you are in great confusion as an actor you tend to watch yourself through the time period. And this thing helped me grow very much in my personal life as well as in Acting.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>Interesting Facts</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Recently has received an accolade for Best Supporting Actor. It was for the Gujrati movie Beey Yaar(2014). Saying of Mr Jariwala in the end, the acting talent and it’s relative skills only matter.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At last, he\'s very happy that Gujrati Regional Language films are coming up.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do comment down below and give your Best wishes to Darshan Jariwala.</span>','Darshan Jariwala | Movies, Tv Shows and Interesting Facts','','publish','open','open','','darshan-jariwala-movies-tv-shows-and-interesting-facts','','','2020-12-26 17:40:50','2020-12-26 12:10:50','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=2850',0,'post','',0),(2863,4,'2020-09-30 14:16:32','2020-09-30 08:46:32','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2865 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1-1.jpg\" alt=\"Oscar Winner Joaquin Phoenix welcomes baby boy with wife\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The lead actor of the Oscar-winning movie, Joaquin Phoenix, and his wife <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rooney_Mara\" rel=\"nofollow\">Rooney Mara</a> has been blessed with a child. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The happily married couple, who have been blessed with a baby boy had been confirmed to be expecting the arrival of a new member in their family back in the month of May.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>What is the name then?</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The name has been confirmed to be ‘River’ and there lies a story behind the name that has been given to the first child of their life together. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/film/2018/oct/25/the-untold-story-of-lost-star-river-phoenix-25-years-after-his-death\" rel=\"nofollow\">River Phoenix</a> was the older brother of Joaquin and unfortunately died of a drug overdose in 1993. With Joaquin’s brother having been born on the 23rd of August, it would be interesting to know if the birthday of the newly born is relatively close to his original birthday as well.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Late River Phoenix had a troubled life. He was an actor as well along with being an activist as well. With no proper schooling, he was a natural on the guitar.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Unfortunately, he succumbed to his death because of a drug overdose. He died at the very young age of 23 in 1993 when Joaquin was even younger.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>A Wonderful Tribute</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Definitely an emotional decision on the part of the couple to name their son ‘River’. Joaquin’s love for his brother is shown in such an emotional decision. </span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2866 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/3-1.jpg\" alt=\"Oscar Winner Joaquin Phoenix welcomes baby boy with wife\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Funny enough, River’s favourite show in the younger days was ‘Batman’. This was years and years ago before his brother would end up winning an Oscar for playing the arch-nemesis. This was one of the most famous Villains in the history of the character of Batman.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His wife ‘Mara’ who is 35 and Joaquin who is 45 himself has made the decision to pay tribute to the late ‘River’ in such a touching manner.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>How did the news break?</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It is interesting to know that the news of both the birth of the child and the naming of him did not come directly from either of the new father and mother.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In fact, according to US Magazine, the news was broken by Victor Kossakovasky who is a Russian Filmmaker. In a Question and Answer session during the 2020 film festival of Zurich earlier this week on Sunday, he confirmed the news. Present for his movie ‘Gunda’ which has in fact been produced by Joaquin Phoenix himself. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In fact, the news broke when Victor was asked why Phoenix was not present to promote the movie. Considering that such a huge personality, an Oscar winner promoting the movie that he has produced with garner a lot of attention.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When questioned, he said that Joaquin had recently been blessed with a beautiful boy who has been named ‘River’. That because of that reason, he was not available to promote the movie alongside the rest of them there.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are several interviews by Phoenix in which he spoke of his brother, his struggles with death, and his love for his brother as well. Considering all of it, it is not a surprise to see him pay tribute in such a manner.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>The Blessed Married Couple</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2867 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/2-1.jpg\" alt=\"Oscar Winner Joaquin Phoenix with wife\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The new parents met years ago in 2016 when they were both in the movie, ‘Mary Magdalene’. The wonderful actors met on the set in which Joaquin was the lead character playing the role of ‘Jesus’ in the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">movie</a>. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">They began dating once the movie concluded and have been together ever since.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">They even made their public appearance together during the Cannes Film Festival. After that they appeared together in the closing in the 2017 edition of the famous Film Festival. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Then last year broke the news that the couple had got engaged as well. They have been reported to have been engaged in July of 2019.</span>\r\n<blockquote><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">-Aayush Naik</span></blockquote>','Oscar Winner Joaquin Phoenix Welcomes Baby Boy with Wife Rooney Mara','','publish','open','open','','oscar-winner-joaquin-phoenix-welcomes-baby-boy-with-wife-rooney-mara','','','2020-12-25 17:43:16','2020-12-25 12:13:16','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=2863',0,'post','',0),(2875,4,'2020-10-02 19:39:13','2020-10-02 14:09:13','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2879 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/SS-min.jpg\" alt=\"10 reasons to watch Anurag Kashyap movies over Karan Johar Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Two of the most well-known names in the film industry in India. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anurag_Kashyap\" rel=\"nofollow\">Anurag Kashyap</a> and Karan Johar. We have seen movies and content made by both of them and there has been a lot of Karan johar and Anurag Kashyap movies! </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Most of us have a preference when it comes to the two filmmakers. From the style of direction to the type of story that is written to the realism and fantasy lands that are shown. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The differences between the two of them are very vast. And we are on the side of preference for Anurag Kashyap and the movies that he makes. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Looking to get convinced to watch Anurag Kashyap over Karan Johar? Well here is our top ten reasons why you should prefer Anurag Kashyap rather than Karan Johar movies.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>1. Realism vs Fantasy</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Anurag Kashyap has always relied on showing how the world really is, rather than a world of fantasy as Karan Johar so often does. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Looking at the movies made by Johar shows a world that does not exist, with barely any realism when compared to the movies made by Kashyap.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>2. Gritty vs Hesitant</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Anurag’s movies get as rough and tough as they can be. Watching movies such as ‘Gangs of Wasseypur’ shows us a rough and edgy world that Karan Johar has never done before. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Karan Johar has always been a great deal more hesitant to show the roughness of the world as it is.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>3. Middle-Class vs Rich</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Watching movies of Karan Johar such as ‘Student of the Year’ one thing is very obvious. The movie shows the lifestyle of the rich. The life that is not practical for so many of us. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">W</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">hile Kashyap’s movies such as the very underrated ‘Udaan’ show the life and world of middle-class families and how they survive every day.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>4. Type of Protagonist </strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The lead of the movie is very distinctly different in the movies that they make. You could combine all the points we write and add it to the type of protagonist they use. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Johar’s will be the perfect hero character that will save the damsel in distress and do the right thing. While Kashyap’s protagonist will be the real, conflicted character who wonders about what is right and what is wrong. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He shows his protagonist to be someone real and how many of us would react in the same situation.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>5. Outsiders vs Nepotism</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Karan Johar has a reputation of taking the only star kids and not giving the deserving candidates their chance. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So many of his movies neglect the new stars who want to make their name and cast <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/nepotism-and-favouritism-in-bollywood-star-kids-vs-outsiders/\">kids of already famous stars such as Alia Bhatt</a> etc. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Kashyap has always given priority to acting skills and gives debuts and opportunities to deserving people.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>6. Grounded vs Over the top</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Karan Johar has movies that are known to be over the top in all aspects. From the action scenes to the dramatic moments. They are all well known to be over the top and not realistic.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Kashyap has a method of showing raw emotions and realism in whatever he does. He shows the grounded characters reacting to how many of us would.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>7. Dialogue Writing</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Oh, where do we start with this one? What is your preference? </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/list-of-top-10-most-popular-salman-khan-dialogues-ever/\">Cliche cinematic dialogues</a> or original quality dialogues are written that are unique to the movie? You know which to choose. We won’t decide that for you.</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>8. Quality vs Commercia</strong>l</span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Kashyap has always made movies that give importance to quality rather than the amount of money that is made. In comparison, Johar’s movies rely heavily on revenue made. </span>\r\n<h3><strong>9. Open vs Conservative</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Anurag Kashyap is definitely not afraid to show anything. From intimate scenes as they are, to the blood and gore that make a movie more real. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Karan Johar and the conservative approach he takes to hold the movie back in several such aspects.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>10. Script vs Cast</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Anurag Kashyap first has the script and then casts appropriate actors for the film. While Karan Johar is more reliant on the stars being cast early and building the movie around them. More than enough reason to pick Kashyap.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">While both are definitely quality <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">movie makers</a>. There is an obvious preference on our part and we definitely believe you would be convinced by the end of it as well. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do you agree or disagree? Let us know in the comment section below!</span>\r\n<blockquote><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">-Aayush Naik</span></blockquote>','10 reasons to Watch Anurag Kashyap Movies over Karan Johar Movies','','publish','open','open','','10-reasons-to-watch-anurag-kashyap-movies-over-karan-johar-movies','','https://www.thetvfreak.com/nepotism-and-favouritism-in-bollywood-star-kids-vs-outsiders/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/list-of-top-10-most-popular-salman-khan-dialogues-ever/','2020-12-25 17:41:53','2020-12-25 12:11:53','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=2875',0,'post','',0),(2884,6,'2020-10-05 12:02:48','2020-10-05 06:32:48','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2889 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/1.jpg\" alt=\"happy birthday sanjay mishra\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When it comes to actors who can play a large variety of roles. <strong>Born on 6th October</strong> the actor who has a slight Bihari Ascent naturally. For <strong>Sanjay Mishra Birthday</strong>, we are unhiding some facts and interests related to him.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Then <a href=\"https://twitter.com/imsanjaimishra\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sanjay Mishra’s</a> name fits in perfectly in the slot. Sanjay Mishra is an actor in the Bollywood Industry. He especially is known for his comedy timing and his dynamic acting in movies like Golmaal, Dum Laga Ke Haisha.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So lets some of the interesting facts which are unknown to you:-</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sanjay Mishra Loves Photography </span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2896 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/8.jpg\" alt=\"sanjay mishra Loves Photography\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sanjay Mishra is a photogenic person. He likes to click pictures around various monuments and interesting places. Also, he likes to be clicked in a photo. It seems that he wants to spread happiness and positivity through his photos. </span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sanjay Mishra Loves Cooking</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2895 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/7.jpg\" alt=\"Sanjay Mishra Loves Cooking\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> He is a lover of cooking. It’s said that whenever Sanjay Ji goes outside for a shoot or on a tour. Then during that journey, he buys a cylinder, all the cooking materials and likes to cook at his accommodation.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Multilingual Actor</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2890 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/2.jpg\" alt=\"multilingual actor sanjay mishra\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As you are aware of Sanjay Mishra’s Versatility. But do you know that he is a multilingual actor?. Sanjay Mishra has worked in a variety of languages. Some of them are Bhojpuri, Tamil, Telegu.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of his famous films in the Telugu language is “Kick 2”.Some extraordinary characters portrayed by him are in the movies Golmal, Golmal Returns, Dum Laga Ke Haisa. He was also a part of the famous Hindi Tv Serial “Chanakya”.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sanjay Mishra Work Over Family</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2897 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/9.jpg\" alt=\"family love\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The attribute which makes an actor great is his dedication to his work. But Sanjay Mishra has touched the highest level of this attribute. I will share an incident with you listening to which you will be shocked. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once Mr.Sanjay was shooting for a movie named “Baadshaho”.In the middle of the shooting, he was informed of the news. The news was about his brother going into a coma. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The actor was shocked and eagerly wanted to see his brother. But at that moment he showed his greatness. He gave preference to his work, his shooting. That shows that acting is his job and he is fully committed to it.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Unique Philosophy on Small Films</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2893 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/5.jpg\" alt=\"phillosipy of small fans\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You might have seen many actors always wanting to do big-budget movies. Most of them try to avoid or keep away small budget films. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">But Mr.Mishra has a different take on that. He thinks that when you do small films then they provide you with handy practice sessions. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It is like you are doing rehearsals for the big-budget movies. He also shared an interesting thought. It was that when you sign a lot of small budget movies then you have the opportunity to travel a lot. And Sanjay Mishra loves traveling.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Has a Never Give Up Attitude</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2894 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/6.jpg\" alt=\"police role struggle\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tragedies have been a lot in Mr.Mishra’s life. Do you know that after his father’s demise?. He was so in that deep tragedy that he left his acting career once for all.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> And as an earning medium, he chooses to sell omelets in a Dhaba. People use to wonder why this man is doing like this, many advised him to continue his acting career. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">But he did not change his mind. Lastly, Rohit Shetty somehow made him agree to work on his movie named ”All the Best”.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sanjay Mishra Giving Several takes for his first acting shot</span></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2892 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/4.jpg\" alt=\"sanjay birthday\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the year 1991, when he was shooting for the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chanakya_(TV_series)\" rel=\"nofollow\">Tv serial Chanakya</a>. Then a kind of funny thing happened on the first day of the shoot. On the shoot day when Sanjay Mishra was giving his first shot. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He did not execute that shot properly. And he was so into the character that it took 28 </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">takes to take that one particular shot. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The takes failed because the Director had something different in his mind. And Sanjay Ji was naturally so much into character that he did those things that the Director did not want.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So that’s it, hope you like the content. Also, Subscribe to the webpage to get regular updates and <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">daily news in the entertainment industry</a>.</span>\r\n<blockquote>S.Mohan Kumar</blockquote>','Sanjay Mishra | Biography, Life, Facts and Interests | On His Birthday 6 oct','','publish','open','open','','sanjay-mishra-biography-life-facts-and-interests-on-his-birthday-6-oct','','','2021-01-24 17:07:31','2021-01-24 11:37:31','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=2884',0,'post','',0),(2910,4,'2020-10-09 21:12:32','2020-10-09 15:42:32','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The joy in our lives comes from watching films. The fun, entertainment, excitement, and thrill it provides is like nothing else that we can find in anything else. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">And among those comes comedy movies and the fun it provides. The joy and laughter they provide are unmatched. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So what are the best comedy movies that have been made in Bollywood? The ones that always give us joy, love, and happiness along with laughter! Here is the ultimate <strong>list of Comedy movies</strong> that have ever been made!</span>\r\n<h2><b>50) Entertainment (2014)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb Rating</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: 4.5</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Farhad Samji, Sajid</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Star Cast</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/akshay-khiladi-kumar-s-love-for-his-country/\">Akshay Kumar</a>, <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/tamannaahspeaks\">Tamannaah</a>, Johnny Lever</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2969 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/45-1.jpg\" alt=\"top 50 comedy movies \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weigh