falling-in-love/\">love &amp; bonding movies</a>, our pick of timeless flicks that have won (as well as broken) the hearts of the audience everywhere and reminded us what true marital affection is all about.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span>\r\n<h2><strong>1. Shaadi Ke Side Effects (2014)</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 5.6</b></li>\r\n <li><strong>Director: Saket Chaudhary</strong></li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast: Farhan Akhtar, Vir Das, <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/balanvidya/?hl=en\" rel=\"nofollow\">Vidya Balan</a></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3007 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/1-4.jpg\" alt=\"Shaadi Ke Side Effects (2014)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Any newly made Dad would testify that the transition from husbandhood to fatherhood is not a smooth one. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In this hilarious comedy, Sid (Farhan Akhtar) - a struggling musician by profession and a man child by nature is facing a similar challenge as his life is torn between playing the roles of a husband and a father while - Trisha (Vidya Balan), plays an ideal wife and mother.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Iu18_rNpTA0[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Shaadi Ke Side Effects gives us an amusing account of how a couple manages to keep their love intact in the early years of marriage which is fraught with confusion, uncertainty, and sometimes even comical tragedies. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie is rife with extremely witty dialogues delivered smoothly by Farhan Akhtar as well as having a few sensitive &amp; emotional moments shared between our on-screen couple. So if you are venturing into a serious relationship and want to witness a fun riot, these Husband-Wife Movies will not disappoint you. </span>\r\n<h2><strong>2. The Sky Is Pink (2019) </strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.5</b></li>\r\n <li><strong>Director: Shonali Bose</strong></li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast: Farhan Akhtar, <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/priyankachopra/?hl=en\" rel=\"nofollow\">Priyanka Chopra</a>, Zaira Wasim</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3008 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/2-4.jpg\" alt=\"The Sky Is Pink (2019) Husband-Wife Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">“It’s a small world” is a popular expression but go ask a couple who had to witness the demise of their child…for them, it’s a big, merciless, and devouring world. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This heart-wrenching, poignant yet warm film was widely considered to be one of the best movies of the year 2019. It has a remarkably strong script and groundbreaking performances by both Priyanka Chopra and Farhan Akhtar who play the roles of a normal couple trying to save their daughter’s (Zaira Wasim) life.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=prwUFBsDRLk[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Director Shonali Bose has put her heart out in exploring this true and overwhelming story that will leave you with an emotionally devastating cinematic experience but will also heal your soul by the end. </span>\r\n<h2><strong>3. Sui Dhaaga (2018)</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 6.8</b></li>\r\n <li><strong>Director: Sharat Katariya</strong></li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast: Anushka Sharma, Varun Dhawan, Namit Das</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3009 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/3-4.jpg\" alt=\"Sui Dhaga (2018) Husband-Wife Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Director Sharat Katariya of Dum Laga Ke Haisha (2015) fame brings another family movie set in the simplistic backdrop of a small town in UP. The life of Mauji (Varun Dhawan) changes completely after marriage when his wife Mamta (Anushka Sharma) motivates him to have a higher ambition in life while the couple struggles to make ends meet.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The first half of the movie is with rib-tickling scenes. While the second half is slightly melodramatic. The movie is very detailed when it comes to costumes, sets, and makeup. The characters are very authentic and the acting is impressive.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VUe3p23AJMo[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is a story of the struggles of a common family in India and a true example of the fact that you can achieve your dream, against all odds, once you set your heart to it.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span>\r\n<h2><strong>4. Toilet- Ek Prem Katha (2017)</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.2</b></li>\r\n <li><strong>Director: Shree Narayan Singh</strong></li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast: Bhumi Pednekar, Akshay Kumar, Anupam Kher</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3010 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/4-4.jpg\" alt=\"Toilet- Ek Prem Katha (2017)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Who would have thought that a social cause can be narrated comically and still be able to get the message through! Well, Toilet- Ek Prem Katha did a splendid job of doing just that. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie raises a major Indian issue of the need of having a toilet in a rural household. Akshay Kumar and Bhumi Pednekar give a very believable performance as a common man and an educated girl respectively.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ym4EJQ7XORk[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you are a fan of <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/akshay-khiladi-kumar-s-love-for-his-country/\">Akshay Kumar</a> and love his choice of scripts then this Husband-Wife Movies based on a social issue will not disappoint you.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>5. Pati Patni Aur Woh (2019)</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 5.8</b></li>\r\n <li><strong>Director: Mudassar Aziz</strong></li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast: Bhumi Pednekar, Ananya Panday, Kartik Aaryan</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3011 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/5-4.jpg\" alt=\"Pati Patni Aur Woh (2019) Husband-Wife Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Inspired by the original movie with the same name, which was directed by the legendary director B. R. Chopra, this movie focuses on the issue of an extra-marital affair in modern society. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Few years into the marriage, Abhinav Tyagi aka Chintu (Kartik Aryan), and Vedika Tripathi (Bhumi Pednekar) begin to lose their spark in married life. It was during this time that Chintu meets Tapasya Singh (Ananya Pandey) who enamours his heart and soon Chintu finds himself torn between his wife and “woh”!.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L7a1JSeqaXk[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie has a hilarious script and dialogues are apt to the screenplay. If you want to watch a light-hearted Husband-Wife Movies with friends then this one does the job.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>6. Luka Chuppi (2019)</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 6.7</b></li>\r\n <li><strong>Director: Bash Mohammed</strong></li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast: Kriti Sanon, Kartik Aaryan, Pankaj Tripathi</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3012 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/6-2.jpg\" alt=\"Luka Chuppi (2019) Husband-Wife Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you have recently heard the famous 90’s song “Poster Lagwa Do” on someone\'s cellphone as a ringtone, it’s probably a remake of the old song featured in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luka_Chuppi\" rel=\"nofollow\">Luka Chuppi</a>.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As developed as our modern Indian society may be, it still has big problems when it comes to accepting live-in relationships.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Guddu (Kartik Aaryan) and Rashmi (Kriti Sanon) - are a couple from Mathura. They hide their unmarried status and experience a live-in relationship in a small town.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This results in a series of hilarious situations that conclude to a very twisted climax. This light-hearted comedy was connected well with the audience and the spectacular performance by Pankaj Tripathi was a show-stealer.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SVj26LvQMPA[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Overall, it is a slapstick comedy with a simple storyline worth spending an afternoon with. This is the 6th movie from our Husband-Wife Movies list.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>7. Dum Laga Ke Haisha (2015)</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.5</b></li>\r\n <li><strong>Director: Sharat Katariya</strong></li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast: Ayushmann Khurrana, Sanjay Mishra, Bhumi Pednekar</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3013 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/7-2.jpg\" alt=\"Dum Laga Ke Haisha (2015)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ayushmann Khurrana is famous for his amazing performances. But Bhumi Pednekar - a new face in 2015 stunned the audience with her astoundingly natural acting of a girl struggling with her weight issues. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Set in the backdrop of the ’90s, this movie is based on a middle-class family that has an introvert and loyal son- Prem Prakash Tiwari (Ayushmann Khurrana), who follows the family tradition of arrange-marriage and ends up becoming a husband to an overweight girl - Sandhya Verma (Bhumi Pednekar).</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lFZpPpSU3k0[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The story explores the apprehension of a man under the pressure of getting married to a girl of his parent’s choice and the difficulties that a girl faces, after marriage, as she tries to adjust herself with her in-laws till fate turns a kinder side to them and the issues are neatly resolved by the end.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span>\r\n<h2><strong>8. Namastey London (2007)</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.1</b></li>\r\n <li><strong>Director: Vipul Amrutlal Shah</strong></li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast: Katrina Kaif, Akshay Kumar, Rishi Kapoor</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3014 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/8-2.jpg\" alt=\"Namastey London (2007)Husband-Wife Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It is said that “Man proposes and God disposes of”, in this case, it was a woman who proposed to live her life on her own terms but heavens had a different plan for her. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jazz (Katrina Kaif), an Indian girl born and raised in London, due to a strange turn of events, marries Arjun Ballu Singh (Akshay Kumar)- a desi Punjabi guy who can hardly form a sentence in the English language.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IPn66pCCQC4[/embedyt]</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Watch Full Movie:</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eol5ZfVo5eM[/embedyt] </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie captures the scenic view of London magnificently while making you feel good about India. It is a story that reminds us that if you love someone, truly and unconditionally, they will eventually come to you. </span>\r\n<h2><strong>9. Rab Ne Bana Di Jodi (2008)</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.2</b></li>\r\n <li><strong>Director: Aditya Chopra</strong></li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast: Anushka Sharma, Shah Rukh Khan, Vinay Pathak</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3015 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/9-2.jpg\" alt=\"Rab Ne Bana Di Jodi (2008)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It is said that to connect with someone you have to find something in common. Rab Ne Bana Di Jodi is an exception to that adage. If there ever was a couple with personalities poles apart, this is the one! </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Surinder (Shah Rukh Khan) - a man with the most boring, predictable, and mundane life imaginable marries Taani (Anushka Sharma). She is a vibrate, high spirit, and extrovert girl. And the result - an unhappy married life that becomes a drag for Taani but little did she know that her life is going to turn inside out and upside down, thanks to a dance show.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eBi8syxPd14[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rab Ne Bana Di Jodi is a beautiful movie with a brilliant soundtrack and choreography. The songs are both upbeat and cathartic. The chemistry between the pair is fantastic and is a must-watch these Husband-Wife Movies for all Shah Rukh Khan fans. </span>\r\n<h2><strong>10. Tanu Weds Manu Returns (2015) </strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating: 7.6</strong></li>\r\n <li><strong>Director: Aanand L. Rai</strong></li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast: Kangana Ranaut, Jimmy Sheirgill, R. Madhavan</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3016 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/10-1.jpg\" alt=\"Tanu Weds Manu Returns (2015) Husband-Wife Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A sequel to the major box office hit Tanu Weds Manu (2011), this movie pulled all the viewers of its prequel to theatres and a lot of new ones. The film takes on where its prequel left off and is about the life of Tannu (Kangana Ranaut) and Manu (R. Madhavan) after-marriage.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wGGmyaurjAI[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie is based on the less appealing side of arrange marriage which sometimes leads to the shattering of our expectations from our partner as bitterness and disappointment sets in our hearts. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Kangana Ranaut has completely immersed herself in her characters - yes, you read that correctly, she plays a dual role in the movie and has done such an outstanding job that there are moments when you forget it’s the same actress playing two different characters. This one of the top Husband-Wife Movies.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is a wonderful rom-com by Aanand L. Rai that explores some issues but overall carries a happy emotional tone, making it a complete family entertainment for the audience.</span>','Top Bollywood Husband-Wife Love & Bonding Movies.','','publish','open','open','','top-bollywood-husband-wife-movies','','https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-movies-about-billionaires-falling-in-love/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/akshay-khiladi-kumar-s-love-for-his-country/','2021-01-19 11:29:27','2021-01-19 05:59:27','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3004',0,'post','',0),(3028,8,'2020-10-28 15:16:13','2020-10-28 09:46:13','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3038 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/1-5.jpg\" alt=\"SCAM 1992 : Behind the Hype\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Okay, before I even begin to dissect every bit of series \"SCAM 1992\", let me tell you why I started watching it in the first place: the groovy theme track. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Oh boy! I have to say Achint Kakkar did a great job making this piece of music. Well, the graphics designer for the credits scene deserves a raise too but all that aside, let’s unravel what the hype is all about.</span>\r\n<h2>The \"This and That\" You Should Know...</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Based on the famous Stock Broker <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harshad_Mehta\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Harshad Shantilal Mehta</a>’s rags-to-riches life, Scam 1992 is a chronicle of how one can fall back hard if they rise without their feet planted to the ground. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Frustrated from working menial jobs and his small house and a life full of compromises, Mehta decides to try his luck in the stock market. And sure enough, as you know, he makes it B-I-G.</span>\r\n<h3>Didn\'t you watch the Trailer, Go Ahead:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ISORfez27og[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">From the high-stakes trading scenes at the “Ring” at the Bombay Stock Exchange or the smooth meetings that Harshad so eloquently pulls off with high ranking officers of the big banks of the country, this series has all to offer. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">And sure enough, watching a Gujrati do business is already entertaining enough but when you pack that with the sub-plots involving the foreign banks and the then socio-economic portrayal of the country, it automatically becomes the phenomenon that this <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/series/\">series</a> has become.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3039 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/2-5.jpg\" alt=\"SCAM 1992 \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The character of Sucheta Dalal, who busted this entire scam has surprisingly neither been portrayed as heroic nor villainous, instead, it is more of an anti-hero. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Maybe that is because by the end the viewer develops so much attachment to Harshad Mehta that his enemies seem a little less heroic to you, but that’s just my theory.</span>\r\n<h2>The Cast Couldn\'t Have Been Better</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It would be fair to say that no one could have pulled off Harshad Mehta’s character as Pratik Gandhi did. The conviction in his acting, the confidence, the Gujrati Factor, and of course, the looks which so closely resemble the real-life Broker have made us all believe no one else could have played it better.</span>\r\n<h2>Check out the best Dialogue:</h2>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dYvr9RPfxlM[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A dialogue from the series “Agar Risk hai to Ishq hai” comes various times in the series. It comes particularly when he has to grease a bank official into doing something which involves a considerable amount of risk. The characters of Manu Mundra (played by Satish Kaushik) and Mr Rao (played by Mamik Singh) make sure there is never any comical draught in the series. What can I say, I can watch Satish Kaushik verbally abuse any day of the week and be content with it.</span>\r\n<h3>Check out, what the Ujjwal Patani Says about the movie:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QXfEaJrZjqg[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Notable characters such as <a href=\"https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kochi/cbi-former-joint-director-k-madhavan-passes-away/articleshow/73363574.cms\" rel=\"nofollow\">CBI Agent K Madhavan</a> (Played by Rajat Kapoor) and RBI Governor S Venkatraman appear much later in the series but I have to admit, they make up pretty well for their absence in the initial part of the series. Rajat Kapor has been just phenomenal in his acting. His part is very convincing, and keeps you on the edge of your seats, especially during the interrogation scenes.</span>\r\n<h2>Did I Mention How Amazing the Filmography Was?</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Well now that I have seen the series, I am beyond convinced that Hansal Mehta (The Director) has a forte for the Urban Drama genre. His directorial supremacy is clearly evident in the brilliant character placement and the well-researched peek into the stock market that the viewer gets to witness.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3037 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/3-5.jpg\" alt=\"SCAM 1992 : Behind the Hype\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The tension that builds up is quite subtle but you can really feel it as the story ends. It would be foolish to say that the series is targeted only towards the people in the commerce sector.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Although I have to warn you,  the first episode can be a bit heavy on financial terminology. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, I urge you to stick for some time, as things will be as clear as a whistle by the time you are halfway through the series. I am a Medical Student and heck, even I could follow all the banking words and phrases(with a few Googles of course).</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Coming to Sucheta Dalal’s portrayal of this entire “Scam 1992”, I believe that she has been really honest in her approach as to why she was hell-bent on uncovering Harshad Mehta’s dirty business and a simple answer to that is FAME which she conveniently admits several times in the show. And I, for one, am not judging her.</span>\r\n<h2>If it Wasn\'t Clear By Now.....</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This series has its fair share of political sub-plots and to spare you the spoilers, let’s not discuss that. However, I am definitely going to mention one mysterious “Swami Ji” who seems to be the big guy pulling all the strings in the unfortunate series of events for Harshad Mehta. Without divulging much into the details of the plot, let me say that this series has been an eye-opener for me. I’ll leave the rest up to you.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As an Indian, you can’t help but develop a strange sense of satisfaction and even develop an affection for Harshad Mehta. And why not, after all, he destroys the monopoly of various foreign banks in the money market and pumps huge sums of money in the stock market which makes the Sensex shoot up. He makes huge sums of money, not just for himself but also for the clients of his </span>broking firm.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">To sum it up, this is a power-packed series full of everything one could ask for. It has drama, comedy, tragedy, knowledge and the cherry on the top is, of course, the “Based on Real Events” tag. In Hansal Mehta’s Scam 1992 you watch bouts of pure Buearocracy with such interest even you will be surprised at yourself. And yes, if you can handle a few cuss words, this is the one to watch along with your dad!</span>\r\n<h2>Also, Read</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-bollywood-husband-wife-movies/\">Top Bollywood Husband-Wife Love &amp; Bonding Movies.</a></li>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-50-ultimate-list-of-comedy-movies-funniest-films-you-must-watch/\">Top-50 Ultimate List of Comedy Movies</a></li>\r\n</ul>','SCAM 1992 : The Harshad Mehta Story, Behind the Hype','','publish','open','open','','scam-1992-the-harshad-mehta-story-behind-the-hype','','https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-bollywood-husband-wife-movies/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/top-50-ultimate-list-of-comedy-movies-funniest-films-you-must-watch/','2021-01-19 11:21:32','2021-01-19 05:51:32','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3028',0,'post','',3),(3048,7,'2020-10-29 18:11:13','2020-10-29 12:41:13','<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Befuddled, bemused, confounded, and confused!. They have challenged the audience\'s intelligence. They made them question their sensibilities. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Today, we look at the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/hollywood/\">top 10 Hollywood Movies</a> that nobody understands. So, in case you have bragged to your friends that you “get” them but secretly don’t. Worry not! Your secret is safe with us.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>10. Predestination (2014)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We begin with the most recently released movie on our list. Starring Ethan Hawke and Sarah Snook for the “most parts” (pun intended), this groundbreaking time travel sci-fi is based on a short story called <a href=\"https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/13030110-all-you-zombies\" rel=\"nofollow\">All You Zombies</a> by legendary science fiction writer <a href=\"https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/205.Robert_A_Heinlein\" rel=\"nofollow\">Robert A. Heinlein</a>.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3074 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/thetvfreak-11.jpg\" alt=\"movies like Predestination (2014)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ethan Hawke’s character (known as The Bartender) is a <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/10-best-time-travel-movies-you-must-watch-right-now/\">time-traveling</a> agent working for a secret agency. As his final assignment, he must stop a terrorist known as the Fizzle Bomber. He detonates a bomb in New York City in 1975 killing thousands.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This highly complicated time-travel movie starts off slow but takes a very hard turn when you are least expecting. The plot turns suspenseful. Soon, you will find it challenging to guess the direction in which the story is heading till a great revelation is made in the climax that leaves you putting plot-pieces together.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you are a fan of the sci-fi genre in Hollywood movies, this film will impact you heavily. It will leave you thinking for weeks.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xxG-YfedrfU[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>9. American Psycho (2000)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Patrick Bateman (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Christian_Bale\" rel=\"nofollow\">Christian Bale</a>) is a rich New York City Investment Banker. He lives a superficial life of normality. But deep-down, within him, hides a murderous monster. At work, he spends time listening to music and envying his colleagues. Outside of work, he unleashes his repressed rage by butchering just about anyone, colleagues, women, bums, and even dogs.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3068 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/thetvfreak-5.jpg\" alt=\"movies like American Psycho (2000)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie turns mind-bending when one of the colleagues whom he had killed makes an appearance in the movie later. It is at this point that the line between reality and imagination becomes blurred. The audience is made to wonder whether his heinous crimes are real or just figments of his psychotic imagination.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Christian Bale has delivered cinema’s one of the most convincing performances as a psychopath. If you are a fan of film noir with a strong stomach, this gritty movie will appeal to your dark side.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5YnGhW4UEhc[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>8. The Fountain (2006)</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3075 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/thetvfreak-12.jpg\" alt=\"The Fountain (2006)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another one from Darren Aronofsky, this is a sci-fi cum love story. Hugh Jackman and Rachel Weisz play eternal lovers who are destined to live in tragedy through their several incarnations over the course of three stories set in the past, present, and future woven together into one masterpiece of art.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie deals with the philosophical aspect of human mortality and the cycle of life. The storyline is nonlinear and the scenes and special effects are exquisite. At the crux, this is a simple story beneath layers and layers of artistic refinement and glorious imagery.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3069 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/thetvfreak-6.jpg\" alt=\"movies like The Fountain (2006)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The performance of both actors can be described as remarkable. Hugh Jackman and Rachel Weisz have made their characters deep and emotional with their hearts filled with love. The Fountain makes heavy use of symbolism and is not meant to be appreciated by all types of Hollywood movies audience.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m8IlyFCbNZg[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>7. Mulholland Dr. (2001)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">David Lynch’s Mullholand Dr. is widely considered to be a masterpiece without anyone actually getting the point of this movie. This is a dream-like film that would carry on stirring up your thoughts long after you have watched it.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3065 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/thetvfreak-2.jpg\" alt=\"Mullholand Dr. (2001)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mullholand Dr. is the story of a struggling actress Diane Selwyn (Naomi Watts) who falls in love with a successful actress Camilla Rowles (Laura Harring). When Diane realizes that her love will remain unrequited she plans to get rid of Camilla by hiring a hitman. She consequently, gets her comeuppance in the form of deep guilt. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This Academy Award-nominated movie has a top-notch performance by Naomi Watts. We suggest, before watching this movie you get acquainted with the filmmaking style of David Lynch by watching <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Lynch_filmography\" rel=\"nofollow\">some of his other creations</a>. This movie requires a patient viewer. You will definitely have to watch it a second time for your mind to pick up clues from this movie to make meaning of the storyline.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jbZJ487oJlY[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>6. Donnie Darko (2001)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Not every movie has a fansite dedicated to it. This movie does and you can check it out <a href=\"http://www.donniedarko.org.uk/\" rel=\"nofollow\">here!</a> Set in the small and simple town of Middlesex, Virginia this movie has a not-so-simple (or even linear) storyline.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3066 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/thetvfreak-3.jpg\" alt=\"Mullholand Dr. (2001)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It follows the eponymous protagonist, who is later described in the movie to be a paranoid schizophrenic over the course of a month. In this period, he has visions of Frank, a seven-foot-tall guy wearing a metal-headed, skull-faced, rabbit suit that gives him the appearance of a demon. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Frank guides Donnie (Jake Gyllenhaal) to avert the end of the world. As to why the world is ending, no clear explanation has been provided in the movie. Frank travels time by going back in the past and making Donnie aware of an event that will result in Donnie\'s demise while manipulating him to commit a series of crimes.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The tone of the movie is very dismal. A lot of viewers have found this movie to be unbearably weird.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZZyBaFYFySk[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>5. Pi (1998)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Most of us are not good in numbers, but they speak to a few gifted individuals. We call them Math Prodigies. However, our next movie on the list is so incredibly complex that it was hard to pin down even by mathematicians.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3070 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/thetvfreak-7.jpg\" alt=\"Mullholand Dr. (2001) Hollywood movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This debut movie of director Darren Aronofsky is based on a number theorist, Max (Sean Gullette) whose obsession with an apparently “divine number” leads him on a convoluted journey. Max suffers from paranoia and hallucinations making the line between delusion and reality very ambiguous.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film explores several religious and existential themes. When added to all the mathematics stuff, it culminates in a film that goes over most viewers\' heads. All we can say is that right down to its rather vague ending, this movie has something going on that has to do with the number Pi.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r0SC582sJvE[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>4. Cloud Atlas (2012)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Creator of the Matrix trilogy, the Wachowski duos are famous for creating ambiguous plots but this adaptation makes their other stuff seem simple and unambitious.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3071 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/thetvfreak-8.jpg\" alt=\"Mullholand Dr. (2001) Hollywood movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cloud Atlas follows several groups of characters, played by Tom Hanks, Halle Berry, Hugo Weaving, and others, whose lives seem connected especially since these actors play multiple characters across the tale.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Whether they are reincarnations of one another is somewhat unclear and the fact that some stories are referred to as fictional in the context of other segments leaves the viewers uncertain as to what is real and what is not.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hWnAqFyaQ5s[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>3. The Tree of Life (2011)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hollywood movies director <a href=\"https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000517/?ref_=nv_sr_srsg_0\" rel=\"nofollow\">Terrence Malick</a> is known for his symbolic style of expressing ideas. The Tree of Life is ostensibly a visual story about a man with the name Jack (Sean Penn) and his boyhood experiences.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3073 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/thetvfreak-10.jpg\" alt=\"The Tree of Life (2011) Hollywood movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You will find that this movie is interspersed with imagery of the creation of the Universe and the development of Earth with its sparse dialogues and seemingly random but beautifully shot footage. The Tree of Life is definitely an art-house film. Therefore, this movie isn’t for everyone since such films are often open to interpretation.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RrAz1YLh8nY[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>2. Primer (2004)</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3067 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/thetvfreak-4.jpg\" alt=\"Primer (2004) Hollywood movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie left even the critics divided. Primer is a prime example of movies that nobody understands. All we have are theories. Even those can be difficult to wrap our brains around.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Primer depicts two friends. They invent time travel and the fallout of their attempts at manipulating the past. Typical time-travel mayhem ensues with multiple versions of the characters encountering one another and themselves as well as branching timelines.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Very little of the technical jargon is dumbed down for the audience. So unless you are very good in engineering terminology a lot of details can be really hard to follow.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3064 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/thetvfreak-1.jpg\" alt=\"Primer (2004) Hollywood movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With Shane Carruth as the writer, director, and star of the movie, you will find yourself watching Primer time and again in hopes of understanding it.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-vD-yj9o664[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>1. 2001: A Space Odyssey (1968)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What to say about this movie that hasn’t already been said? Stanley Kubrick’s 2001 a Space Odyssey, the grandmaster of all space-travel movies. It is a work of science-fiction that inspired many Hollywood movies in the same genre.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3072 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/thetvfreak-9.jpg\" alt=\"A Space Odyssey (1968) Hollywood movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2001: A Space Odyssey is one trippy trip through space. This film is in three sections. First at the dawn of man, next on a manned space flight, and lastly in a strange environment experienced by the last surviving astronaut of the space journey. All these are connected by a mysterious monolith.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oR_e9y-bka0[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Firstly, This movie tells you its story primarily through visuals and music. That\'s why it is very thematically driven rather than story-driven though the middle is fairly straightforward.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Secondly, This masterpiece is absolutely captivating from its beginning to its surreal and grandiose end. It deserves the top spot on our list of top 10 Hollywood Movies that nobody understands.</span>\r\n<blockquote><b>- Abhishek Tewari</b></blockquote>\r\n<h2><strong>Also Read:</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-sports-movies-based-on-real-life-stories/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Best Sports Movies Based on Real Life Stories</a></li>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/science-and-mathematics-movies-based-on-real-life/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Top 13 Movies like Hidden Figures Based on Real Life</a></li>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-real-life-movies-based-on-entrepreneurs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">11 Entrepreneur Movie like Steve jobs Based on Real Life</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Top 10 Hollywood Movies that nobody understands.','','publish','open','open','','top-10-hollywood-movies-that-nobody-understands','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/10-best-time-travel-movies-you-must-watch-right-now/','2021-01-09 11:20:41','2021-01-09 05:50:41','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3048',0,'post','',0),(3084,8,'2020-10-31 21:12:49','2020-10-31 15:42:49','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We often look for an escape from our boring and mundane lives. Be honest, how often do you curse your 9-to-5 job. You wish you led a more adventurous life, right? So you open your device and look for one of those James Bond classics. The foreign locations, the women, the booze, and of course the cars you see have you hating your life even more. But the matter of fact is that the lives of actual spies aren’t all that glamorous.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So naturally, you go on looking for some real-life thrilling spy movies and that lands you here. Let me introduce you to these top 5 real-life spy movies. These <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">movies</a> will keep you on the edge of your seats. And yes, you can thank me later</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Munich (2015)</span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">IMDb: 7.5/10</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is the gut-wrenching story of Israeli MOSSAD spies who were a part of an operation so massive and dangerous that it had to be named “<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operation_Wrath_of_God\" rel=\"nofollow\">Operation Wrath of God</a>.”</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3092 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/3-6.jpg\" alt=\"Munich (2015)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The 1972 Olympics massacre of 11 Olympians from the Israel Team left the entire country and the whole world shook. The terrorist group Black September was responsible.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Promising to take revenge, the Israel Government sends their deadly <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mossad\" rel=\"nofollow\">MOSSAD</a> spies on a manhunt for those responsible. TWENTY YEARS! The MOSSAD hunted the Palestinian Terrorist Group for twenty-whole-years until almost everyone who had a hand in the attack was dead.</span>\r\n<h3>What\'s so Different?</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie keeps us hooked to the screens as the modus operandi of the Israeli’s is something to watch. The novel ways and means by which they avenge their fallen countrymen are striking indeed! Buying information, killing for information, or not bothering at all and just killing, this movie packs a punch!</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0LFfT44BlaQ[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie also portrays how difficult life is for a spy. Not seeing one’s family for twenty years is painful. This cinematographic masterpiece by Steven Spielberg is the one to watch closely, should you blink an eye, you miss what happens, eh, I mean, who dies. This is one of the most-watched spy movies.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Argo (2012)</span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">IMDb:7.7/10</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2nd one from the list of real-life spy movies. I had heard a lot about this movie because of the three friggin’ Oscars it took home. Can you believe three! So, finally, I decided to watch it. And if it were up to me I’d give this film three more Oscars. Yes, it is that good.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3090 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/1-6.jpg\" alt=\"Argo\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In 1979, when the Iran-US tensions are at a peak, protests break out in the Capital City of the former, Tehran. Caught in the wildfire, the locals invade the U.S. Embassy in Tehran. They try to kill every American they can lay their hands on. Luckily, a group of people escapes the embassy. They lodge themselves in the residence of the Canadian Ambassador to Iran.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie is a story of how the CIA sends an “Exfil” expert (abb. exfiltration) to rescue their men. Tony Mendez’s  (played by Ben Affleck) job is to bring back all of them unharmed. How he does it? He poses as a Canadian film director wanting to shoot in Tehran. The name of the film, you ask? It’s Argo.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Watch this thriller if you are….. No wait, there’s no “if’s and but’s” for this one, JUST WATCH IT. Yes, it’s THAT good. And side note, Ben Affleck’s hairstyle in this movie is something I’m personally trying to emulate. Eh, too much information?</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w918Eh3fij0[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Confessions of a Dangerous Mind (2002)</span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">IMDb:7/10</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you were an American and born 60 years ago, you wouldn’t need an introduction to Chuck Barris. But probably, you are neither of them, are you? That’s why I’m here to help.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3091 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/2-6.jpg\" alt=\"Confessions of a Dangerous Mind spy movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chuck Barris was a famous television show presenter who was once a household name in the U.S. He had written ideas for various superhit TV Reality Shows and Game Shows and hosted them too. But here comes the twist. He claimed to be a CIA assassin. And this spy movie is about his life as an agent. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The CIA had never officially accepted him as their agent. And hence you can see why the movie gained so much fame. But then, spy agencies are famous for not acknowledging their men.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Barris’s character, played by Sam Rockwell, grows at a steady pace as the movie proceeds. From someone who is rejected by most women, he becomes the “ladies’ man” as the movie ends. At the beginning of the movie, Barris is shown to be feeble and shaky but oh boy! he transforms into this charismatic, sharp, and somewhat lethal spy.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mWyLE7kjGrw[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This one is a no-brainer when it comes to getting that dose of controversy you’ve been longing for. And don’t take my word for it, the ratings speak for their own.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Zero Dark Thirty (2012)</span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">IMDb: 7.4/10</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do you like movies with satisfying endings? If the answer is yes, you are definitely gonna love this one. This is the story of how a brave CIA analyst named Maya spends a whole decade tracking the most wanted man in America, yes, Osama Bin Laden. Interested yet?</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3093 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/4-5.jpg\" alt=\"Zero Dark Thirty\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Maya (played by Jessica Chastain) is on a blood-thirsty hunt for Al-Qaeda’s whereabouts. She does everything in the books to get to her goal. Her resilience and determination often leave us awestruck. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sure, she gets her fair share of failures, but she just cuts through them like a hot knife on butter. From bomb attacks to bureaucratic hurdles, she faces them all. And did I tell you being an analyst and a woman in the CIA is not the best combination?</span>\r\n<h3>Famous. For all the Wrong Reasons Though...</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film also attracted some unwanted attention for showing some gruesome torture scenes. Some interpreted it as an exposé and some said it was pro-torture propaganda. Either way, it got some free publicity.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The final sequence where they actually hunt down UBL(short for Osama) is the one where you hold your breath. And to be frank, the part where they dramatize the decade long hunt for Al Qaeda operatives is a treat to watch. Getting an insight into CIA’s “methodologies” and how they retrieve information is a mind-game for any spy nerd.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Strong women, I need not tell you why you should watch and promote this movie. And yeah, for your convenience this one is available on many famous streaming platforms.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LJFra3B9sbA[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bridge of Spies (2015)</span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">IMDb: 7.6/10</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is my most recent discovery in this genre. Ok so let me acclimatize you with the setting of the movie. The year is 1957, the height of the Cold War between the U.S. and the USSR. Espionage is at its peak. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Agents from both sides are trading information, getting caught, killed, and being disowned by their respective nations. The threat of a Nuclear War looms over everyone’s head. In the middle of all this, the CIA catches a Russian Spy.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3094 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/5-5.jpg\" alt=\"Bridge of Spies (2015) spy movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The funny thing is that the lawyer appointed to the spy thinks he shouldn’t die. Tom Hanks plays the lawyer, who convinces the Supreme Court to defer his death penalty in order to exchange him for one of the US soldiers caught in the USSR. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie portrays Tom Hanks as a prudent lawyer who is a master of negotiation. He is sent off to East Berlin to negotiate the exchange of the Prisoners on behalf of his Government.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mBBuzHrZBro[/embedyt]\r\n<h3>Spielberg on the Director\'s Chair</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film has some very light-hearted emotional scenes and of course some bureaucracy as well. The part filmed in East Berin in the winters is such a cinematically pleasing experience. Film aficionados like me will appreciate Steven Spielberg’s way of shooting this spy movies. It alternates between parts where the lead is submissive to other characters and then suddenly he dominates. This cycle continues until he succeeds in doing what his government sent him to do.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I will be honest, I am a self-proclaimed sucker for cold war movies. Sometimes, I wish I could get to experience life back then. I know it sounds a bit stupid, but imagine meeting a real-life spy. Sadly, they haven’t invented time machines yet, so this spy movie is the closest to the real deal. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I believe that’s enough said about this one.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Okay, so a few points to take away from this article : </span>\r\n<ol>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Steven Spielberg is the king of this genre</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Spies don’t have the life they show in Bond movies.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You are really really bad at history. And these movies encourage you to learn about some of the major events that have shaped civilization as we know it today.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Kudos to everyone who has read this far. Happy spy movies watching.</span>\r\n<blockquote><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Article by Sarthak Sharma</span></blockquote>\r\n<h2>Also read:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/best-crime-movies-based-on-true-life-stories/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Top 11 Crime Movies Based on True Life Stories</a></li>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/courtroom-movies-based-on-real-life-stories/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Best Collection of Courtroom Movies based on Real Life Stories</a></li>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-11-terrorism-movies-based-on-real-life/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Top 11 Terrorism Movies based on Real Life</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Trust Me! You Need to Watch These 5 Real Life Spy Movies','','publish','open','open','','trust-me-you-need-to-watch-these-5-real-life-spy-movies','','https://www.thetvfreak.com/best-crime-movies-based-on-true-life-stories/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/courtroom-movies-based-on-real-life-stories/','2021-01-24 09:07:55','2021-01-24 03:37:55','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3084',0,'post','',1),(3087,6,'2020-11-01 22:32:23','2020-11-01 17:02:23','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3100 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/1-7.jpg\" alt=\"Vijay verma mirzapur 2\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><strong>Vijay Verma Biography</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When it comes to counting on an Actor who can act in a variety of roles in both Tollywood and <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/bollywood/\">Bollywood</a>. The name which pops out is Vijay Verma. Born on the 29th of March in the year 1984.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mr.Verma is a Telegu cum Hindi Actor. He was born in Hyderabad(Andhra Pradesh)-present Telangana. Vijay Verma hails from a Marwadi Family.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Early Life</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3102 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/3-7.jpg\" alt=\"Vijay verma mirzapur 2\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">From Childhood, Vijay was interested in Acting and he always wanted to become an actor. Vijay had a great passion for Acting. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After completing his basic studies, Vijay got himself enrolled in FTII. FTII(Film and Television Institute of India) is an autonomous body backed by the Ministry of Information &amp; Broadcasting, India. Vijay holds a Post Graduate Degree in acting from the Film and Television Institute of India.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Struggle to get Into FTII</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Though Vijay Verma was very much interested in acting and was passionate about making a career in it. But his mother disliked the fact that he wanted to pursue acting as a career. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She also refused to send Vijay to FTII. But he did not lose any hope. Despite parent’s refusal, Vijay Verma went to FTII, Pune. His funding for the acting course was done by a close friend.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Journey to the Acting Industry</strong></h2>\r\n<h3><strong>Performing Theatres</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3104 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/5-6.jpg\" alt=\"performing theaters\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Vijay performed Theatres at a very early age. Performing in theatres gave Vijay an On Ground Experience in Acting. And also he worked in a variety of plays. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He gained a lot of exposure while acting in plays. And this exposure helped him to get a chance in FTII and complete the course with grace. </span>\r\n<h3><strong>Getting First Film</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Vijay Verma got his Bollywood Breakthrough way back in the year 2008. His debut was in the movie ‘Shor’ which is a <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/trust-me-you-need-to-watch-these-5-real-life-spy-movies/\">thriller movie</a>. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Vijay could not hit success with his first film. But the movie won the title for the Best Short film at MIAAC Festival. The MIAAC festival was held in New York in the year 2008.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Films in a Line</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3101 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/2-7.jpg\" alt=\"movies gully boy\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Thereafter his first film in the year 2008. Vijay got his second movie in the year 2012. He did the movie Chittagong. Thereafter one of his dreams came true when he worked with Amitabh Bachchan. Vijay Verma and Amitabh Bachchan were part of the famous movie ‘PINK’.After the PINK movie, he had no looking back. He got a wide range of offers from various Directors. He acted in</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bollywood Blockbuster movies like  Bhaagi 3, Super 30(Special Appearance), Gully Boy.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Tollywood Debut</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Vijay got the opportunity to make his Tollywood Debut in the year 2017. He debuted in the movie Middle-Class Abbayi. The movie had Natural Star Nani and Sai Pallavi as it’s lead role actors. Vijay Played a sort of state mafia type of character. Fans appreciated lot for Vijay’s effort. Vijay was born and brought up in the Megacity Hyderabad. He had no problem with speaking Telegu.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Vijay Verma on Middle-Class Abbayi</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The actor told in an interview that he learned a lot of things being on the sets of MCA. And he was amazed to see the huge fan following of Natural Start Nani. Also after the release of the movie Vijay went to Hyderabad to see the movie on the first day itself. He saw the movie with Nani. He also mentioned that when the Director of MCA narrated the story to Vijay, he immediately gave a Yes.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Being Hit on the OTT series</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3103 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/4-6.jpg\" alt=\"she series\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Vijay acted in two of the most lovable OTT platform series. One is A Suitable Boy and the Next One is Mirzapur 2. He was also in the lead role in the Series \"She\". This series is about the female constable that how she stuck in the Mortuary market. The series is so much loved by the audience.</span>\r\n<h4>\"She\" Trailer:</h4>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WPlXILGpOFk[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><strong>A Suitable Boy</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Vijay Verma played the role of Rashed in the OTT series A suitable Boy. The film consists of Tabu, Ishaan Khattar as its leads. Rasheed is a sort of character who loves poetry and is always poetic in his world.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Mirzapur 2</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3099 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/7-3.jpg\" alt=\"verma mirzapur 2\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Vijay Verma is one of the main characters of the web series Mirzapur. Mr Verma is playing a part of the Tyagi Family. He is amazed to work with an iconic cast-said Vijay. He also said that let’s hope and see that if he could create his own space. Vijay also said that playing a character in the Mirzapur series was very challenging as well as interesting. As the Director of the Series wanted it to be more authentic. So Vijay had to take help from the writer of the series to understand the Bihari language.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xMKzdQrC5TI[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Also, Vijay saw a wide range of Bihari Videos. He also gave a glance and observed how Pankaj Tripathi used to deliver the dialogues as he was from Bihar. All this Vijay had to do to get that Bihari accent. He had to work on his body language also.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Vijay’s Words</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3105 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/6-3.jpg\" alt=\"Vijay verma movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h3><strong>Rise of OTT culture</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Vijay in an interview says that OTT platforms are providing a great forum for the new actors to perform. Also, people in this stressful world can take out time and watch high-quality content with their families. And watching anything on an OTT platform in a particular language is not a barrier at all. Watching multilingual content is an opportunity for the viewers to get into other cultures and know them.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Coming Future</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He also says that irrespective of the competition between various OTT platforms, the mainstream cinema culture will bloom like anything in the coming months. All the people are awaiting due to the lockdown and eager to see movies in the theatres. Cinemas are not going to die so soon.</span>\r\n\r\nHope you like the Content on Vijay Verma. To subscribe to the website to get the latest updates on the Entertainment Industry.\r\n<blockquote>By-S.Mohan Kumar</blockquote>','Vijay Verma from Mirzapur 2 | Biography, Series and Movies','','publish','open','open','','vijay-verma-from-mirzapur-2-biography-series-and-movies','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/trust-me-you-need-to-watch-these-5-real-life-spy-movies/','2021-01-24 17:07:24','2021-01-24 11:37:24','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3087',0,'post','',2),(3107,8,'2020-11-18 20:25:19','2020-11-18 14:55:19','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What if I told you <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/harshvarrdhankapoor\" rel=\"nofollow\">Harshvardhan Kapoor</a> has some T-Shirts that he paid over 70 thousand rupees for. You would definitely say, “ What\'s the big deal? He is an actor and actors (celebrities) wear outrageously expensive clothes all the time.” But what if I were to tell you that the T-Shirt actually costs just 4000 rupees. Shocked yet?</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ranbir Kapoor has several pairs of shoes, each of them costing him north of 2 Lakh Rupees. How much is the retail price on them? Barely 12 thousand Rupees! </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So why did everyone and their grandmother began spending a fortune on clothes that aren\'t even from luxury brands, just Nikes and some skate brands? Let\'s break down the hype.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>SUPREME: WHO BEGAN IT ALL</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Founded in 1994 by  James Jebbia, Supreme was just a small skateboarding shop in New York. It was rebellious in its design, openly defying authorities and holding skate meets where a bunch of teens would do skateboarding tricks (and maybe vandalise some cop cars).</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Little did anyone know that it would snowball into a multi-billion dollar streetwear industry, thanks to its endorsement by the Rap Culture in Urban America. Supreme would release (and still do) their products in extremely limited quantities which made them highly sought after.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It would collaborate with brands such as Vans, Nike, The North Face and many more which further added to its appeal. Add to this the widespread availability of Social Media in the late 2000s, this brand blew up like anything. A plain white T-Shirt with the iconic “Supreme Box Logo” which retailed for just $35 would resell in the aftermarket for more than $1000! That\'s over 72 thousand rupees for just a plain white T-Shirt.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Just to give you an idea of how crazy people are over this brand, let me tell you that Supreme once released a brick for $30 (about 2100 Rupees) and it was immediately sold for a THOUSAND DOLLARS in the aftermarket. Imagine paying 72 thousand rupees for a brick.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>THE STREETWEAR BOOM</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Big sports brands got to know the power of limited releases and collaborations. Nike signed up Kanye West for his famous Yeezy line of shoes. Later on, he was dumped by Nike and then signed up by Adidas where he would end up creating one of the most sought-after shoes of our time: The Yeezy Boost 350. People went crazy after these shoes. The $220 retail price went up to more than 10x its value in the aftermarket thanks to its extremely limited releases ( just a few thousand pairs worldwide !)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Virgil Abloh’s brand Off-White has been one of the most popular luxury brands and it\'s barely 8 years old. Abloh blurred the line between high fashion and street culture and it paid off. Now A-listers like Anil Kapoor and Abhishek Bachchan don Off-White. Off-White’s insanely popular (and insanely limited) collaboration with Nike’s Air Jordan line fetched over 2 lakhs in the aftermarket. It just retailed for just 14 thousand Rupees!</span>\r\n<h2><strong>BIG CELEBRITIES NAME IN THE GAME</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Next time you stalk your favourite Bollywood star’s Instagram you are definitely going to notice how they are just rocking a pair of New Balance sneakers and not some Gucci or Prada. And why wouldn\'t they, anybody with money can walk into a Gucci store and pick up whatever they like but you’ve got to have some real connections to get something that sells out in seconds (yes seconds!). And that\'s a much bigger flex.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Plus streetwear is much more comfortable than luxury clothing. Why would you walk all day in a pair of Christian Louboutins and blister your feet when you can bust out your super comfortable Yeezys and be noticed 10x more.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">And let me make things easy for you, here are a few celebs who have embraced this culture since the early days and way before the hype began.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>1. RANBIR KAPOOR</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3206 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/2-10.jpg\" alt=\"RANBIR KAPOOR\" width=\"500\" height=\"700\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Well Known celebrities for his massive collection of Jordans, his love for sneakers comes from his love for basketball and the NBA. He owns hundreds of pairs of them. Not many of you noticed but he even rocked a pair of Yeezy Boost 750s in the movie Ae Dil Hai Mushkil. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/7-bollywood-celebrities-who-underwent-a-dramatic-transformation/\">Ranbeer Kapoor</a> has been drawn towards street culture before anybody in B-Town knew what it was. A true “OG”, his sneaker advice is sought by Shah Rukh Khan and of course the rest of the Kapoors.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3205 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/1-9.jpg\" alt=\"RANBIR KAPOOR\" width=\"500\" height=\"700\" />\r\n<h3><strong>2. Diljit Dosanjh</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3208 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/4-8.jpg\" alt=\"Diljit Dosanjh\" width=\"500\" height=\"700\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do I even need to say anything about <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/good-newwz-the-tv-freak/\">Diljit’s</a> streetwear game? Well let me put it short, it requires courage to wear fanny packs around your chest when everybody else around you is wearing fur coats and dress shoes. Celebrities style game was way ahead of his time and see,  now everyone is following suit.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3207 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/3-10.jpg\" alt=\"celebrities diljit\" width=\"500\" height=\"700\" />\r\n<h3>3. THE ENTIRE KAPOOR FAMILY</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3209 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/5-7.jpg\" alt=\"KAPOOR FAMILY bollywood celebrities\" width=\"500\" height=\"700\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">From the young to the old, men and women, famous or not, that family has some serious obsession with Off-White and Heron Preston. I just cannot name enough Kapoors(celebrities) whom I’ve seen wearing limited-edition streetwear. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">And how could we even forget Anand Ahuja (celebrities) who slowly converted his wife Sonam, his brother-in-law, Harshvardhan, and his father-in-law Anil Kapoor into hardcore sneakerheads?</span>\r\n<h3><strong> 4. Ranvijay Singha</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3210 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/6-4.jpg\" alt=\"Ranvijay Singha\" width=\"500\" height=\"700\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Although he isn\'t an A-lister Bollywood star, celebrities, there’s no way I’m writing an article on streetwear without mentioning his 4000 plus pair sneaker collection. (He owns shoes that lace themselves, and that too several of them)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">“Yeah that\'s cool, but how do I get a piece of the pie”</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Well, assuming you have the cash to burn and the patience to find the piece you are looking for, there’s nothing that\'s stopping you from wearing what your favourite star is wearing these days. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You can Instagram some resellers like @vj_kicks or @marketplacebymainstreet and ask them if they have what you like. If you want to avoid the hassle (but pay extra in shipping and customs) you can always shop from overseas websites like <a href=\"https://stockx.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">StockX</a> and Stadium Goods.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">To be honest this niche is for enthusiasts and definitely not for the faint-of-heart. You just cannot wear a neon hoodie expect people not to bat an eye. But that\'s the beauty of it, you get people talking, it may be a good talk or bad talk, but hey! THEY ARE TALKING.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Next time you stop scrolling and wonder why a Gucci-head B-Towner is now suddenly into Nikes and Pumas, know that he/she didn’t go broke, but quite the contrary, they are making a killing.</span>\r\n<blockquote><strong>Article by Sarthak Sharma</strong></blockquote>','Why do Celebrities Pay 10X for Their Sports and Stuff?','','publish','open','open','','why-do-celebrities-pay-10x-for-their-sports-and-stuff','','https://www.thetvfreak.com/7-bollywood-celebrities-who-underwent-a-dramatic-transformation/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/good-newwz-the-tv-freak/','2020-12-25 17:19:42','2020-12-25 11:49:42','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3107',0,'post','',0),(3109,8,'2020-11-07 21:08:39','2020-11-07 15:38:39','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3138 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/1-8.jpg\" alt=\"KANYE WEST \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">While most rappers these days rap about how their Codeine infused drinks cost more than your rent money or how their credit card company allows them to buy a quarter-million-dollar watch, Kanye West is chanting praises of God and still getting more appreciation than any other rapper. Big deal?</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Well, not yet. He recently became the richest rapper ever, overtaking Jay-Z by a whopping  $2.2 BILLION! Impressed yet? Well, hold on until I tell you that he is also suffering from <a href=\"https://www.healthline.com/health/bipolar-disorder#:~:text=Bipolar%20disorder%20is%20a%20mental,bipolar%20disease%20or%20manic%20depression.\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bipolar Disorder</a> and yet he is raising his 4  kids with grace. Now that’s truly remarkable. Let\'s find out how he reached where he is.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Struggle, But That\'s Not the Point! Kanye West</span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Almost every rapper has struggled to be where they are. Most have come from poverty, so has Mr West. Most have done minimum wage jobs to sustain a livelihood, so has Mr West. Most rappers have struggled with drug addiction when they made it big in the industry, so has Mr Kanye West. Most rappers have had to deal with their fair share of violence, so has Mr Kanye West. Most black rappers have had the pressure of voicing their community’s plea for help, so has Mr West.  BUT THAT\'S NOT THE POINT.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3140 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/3-9.jpg\" alt=\"KANYE WEST \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How many rappers have gone from making songs about women’ bottoms and bosoms to making songs about God? How many rappers talk openly about their struggles with Mental Health?</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How many black <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/celebrities/\">celebrities</a> support Donald Trump just because they feel like, get hatred from their own community and yet love them back? How many rappers became <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-movies-about-billionaires-falling-in-love/\">billionaires</a> after running into neck-deep debt?  How many rappers announced they are going to run for president? (although he was late in taking this decision, that\'s another story). So, you see where I am going with this. Well, there’s more.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Kanye Omari West’s journey began where most rappers’ journey ends. A big house, a string of girlfriends, thick wads of cash, and lots of prescription drugs, he had it all but that wasn’t why he came on this Earth.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">WHAT GOES ON INSIDE HIS HEAD</span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Well, the clear answer to this question can only be given by the man himself but here’s something he has shared with us in the past. He said he didn’t want to be identified as a rapper(although he was making a killing off it). So he ventured into fashion. His early day\'s collaborations with the likes of Louis Vuitton and Bape are now the apple of all collectors’ eyes.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3137 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/4-7.jpg\" alt=\"KANYE WEST wife\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He designed his widely successful line of Yeezy sneakers with Nike and everyone went nuts. Fast forward a few years, Nike kicked out ‘Ye ( his nickname) because he wasn’t an athlete and Nike said only sportspeople could have their own line. So he decided to make sure Nike regretted their decision (and they did). He moved in with Adidas and made Yeezy into a phenomenon and not just some cool sneakers.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Expanding far beyond shoes, he started his line of clothing and accessories which surely turned some heads in New York Fashion Week and later on Paris Fashion Week. The tremors of his success could be felt. As I write this article, ‘Ye is working on adding an interior design segment to his billion-dollar Yeezy brand all while recovering from COVID-19 and Bipolar Disease.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Erratic? Sure. Cocky? Sure. Unstable? Sure, but proudly Unstable</span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His famous line in his song Yikes,” That’s my bipolar sh*t, ni**a, what? That’s my superpower, ni**a, ain’t no disability” filled our hearts with appreciation. Never before has someone in his line of work called their mental disability a “superpower” let alone even discuss it openly. Any amount of credits given to him for this are less. But wait for a second, did he call his condition a superpower just to shed the stigma around it or was it something else?</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3139 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/2-9.jpg\" alt=\"KANYE WEST wife\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bipolar disorder, or the “</span><b>manic-depressive disorder”  </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">is a condition that surely makes him depressed at times but on the other hand, it also gives him bouts of heightened cerebral activity in which he takes some heavy decisions ( and tweets them instantly) which he otherwise wouldn’t. And they end up working out for him. His tweeting sprees are famous among his fans.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He once tweeted that he forgave Nike for kicking him out. And the other day, when he said he loves Jordans despite having dissed the Jordan Brand in one of his recent songs. He has been managing to spread positivity around him and believe it or not, its the “manic” phase of his bipolar bouts that allow him to do this.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Love who you are, Just Like “Kanye West Loves Kanye”</span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I know there’s a lot to take home from this article. So let me ease your job and tell you what I learned from his life in 6 simple points:</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">No one sets your limits but yourself. Not your folks, not your teachers, definitely not some strangers on the internet.</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Find a higher power to believe in, doesn’t have to be God, but bigger than yourself.</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Family comes first. Always.</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Don’t be one thing in your life. You should use ‘and’ at least three times when you introduce yourself. For example, I am a doctor and a Pianist and a Coder and a Writer.</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Life is too short to hate. Forgive and forget.</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You cannot live for others unless you love yourself.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<blockquote><strong>Article by Sarthak Sharma</strong></blockquote>','Why You Need to Hear the Kanye West Story and Possibly Emulate Him','','publish','open','open','','why-you-need-to-hear-the-kanye-west-story-and-possibly-emulate-him','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-movies-about-billionaires-falling-in-love/','2020-12-25 17:33:40','2020-12-25 12:03:40','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3109',0,'post','',1),(3116,7,'2020-11-12 10:52:36','2020-11-12 05:22:36','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It’s that time of the year again! Time for carved pumpkins, spooky parties, scary parades, campfire story narrations, and of course, fright films. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Today, we bring to you Top10 Fright and horror movies for Halloween 2020 approved by the board of trick or treaters. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">These <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/hollywood/\">Hollywood movies</a> are absolutely terrifying. Just the sort of horror flicks that will get you in the Halloween mood.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>10. The Nun (2018)</strong></h2>\r\nThis one is a good old-fashion ghost story. The Nun (2018) is another chapter in The Conjuring franchise. This movie is about a priest who go to Romania by the Vatican to investigate the death of a young nun. She is confronted with a malevolent demonic nun by the name of Valek.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3184 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/6-1.jpg\" alt=\"The Nun (2018)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThis movie has magnificent cinematography, a spooky atmosphere, good tension in certain areas, and a wonderful performance by the star cast. You need to watch this horror movie alone and in absolute silence, as it mostly relies on jump scares and the dialogues are sparse. Overall, The Nun (2018) manages to keep you engage with its great storyline and the way it\'s narration.\r\n\r\nThe Nun is the most popular movie out of all horror movies for Halloween 2020.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zwAM5UnGd2s[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>9. The Babadook (2014)</strong></h2>\r\nIt is said that it is hard to be a single-parent. Now, imagine trying to raise a child while grieving over the demise of your partner. That must be downright maddening!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3189 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/11.jpg\" alt=\"The Babadook (2014)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThis movie’s storyline revolves around a single mother, her troubled son, and a book titled “Mister Babadook” that he pulls off the shelf one night. Essie Davis does an incredible job of playing a single mother and conveying the deep exhaustion felt by her character.\r\n\r\nThe Babadook (2014) is not for all types of audiences. If you are looking for jumpscares you will not find any in this movie. This is a suspenseful, provocative, and thoughtful horror film. This horror movie also gave us an original movie monster that was unconventionally scary.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k5WQZzDRVtw[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>8. It Follows (2014)</strong></h2>\r\nJust like The Babadook (2014), our next film does not rely on blood and shock value to offer a terrifying experience rather it makes use of the psychological element to scare the audience.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3187 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/9-1.jpg\" alt=\"It Follows (2014)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nIt Follows (2014) addresses deep questions about the anxieties of teen sexuality and STDs as the story is about a teenage girl who is followed by a supernatural entity after a sexual encounter.\r\n\r\nThis is an impressively shot film featuring some creative wide-angle cinematography. The movie is further amplified by Mikah Monroe\'s performance in the lead role.\r\n\r\nUltimately, It Follows (2014) is a compelling horror film and draws many comparisons to John Carpenter\'s style of filmmaking.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HkZYbOH0ujw[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>7. Evil Dead (2013)</strong></h2>\r\nEvil Dead is a remake of Sam Rami’s original film <a href=\"https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0083907/?ref_=nv_sr_srsg_0\" rel=\"nofollow\">The Evil Dead (1981)</a> although with a very different storyline from the original trilogy. It is more of a homage to the 1981 cult classic than a remake.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3193 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/1-3.jpg\" alt=\"Evil Dead (2013)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThis movie has some of the goriest and most disturbing scenes performing without CGI. And proves that a bloody movie can be made to look just as convincing using makeup alone.\r\n\r\nThe story picks up 30 years after the original film ended. This time with a new group of teenagers visiting the same cabin and accidentally stumbling across the \'book of the dead\' that unleashes an ancient evil.\r\n\r\nIf you can stand extreme gore and want to see a movie that is creepy, visceral, and an absolute blast of gruesomeness then this is the one.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FKFDkpHCQz4[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>6. The Cabin in the Woods (2011)</strong></h2>\r\nShortly after Chris Hemsworth played Thor, he starred in this dreadful carnage of a movie that was an inspiration to several 2020 memes.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3194 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/2-1-1.jpg\" alt=\"The Cabin in the Woods (2011)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nWhat really earns this movie a spot on our list is how deftly it manages to subvert expectations and really isn\'t that the hallmark of a great horror film?\r\n\r\nThe Cabin in the Woods has a melange of every monster/fantastical beast ever imagined. But beneath this chaos of supernatural lies an elaborate government conspiracy, one that makes the whole thing feel like a brilliant love letter to the horror genre.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NsIilFNNmkY[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>5. Hereditary (2018)</strong></h2>\r\nThis is the sort of movie that people were praising and warning each other about in the same line. A morbidly disturbing supernatural/ psychological <strong>horror movies.</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3188 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/10-1.jpg\" alt=\"Hereditary (2018) Horror movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nHereditary follows a family haunted by the death of their grandmother but it\'s so much more than that. Not only is it extremely unsettling to watch, but it\'s also chock-full of unforgettable moments that will put images in your head that simply wouldn’t leave.\r\n\r\nThis film is a true work of art both narratively and visually. Despite its colourful setting, it gives you a deeply unnerving experience.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V6wWKNij_1M[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>4. A Quiet Place (2018)</strong></h2>\r\nWho knew John Krasinski had it in him? Widely popular for his role of Jim Halpert from The Office, Krasinski has proven himself to be a versatile actor in the years since, but he took everyone by surprise with his entry into directing horror.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3183 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/5-2.jpg\" alt=\"A Quiet Place (2018) Horror movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nA quiet place takes a solid premise of a world overrun by blind monsters who hunt using a heightened sense of hearing. This movie makes masterful use of sound-design that draws you into the world of the film and makes you fear the slightest pin drop.\r\n\r\nJohn Krasinski and his cast, including his spouse Emily Blunt, all deliver committed performances that serve as the film\'s beating heart. You empathize and grow attached to the on-screen family and this attachment creates real and terrifying stakes.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WR7cc5t7tv8[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>3. The Conjuring (2013)</strong></h2>\r\nAfter unleashing not one but two major horror franchises upon the world, we have Saw and Insidious franchise filmmaker James Wan deliver one of the greatest haunted house films in decades.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3182 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/3-2.jpg\" alt=\"The Conjuring (2013) Horror movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nUnlike most of the movies on our list The Conjuring (2013) does not necessarily feel like it pushes the boundaries of the genre, in fact, it is quite an old-school horror flick.\r\n\r\nWhat makes it so worthwhile is its attention to detail. It\'s an extremely well-crafted and wonderfully paced movie with great characters that we really care about.\r\n\r\nIn short, it\'s the perfect supernatural horror film, one with superb scares and a lot of replay value.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ejMMn0t58Lc[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>2. Get Out (2017)</strong></h2>\r\nWe are definitely witnessing a new generation of horror flicks leaving their mark on the genre but arguably no horror filmmaker working today is more exciting than Jordan Peele from Key &amp; Peele.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3191 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/2-2.jpg\" alt=\"Get Out (2017) Horror movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nWith his directorial debut, Get Out (2017), he solidified his status as one of the most influential voices in the genre. Completely original and terrifying in the most unexpected of ways. This movie delivers a scathing and profound social critique at highlighting racism.\r\n\r\nIt is also a tight craft film, expertly shot and well-pace. Added to that a uniquely unnerving ambiance and great performances all around. In other words, it’s a modern horror masterpiece.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sRfnevzM9kQ[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>1. IT (2017)</strong></h2>\r\nThis past decade has felt like a renaissance for <strong>horror movies</strong> especially those centering on the misadventures of teens. Our final movie is not only the highest-grossing horror movie worldwide but is also a tribute to the teenage-horror genre.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3190 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/1-2.jpg\" alt=\"Horror movies IT 2017\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nIT (2007) is based on <a href=\"https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/3389.Stephen_King\" rel=\"nofollow\">Stephen King’s</a> (a.k.a King of Horror Fiction) phenomenally successful novel by the same name. In this film, Bill Skarsgard plays the horrifying character Pennywise, the dancing clown. His brilliant portrayal of the infamous clown is accompanied by the excellent performance of the film’s young ensemble.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FnCdOQsX5kc[/embedyt]\r\n\r\nRelying mostly on jump scares, this film delivered a sinister and looming sense of dread throughout its runtime and that is the reason this film earned the number 1 spot on <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">The Tv Freak</a> list of Top 10 Fright and horror movies for Halloween 2020.\r\n\r\n<b>– Abhishek Tewari</b>','Top 10 Best Fright and Horror Movies for Halloween 2020','','publish','open','open','','top-10-best-fright-and-horror-movies-for-halloween-2020','','','2021-01-09 10:53:51','2021-01-09 05:23:51','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3116',0,'post','',0),(3146,7,'2020-11-11 10:32:12','2020-11-11 05:02:12','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You’d think that great movies make up for an easy viewing experience but you would be wrong. There are a lot of filmmakers in Hollywood that make outstanding films. However, only a few make ones that are both outstanding and difficult to watch. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Today, we are looking at <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-hollywood-movies-that-nobody-understands/\">Hollywood</a> Top 10 Emotional and sad Movies. These movies are based on subjects that are actually emotionally upsetting.</span>\r\n\r\nThese <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/movies/\">movies</a> are ranked according to their subject, quality, and how they were received by audiences all over the world.\r\n<h2><strong>10. Precious (2009)</strong></h2>\r\nOur list begins with a producer known to explore themes that other producers wouldn’t dare to. Oprah Winfrey’s Precious (2009) is about the life of a 16-year-old girl. A girl who is raped by her father and becomes pregnant on two separate occasions.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3167 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/1-1.jpg\" alt=\"Precious (2009)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She soon delivers a baby who is suffering from Down’s Syndrome. Precious’ malevolent mother uses her and her child to receive welfare from the State.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie becomes further unsettling when Precious learns that she has contracted HIV from her father. Although the movie has an uplifting climax the preceding two hours make for an extremely upsetting tale.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This film has stellar performances and a disturbingly realistic portrayal of abuse and poverty.  Precious bagged two Academy Awards in the category of Best Actress in a Supporting Role and Best Writing, Adapted Screenplay.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=urFY3jp759c[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>9. House of Sand and Fog (2003)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Next is an outstanding yet not-so-popular movie.  House of Sand and Fog (2003) stars Ben Kingsley and Jennifer Connelly in the lead roles.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3168 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/2-1.jpg\" alt=\"House of Sand and Fog (2003)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThis film is about two parties battling for control of a house and the destruction of the various lives involved<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. </span>This chaos culminates into a depressing climax where we bear witness to the suicides of an Iranian couple.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie is based on the New York Times Bestseller novel with the same name by author Andre Dubus III. What’s remarkable about this novel is that it has an even darker climax compared to the movie. Needless to say, House of Sand and Fog is a difficult watch and a difficult read.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-9_vNEfR7VM[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>8. Sophie\'s Choice (1982)</strong></h2>\r\nUnlike our previous entry on the list, this is a widely popular movie. In fact, so popular that even those who haven\'t seen the film are well aware of what it involves.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3169 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/3-1.jpg\" alt=\"Sophie\'s Choice (1982)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The idea of a mother being forced to condemn her child to death is the central theme of the movie that makes up for an extremely difficult scene to watch.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Meryl Streep delivers a mesmerizing Academy Academy winning performance in the movie. It is said that Sophie\'s Choice(1982) is a realistic, emotionally devastating, and memorable film.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=STPJVf6wqCk[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>7. Grave of the Fireflies (1988)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is an animated movie. However, its effect on viewers is so profound that we couldn’t afford to exclude it from our list.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3170 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/4-1.jpg\" alt=\"Grave of the Fireflies (1988)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Grave of the Fireflies (1988) is a harrowing and realistic look into Japanese life at the end of World War II. The movie begins with the traumatic scene where a young boy starves to death. From there on, the film jumps in past and shows us, in excruciating detail, the slow descent into desperation and finally the deaths of our protagonist brother &amp; sister, Seita and Setsuko.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie is often considered to be one of the greatest anti-war films ever made due to its overwhelming depiction of innocent lives caught in the cross-fire. This is the best movie from the list of Hollywood emotional Movies.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4vPeTSRd580[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>6. Million Dollar Baby (2004)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are only a few movies with a jaw-dropping plot-twist comparable to </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Million</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Dollar Baby (2004). Winner of four Academy Awards in various categories including Best Motion Picture, this movie starts as a female version of Rocky (1976).</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3171 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/5-1.jpg\" alt=\"Million Dollar Baby (2004) Hollywood Emotional Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">An aspiring boxer named Maggie (Hilary Swank) trains with a grumpy old man named Frankie (Clint Eastwood). However, the movie takes a huge turn in the middle when Maggie meets a tragic fate. The film then spirals into an emotionally exhausting story of family tragedy and the morality of euthanasia.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Starring Morgan Freeman in supporting-role Million Dollar Baby (2004) makes for a very challenging viewing experience.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5_RsHRmIRBY[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>5. Hotel Rwanda (2004)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Based on true events, Hotel Rwanda (2004) chronicles the real story of the Rwandan genocide. This tragic event saw the deaths of nearly one million people in the spring and summer of 1994 in the East African country called Rwanda.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3172 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/6.jpg\" alt=\"Hollywood Emotional Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The story is about Paul Rusesabagina (Don Cheadle) who saved the lives of several citizens in the infamous conflict between two Rwandan ethnicities, Hutu and Tutsi.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hotel Rwanda (2004) is rife with scenes of extreme violence and hate such as the famous road scene that will stick in your head for years. The constant reminder that this movie is based on true incidents makes it even harder to watch.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qZzfxL90100[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>4. The Boy in Striped Pajamas (2008)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Movies concerning the Holocaust are generally upsetting to watch and The Boy in Striped Pajamas (2008) is no exception to that.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3173 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/7.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This story follows a German boy named Bruno (Asa Butterfield) who befriends a Jewish boy named Shmuel from a concentration camp. The movie has some extremely unsettling scenarios including a vicious beating of an old man and the plight of weakened prisoners of the camp.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Holocaust is obviously a grim theme but this movie ends on an especially despairing note.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uwysOfnX2Qg[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>3. Requiem for a Dream (2000)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Perhaps this is the most consistently depressing film on the list. Darren Aronofsky’s masterpiece Requiem for a Dream (2000) is a film that reflects the depravities of drug addiction.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3174 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/8.jpg\" alt=\"Requiem for a Dream (2000) Hollywood Emotional Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sara (Ellen Burstyn) becomes addicted to amphetamines and grows manic resulting in a dismaying scene of electroshock therapy. Harry’s (Jared Leto) arm becomes infected due to the regular use of intravenous drugs leading to amputation as the only option. Marian (Jennifer Connelly) regrettably sells her body for heroin.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie has a pessimistic storyline filled with bleak and haunting imagery. This is a mournful movie with some soul-crushing and unforgettable performances.</span>\r\n\r\nYou will definitely like this movie if you love to watch Hollywood emotional movies.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QBwzN4v1vA0[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>2. The Pianist (2002)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Roman Polanski had already established himself as a great movie Director by the turn of the century with major hits such as Rosemary\'s Baby (1968) and Chinatown (1974) under his belt. However, this is the movie in which he spoke from his heart.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3175 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/9.jpg\" alt=\"The Pianist (2002) Hollywood Emotional Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Polanski had a personal brush with the Holocaust as both his parents were taken as prisoners in Jewish ghettos. This is clearly evident in the movie by its depiction of hopelessness and loneliness.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This truly heart-wrenching story of a Pianist, Wladyslaw Szpilman (Adrien Brody), whose life gets from bad to worse as the movie progresses, is based on real events. It is a deeply disturbing film because of its sequence of enthralling scenes showing Szpilman’s struggle to survive deprivation, starvation, and terror of Nazi soldiers.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Winner of three Academy Awards including Best Actor in a Leading Role, The Pianist (2002) is one of the most detailed, realistic, and shocking accounts of the treatment of the Jews by the Nazis.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BFwGqLa_oAo[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>1. Schindler\'s List (1993)</strong></h2>\r\nThis movie is the top movie form the list of Hollywood Emotional Movies.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sophie\'s Choice(1982), Hotel Rwanda (2004), The Boy in Striped Pajamas (2008), and The Pianist (2002) are all extremely overwhelming to watch movies. However, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steven_Spielberg\" rel=\"nofollow\">Steven Spielberg</a> is known as the master of his craft for a clear reason.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3166 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/10.jpg\" alt=\"Schindler\'s List (1993) Hollywood Emotional Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Winner of four Academy Awards, Schindler\'s List (1993) is the most painful movie to watch on our list of Hollywood’s Top 10 Emotionally Upsetting Movies.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Considering all the depravity of the on-screen violence this movie presents to the viewers, this can arguably be said to be the most disturbing and horrifying account of the Holocaust ever put to film.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JdRGC-w9syA[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Firstly, The acting is incredibly realistic as we feel every ounce of pain, fear, and disgust experienced by the movie’s unfortunate characters. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Secondly, With a heart-breaking, cathartic climax that will leave you a blubbering mess, it is undeniably a masterpiece and clear evidence of how a powerful motion picture is capable of stirring our emotions.</span>\r\n\r\nSo here we end the list of Hollywood emotional movies. Hope you like the list of The Tv Freak.\r\n<blockquote><b>– Abhishek Tewari</b></blockquote>\r\n<h2>Also, Read the about most Interesting Movies:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/best-crime-movies-based-on-true-life-stories/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Top 11 Crime Movies Based on True Life Stories</a></li>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/courtroom-movies-based-on-real-life-stories/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Best Collection of Courtroom Movies based on Real Life Stories</a></li>\r\n <li><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-11-terrorism-movies-based-on-real-life/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Top 11 Terrorism Movies based on Real Life</a></li>\r\n</ul>','10 Best Hollywood Emotional and Sad Movies Which Will Make You Cry','','publish','open','open','','10-best-hollywood-emotional-and-sad-movies','','https://www.thetvfreak.com/best-crime-movies-based-on-true-life-stories/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-hollywood-movies-that-nobody-understands/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/courtroom-movies-based-on-real-life-stories/','2021-01-09 11:02:53','2021-01-09 05:32:53','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3146',0,'post','',0),(3154,6,'2020-11-10 14:35:48','2020-11-10 09:05:48','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A lot of actors, producers, and directors have initialized their careers in Gujrati film and then transitioned to Hindi Film Industry. Some prominent names are Sanjay Leela Bansali, Hansal Mehta. But a name that is trending now is  Pratik Gandhi.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3158 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/1.jpg\" alt=\"Pratik Gandhi in Scam 1992 ott series web series\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><b>About Pratik</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Born in Surat Pratik Gandhi has his roots in Gujrat. Both his parents were professional teachers. By Profession, he is an Engineer. He has work experience working in a variety of fields and roles. Starting from Reliance Industries and ending up in a</span><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multinational_corporation\" rel=\"nofollow\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Multinational Cooperation</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n<h3>In Kapil Sharma Show:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZxLiYt8VqXU[/embedyt]\r\n<h3>Finest Answer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D-GzS9IKgMI[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Doing the Undoing</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3159 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/2.jpg\" alt=\"Pratik Gandhi in Scan 1992 ott series web series\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Initially seeing the life of Pratik, it seems that he had no defined Goal in Life. Pratik was not a so-called academic Good student at school. He had low grades in his school. Because of his low grades in school, he had to change his decision from pursuing MBBS to Engineering. Thereafter completing Industrial Engineering he got a job at Reliance and he started his journey as a Corporate Employee.</span>\r\n<h3>Something you don\'t know about him, But you should:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-TJT34ABD80[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Initial Struggle</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Initially, the journey was very hard for Pratik. So after completing his Engineering, when Pratik went to Fulfill his Dream. He faced a lot of difficulties. As the cost of living in Mumbai is very high, so he used to do theatres additionally. His day job used to be as a Corporate Employee. And in the second half of the day, he did theatres. Then also if he used to have a shortage of money, then he used to entertain Children at their Birthday Parties.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Movies of Pratik Gandhi</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pratik Gandhi started his career in the year 2006. His first movie was an English Language movie which is named “Yours Emotionally”.In that movie, he plays the character named “Mani”.Thereafter he showcased another movie which was of English Language name “68 Pages”.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Doing Gujarati Movies</b></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3039 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/2-5.jpg\" alt=\"SCAM 1992\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After 2013, Pratik Went on to do four Gujrati movies. Some of them were “Beey Yaar”, Tamburo and Love Ni Bhavai. His work in the National Award Winning Movie “Wrong Side Raju” was highly appreciated.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ISORfez27og[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Something from the movie “ Wrong Side Raju”</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pratik played the lead role in \" Wrong Side Raju\". It is one of the blockbuster movies of Dhollywood(Gujrati Movie Industry). The movie of the genre “Thriller” and inspired by a Hit &amp; Run Case. The hit &amp; run case happened in Ahmedabad in the year 2013. The film won a National Award. The award was given because it highlighted the ethos of the Moral Dilemma.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Making his Bollywood Debut</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pratik made his Bollywood Debut in the year 2018. He played a comedy character in the movie. Pratik played the character named  “Negative”.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Something About the Character</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pratik Played the character Negative. The character was not Negative but it was named like that. Negative is the sort of person who always gives his views in a Negative way. He would be the only single person in a crowd who speaks the opposite way to all people speaking in the same way.</span>\r\n<h3><b>The way Forward</b></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3161 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/4.jpg\" alt=\"Pratik Gandh\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Thereafter Loveryatri in 2018 he had no turning around. He did three movies back to back. The movies were Mitron, Ventilator, and Dhunki.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Hitting the OTT platform with a bang</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Recently Mr. Pratik success with the series named “</span><b>Scam 1992</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">”.The drama series is featured on the OTT platform SonyLiv. And the series was released on the date 9th October 2020.</span>\r\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/scam-1992-the-harshad-mehta-story-behind-the-hype/\"><b>About Scam 1992</b></a></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Scam 1992 is a drama series that featured on the SonyLiv platform. The series is about the Famous Stock Broker “Harshad Mehta”.It showcases how</span><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/scam-1992-the-harshad-mehta-story-behind-the-hype/\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Harshad Mehta</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> transformed his life from Rags to Riches. All it shows how Mr. Mehta made everyone buy the stocks at high prices. When the Stock Exchange crashed, all the money invested had gone waste.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3162 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/5.jpg\" alt=\"scam\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h3><b>Pratik Playing Harshad Mehta</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pratik Gandhi played the main character of the series which is Harshad Mehta. People were astonished to Pratik see this type of character. Pratik did a lot to play the character. He had to develop the type of talking ability, style, attitude similar to Harshad Mehta. And people even seemed to be digesting that Harshad in real might be looking the same as portrayed by Pratik in the series.</span>\r\n<h3><b>How Pratik Prepared for the role</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pratik had done a lot of theatres earlier in his life, which someway helped him in playing the character. But the main thing which Pratik told in an interview. He said that he used to practice the formula “Learn and Unlearn”.He only used to focus on those qualities which somehow helped him to create a character.</span>\r\n<h3><b>What Pratik Has to Tell You About Shooting?</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pratik tells that he had a great time in the shooting and it was fantastic. The vintage cars and bell-bottom pants all were very authentic and unique stuff to wear now. Pratik was in High School when this fashion was on a high. And to wear those clothes again was like reliving your young age.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Love Life and Family</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3160 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/3.jpg\" alt=\"Pratik Gandhi in Scan 1992\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pratik Gandhi did not have many rumors about his love life. But he fell in love with Theatre and TV actress Bhamini Oza. They tied knots in the year 2009. And in the year 2014, his daughter was born as a blessing.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Is Pratik from a Filmy Background?</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Surely not, Pratik Gandhi does not have any film background. Both his parents were teachers. And Pratik’s Elder brother Mr.Punit Gandhi is a designer by Profession and a part-time singer. He recently gave his voice in one of the Gujrati Movie” Lovi Ni Bhavai”.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hope You like the content on Pratik Gandhi. To subscribe to</span><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Tv Freak</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> for further updates on the entertainment industry.</span>','Pratik Gandhi From “Scam 1992” | Biography, Movies and Web Series','','publish','closed','closed','','pratik-gandhi-from-scam-1992-biography-movies-and-web-series','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/scam-1992-the-harshad-mehta-story-behind-the-hype/','2021-01-24 17:07:15','2021-01-24 11:37:15','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3154',0,'post','',0),(3214,7,'2020-11-16 21:45:24','2020-11-16 16:15:24','Life is full of surprises but not all surprises are pleasant! Consider <a href=\"https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/?utm_campaign=homeAdvegas1?\" rel=\"nofollow\">COVID-19</a>, for instance, one virus that hit the world so fast and hard that everything became topsy-turvy. The situation turned haywire and beyond our control in the blink of an eye. As bad as it may seem, it could have been worse. If you don’t believe that, allow us to change your mind. You’d be thankful that these Pandemic/ Epidemic are fictional as we take you through our list of Top 10 Pandemic/ Epidemic Movies.\r\n<h2><strong>10. Pontypool (2008)</strong></h2>\r\nOur list begins with the strangest if not, the deadliest virus Hollywood has ever produced. An outbreak affects a small town of Ontario brought about by a virus so unusual that all it needs to spread are words!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3222 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/1-4.jpg\" alt=\"Pontypool (2008) Pandemic/ Epidemic Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nPontypool (2008) has a slow but suspenseful first half where we are introduced to a radio host and his team that is airing a radio program.\r\n\r\nSoon reports channel through about some bizarre events taking place in the town. The second half is when the mystery begins to unfold, and we find our protagonists struggling to save their lives.\r\n\r\nThe film\'s intelligent script and top-notch acting by Stephen McHattie keep the audience on the edge of their seats. At times hilarious but altogether suspenseful, this movie offers a fresh look at the genre of pandemic/ epidemic movies.\r\n<h2><strong>9. Cabin Fever (2002)</strong></h2>\r\nEli Roth is known for making <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">movies</a> that are gory, bloody, scary, and crazy. All those at the same time and Cabin Fever (2002) is not an exception.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3224 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/2-3.jpg\" alt=\"Cabin Fever (2002) Pandemic/ Epidemic Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThe movie is about five college kids that visit a cabin in the woods to enjoy a vacation. Little did they know that their idea of a get-away will soon turn into a nightmare when they come in contact with a deadly flesh-eating bacterium.\r\n\r\nThe story is well-developed and is a change from Roth\'s usual slasher-films. The acting is appreciable considering that the star cast was a group of new actors. If you have liked movies like Hostel, Evil Dead, Last House on the Left, and Texas Chainsaw Massacre, you will love this movie.\r\n<h2><strong>8. REC (2007)</strong></h2>\r\nA virus that turns ordinary people into savage killers is terrible, isn’t it? Now imagine being trapped inside a sealed-off building with the infected ones. That is stuff from a nightmare!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3225 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/3-3.jpg\" alt=\"REC (2007) Pandemic/ Epidemic Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThe movie starts with Reporter Angela Vidal (Manuela Velasco) and her associate Pablo. They follow a group of firefighters into a building on a routine call. The last thing they expected to face there was the fallout of a rabies-like virus. This virus was a result of an enzyme that turned the building inhabitants into zombies running amok. This movie is one of the best from Pandemic/ Epidemic Movies.\r\n\r\nShaky camera movements. Constant feeling of claustrophobia. This found-footage style Spanish film will send chills down your spine leaving you squirming in your seat.\r\n<h2><strong>7. Mimic (1997)</strong></h2>\r\nDirector Guillermo Del Toro’s science fiction horror film dispenses the same moral advice- Do not interfere with Nature.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3226 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/4-2.jpg\" alt=\"Mimic (1997) Pandemic/ Epidemic Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThe epidemic in Mimic (1997) is spread cockroaches instead of any micro-organism. However, this is one of the examples where the cure is worse than the disease itself. Entomologist Dr Susan Tyler (Mira Sorvino) develops a cockroach killing insect to get Manhattan rid of them.\r\n\r\nThe bug eliminates the cockroach problem by killing them off although there is an unfortunate after effect. To everyone’s horror, the man-made insects mutate and become gargantuan and gain the ability to roughly imitate Human Beings in appearance.\r\n\r\nDarkness, rot, and masses of unidentifiable biological material are a common sight in the movie. The special effects used in presenting creatures are fantastic. The story builds-up a constant atmosphere of suspense coupled with a well-paced direction.\r\n\r\nThroughout the movie, you\'d be able to guess if any of the characters will survive.\r\n<h2><strong>6. 12 Monkeys (1995)</strong></h2>\r\nUnlike our previous movies on our list, this one is set in the not-so-distant future. The year is 2035 and a prisoner named James Cole (Bruce Willis) is sent back in time to the year 1990 to stop a plague from spreading. A plague so malignant, it destroys the entire human population saving a handful that must live underground to escape its effects.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3227 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/5-3.jpg\" alt=\"12 Monkeys (1995)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nWhat’s scary about this dark sci-fi is that the virus was created and released on purpose. An army of eco-terrorists called The 12 Monkeys does so in the spirit of saving the environment. It was later that we discovered that 12 monkeys are only a red-herring and the virus is unstoppable.\r\n\r\nThis film benefits from its great cast. Brad Pitt steals the show as a lunatic with his memorable performance in the asylum. Bruce Willis gives a fantastic performance as a confused man affected by the psychological impact of <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/10-best-time-travel-movies-you-must-watch-right-now/\">time-travelling</a>. Imaginative, engaging, and full of possibilities. This Pandemic/ Epidemic Movie acts as a warning of what we could lose one day if we don’t listen.\r\n<h2><strong>5. Rise of the Planet of the Apes (2011)</strong></h2>\r\nOur next movie is again about a man-made....damn it, people! Are you not listening? Stop engineering viruses! However, in this case, James Franco\'s character Will Rodman means well.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3228 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/6-2.jpg\" alt=\"Rise of the Planet of the Apes (2011)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThis Planet of the Apes reboots witnesses Rodman testing a virus-based drug on chimpanzees to cure Alzheimer\'s Disease. It’s a gene therapy that allows the brain to create its own cells to repair itself. It’s effective but only for a while. The problems start when a more powerful gaseous version of the drug is created that enhances simian intelligence.\r\n\r\nThe drug spreads rapidly leading to an ape uprising and eventually killing off 99% of the human race. Talk about side effects!\r\n\r\nAndy Serkis delivers a great performance as the voice to the leading ape. A simple terrifying look from an angry ape to their kind\'s full-out uprising against humans. Everything in this movie is thought-provoking and an emotionally driven thrill ride.\r\n<h2><strong>4. Contagion (2011)</strong></h2>\r\nThis next movie closely resembles our current COVID-19 situation. It is also perhaps the most believable characterization of a pandemic. With admiration from the critics, Contagion (2011) doesn’t have a single scene that seems contrived.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3229 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/7-2.jpg\" alt=\"Contagion (2011)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nA flu-like virus that is a hybrid of viruses from animals spreads rapidly across the world. The audience navigates the chaos resulting from this inexplicable outbreak as they witness a team of medical personnel race the clock to formulate a vaccine. How the pandemic came to be is not revealed till the end when the storyline jumps back in time.\r\n\r\nThis Steven Soderbergh movie has a multi-star cast including Academy Award winner Kate Winslet. We get the story from the perspective of different on-screen characters. The movie explores the pandemic in a realistic, compelling but non-sensationalistic way.\r\n\r\nExtensive research with medical experts and representatives from the World Health Organization is responsible for this movie’s gritty realism.\r\n<h2><strong>3. 28 Days Later (2003)</strong></h2>\r\nThe road to hell is paved with good intentions from well-meaning people when it comes to movie viruses. A group of animal liberation activists just want to free some hapless chimpanzees in this Danny Boyle\'s post-apocalyptic horror film. However, scientists have infected these chimps with a virus that causes uncontrollable rage.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3230 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/8-2.jpg\" alt=\"28 Days Later (2003)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nTransmitted through blood and saliva this virus quickly turns strangers, friends, and loved ones against each other. Society witnesses a complete collapse by the time protagonist Jim (Cillian Murphy) wakes up in a hospital in London 28 days later. There are only a few survivors and hordes upon hordes of really fast-moving zombies.\r\n\r\nCillian Murphy has given a remarkable performance. This is the kind of movie that makes you feel physically drained.  It also sheds new light on the survival instinct of mankind.\r\n<h2><strong>2. Resident Evil (2002)</strong></h2>\r\nA common subject in many science fiction horror flicks is viruses.  Micro-organisms that turn people into zombies. Such viruses never lose their ability to spook the living hell out of us.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3231 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/9-2.jpg\" alt=\"Resident Evil (2002)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nResident Evils has a particularly nasty example of such a virus engineered with a benign motive to cure crippling diseases. As expected, things take a turn for the worse and the virus not only begins to kill but also mutates hosts into horrible monsters. And to make matters even more severe, it\'s easily transmissible spreading through fluid or air.\r\n\r\nThis video-game based movie franchise gave actress Milla Jovovich her most iconic role as Alice. It shows the world plunging the world into an apocalyptic nightmare. You know it’s a resilient virus when its movie spawned five sequels.\r\n<h2><strong>1. I am Legend (2007)</strong></h2>\r\nThis movie is the best among all above Pandemic/ Epidemic Movies. Based on Richard Matheson\'s 1954 novel of the same name, this movie also explores the perils of an engineered virus.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3221 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/10-2.jpg\" alt=\"Resident Evil (2002)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nIn this post-apocalyptic thriller scientists genetically re-engineered a measles virus to cure cancer.  As an unforeseeable and bizarre consequence, ninety percent of the world\'s population dies. The remaining human beings turn into cannibal mutants allergic to sunlight.\r\n\r\nThe film makes your heart pound with action/suspense scenes coupled with superb sound direction. It explores the psychological effects of long-term desolation through Will Smith’s utterly convincing performance as one of the only humans in the devastated City of Manhattan.\r\n\r\nThis is our list of top 10 best Pandemic/ Epidemic Movies you must watch.\r\n\r\n<b>– Abhishek Tewari</b>','Top 10 Best Pandemic/ Epidemic Movies You Must Watch','','publish','open','open','','top-10-best-pandemic-epidemic-movies-you-must-watch','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/10-best-time-travel-movies-you-must-watch-right-now/','2020-12-25 17:20:41','2020-12-25 11:50:41','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3214',0,'post','',0),(3244,7,'2020-11-19 13:39:08','2020-11-19 08:09:08','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The last 20 years have been very rewarding for avid fans of martial-arts movies. We can say that in plenty of ways, we live in the golden period of this genre and our list is a testimony to that.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Today, we want you to take a look at our choice of the Top 10 Most Popular Martial Arts Movies. Films starring Jackie Chan and Bruce Lee indubitably stand apart that\'s why we will be excluding their <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/movies/\">films from our list</a>. </span>\r\n\r\nLet\'s begin!\r\n<h2><strong>10. House of Flying Daggers (2004)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The beginning years of our Century witnessed martial arts films that were created with a focus on elegance and style. Our first entry on the list is a prime example of that.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3250 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/1-5.jpg\" alt=\"House of Flying Daggers (2004)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie is based on a cop called Jin (Takeshi Kaneshiro). Jin is on a mission to trail a rebel group called House of Flying Daggers. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This rebel group has a mission to overthrow the corrupt ruling Government. His pursuit leads him to Jin meets Xiao Mei (Ziyi Zhang), a sightless dancer who could be a rebel herself and belong to the House of Flying Daggers.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We witness Jin\'s loyalty put to test when his love for Xiao Mei stands against his sense of duty. This is a beautifully haunting movie featuring some wonderful fight sequences. It is an action-packed movie while also being a tale of duty and love.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>9. Fearless (2006)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hailed as the last of its kind in the genre, Fearless (2006) features martial arts star Jet Li. He plays the role of Huo Yuanjia, a legend among Chinese martial artists.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A hero who, in the early 20th century, had conquered a number of fighters from abroad in open matches.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3251 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/2-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">These combats were a huge victory for the national pride of China. Li\'s portrayal of Huo Yuanjia is a tribute to Huo Yuanjia\'s legacy.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Under the brilliant direction of Ronny Yu, Jet Li has displayed action sequences with calculated movements. This movie reminds viewers why Li will always be among the greatest in his genre.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>8. Tom Yum Goong (2005)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We shall cover Tony Jaa’s debut movie shortly. But first, let\'s explore the movie that solidified him as an important star of this genre.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3252 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/3-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In Tom Yum Goong (2005), Jaa plays the role of Kham, a man entrusted with the responsibility of protecting the elephants of Thailand\'s King. However, a corrupt politician, having connections with the underworld, takes away one royal elephant. Kham\'s search for his tusked friend leads him to the main city where he uses his martial arts to cracks the enemy\'s skulls and breaks their bones.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie is rife with remarkable jaw-dropping action and stunts. You can see a full-on display of Tony Jaa’s mastery of Muay Thai.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>7. Ong Bak (2003)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tony Jaa launched himself in the martial arts movie world with his debut film that delivered a flying elbow to the head of the martial arts genre.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3253 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/4-3.jpg\" alt=\"Ong Bak (2003)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This film has Tony Jaa playing a village man set on a mission to recover the stolen head of an ancient statue of Buddha. His mission brings him to Bangkok\'s underworld where his feisty Muay Thai talents are once again unleashed on the enemy.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Earlier, Chinese disciplines dominated the martial arts cinema. However, Ong Bak (2003) brought Muay Thai along with other non-Chinese Asian disciplines to the spotlight. The film\'s two other parts Ong Bak 2 (2008) and Ong Bak 3 (2010) explored the style of Muay Thai even further.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>6. Kung Fu Hustle (2004)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is a movie by a very versatile Hong-Kong cinema personality Stephen Chow. This Writer/Director and actor of Shaolin Soccer (2001) fame and a catalogue of other Kung Fu comedies under the belt presented Kung Fu Hustle to the world in 2004.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3254 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/5-4.jpg\" alt=\"Kung Fu Hustle (2004) martial arts movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie is about a man named Sing (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stephen_Chow\" rel=\"nofollow\">Stephen Chow</a>) who inspires to be a big-time gangster. However, he gets caught up in the crossfires of a conflict between a local axe-wielding gang and the occupants of a run-down apartment. To the surprise of Sing and the gang, the apartment block is the property of a married couple who are retired Kung Fu masters.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie is an amalgamation of martial arts and special effects resulting in a cinematic experience that is breathtaking.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>5. Flash Point (2007)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">While history drama forms a major component of cinema on martial arts we\'d be wrong if we didn\'t accommodate contemporaneous crime dramas in our list such as Flash Point (2007).</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3255 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/6-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In this movie, Donnie Yen plays the role of a cop hunting a group of gangsters. This pursuit climaxes in a knock-down-and-drag-out fight between Yen and star Collin Chou.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We don\'t have to mention that the movie, as a whole, is also quite brilliant but the final duel is certainly one of the most intensely choreographed showdowns ever. This fight sequence alone should make you want to see this movie if you haven\'t already.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>4. Hero (2002)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Going back to history-drama films this next entry once again features Jet Li in union with director Yimou Zhang for yet another martial arts movie of epic style.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3256 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/7-3.jpg\" alt=\" martial arts movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The story involves L\'s character as a swordsman with no name and the soon-to-be Chinese Emperor. The Emperor giving a conflicting account of Li’s victory over a group of murderers. Li states that his mission concern only the protection of the Emperor. However, the Emperor suspects that it all involves foul play for some reason.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie contains a number of beautiful performances and magnificently choreographed action sequences. They look more like elegant and brimming dance sequences than the rigorous showdowns.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>3. Ip Man (2008)</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3257 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/8-3.jpg\" alt=\"Ip Man (2008) martial arts movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Our next movie has, perhaps, Donnie Yen\'s career\'s most popular role. The actor plays the legendary fighter Ip Man. A venerated personality in the community of Chinese martial arts.  A grandmaster of Wing Chun discipline. Ip Man fought off Japanese warriors that had occupied China in the 1930s.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This film evolved into a four-part franchise that continued to narrate the tale of Ip Man\'s life and achievements. And this first installment from 2003 is where it all began.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie is widely popular for its iconic scene where Yen engages in combat against ten black belts. Fighting all of them at the same time!</span>\r\n<h2><strong>2. The Raid: Redemption (2011)</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Few m