<a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-movies-about-billionaires-falling-in-love/\">rich people movies</a>. In fact, we have a list of five <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">movies</a> to help you keep up with some of these most notable and wealthy figures. So let’s dive in!</span>\r\n<h2><strong> The Inventor (2019):</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 7.1</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Alex Gibney</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  N/A</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3338 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/1-10.jpg\" alt=\"The Inventor (2019): \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First from the list of Millionaires movies. This recent documentary features the founder of Theranos, Elizabeth Holmes, whose 9 Billion Dollar worth company came crashing down from the peaks of Silicon Valley.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The documentary entails how a Stanford dropout became a Silicon Valley visionary. What the world considered her to change the world’s health issues, turned out to be one of the biggest frauds in history. All her promises she made from inventing a blood analyzer, came out to beguile many investors and her failure stands out to be Silicon Valley’s biggest cataclysm.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Achievements/ Nominations:</b><b>\r\n</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Primetime Creative Arts Emmy Award - Outstanding Documentary (2020)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> HBO</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>2. The Wolf of Wall Street (2013):</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 8.2</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Martin Scorsese</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Leonardo Dicaprio, Margot Robbie, Matthew McConahey</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3339 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/2-9.jpg\" alt=\"The Wolf of Wall Street (2013)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Firstly This movie is known to be based on the very title of a Memoir, published back almost a decade ago. It features the life of once an eccentric billionaire named, Jordan Belfort, who emerges on Wall Street as a prominent stockbroker. The Millionaires movies unfold in showing the audience how he started, before his breakthrough. When he first steps foot in Wall Street, he takes an entry-level job at a Wall Street brokerage firm.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Despite his lack of experience and that only coming from working in the firm, he started from scratch and started making a name for himself. By the 90s and while still in his 20s, Belfort emerged his own firm by the name of Stratton Oakmont.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie then shows his prime how he spent in a spree of his well-earned luxurious life, while he, with his merry and hungry band of brokers, made a huge fortune by defrauding wealthy investors out dry. While Belfort and his band live the high life, the SEC and FBI come knocking on his door and try to stop him this gargantuan fraud that he makes time and time again, relentlessly. But may I suggest you watch these Millionaires movies alone, for the high life is too graphic and uncomfortable around your family members.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Achievements/ Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">MTV Movie Award - Best Jaw-Dropping Moment: Leonardo DeCaprio (2014).</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">MTV Movie Award - Best Comedic Performance: Jonah Hill (2014).</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Empire Award - Best Female Newcomer: Margot Robbie (2014).</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Fact:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie is known as Martin Scorsese\'s major commercial success, grossing roughly $392 million worldwide. This movie has been his highest-grossing film by far, and also sets a Guinness World Record, for the most instances of swearing in any film. (It was three hours long; Do the Math!)</span>\r\n<h3><b>Platforms:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Netflix</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Amazon Prime.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>3. The Theory of Everything (2014):</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 7.7</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> James Marsh</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Eddie Redmayne, Felicity Jones, Charlie Cox, Tom Prior, Sophie Perry.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3340 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/3-9.jpg\" alt=\"The Theory of Everything (2014)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Theory of Everything is the narration of the most brilliant and celebrated physicist of our time, Stephen Hawking, and his love interest, later became his wife, an art student from Cambridge, Jane Wilde. At age 21, he got diagnosed with a fatal illness, capable of paralyzing Stephen\'s locomotion, while told by his doctor of a life expectancy of two years only.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Despite all odds stacked in front of him, he and Jane persevere. He went on to be titled \'The Successor to Einstein\', a husband and a father of three. But over the course of his marriage, Stephen’s body continued to collapse in trade to his academic renown elevated. His marriage also got tested in the trade as well, adversely altering the course of both of their lives.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Achievements/ Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Academy Award - Best Actor in Leading Role: Eddie Redmayne (2015).</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Screen Actors Guild Award - Outstanding Lead Role (Male): Eddie Redmayne (2015).</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">BAFTA Award - Best British Film: James Marsh (2015)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Platforms:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Netflix</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Amazon Prime.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>4. The Social Network (2010):</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 7.7</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> David Fincher</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Jesse Eisenberg, Andrew Garfield, Justin Timberlake.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3341 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/4-8.jpg\" alt=\"The Social Network (2010): Movies based on real-life Millionaires\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Social Network highlights Mark Zuckerburg’s ingenious networking website in 2003, which is known to the world as FaceBook today. However, Mark met his unprecedented success, which also led to both personal and legal complications.  He even ends up on the receiving end of two lawsuits, one involving his former friend, Eduardo. His invention of FaceBook led to an aspect that became a part of today’s Globalization.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Achievements/ Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Academy Award for Best Writing (Adapted Screenplay): Aaron Sorkin (2011)</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Golden Globe Award for Best Motion Picture – Drama (2011)</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">National Society of Film Critics Award - Best Actor: Jesse Eisenberg (2011)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Platforms:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Netflix</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Amazon Prime.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>5. Pirates of Silicon Valley (1999):</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 7.3</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Martyn Burke</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Noah Wyle, Anthony Michael Hall, John DiMaggio</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3342 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/5-8.jpg\" alt=\"Pirates of Silicon Valley (1999): rich people movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie isn’t about one millionaire; it\'s about two of them! Steve Jobs and Bill Gates are known to be one of the biggest visionaries of the 1970s, who revolutionized the progress of the computer industry, and how computers are perceived in today’s world. The movie highlights how these two visionaries met each other at Harvard University, but as time went on, their ideas about computers also lead them into a personal rivalry.</span>\r\n\r\nThis is the last movie form our Millionaires movies list.\r\n<h3><b>Achievements/ Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Primetime Emmy Award - Writing (Movie or Dramatic Special): Martyn Burke (1999).</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Fact:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The word “Pirates” appears in the title of the movie to depict the darker side to the revolution of Computers. While Jobs of Apple and Gates of Microsoft were indisputably brilliant men, each in their own way, they didn’t invent much of the technology that is widely attributed to the theme.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Platforms:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Netflix</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Amazon Prime.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>6. Bonus Millionaires Movies: Pursuit of Happiness (2006):</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 8</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Gabriele Muccino</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Will Smith, Jaden Smith, Dan Castella</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3337 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/6-6.jpg\" alt=\"Pursuit of Happiness (2006): rich man movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<b>About:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">    The Pursuit of Happiness is one of the best motivational movies portraying Chris Gardener, founder of Gardner Rich &amp; Co. (1987). The movie highlights the struggles of Gardener in the 1980s, where he was at his lowest of times. He loses his life\'s earnings selling a product he invested in.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The financial troubles make him lose his apartment, his wife leaving him, being left with the custody of his son. While Gardener takes part in an unpaid internship in a brokerage firm, he tries to fend for his son and endures the troubles the city offers him. His undying spirit and his love of his son finally leads him to secure the job as a broker. </span>\r\n<h3><b>Achievements/ Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">MTV Movie Award - Best Breakthrough Performance: Jaden Smith (2007).</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Teen Choice Award - Choice Movie Actor: Drama: Will Smith (2007).</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Teen Choice Award - Choice Movie: Chemistry: Will Smith and Jaden Smith (2007).</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Platforms:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Netflix.</span></li>\r\n</ul>','5 Movies Based on Real-Life Millionaires and Rich People','','publish','open','open','','5-movies-based-on-real-life-millionaires-and-rich-people','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-movies-about-billionaires-falling-in-love/','2021-01-24 09:07:31','2021-01-24 03:37:31','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3310',0,'post','',0),(3319,7,'2020-11-29 07:44:12','2020-11-29 02:14:12','War is hell. This is a popular subject for movies. However, only a few <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-13-war-movies-based-on-real-stories/\">War films</a> have been successful in capturing the realism of frantic combat. Today, we invite you to look at our pick of Top 10 Hollywood War Movies. Real wars and combat battles have inspired these films, and they have been praised for their authentic portrayal of war and its side effects.\r\n<h2><strong>10. Enemy At The Gates (2001)</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3325 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/1-9.jpg\" alt=\"movies like Enemy At The Gates (2001)Hollywood War Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThis movie is based on what is considered to be an extremely infamous event of WW II, The Battle of Stalingrad.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4O-sMh_DO6I\" rel=\"nofollow\">Enemy At The Gates (2001)</a> involves a man named Vassili (Jude Law) who rose to fame as a part of a Government plot. A scheme to eliminate Russian forces. Situations lead to Vassili almost losing his own faith as he embarks upon the challenge of his life. Facing a fierce German Sniper.\r\n\r\nEnemy At The Gates (2001) portrays war vividly and graphically. Director Jean Annaud explored subjects like love and friendship amidst death, destruction, and chaos.\r\nThe film constantly maintains a disturbing atmosphere of hopelessness. The combat scenes are short but when put together, the movie makes up for a fast-paced war experience.\r\n<h2><strong>9. Platoon (2006)</strong></h2>\r\nIt\'s no secret that director Oliver Stone is a war veteran. Not long after his tour concluded in 1968, Stone wrote a semi-autobiographical screenplay. This screenplay would late be the inspiration for Platoon (2006).\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3326 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/2-8.jpg\" alt=\"movies like Platoon (2006) Hollywood War Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nOliver Stone was so meticulous when it came to recreating Vietnam that he made the star cast undergo army training. He even had red dirt imported to the movie-set location in the Philippines. All this just to get into the mindset of soldiers.\r\n\r\nCharlie Sheen, Willem Dafoe, and Tom Berenger play US soldiers stationed in Vietnam.  Platoon (2006) is full of widely varied personalities and levels of morality. This is a harrowing and haunting war movie.\r\n<h2><strong>8. Flag of our Fathers (2006)</strong></h2>\r\nDirected by legendary actor/director/producer, Clint Eastwood and based on James Bradley\'s novel, it is one of the rare movies that remain true to its book. It explores thought-provoking subjects such as heroism and war-propaganda.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3327 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/3-8.jpg\" alt=\"movies like Flag of our Fathers (2006) Hollywood War Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nSix soldiers photographed hoisting the United States flag on Mt. Suribachi in the Feb of 1945. Flag of our Fathers (2006) is a story following the lives of three of them. These three managed to survive the war and had flown back to their country. The Government later uses these new war heroes to sell government bonds.\r\n\r\nThis film deals with the aftermath of war rather than the combat itself sending a message, there are no heroes in war.\r\n<h2><strong>7. Apocalypse Now (1979)</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3328 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/4-7.jpg\" alt=\"movies like Apocalypse Now (1979) Hollywood War Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nApocalypse Now covers the topic of the psychological repercussions of war. This violent and gritty story follows Captain Benjamin Willard (Martin Sheen). Willard is a detached military man in search of a mission. This mission later turns out to be an assassination attempt on a reclusive renegade Colonel by the name of Kurtz (Marlon Brando).\r\n\r\nMarlon Brando\'s character of a mentally unhinged Colonel does not appear until the film\'s climax.  However, both Sheen and Brando\'s immensely powerful and authentic performances continue to haunt viewers to this day.\r\n<h2><strong>6. Full Metal Jacket (1987)</strong></h2>\r\nYou wouldn’t see much warfare until the second half of Full Metal Jacket (1987). However, the opening scenes are arguably even harder to watch.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3329 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/5-7.jpg\" alt=\"movies like Full Metal Jacket (1987) Hollywood War Movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThe first half is about a cruel Drill Instructor (R Lee Ermey) pushing one vulnerable private over the edge of sanity.\r\n\r\nErmey served as an actual drill instructor in Vietnam and thus improvised many of his character\'s callous insults.\r\n\r\nErmey’s performance is not the only aspect of this film that\'s shockingly accurate. It is said that director Stanley Kubrick started researching the Vietnam War in 1983. He was influenced by documentaries, Vietnamese newspapers, and a plethora of photos.\r\n<h2><strong>5. Dunkirk (2017)</strong></h2>\r\nDunkirk (2017) follows a non-linear storyline like a few other Christopher Nolan\'s movies.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3330 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/6-5.jpg\" alt=\"movies like Dunkirk (2017)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nExplored from three perspectives, Dunkirk (2017) is based on a World War II event where the Allied soldiers from Britain and France were held up in the city of Dunkirk, France. Surrounded by Germans they made an attempt to evacuate during a raging battle.\r\n\r\nNolan is known for his rare use of CGI and this movie is no exception. The film had a crew of six-thousand extras, authentic vehicles from WW II, and realistic sets.\r\n\r\nDunkirk (2017) doesn’t have a lot of dialogues and relies on sound-design during most of the movie runtime. To put it shortly, Dunkirk (2017) is an achievement in war cinema.\r\n<h2><strong>4. 1917 (2019)</strong></h2>\r\n1917 (2019) is a unique film as far as cinematography is concerned. This film is made in a one-take style ensuring that you can\'t look away.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3331 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/7-4.jpg\" alt=\"movies like 1917 (2019)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nDirected by Sam Mendes and winner of three Academy Awards, this movie has a very linear storyline. The movie is about two soldiers who are ordered to deliver one message that will save the lives of 1600 soldiers who are about to march into certain death. These two soldiers must race against time to deliver the message.\r\n\r\nA great plot, wonderfully written characters, and fabulous performances all around. Needless, to say, every aspect of the movie is near perfect among all Hollywood War Movies list.\r\n<h2><strong>3. The Hurt Locker (2008)</strong></h2>\r\nThis movie created history! This was the first time in Hollywood that a female moviemaker had received the Best Director Academy Award.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3332 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/8-4.jpg\" alt=\"movies like The Hurt Locker (2008)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nDirected by Kathryn Bigelow, this action thriller follows a bomb diffusal unit stationed in Iraq during the Iraq war.\r\n\r\nAn atmosphere of smouldering tensions arises between new Squad Leader William James (Jeremy Renner) and his crew as they execute their operations of defusing bombs.\r\n\r\nJeremy Renner along with his co-stars make The Hurt Locker (2008) stand out on our list of Hollywood’s Top 10 War Movies.\r\n<h2><strong>2. Black Hawk Down (2001)</strong></h2>\r\nDirector Ridley Scott plunges the viewers into explosive anarchy and never gives us a second to catch our breath in Black Hawk Down (2001).\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3333 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/9-4.jpg\" alt=\"movies like Black Hawk Down (2001)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThis exceptional film chronicles the 1993 Battle of Mogadishu from the perspective of American soldiers. This movie is an adaptation of Mark Bowden\'s non-fiction book and takes gritty realism to new levels. It approached the US Somalia conflict with the finesse of a documentary.\r\n\r\nPerhaps the most authentic aspect of the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">film</a> is the camaraderie between our central characters as some cast members trained with real soldiers. This created a constant sense of brotherhood that shined through in the final product.\r\n<h2><strong>1. Saving Private Ryan (1998)</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3324 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/10-4.jpg\" alt=\"Saving Private Ryan (1998)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nlast of the Hollywood War Movies list and best one. War is full of horrors and you can never be psychologically prepared for it. However, Saving Private Ryan (1998) is the closest you can come to having a war experience without enlisting as a soldier. In fact, the very first scene of the movie, the D-Day sequence proved so believable that some veterans experienced PTSD while watching it.\r\n\r\nFrom the seasickness to the relentless mayhem that ensued. Everything about the movie’s portrayal of the Normandy invasion on June the 6th, 1944 rings true.\r\n\r\nThe first twenty-minutes is what most people discuss. However, the movie also focuses on a squad with a mission is to find Private James Ryan whose three brothers perish during the conflict.\r\n\r\nThere is a fine balance between action and emotion in this movie. With its immense critical and commercial success, Saving Private Ryan (1998) occupies the top position on our Top 10 list of <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/hollywood/\">Hollywood</a> War Movies.','Hollywood War Movies | List of Top 10 You Must Watch','','publish','open','open','','hollywood-war-movies-list-of-top-10-you-must-watch','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/top-13-war-movies-based-on-real-stories/','2020-12-25 17:16:00','2020-12-25 11:46:00','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3319',0,'post','',1),(3402,9,'2020-12-11 20:13:36','2020-12-11 14:43:36','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mystery, Crime movies, and Thriller have been volatile Genres when it comes to all the movies out there. It has been timeless and has been adaptable to every kind of subject, for it can reflect people\'s demeanour or even how they can take fight or flight.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It introduces not only to characters in a subtle kind of way, but it shows what kind of problems can people live with, and how they would react to it, either in plain sight or in secret. Some of them rise to stardom at times that they can get the chance to be revived by <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/hollywood/\">Hollywood</a>. And speaking of adaptations, today’s list will bring you crime movie adaptations that have been derived from <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/best-crime-movies-based-on-true-life-stories/\">Crime Novels</a>.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span><b>1. Trainspotting (1996):</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 8.1</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Danny Boyle</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Ewan McGregor, Ewen Bremner, Kevin McKidd, Robert Carlyle</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3594 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/1-1.jpg\" alt=\"Trainspotting (1996) Top Crime Movies based on Novels\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie revolves around a novel bearing the same title. It talks about a young man named Renton, who is depicted by the novel as the voice of reason among his toxic group of friends. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Renton happens to have an addiction and fondness for heroin which gets him into trouble and shenanigans time and time again. His parents would then intervene and help him get better.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As time passes, Renton gets clean, moves on to London, and does better for himself by getting a good life, with a good job. But as things get better, they get much worse by the news of his friend’s death, Tommy. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Renton reunites with his friends who would mourn as becoming drug dealers. He cynically narrates his life struggles and shows how he desired to choosing life over his addictions.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie not only involves the abuse of heroin but introduces other types of addictions. These include that of having an unhealthy company, watching TV, eating junk, and getting involved in violence.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Achievements:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">BAFTA Award - <a href=\"https://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/1996\">Best Adapted Screenplay (1996)</a></span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Empire Award - Best British Film (1997)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Empire Award - Best British Actor: Ewan McGregor (1997)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> The word ‘Trainspotting’, which is the title of the movie, refers to being obsessed with a trivial topic. However, it also refers to the hobby of watching trains and counting them as they pass.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Vudu, Amazon Prime</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8LuxOYIpu-I[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span><b>2. The Sisters Brothers (2018):</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 7</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Jacques Audiard (Also directed ‘A Prophet’ and ‘Rust and Bone’)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 40