thetvfreak.com/?p=3402',0,'post','',0),(3414,7,'2020-12-06 19:36:41','2020-12-06 14:06:41','Some movies just make you feel good. They make you feel grateful and thankful for your share in life.\r\n\r\nToday, we’re counting films for our list of <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/hollywood/\">Hollywood\'s</a> Top 10 Feel-Good Movies. For this list, we will consider movies that have made the audiences appreciate life for one reason or the other.\r\n<h2><strong>10. 50/50 (2011)</strong></h2>\r\nWe\'re bound to feel bad for Adam (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joseph_Gordon-Levitt\">Joseph Gordon-Levitt</a>) as he discovers that he has a malignant tumour.  This tumour is present in his spine and, as the movie title suggests, his chances for survival are only 50/50.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3443 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/1.jpg\" alt=\"50/50 (2011) feel good movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nHis misery is further amplified upon discovering that his girlfriend is cheating on him. But, when things don\'t seem like they can get any worse, they actually get a bit better.\r\n\r\nAdam meets a marvellous girl <span class=\"wo fr-10 replaced\" data-num=\"10\">—</span> Katherine (Anna Kendrick) as his therapist.  He also begins to accept how his loved ones are coping with his illness. Of course, Adam has got his best friend Kyle who\'s always at his side no matter what.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MiMlrrA2PRk[/embedyt]\r\n\r\nNot wallowing in doom and gloom, 50/50 (2011) could have been a depressing movie. Instead, it made us grateful for our health and the people who will stick with us even in our bad times. Especially then! You watch this movie from the list of Hollywood feel-good movies.\r\n<h2><strong>9. Punch-Drunk Love (2002)</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3444 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/2.jpg\" alt=\"Punch-Drunk Love (2002)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nBarry <span class=\"wo fr-0\" data-num=\"0\">Egan</span> (Adam <span class=\"wo fr-1\" data-num=\"1\">Sandler</span>) is a man who seems exceptionally weak at first glance. However, like a calm ocean that conceals a bevy of predators under the surface, there is an inner strength in him trying to break free. So, when he meets a woman that sees through his quiet facade, he comes to feel a sense of self-worth, perhaps for the first time.\r\n\r\nDirected by Paul Thomas Anderson, this is a unique tale of romance. It has both another worldly and a realistic feel. This romantic comedy-drama can\'t help but make us feel that anybody can find love if they try hard enough.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VNeZi1y_v88[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>8. The Blind Side (2009)</strong></h2>\r\nBased on true incidents, The Blind Side (2009) tells the remarkable life-altering story of Michael <span class=\"wo fr-2\" data-num=\"2\">Oher</span> (Quinton Aaron). A young man who is adopted by a well-to-do family that takes him out of the impoverished world he\'s been brought up in.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3445 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/3.jpg\" alt=\"The Blind Side (2009) feel good movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nFor most of his earlier life, Michael had to constantly fend for himself. But thanks to the kind <span class=\"wo fr-3\" data-num=\"3\">Tuohy</span> family, he finds an opportunity to focus on his academic and athletic. As a result, this massive man accomplishes his dreams and makes it to the NFL(National Football League).\r\n\r\nThis sports drama made in the form of semi-biography tells us that sometimes all you need is one person to believe in you.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gvqj_Tk_kuM[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>7. Love actually (2003)</strong></h2>\r\nLove actually (2003) is a movie with several intertwined stories of love. Some of those turn out well while others<span class=\"wo fr-4\" data-num=\"4\">..</span>not so much.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3446 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/4.jpg\" alt=\"Love actually (2003)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThis movie attempts to provide a balanced but optimistic view of love and relationships. This love can be between two longtime friends. A Brit and a bevvy of beauties. And even a Prime Minister and one of his aides, we can\'t help but root for them. There is something for nearly everyone.\r\n\r\nYou\'ll find that the movie will leave you with a feeling of thankfulness for the possibility of finding love.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KdzH6a-XEGM[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>6. The Green Mile (1999)</strong></h2>\r\nBased on a story by the master of horror Stephen King and three times Academy Award-nominated director Frank <span class=\"wo fr-6\" data-num=\"6\">Darabont</span>, this movie is a tearjerker. With a brilliant story, fantastic narration, exceptional acting, The Green Mile (1999) is an outstanding drama.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3447 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/5.jpg\" alt=\"The Green Mile (1999)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThis movie is about how the life of a prison warden named Paul <span class=\"wo fr-7\" data-num=\"7\">Edgecomb </span>(Tom Hanks) changes when a death row inmate with a special gift makes an entry into the prison.\r\n\r\nThis over three-hour-long film keeps you riveted to your seat as you go through a roller coaster ride of emotions. It will make you smile, cry, and sometimes fill you with emotions that cannot be put into words. The movie ends with a very cathartic note making you feel grateful for the gift that is called life.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ki4haFrqSrw[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>5. Life is beautiful (1997)</strong></h2>\r\nYou\'d think that a film in which a father and son are sent to a Nazi death camp wouldn\'t belong to this list. But you\'d be wrong!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3448 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/6.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThe audience is left in awe when a father successfully convinces his son that they\'re in the midst of a large game. All this to shield him from the horrors of their everyday life in the concentration camp.\r\n\r\nThe healing nature of this comedy comes from the fact that it takes a dark subject matter and shines a light of hope upon it.  Life is beautiful (1997) leaves us appreciative of the love of family and the sacrifices people make for those they care about.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8CTjcVr9Iao[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>4. Cast Away (2000)</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3449 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/7.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nChuck <span class=\"wo fr-8\" data-num=\"8\">Noland</span> (Tom Hanks) takes a flight over the Pacific Ocean to deliver a package with disastrous results. This FedEx Depot engineer gets marooned on an island with nothing but a volleyball to keep him company. He undergoes physical and mental transformation but continues to fight for survival and to get home.\r\n\r\nTom Hank\'s acting is top-notch in this movie. It also features a kick-ass plane crash scene that started it all. Cast Away (2000) is an inspiring tale of perseverance that leaves us in admiration for the human spirit.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qGuOZPwLayY[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>3. Forrest <span class=\"wo fr-9\" data-num=\"9\">Gump</span> (1994)</strong></h2>\r\nThis movie has given us one of Hollywood’s most memorable characters. Tom Hanks, in the titular role, gave a performance of a lifetime. The movie is about the life of Forest (Tom Hanks) <span class=\"wo fr-10 replaced\" data-num=\"10\">—</span> a young man with a double-digit IQ but a heart of gold. Going through a series of true historical events in the United States, Forest’s only desire is to unite with the love of his life.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3450 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/8.jpg\" alt=\"feel good movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nWith Hanks’ exceptional acting and an amazingly well-written story, this movie teaches you a lot about life as a journey and its meaning. It tells you that life can throw a lot at you, some of it may not be pleasant, but we shouldn’t let setbacks hold us back.\r\n\r\nThis movie also sends a message that you don’t have to be smart to be happy and even the actions of a simple man can affect the lives of people around him in a very positive way.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bLvqoHBptjg[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>2. The <span class=\"wo fr-11\" data-num=\"11\">Shawshank</span><span class=\"wo fr-12\" data-num=\"12\">  </span>Redemption (1994)</strong></h2>\r\nWe return once again to our duo from The Green Mile (1999) — writer Stephen King and director Frank <span class=\"wo fr-13\" data-num=\"13\">Darabont</span>. This movie is perhaps the best and most memorable creation from the famous writer and director.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3451 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/9.jpg\" alt=\"feel good movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThe <span class=\"wo fr-14\" data-num=\"14\">Shawshank</span><span class=\"wo fr-15\" data-num=\"15\">  </span>Redemption (1994) takes a horrific environment and turns it into a <span class=\"wo fr-16\" data-num=\"16\">petri-dish</span> of humanity. This <span class=\"wo fr-17\" data-num=\"17\">petri-dish</span> comes in the form of a prison populated with some truly awful men as well as men who have done awful things but are becoming better humans.\r\n\r\nAfter the credits roll we are left feeling glad knowing that people and hope can survive even in the darkest of places.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NmzuHjWmXOc[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>1. The Pursuit of Happyness (2006)</strong></h2>\r\nThis is a top movie from the list of Hollywood feel-good movies.\r\n\r\nIf you want to see a movie about what a perfect father should be, then you must watch The Pursuit of Happyness (2006). Based on the real-life story of Chris Gardner played by Will Smith, this movie depicts the struggle of a poor father trying to give his son a good life while attempting to switch to a life-changing professional career.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3452 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/10.jpg\" alt=\"The Pursuit of Happiness (2006)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThe director could not have picked a better cast than Will Smith and real-life his son <span class=\"wo fr-18\" data-num=\"18\">Jaden</span> Smith. This movie’s gritty realism will make you feel as if you’re watching a documentary on someone’s life.\r\n\r\nThe Pursuit of Happyness (2006) celebrates virtues like hard-work and integrity in a man. It doesn’t just show you the hardships of an impoverished single parent but also sends you a message that no matter how hard you are pushed by life, you can always get up.\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DMOBlEcRuw8[/embedyt]\r\n\r\nSo this is our list of Hollywood\'s Top 10 Feel-Good Movies, hope you liked our content\r\n\r\n<b>– Abhishek Tewari</b>','Hollywood\'s Top 10 Feel-Good Movies You Must Watch','','publish','open','open','','hollywoods-top-10-feel-good-movies-you-must-watch','','','2021-01-08 11:05:19','2021-01-08 05:35:19','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3414',0,'post','',0),(3421,9,'2020-12-19 16:29:50','2020-12-19 10:59:50','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Technology is without a doubt a blessing, which has helped the human race reach new heights of progress. From the 18th Century, we have seen its rise in almost all aspects of society. For example, for cooling ourselves off on a hot day, we had electric fans. And For communicating with people from afar, we have mobile phones. For moving from place to place, we have now cars. And speaking of cars, today’s list will feature some of the well-known and great car racing movies that will help you remain entertained in the pandemic. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This car racing movies list will ensure you to move your seat to a distant place and away from all the problems, you can possibly have with the pandemic. So let’s dive in!</span>\r\n<h2><b>10. Fast and Furious (2000-21):</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> -Best</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Justin Lin, Vin Diesel, F. Gary Gray.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0004874/\">Vin Diesel</a>, Paul Walker, Jordana Brewster</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1122 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/fast-and-furious-8-min.jpg\" alt=\"Fast and furious\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So saving best for the last. I hope you were waiting for this Franchise to pop up anytime now! So this Franchise went from illegal street racing to becoming fugitives living abroad. Then finally took its turn as hunting down spies and cyber terrorists (that’s a real thing now!). The movie shows how so many Ludacris odds (no pun intended)  were stacked in the form of the FBI, the Cartel, the Shaw Family, and now a cyber-terrorist named Cipher.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The idea of fast cars and family intertwined with one another, making it one of the biggest franchises in Hollywood, lasting for two decades now! So instead of one movie, I would suggest eight of them instead! </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So here is something you might never know about the title of the movie. The title happens to be known as ‘Redline’ at first for the very first movie. It implies the maximum speed a car can go. After a very tiring discussion from the cast members, they finally decided to come up with the title that promised in making billions in the box office</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Netflix, Prime Video</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uisBaTkQAEs[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>9. Mad Max: Fury Road (2015):</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 8.1</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">George Miller</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Charlize Theron, Tom Hardy (Inception, Venom, the revenant), Nicholas Hoult</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3675 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/racing-movies-2.jpg\" alt=\"Fast and Furious (2000-21) racing movies (2)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So at first glance, people think why are these people crazy? The answer is that they just are. In a post-apocalyptic world, where people make monster-like cars and trucks into ships with grotesque Cirque du Soleil Acts on top (literally), we see how people tend to fight in tribes over scarce resources.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This Australian Movie Brings us to a landscape as the entire world is on the brink of extinction, but civilization is emerged by a tyrannical ruler. One of the warriors of this ruler happens to take away the ruler’s wives and makes an escape for their lives.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Along the way, she joins forces with one of the captives of the same ruler, Max Rockatansky. They make a run from the ruler in a heavily fortified truck called the War Rig, and battle with the ruler’s henchmen in a high-speed chase across the deserts.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Achievements/ Nominations:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Academy Award - Best Production Design: Lisa Thompson, Colin Gibson (2016)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">MTV Award - Best Female Performance: Charlize Theron (2016)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Critics’ Choice Award - Best Actor (Action Movie): Tom Hardy (2016)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  The Director of the movie, George Miller, also happens to have an M.D. Secondly, Max is not the main character of the film, although he has a major presence in the movie itself. It is actually Imperator Furiosa (Charlize Theron), who intends to escape the tyrant ruler, Immortan Joe.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> WarnerBros, Vudu, Fandango, Prime Watch</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hEJnMQG9ev8[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>8. Locke (2013):</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 7.1</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Steven Knight</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Tom Hardy, Tom Holland, Olivia Coleman</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3676 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/racing-movies-3.jpg\" alt=\"Locke (2013): racing movies (3)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So this movie is although a bit underrated but is really good while watching. It talks about a successful construction worker who faces adversity in the next one and a half-hour or so. In the meantime, he makes his way from Birmingham to London, where his one-night stand comes into labour. This led to Ivan (Locke) losing his marriage and his job in the process.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Although he regrets his wrong and admits it on the phone (while en route to London for his affair), he tries to fix whatever he can on the phone and tries to confine the entire story inside his car. The entire movie exhibits various emotions inside of the car as the main character reveals his true intentions behind all of his actions.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Achievements/ Nominations:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">British Independent Film Award - Best Screenplay: Steven Knight (2013)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Despite the character’s soft-spoken and soothing tone towards all the calls he made in his car, Tom Hardy was actually suffering from a cold during the course of the film production.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Vudu, Fandango, Prime Watch.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2Ao2r6qD22A[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>7. Rush (2013):</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 8.1</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Ron Howard</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/best-movies-of-chris-hemsworth-except-mcu/\">Chris Hemsworth</a>, Daniel Bruhl, Alexandra Maria Lara.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3677 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/racing-movies-4.jpg\" alt=\"Rush racing movie\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The suggested title of this movie shows a lot of excitement as two of the best and most skilled drivers went head to head with one another. The movie features F1 Racing legends James Hunt and Nikki Lauda.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie portrays their intense rivalry on the race track where Nikki Lauda often came out victorious. James at one point bested Nikki but that situation entirely changed over time. Hunt embarks on a journey to best Lauda once again, which tests his skill and undying spirit altogether.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Nikki Lauda and James Hunt were actually great friends both on and off the track. The fact that both are shown in the movie as bitter rivals are seriously frowned upon by both the legends. Call it showbiz if you will!</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Netflix, Prime Video, Fandango.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cAXofKV19g4[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>6. Talladega Nights: The Ballad of Ricky Bobby (2006):</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 6.6</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Adam McKay</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Will Ferrel, John C. Reilly, Adam McKay</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3678 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/racing-movies-5.jpg\" alt=\"Talladega Nights: The Ballad of Ricky Bobby (2006) racing movies (5)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Born inside a fast-moving car (NSFW), Ricky is destined to become a sensation in the world of motorsport. As a matter of fact, he does become the number one racer in NASCAR. But as the order of the world is naturally concerned, some drivers have their ups and some of them have their downs.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The story then takes a turn, as a former F1 driver from France, takes over the NASCAR Division and dethrones Ricky in the process. The movie hilariously shows his resurgence in the sport that he loves and how he takes back his throne from Jean (the French Driver!).</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The amazing chemistry of the comedic duo of John C. Reilly and Will Ferrel was never existent without Molly Shannon, who introduced them to one another. These two later on featured in various movies like ‘Step Brothers’ and ‘the Land of the Lost’.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Fandango, Vudu, Amazon Prime.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=myKtVl8N7jU[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>5. <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/ford-v-ferrari-2019/\">Ford vs Ferrari (2019)</a>:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 8.1</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> James Mangold</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Matt Damon, Christian Bale, Jon Bernthal</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3679 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/racing-movies-6.jpg\" alt=\"Ford vs Ferrari (2019): racing movies (6)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ford vs Ferrari is a timeless classic, featuring the rise of a small car manufacturing company, Ford, which rises to the occasion to take down a European car manufacturing Giant (Ferrari) at the Le Mans, one of the most famous racing venues.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It also brings Caroll Shelby (being the only American to ever win in the Le Mans) and Ken Miles (a famous race car driver) to stand up to the occasion, and team up with Ford to take down Ferrari with their best car, the GT40.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you have a little bit of love for cars or acting then you will love this movie and after watching this you will try to finish this whole list as well. Yes, this is the best in all car racing movies in 2019. This is also on top in the list of <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-sports-movies-based-on-real-life-stories/\">Top Sports Movies Based on Real Life Stories</a></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Achievements/ Nominations:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Satellite Award - Best Actor: Christian Bale (2020)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Satellite Award - Best Director: James Mangold (2020)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">BAFTA Award - Best Editing: Andrew Buckland (2020)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Ken Miles is known as a World War veteran who is known for breaking his record at Le Mans three times in a single race. He is especially regarded as winning the Sebring, Daytona, and Le Mans in a single year (1966). Although there was this conspiracy known (as also shown at the near end of the movie) that the victor was declared as Bruce McLaren.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Netflix, Amazon Prime.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I3h9Z89U9ZA[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>4. REV (2020):</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> -</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Ant Horasanli</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Francesco Filipe, Vivica A. Fox, Sean Rey.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3680 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/racing-movies-7.jpg\" alt=\"REV (2020)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So this is one of the best car racing movies 2020 and happens to be also a heist movie, as it is about this young delinquent who happens to commit Grand Theft Auto for a living. However, such a life got the best of him, forcing him into becoming an informant for the police.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The police intended in taking down an organization, responsible for stealing a lot of exotic cars and shipping them off to West Africa. In their own words, they wanted to become \'A car sales insurance’s worst nightmare’. Tensions only rose as things started to unfold in the story. And it now becomes more than a large car shipping operation.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Netflix, Amazon Prime.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jYW8Qjhx3KM[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>3. Baby Driver (2017):</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 7.6</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Edgar Wright</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Ansel Elgort, Jamie Foxx, Lily James</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3681 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/racing-movies-8.jpg\" alt=\"Baby Driver (2017)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> So this one is a little off the bat. Just like ‘Drive’, we see an escort named ‘Baby’, who happens to pay his debt to his superior after attempting to steal his car. He pays it off by being the getaway driver in many heist jobs.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He dodges all the police cars around effortlessly and manages to get away with it every time (at least that is true in the movie for now). However, when the deal is paid off, he finds that he is still needed for one last job, which leads him to further trouble with his boss. Time only tells whether he will be able to escape with his newly met affair. No doubt that it is also the best selection for the car racing action movies list.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Achievements/ Nominations:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">BAFTA - Best Editing: Jonathan Amos (2018)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">NME Awards - Best Film (2018)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> \'Baby\' in the movie is actually an autistic individual, which is discreetly implied by the number of iPods he has in his pockets and the fact that he can drive masterfully behind the wheel. And speaking of ‘Drive’ from earlier on, the movie may resemble in many aspects but it does not pay homage to Ryan Gosling’s character at all.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Vudu, Google Play, Netflix.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D9YZw_X5UzQ[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>2. Drive (2011):</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 7.8</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Nicholas Winding Refn</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Ryan Gosling, Bryan Cranston, Carey Mulligan, Christina Hendricks.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3682 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/racing-movies-9.jpg\" alt=\"Drive (2011)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie features Ryan Gosling, a getaway driver with no name except for an alias as ‘Driver’. He is known to be one of the best precision and rally car drivers from Hollywood. The first 12 minutes only show what the character is made of and how he deals with the pressure around him as he masterfully sneaks around and discreetly escapes the cops, while he escorts a band of robbers with him. He later falls in love with a woman, Irene, who is also the wife of a criminal. The driver would then involve himself in the criminal\'s situation and the audience will only take note of how things get only worse from there.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> In the production phase of the film, Ryan was allowed to pick any car for his character development and instructed him to rebuild it.  He solely chose and rebuilt a 73’ Chevrolet Malibu.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Netflix, Vudu, Fandango, Google Play.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KBiOF3y1W0Y[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>1. Need for Speed (2014):</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 6.4</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Scott Waugh</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Aaron Paul, Imogen Poots, Dominic Cooper</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3674 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/racing-movies-1.jpg\" alt=\"Need for Speed (2014): \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So the critics might have underrated this movie, but it still harbours great nostalgia and a decent plot. I mean why not? This movie is one of the best racing movies that are also made for the kids as well here! The movie, as we all know, is based on a global racing game franchise since the 1990s, and it still is a global phenomenon to this day. This movie is the best selection for the list of movies for car enthusiasts.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Anyway, the story starts with a famous racing prodigy from Mount Cisco named Tobey Marshall. He was bested once from his long arch-rival Dino Brewster, in this race in which Dino took away everything from Tobey. Dino would set on to become a famous race car driver while Tobey stayed and worked in his Father’s garage. The two meet again, as Dino offers him to work on a new car. It was also at this point, his father died and Tobey was facing financial debt otherwise he was to lose his garage.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This only coerced him into accepting Dino’s offer but it also led Tobey in losing not only his garage but his freedom and one of his friends. He spent time behind bars and he devised to exact his revenge through a way they were both good at and that was behind the wheel.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Netflix.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u3wtVI-aJuw[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Conclusion:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As a car enthusiast myself, I assure you that there are still more street racing movies from the world of cars. So please stay tuned for I will be posting soon by next week 5 or 10 more car action movies. Until then, Happy Binging! </span>','List of Top 10 Car Racing Movies Including Ford vs Ferrari (2019)','','publish','open','open','','list-of-top-10-car-racing-movies-including-fast-and-furious','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/best-movies-of-chris-hemsworth-except-mcu/','2020-12-20 17:52:27','2020-12-20 12:22:27','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3421',0,'post','',0),(3609,9,'2021-01-11 22:06:30','2021-01-11 16:36:30','<h2><b>Introduction:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We have given so many lists that are based on different categories but one of our favourites is now live. I am sure you will get it from anywhere but the quality of stuff you will get from here can not be seen anywhere. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Let me tell you a bit about myself. I love basketball and if you are not much familiar with the culture of the NBA, then this is your chance. These basketball movies lists happen to be based on the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/hollywood/\">best Hollywood movies</a> on sports. It is either used as a medium for teaching or even as a form of entertainment. You would be amazed to know that most of the fans have already watched them. Nonetheless, these are some of the movies I can find for you to enjoy. So let’s Dive in!</span>\r\n<h2><b>1. White Men can’t jump (1992) | Basketball movies</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 6.8</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Ron Shelton</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Woody Harrelson, Wesley Snipes, Rosie Perez</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So this movie talks about a white baller named Billy Hoyle. He is known to bet on basketball games and makes his opponents always underestimate, simply because he is told to be white. But that doesn’t stop him from embarrassing them now and then.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4148 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/basketball-movies-based-on-true-stories-4.jpg\" alt=\"White Men can’t jump (1992) basketball movies based on true stories (4)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of his opponents becomes his biggest allies on the court, named Sidney Dean, and together they stack up a lot of money from any competition they find on the court.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Billy stacks up this money so that he could avoid the mobsters and pay them off. He also tries to keep his wife unaware of his situation while earning some money on the court.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> When it comes to real life, Both Harrelson and Snipes were actually good at basketball. They were so good that both could have made it easier in the NCAA III Division. In fact, it was Harrelson who bested Snipes every time in real life as well.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Fandango, Vudu, Amazon Prime.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:<