e (at least I do...). When people said that the sky\'s the limit (pun intended of course), now I feel like there is no limit to things at all. These space travel movies say a lot about the universe and the best thing is that all of these <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/9-best-movie-franchises-like-harry-potter-to-binge-about/\">movies are family-friendly</a> space movies. So let me deal with this list without justifying any boundaries to production. So let’s dive in!</span>\r\n<h2><b>1. Gravity (2013)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 7.7</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Alfonso Cuaron (Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban, Roma)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Sandra Bullock, George Clooney, Ed Harris</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3705 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/2-2.jpg\" alt=\"Gravity (2013)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Gravity is a modern Sci-Fi Thriller that presents a unique subject in mind: How can somebody survive space all alone? This is also considered the best in all sci-fi space movies.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The story starts off as an engineer, Ryan Stone, and an astronaut, Matt Kowalski, become stranded in space due to debris impacting a satellite they were working on. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ryan manages to survive but must encounter the challenge to reach another ship or satellite in space. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She tries to make her way when she is unable to control herself spinning out of control with almost nothing to leverage herself with (there’s no friction in space, obviously!). The movie shows her resilience although she doesn’t believe in possessing it. Her life is put to the test in an almost uncertain way.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OiTiKOy59o4[/embedyt]\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Achievements/ Nominations:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Academy Award - Best Cinematography: Emmanuel Lubezski (2014)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">BAFTA Award - Cinematography: Emmanuel Lubezski (2014)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> The fact that the movie is well regarded for its picture quality and cinematography. However, 80% of the movie is CGI made. Another fun fact to mention is that the voice actor for mission control is Ed Harris. His presence hints subtly at another film named ‘Apollo 13’.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Warner Bros, Fandango, Vudu, Amazon Prime.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>2. Apollo 13 (1995)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 7.6</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Ron Howard (A Beautiful Mind, Cinderella Man, Rush, In the Heart of the Sea)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Tom Hanks, Kevin Bacon, Ed Harris.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3700 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/3-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Speaking of Apollo 13, the movie added to this list will also be in the discussion. This is one of the movies about space that came years ago.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> It focuses on three Astronauts (Lowell, Haise, and Swigert) who are among the Apollo 13 Moon mission.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">During the course of the journey to the moon, the three astronauts find themselves stranded in their ship due to internal failures. It becomes only a  matter of time for them to resolve the problems before it\'s too late.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KtEIMC58sZo[/embedyt]\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Achievements/ Nominations:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Screen Actors Guild Award - Outstanding Supporting Male Actor: Ed Harris (1996)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Screen Actors Guild Award - Outstanding Cast Performance: Kevin Bacon, Tom Hanks (1996)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> The mission for Apollo 13 was to complete a six-day flight and attempt a third lunar landing. The mission was aborted and therefore classified as a failure simply due to the serious rupture of the service module oxygen tank.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Vudu, Prime Video, Fandango.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>3. The Martian (2015)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 8</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Ridley Scott (Gladiator, Robin Hood, Exodus: Gods and Kings)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Matt Damon, Sebastian Stan, Kate Mara</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3701 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/4-2.jpg\" alt=\"The Martian (2015)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Martian is one of the biggest movies of 2015 and also still considered a new space movie. About an astronaut named Mark Watney, he gets left behind on Mars from his team due to a huge storm. All alone he must find a way to live on till help arrives. In the meantime, Mark tries to survive by growing plants on Mars and synthesizes water. The movie has its own sense of nostalgia as well as various experiences of emotions along the way.</span>\r\n\r\nIf you are a science student then this is one of the sci-fi space movies that motivate students to do something big.\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ue4PCI0NamI[/embedyt]\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Achievements/ Nominations:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Golden Globe Award- Best Motion Picture (2016)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Golden Globe Award- Best Actor: Matt Damon (2016)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  The Venue for the Martian wasn’t CGI-Based; it was made in the Red Desert in Jordan. In fact, Another movie made in this venue was the ‘Red Planet’ (2000).</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Vudu, Fandango, Prime Watch.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>4. First Man (2018)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 7.3</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Damian Chazelle (Whiplash, La La Land)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Ryan Gosling, Claire Foy, Jason Clarke.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3702 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/5-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After the production of La La Land came Chazelle’s ‘First Man’, which also features Ryan Gosling, uptaking the role of Neil Armstrong. We all might have heard about the Space Race but never comprehended it exactly; This movie is the answer to that question, as it uncovers the launch of Apollo 11. It shows how the Space Race came to an end, as Neil Armstrong and Ed White became the first two men to step foot on the moon. This movie is one of the best of <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/science-and-mathematics-movies-based-on-real-life/\">the top movies based on Science and Mathematics.</a></span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PSoRx87OO6k[/embedyt]\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Achievements/ Nominations:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Critics’ Choice Award- Best Score: Justin Hurwitz (2019)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  After the NASA project became a huge success, Neil Armstrong was awarded the Medal of Freedom by President Nixon as well as the Congressional Space Medal of Honor by President Jimmy Carter.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Netflix</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>5. Interstellar (2014)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>IMDb rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 8.6</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Christopher Nolan (The Prestige, The Dark Knight, Inception, Man of Steel)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Matthew McConaughey, Anne Hathaway, Michael Caine</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3703 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/6-2.jpg\" alt=\"Interstellar (2014)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Interstellar takes you to the future (Period!). As mesmerizing as it is thought-provoking, it brings us to the possibility of human Manifestation and existence elsewhere other than planet Earth. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The story is about a farmer and ex-NASA pilot Cooper, who embarks with a group of researchers on seeking other alternatives for mankind to thrive in, as the world is slowly rendered uninhabitable. Professor Brand attempts to resolve a problem and devises a plan to move the human population off to another planet via a wormhole. The entire movie shows the beauty of space and all the stars and planets the crew comes across. The movie can definitely take its time in having you lost in outer space and question your own existence, as Nolan created an epic mystery.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8ZCsQfWPZPo[/embedyt]\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Achievements/ Nominations:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Academy Award- Best Visual Effects: Paul J. Franklin (2015)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> The accuracy of the film is certainly appreciated by scientists as well if it wasn’t for the influence of Dr. Kip Thorne (a theoretical physicist and a Nobel Laureate). Prior to the making of the film, Dr. Thorne laid two rules for the director to abide by while making his film: the movie should abide by the laws of physics and any outrageous speculation should come from the mind of a scientist; not of the director or writer. The guidelines were strictly followed by Nolan, which ultimately contributed to the greatness of the film itself.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Netflix, Fandango, Vudu, Prime Watch.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>Conclusion:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">To safely conclude, this list will act as a great guide in picking such kinds of movies and all of them in the list will bring great nostalgia. Happy Binging Everyone!</span>','5 Realistic Space Movies for Anyone Curious About Space','','publish','open','open','','space-movies-for-anyone-curious-about-space','','','2020-12-22 19:11:48','2020-12-22 13:41:48','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3663',0,'post','',0),(3685,9,'2021-01-01 21:31:33','2021-01-01 16:01:33','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So last time, I brought you some of the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/9-best-movie-franchises-like-harry-potter-to-binge-about/\">best franchises</a> to watch altogether. But now I am bringing my list of some of the best trilogies movies for you to watch now. This list will definitely assure you to watch some of the best movie trilogies in the movie history made with sequels and will give you the time you need to enjoy. So let’s dive in!</span>\r\n<h2><b>1. The Matrix Trilogy (1999-2003) | Best Trilogies</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Lana Wachowski, Lily Wachowski</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Keanu Reeves, Laurence Fishburne, Carrie-Ann Moss.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The series is a cyberpunk subgenre of Sci-Fi, based on the phenomena of Artificial Intelligence, a phenomenon that was predicted back two decades ago. This theme brings us to a computer programmer named Thomas Anderson, by the alias of Neo (who is also a hacker). He pursues the true meaning of his world and therefore, tries to unravel “The Matrix”.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3739 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Some-of-the-Best-Trilogies-worth-Watching-3.jpg\" alt=\"The Matrix Trilogy (1999-2003) \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This pursuit led him to be recuperated from a state of physical inactivity, as Neo realizes that the world he lived in was digitized. In fact, what he came to realize was the downfall of human beings from Intelligent Machines, which managed to outsmart humankind and revolutionize themselves into an army. Neo is the key to bringing down the machines and tries to bring a war between the humans and the machines once and for all.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vKQi3bBA1y8[/embedyt]\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> So the man behind the chosen one’s rescue is Morpheus. But may I indulge with the origins of that word; well, from Greek Mythology, ‘Morpheus’ refers to the god of dreams.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Warner Bros.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>2. Back to the Future (1985-1990) | Best Trilogies</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Robert Zemeckis.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Christopher Lloyd, Michael J.Fox, Lea Thompson.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ever thought of writing a right in place of a wrong by having a time machine? Well, this series is based on an adolescent named Marty who travels in a time machine, to do just that.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3740 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Some-of-the-Best-Trilogies-worth-Watching-4.jpg\" alt=\"Back to the Future (1985-1990)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Marty had a tough life growing up and himself being bullied at school. He meets an eccentric friend named Emmett Brown, who was the mind behind his time machine, which was a car that ran on Plutonium. As he uses his car to transverse back into the past, he realized that his actions can inadvertently affect the future. The movie has many different twists with its story, along with a few gags. It is definitely a classic if you are into its nostalgia.</span>\r\n\r\nThis is one of the greatest movie trilogies that are based on science. Actually, we can say only interesting trilogy.\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aMOgXa2PIuE[/embedyt]\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> The scientist in the film planned to have a pet chimpanzee as his assistant and companion. However, due to the budget being short, the directors instead opted for a dog.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Netflix, Prime Video, Fandango.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>3. Lord of the Rings (2001-2003)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Peter Jackson</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Elijah Wood, Ian McKellen, Orlando Bloom</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So this trilogy takes you back to Middle Earth, an adaptation of the writer of the novel, J.R.R. Tolkien. It brings you to a land of magic, harbored by Orcs, Elves, Wizards, Dragons, Dwarves, and Men (Mankind) into one place.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3741 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Some-of-the-Best-Trilogies-worth-Watching-5.jpg\" alt=\"Lord of the Rings (2001-2003) Some of the Best Trilogies worth Watching (5)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It talks about a constant struggle between good and evil, with the antagonists having the upper hand, under the command of Sauron. But an epic battle between both forces lead to evil dormant but for only a matter of time.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A companionship of Hobbits, Humans, an elf, and a Dwarf aims to bring down Sauron once and for all, as his soul is trapped in a ring which can only be destroyed from the flames it was shaped into. This trilogy immerses us in a saga of their adventure as this group embarks on a journey to evil to its demise once and for all.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cKEGZ-CvWHk[/embedyt]\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Warner Bros, Vudu, Fandango, Prime Watch.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>4. The Dark Knight (2005-2012)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Christopher Nolan</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Christian Bale, Tom Hardy, Michael Caine, Heath Ledger.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe don\'t really think that you didn\'t watch it. Almost every movie person knows that this is the best movie trilogies all the time to watch.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3737 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Some-of-the-Best-Trilogies-worth-Watching-1.jpg\" alt=\"The Dark Knight (2005-2012) Some of the Best Trilogies worth Watching (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The DC Universe decided to reboot the making of Batman in a more sober yet epic fashion, back in the early 2000s. In the city of Gotham, where crime being at an alarmingly high rate is considered normal. The city is also a birthplace for many superheroes among whom, is none other than the Dark Knight. This trilogy shows how the Knight came to be, his struggles against his biggest foes like the Joker, Bane, and Scarecrow.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EXeTwQWrcwY[/embedyt]\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  This is known to be the only Batman trilogy completed by a single director. In the beginning of every movie, the henchmen are dressed in the shape of the main villain.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> WarnerBros, Vudu, Fandango, Prime Watch</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>5. The Godfather (1972-1990)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Francis F. Cappola.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Starcast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Al Pacino, Marlon Brando, James Caan</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The trilogy of this mob drama is derived from the novel of Mario Puzo, having the same name. It focuses on the powerful Italian-American crime family in New York named the Coerleones.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3743 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Some-of-the-Best-Trilogies-worth-Watching-2-1.jpg\" alt=\"Some of the Best Trilogies worth Watching (2)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">They were a powerful family by the 1940s (according to Puzo\'S Adaptation). When the don\'s youngest son, Michael (also a Marine from World War II), reluctantly joins the Mafia, he becomes involved in a series of events leading to fights and betrayal. This trilogy provides a saga revolving around Michael. It\'s very first instalment is the main reason why this series was even a trilogy in the first place!</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sY1S34973zA[/embedyt]\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Fun Fact: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The initial instalment of the trilogy was the highest-grossing film of 1972, and back then the highest-grossing film ever made.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Platforms:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Prime Watch</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>Conclusion:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So this is my list of trilogies worth the watch. I assure you each component of every trilogy will be worth the binge and will keep you amused for hours. Happy Binging Everyone! <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">The Tv Freak</a></span>','Some of the Best Trilogies Movies Worth Watching','','publish','open','open','','some-of-the-best-trilogies-movies-worth-watching','','','2021-01-01 21:31:33','2021-01-01 16:01:33','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3685',0,'post','',0),(3692,7,'2020-12-26 22:25:58','2020-12-26 16:55:58','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">They\'re undeniably evil, in fact, they are so bad that we consider them good enough to dedicate a whole list to them. Today, we are counting down our picks for Top 10 Hollywood Villains. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Our list will include the best superhero villains as well as ordinary people committing some extraordinarily villainous acts. However, we will not be including any animated characters on this list. Let’s begin.</span>\r\n<h2><b>10. Amy, Gone Girl (2014) | Hollywood Villains</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3711 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Villains-1.jpg\" alt=\"Amy, Gone Girl (2014) \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We begin our list with Amy (Rosamund Pike) who fills in the shoes of a traditional female villain archetype. Gone Girl (2014) begins as a mystery movie revolving around Amy’s sudden disappearance with her husband Nick (Ben Affleck) as the primary suspect. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As is the case with many other mystery <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/hollywood/\">Hollywood movies</a>, you begin to piece together evidence to form an explanation. But no sooner than you manage to make sense out of it all, the movie takes a dark and twisted turn.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Gone Girl (2014) has given Rosamund Pike a once in a lifetime role. This movie sends a message that when a couple leaves each other but somehow can\'t make it work, that might turn into a real tragedy.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ym3LB0lOJ0o[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>9. The Armitage Girl, Get Out (2017)</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3712 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Villains-2.jpg\" alt=\"The Armitage Girl, Get Out (2017) \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Imagine meeting the love of your life, a girl who is just perfect in all ways possible. As time passes by, this girl takes you to her parents\' house to meet them. Once in the house, the next thing you realize is that her family is trying to sell your body in an auction.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Armitage girl comes from a family that is heavily racist. A family that takes manipulation to an incredible height. A family that can only be described as evil. What makes this family stand apart is that on the outside they\'re just your regular next-door family. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">They maintain an outward appearance of being open-minded, progressive like any other urban family. But behind closed doors, they indulge in humanity\'s most gruesome and selfish desires.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K9su2d0WM2I[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>8. Killmonger, Black Panther (2018) |</b><b> Hollywood Villains</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3713 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Villains-3.jpg\" alt=\"Killmonger, Black Panther (2018) Top 10 Hollywood Villains (3)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/the-chronological-order-of-the-marvel-cinematic-universe/\">Marvel Comic Universe</a> has brought us some impressive villains. With Erik “Killmonger” Stevens, they really nailed it! Black Panther (2018) is the first comic book superhero film nominated for the Best Picture at the Oscars.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Although a number of reasons contributed to this nomination it’s not hard to see that Killmonger was an essential one.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Played remarkably by Michael B Jordan, Killmonger is a full-fledged villain. For all his lethal methods, he has sympathetic and relatable motivations.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">An emotionally deep character having a solid backstory. Combining that with his personality...you\'ve got an outstanding villain matching our superhero in all respect.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xjDjIWPwcPU[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>7. Terrence Fletcher, Whiplash (2014)</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3714 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Villains-4.jpg\" alt=\"Terrence Fletcher, Whiplash (2014)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The villains discussed so far have been notorious characters for the most part. But our next villain is just a music teacher/ conductor with no murderous intention. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It\'s exactly this trait that makes him a villain like any other.  The kind of antagonist anyone could come across in their regular academic/ professional careers.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">J.K. Simmons won an Academy Award for the Best Actor in a Supporting Role for playing Terrence Fletcher. He is an emotional manipulator who preys on the vulnerability as well as the ambitions of his students.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">All this just for his hunt for musical perfection. He\'s cruel. He\'s violent. But he\'s fundamentally human with a certain amount of sentiment and honour. But just like many other villains, he doesn’t consider himself as one.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7d_jQycdQGo[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>6. Joker, The Joker (2019) </b><b>| Hollywood Villains</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Joker is one of the best Hollywood villains in movie history. In The Joker (2019), this character has demonstrated that he doesn\'t need Batman to maintain that fame.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3715 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Villains-5.jpg\" alt=\"Joker, The Joker (2019)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mental illness is a difficult subject to address. There’s always an apprehension of demonizing it especially in a situation when the character featured is a villain. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The moviemaker did a fantastic job of turning this character into someone who can be both sympathetic and someone who lives up to his villainous legacy.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When Arthur Fleck puts on his Joker persona and allows his dark side to take over, he becomes an agent of chaos.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zAGVQLHvwOY[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>5. Calvin Candie, Django Unchained (2019)</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Leonardo DiCaprio is among the most talented actors of our generation. Can you imagine anyone else playing the role of Jordan Belfort in The Wolf of Wall Street (2013) so well? He made Belfort both reprehensible and so magnetically charming at the same time.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3716 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Villains-6.jpg\" alt=\"Calvin Candie, Django Unchained (2019)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">But he\'s just as skilful in turning off that charm. His portrayal of a 19th-century vicious slave owner called Calvin Candie in Django Unchained (2019) is a testament to that. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">DiCaprio truly commits to this sadistic, spiteful, and entirely repulsive villain. His racism has no limit nor does his bigotry. But the swagger, finesse, and quirks with which DiCaprio portrayed this character made him one of the most loved Hollywood villains.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The fact that he didn\'t get a nomination in the Academy Awards despite this stellar performance is unbelievable.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_iH0UBYDI4g[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>4. Lord Voldemort, Harry Potter Series.</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He had established himself as one of the most famous Hollywood villains in the fantasy genre long before he appeared on the big screen. That\'s right! We are talking about Lord Voldemort from the Harry Potter Series.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3717 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Villains-7.jpg\" alt=\"Lord Voldemort, Harry Potter Series\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It was quite a challenge to meet the expectations of the fans while making a motion picture interpretation of the book. But the moviemakers did a splendid job especially Ralph Fiennes at playing Lord Voldemort. In fact, for many fans, it was as if the Dark Lord had appeared right from the page to the screen.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ralph Fiennes holds nothing back, fully capturing the character especially in the final part of this franchise, Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2 (2011). He is imposing, cruel, and cunning. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There is terror in every word he utters. Yet he has a charisma that makes you understand how he seduces characters to take his side.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_EC2tmFVNNE[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>3. Pennywise, It Series</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Our next villain is a horrifying cosmic being in the form of a sinister clown.  Pennywise — the Dancing Clown. He knows how to appeal to the good-natured and sympathy of kids. And he knows how to devour them after he has seasoned their meat using fear.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3718 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Villains-8.jpg\" alt=\"Pennywise, It Series \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bill Skarsgard has given a lifetime performance. He has made an entire generation of movie fans terrified of this evil villain. The horror genre is full of terrifying monsters but with his uniquely evil persona and the pleasure he obtains in his work, Pennywise stands apart.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xhJ5P7Up3jA[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>2. Kylo Ren, Star Wars Series.</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3719 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Villains-9.jpg\" alt=\"Kylo Ren, Star Wars Series. Top 10 Hollywood Villains (9)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">No one will ever be as good as Darth Vader when it comes to Star Wars villains. Kylo Ren (Adam Driver), however, is a worthy successor to Vader.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He’s compelled by his emotions of negative as well as positive kind. He resembles Vader\'s internal conflict between the dark and bright sides of the force personified.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In a lot of ways, he is a tortured and complicated character that the movie-maker was trying to portray with Anakin Skywalker in the earlier films. Adam Driver gave a powerful performance played with nuance taking the franchise to a new height.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aOC8E8z_ifw[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>1. Thanos, Avengers Series</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3710 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Villains-10.jpg\" alt=\"Thanos, Avengers Series Top 10 Hollywood Villains (10)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Loki was the ruling villain of the Marvel Comic Universe before Thanos (Josh Brolin) took that spot. He is, for all intents and purposes, a brute and formidable physical threat but it is his unflinching resolve that makes up for his greatest strength. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This complex yet charismatic character raised the bar for the future generation of villains.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Thanos has something in common with the best Hollywood villains in movie history. He believes that his extreme and catastrophic methods are completely justifiable and reasonable from a utilitarian viewpoint.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Culminating 21 Marvel movies into Endgame (2019), Thanos shook the Universe to its crux. An antagonist the likes of which we have never seen. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A super-villain whose reputation is elevated even more by the sheer magnitude of the cinematic event in which he makes an appearance.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_xBziiJI3DU[/embedyt]','Top 10 Hollywood Villains Who Won Millions of Heart','','publish','open','open','','top-10-hollywood-villains-who-won-millions-of-heart','','','2020-12-26 22:25:58','2020-12-26 16:55:58','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3692',0,'post','',0),(3896,9,'2020-12-30 22:45:49','2020-12-30 17:15:49','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With the current year coming to a close, one certain thing is that there weren’t a lot of Hollywood movies 2020 we heard of being released. In fact, I would beg to differ for a few best movies of Hollywood in 2020 that definitely made their mark this year.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Since we have only a few days left in this year, today’s list should definitely finish your year a little better. For today’s list, I will bring a bit of a countdown sequence for these 10 Hollywood movies, to keep things interesting. So let’s dive in!  </span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span><b>10. </b><b>Project Power</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDb rating:</strong> 6</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director:</strong> Henry Joost, Ariel Schulman</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Starcast:</strong> Jamie Foxx, Joseph Gordon Levitt, Dominique Fishback</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Starting with one of my personal favourites (despite the low IMDB Ratings), this movie is a great combination of mystery and Sci-Fi. Ask yourself this one thing: Why would you have people selling drugs in those Cops movies unless you can let them sell power?</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3900 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Movies-of-2020-2.jpg\" alt=\"Project Power\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Second Question: What’s your Favourite Animal? What’s your Power? All these questions bring out a unique plot to the film and a great sense of nostalgia and adventure.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie will assure you to have your attention undivided throughout. It revolves around a former US ranger who teams up with a cop to stop a bunch of powerful influences to stop giving away their pills which gives ordinary people superpowers. Give it a watch! I won’t fail you!  </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Fun Fact: </strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">From the movie, one of the cast members, Rodrigo Santoro (the mastermind behind the pills), takes one for himself and becomes a grotesque giant with super strength. The fact that his transformation is not CGI-based but itself a nine-hour transformation process is itself astonishing.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Platforms:</strong> Netflix.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xw1vQgVaYNQ[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span><b>9. </b><b>The Nest </b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDb rating:</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 6.3</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director:</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Sean Durkin</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Starcast:</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  Jude Law, Carrie Coon, Oona Roche.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Nest is a great Drama and <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-movies-about-billionaires-falling-in-love/\">Romance movie</a> featuring an entrepreneur, whose life takes a tumble into a twisted turn of events when his family altogether agree to move into an English Manor in Surrey. The story of the movie itself is very compelling.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3901 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Movies-of-2020-3.jpg\" alt=\"the nest Top 10 Hollywood Movies of 2020 (3)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As things worsen for the family, their character begins to exfoliate altogether as a result of which leads to catastrophe for all individual members. The fact that they move into their new home almost penniless, makes things only more chaotic at the climax of the movie itself. </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Platforms:</strong> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Vudu, Prime Video, Apple TV.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i8YJQ0cflo0[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>8. </b><b>Da 5 Bloods</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDb rating:</strong> 6.5</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director:</strong> Spike Lee</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Starcast: </strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chadwick Boseman, Delroy Lindo, Jonathan Majors</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3902 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Movies-of-2020-4.jpg\" alt=\"Da 5 Bloods  \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie is a tribute to the heroes of the unpopular war in Vietnam. </span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It talks about four African-American army veterans who return to Vietnam to seek the remains of their fallen brethren and the gold they intended to hide. These four men battle through the difficulties nature and man bring along the way.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Fun Fact:</strong>  </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie features <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/chadwick-boseman-black-panther-star-dies-at-43biography-and-movies/\">Chadwick Boseman</a>, as his last movie before his tragic death took place (resulting from intestinal cancer).</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Platforms:</strong> Netflix.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D5RDTPfsLAI[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b></b><b>7. Bad Boys for Life</b> <b></b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDb rating:</strong> 6.6</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director: </strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bilall Fallah, Adil El Arbi.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Starcast: </strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Will Smith, Martin Lawrence, Vanessa Hudgens.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I am probably thinking you never saw Bad Boys before. But if you do, you know what’s coming to you now. The story talks about two of the best cop duos in all of Hollywood who is finally reunited after 17 years.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3903 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Movies-of-2020-5.jpg\" alt=\"Bad Boys for Life\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The flair and the emotions they put you through won’t fail you in an age where crime movies are roughly extinct. The movie starts with a Mexican drug Lord’s son and wife, who embark on a quest to rid of those who were involved in his father\'s imprisonment. That includes none other than Detective Mike Lowry as well. Realizing that he cannot stop what\'s coming to him, he decides to take some help from his old friend and partner Marcus. They along with a special group AMMO, try to confront all those responsible and bring them to justice.</span>\r\n\r\nSo if anyone thinking of Hollywood<a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-best-action-comedy-movies-you-must-watch/\"> Action Movies</a> 2020 that this would definitely come to mind.\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Fun Fact:</strong>  </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie was produced by two Belgians, with some cooperation of Will Smith as well. Michael Bay, the former producer of the last two prequels, was not involved in the making of the film due to the limiting budget of the film.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Platforms:</strong> Prime Video, Fandango, Vudu.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jKCj3XuPG8M[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>6. </b><b>The Way Back</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDb rating:</strong> 6.7</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director:</strong> Gavin O’ Connor.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Starcast: </strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Ben Affleck, Janina Gavankar, Melvin Gregg</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ever felt down and you felt like you could never step back up. I know the quarantine can make you loopy but there is always dawn before dusk. The Way Back harbours such a challenge for a former basketball coach, Jack Cunningham.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3904 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Movies-of-2020-6.jpg\" alt=\"The Way Back Top 10 Hollywood Movies of 2020 (6)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His team was once known to make it to the playoffs when he coached his team, but after leaving his team for years, that team never made it to the playoffs. This was due to his personal reasons which weren\'t known by then (they unfold through the plot of the movie). He finds himself then in a meaningless job, suffering from alcoholism. As the title suggests, he makes his comeback and fights back against everything he was held down with, both his personal issues and that of his team.   </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Platforms:</strong> Fandango, Vudu, Prime Watch.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VzNJVSsjE-I[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>5. </b><b>Extraction</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDb rating:</strong> 6.7</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director:</strong> Sam Hargrave</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Starcast: </strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/best-movies-of-chris-hemsworth-except-mcu/\">Chris Hemsworth</a>, David Harbour, Randeep Hooda</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Extraction is one of the best indie-films on the Netflix platform, bringing us a unique and diverse cast with compelling action stories. It features Chris (Tyler) as the main protagonist (a mercenary) but also a traumatized soul whose family is taken away for reasons unknown.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3905 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Movies-of-2020-7.jpg\" alt=\"Extraction Top 10 Hollywood Movies of 2020 (7)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He is brought up on another extraction mission of the Indian crime lord\'s son, who has been abducted by his Bangladeshi counterpart, as vengeance for a botched deal.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie brings adverse consequences to the botched mission where Tyler finds his team shot down, the criminal in his pursuit, and an environment unknown for him to survive in. So, now you get it that Hollywood movies list 2020 can not be completed without this amazing action movie.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Fun Fact: </strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Russo Brothers are especially known to be among the producers of the recent Avengers: Endgame. And it is no wonder the movie is really good to watch! </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Also, one of the cast members, Sam Hargrave, is especially known for being the stunt double for Captain America.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Platforms:</strong> Netflix</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L6P3nI6VnlY[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>4. </b><b>The Devil All the Time</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDb rating:</strong> 7.1</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director:</strong> Antonio Campos.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Starcast: </strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Sebastian Stan, Tom Holland, Robert Patterson</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Devil All the Time features a psychological horror featuring an amazing star cast. It brings us to a small town where a young man named Arvin. At one point in his life, he realizes he realizes how sinful and corrupted their town has become. A preacher living a life of sins, a selfish policeman who is devoted to his own self of justice, a cameraman who hides and takes photos of people’s flaws.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3906 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Movies-of-2020-8.jpg\" alt=\"The Devil All the Time Top 10 Hollywood Movies of 2020 (8)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie is themed under the phrase, ”Some people were born so that they could be buried”. It reflects on how people have this influence to sin time and time again while they live on and get buried with their sins. This movie gives the impression of a horror film, but the irony is that it portrays in its revering way of the human soul.    </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Fun Fact: </strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The venue of the movie is actually a real town. It’s the name of the town where the author of the novel was born in. Its history lives up to the atmosphere of the movie. According to one theory, the name “Knockemstiff” came from two women who argued over a man they both liked. The preacher of that town was involved to settle the dispute whose judgment was short and to the point: ”Knock him Stiff”.   </span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Platforms:</strong> Netflix</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EIzazUv2gtI[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>3. </b><b>Tenet</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDb rating:</strong> 7.6</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director:</strong> Christopher Nolan.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Starcast: </strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> John David Washington, Robert Patterson, Elizabeth Debicki</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So let me put it out there just before I start: It’s a Chris Nolan film so you know it’ll be an epic piece of art for your home theatre. It features a secret agent who embarks on a journey to avoid the Third World War from taking place.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3907 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Movies-of-2020-9.jpg\" alt=\"Tenet Top 10 Hollywood Movies of 2020 (9)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What’s special about the film is especially that some of its scenes play in reverse. At one point, people will be shooting bullets but at another stage, there’ll be bullets being caught by guns (in reverse). Its unique concept definitely receives a lot of praise. </span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Fun Fact: </strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie pays tribute to the former masterpiece of Nolan’s Inception. The manipulation of the timeline pays tribute to the former movie’s concept, as confirmed by John David Washington himself. However, both films aren’t claimed to be sequels of one another.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Platforms:</strong> Netflix, Fandango, Vudu, Prime Watch.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LdOM0x0XDMo[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>2. </b><b>Another Round</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDb rating:</strong> 8</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director:</strong> Thomas Vinterberg.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Starcast: </strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Mad Mikkelsen, Thomas Bo Larsen, Magnus Millang</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-3908 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Movies-of-2020-10.jpg\" alt=\"Another Round Top 10 Hollywood Movies of 2020 (10)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This European movie is another highly praised film of 2020. It talks about four Swedish people, who read this research paper related to alcoholism. It discusses whether people with an alcohol content of 0.5% in their bloodstream lie a happier personal and professional life. Just to make things interesting, they put that theory to the test.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie is a comedic drama, which brings chaos and drunk comedy to the test. And in the end, people found themselves with a great comedic European film of this year.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Platforms:</strong> Apple TV, Fandango, Prime Watch.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=40X5EX6Us7c[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>1. </b><b>American Utopia</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDb rating:</strong> 8.3</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director:</strong> Spike Lee.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Starcast: </strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> David Byrne, Muaro Refusco, Chris Glarmo</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3899 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Top-10-Hollywood-Movies-of-2020-1.jpg\" alt=\"American Utopia Top 10 Hollywood Movies of 2020 (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Finally, we have at the top of this list, we have David Byrne’s ‘American Utopia’. This cinematic film is in fact a live recording of Byrne’s performance on Broadway. It features 11 musicians, who play their “American Utopia” album, on portable musical instruments. It features a simple yet exhilarating experience for all the audience in attendance and hence becomes a very enjoyable documentary as well.</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Platforms:</strong> HBO Max.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lg4hcgtjDPc[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Conclusion:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">To safely conclude, this is my list of the 10 best Hollywood movies of 2020. I hope these movies surely make your days worthwhile. Happy Binging Everyone! </span>','Top 10 Hollywood Movies of 2020 That You Can\'t Afford Miss','','publish','open','open','','top-10-hollywood-movies-of-2020-that-you-cant-afford-miss','','','2020-12-30 22:45:49','2020-12-30 17:15:49','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3896',0,'post','',0),(3919,9,'2020-12-28 12:45:45','2020-12-28 07:15:45','<h2><b>Introduction to Wonder Woman:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Let\'s start with the introduction of </span>Wonder Woman. Th<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">e past couple of years came to a realization that superhero movies were a trend worldwide (even to this day). You got Marvel and DC Comics running head to head with one another. There was even the rise of a third franchise named Variant Comics, courtesy of ‘BloodShot (2020)’. So it also came out obvious that Marvel Comics have the upper hand in this situation because of the variety of emotions they portray throughout their <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">movies</a> via their superheroes and <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-hollywood-villains-who-won-millions-of-heart/\">supervillains</a>.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4055 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/1-3.jpg\" alt=\"Wonder Woman\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">DC happens to have a better quality of superheroes but the thing that lacked the most (as people say for themselves) is that they lacked the emotions expressed through their characters. In fact, nearly all of the DC movies have this aspect lacking.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Not all hope is lost, for in fact one of the movies did manage to survive the critics and what they have to say. This brings me to Zack Snyder’s ‘Wonder Woman’ which has surpassed many expectations and many doubts before it’s release. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This article will highlight the reasons why the movie happens to stand out from all other DC Movies. It can possibly bring a comeback in the rise of DC movies as well. In fact, this also set expectations for its upcoming sequel by tomorrow. So let’s Dive In!</span>\r\n<h2>Wonder Woman Watch Trailer:</h2>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XW2E2Fnh52w[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>The Prequel:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Firstly, let’s talk about the concept. Well, it resembles Marvel\'s Captain America (the initial sequel). But it also shows her character more explicitly as compared to its counterpart. When Zeld is laid under siege, she successfully crosses No Man’s Land (an area well secured by the Germans). </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She intends to save the people held hostage and becomes more selfless, even though war does not leave many behind alive. Her selfless character led the Allied Forces to take over the crossing and defeat the enemy.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4056 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/2-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Secondly, let’s talk about the main character herself. Diana herself is a very overpowering Amazonian. But the fact that her character is flawed and is subjected to development, makes her very balanced in the movie. Not only that, time and time again she is aided by her companions at times of need, even by her affair, Steve Trevor.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Although she has an amazing feat of strength and speed, she finds herself confused in wearing human clothing. At times where she lacks human intelligence, her companions are always there to provide her with wisdom. In a universe filled with many flawed superheroes, she is without a shadow of a doubt one of a kind. Especially as a female protagonist, she is definitely unique to the DC Universe, courtesy of Synder’s directions for the movie plot.</span>\r\n<h2><b>More aspects to note of the Prequel:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Among all of the DC movies made by far, another great aspect about the movie was its mixture of emotions. At some parts of the movie, it was filled with great action sequences, along with gentle and uncanny humor over time. It managed simply debunks the myth to never bring a knife to a gunfight. It also harmonizes with the essence of thrilling adventure and rejuvenating romance. Another thing that makes sense is again her aid from her companions.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4057 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/3-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Finally (and most importantly), how many female superheroes are treated as a main character and protagonist, compared to all other superhero movies? This is an astonishing idea itself when you think about it. In fact, most of the superhero movies have mostly male protagonists with female actors as among the supporting characters or even villains.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Wonder Woman is definitely a unique movie in this aspect, where she deserves the respect that she needs from an overpowering yet stunning superhero. The movie is definitely an indication for all superhero universes that the time for uplifting female superheroes has now begun.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With all those who love to watch this movie, you should definitely find it on the Warner Bros. or even the HBO Max Platform.  </span>\r\n<h2><b>The Sequel:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With its sequel coming by tomorrow, a lot of expectations have accumulated whether the second movie will be any better than the first one. Wonder Woman 1984 will bring a whole situation for both Diana and Trevor. With human technology at new heights, time will definitely tell what is the situation from the plot. So here are some of the expectations I will briefly go through for the upcoming sequel.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4058 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/4-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First, let’s talk about the obvious; character development. First of all, we saw Diana hasn’t aged a bit at all. Given the situation around her, she has become more mature than ever. However, with the return of Steve Trevor, she now has the roles reversed with him in terms of being the role model and the guide for Steve.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As a hero, she has become more skilled than ever. She literally can swing around lightning, just like Spiderman (only making Spiderman ironically new to that web-swinging concept). In one of the fight scenes, her armor is literally gold. Clearly, she came around some relic or realization that she has more power when confronting her villainous counterpart. Secondly (and speaking of counterparts), we came around a new villain, known to be “Cheetah” (also named Barbara Ann) from the comics.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cheetah has a great history as being one of Wonder Woman’s nemesis from DC Comics. But from the trailers, we also see that the actual mastermind behind the whole plot might be Maxwell Lord. So tomorrow’s release of the sequel will definitely unfold his plans.      </span>\r\n<h2><b>My Verdict:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So what I expect about the movie is something really above my expectations. Provided all that is needed to know, I think that Wonder Woman 84 is worth the watch. With a female superhero-supervillain clash by the movie directors as a unique concept for this sequel, I think this film is a must-watch. The concept happens to also complement well with the clues we have been provided. This should definitely be something worth the watch.</span>','Wonder Woman - DC’s Shining Ray of Hope | Review','','publish','open','open','','wonder-woman-dcs-shining-ray-of-hope-review','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-hollywood-villains-who-won-millions-of-heart/','2021-01-24 09:20:42','2021-01-24 03:50:42','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=3919',0,'post','',0),(4061,1,'2020-12-28 16:47:49','2020-12-