ot trust anyone because- “</span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">There is a killer hiding among us.”</span></i>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TQkG2x3qTf4[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>5. Memories of Murder (2003) | Serial Killers Movies</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>IMDb Rating: 8.1 (136,472 votes, #176 in the top 250 movie list)</li>\r\n <li>Director: Bong Joon-Ho (Also directed Parasite, Snowpiercer)</li>\r\n <li>Star Cast: Song Kang-Ho, Kim Sang-Kyung</li>\r\n <li>Platform: Amazon Prime Video, VUDU</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4094 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/movies-featuring-Serial-Killers-6.jpg\" alt=\" Memories of Murders (2003): movies featuring Serial Killers (6)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie is based on the first known serial killer of South Korea. An anonymous man rapes and then kills his victims on rainy nights. A young detective from the capital is sent to the crime area to catch the killer. In this movie, you will notice how characters can go through significant changes due to the impact of situations.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">People came to know about Bong Joon Ho only after his immense success with Parasite. </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">But before Parasite, there was ‘Memories of Murders’. </span></i>\r\n\r\n<b>Fun Facts:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the second feature film directed by Bong Joon-ho.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0n_HQwQU8ls[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>4. Zodiac (2007) | Serial Killers Movies</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>IMDb Rating: 7.7 (460,378 votes)</li>\r\n <li>Director: David Fincher(Also Directed Fight Club, Gone Girl, The Social Network)</li>\r\n <li>Star Cast: Jake Gyllenhaal, Mark Ruffalo, Robert Downey Jr.</li>\r\n <li>Platform: Amazon Prime Video</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1863 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/8-min-5.jpg\" alt=\"Zodiac (2007)\" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is one of the best Serial Killers movies based on true stories and it is based on the true events of the Zodiac Killer. In the late 1960s, a new serial killer appeared in the history of America.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Now the name may suggest that this killer chose his victims based on their Zodiac signs but that’s not the case. Like BTK killer and Son of Sam, the Zodiac killer liked to communicate via newspaper media, and he used to post advertisements that were written in the Zodiac sign. That’s how he got his name.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Here Jake Gyllenhaal acted as a newspaper cartoonist who became obsessed with the Zodiac Killer case and went into a total detective mode. Robert Downey in the role of ‘Paul Avery’ played a sarcastic comic relief character which was really needed in a serious movie like this.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yNncHPl1UXg[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>3. Se7en (1995) | Serial Killers Movies</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>IMDb Rating: 8.6 (1,432,637 votes, #20 in top 250 list)</li>\r\n <li>Director: David Fincher</li>\r\n <li>Star Cast: Morgan Freeman, Brad Pitt, Gwyneth Paltrow, Kevin Spacey</li>\r\n <li>Platform: Netflix, Amazon Prime</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4088 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/movies-featuring-Serial-Killers9.jpg\" alt=\"featuring Serial Killers9\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Another movie by David Fincher. It seems like he has a thing for serial killers and psychopaths.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Do you know about the seven deadly sins stated in the Holy 