g on their piece of land. This film shows how powerful is the mother if she not wants to give up on her struggles.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This film had a huge star cast like Nargis Dutt, Sunil Dutt, Rajkumar, and Rajendra Kumar. Mother India was directed by Mehboob khan. This film has an IMDB rating of 8.1 as well as Rotten Tomatoes rating of 92% fresh.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OFWHKtISBrY[/embedyt]\r\n<h3>Watch Full Movie:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T1xTqCNTGT8[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>2. Do Bigha Zamin (1953)</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The musical drama film based on farming, that clarifies the roots of debt and humiliation of farmers by zamindars in early India after Independence. This film was released in 1953.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4106 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Top-10-Indian-films-based-on-farmers-4.jpg\" alt=\"Do Bigha Zamin (1953) Top 10 Indian films based on farmers (4)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie is about a poor farmer who is unable to pay his debt to zamindar. So the zamindar wants to occupy/seize his and his family\'s piece of land that is DO BIGHA ZAMEEN. So the Shamu the poor farmer works as a rickshaw puller in Calcutta(Kolkata) to earn money.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This film was directed by Bimal Roy, starring Balraj Sahni, Nirupa Roy, Jagdeep. The film has an IMDB rating of 8.4 and rotten tomatoes rating of 82%. This film shows how poor farmers survive and sometimes die due to this system of farming in this country.</span>\r\n\r\nWatch Trailer:\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZkHSIREDmyo[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>1. Foresting life (2013) | Movies on Farmers </b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Firstly you should know that This is a documentary by Aarti Shrivastava, based on the life of a man who created a man-made forest. You will see the famous farms in movies.  In Sandhbar, in a world where uncaring eco-terrorists undertake deforestation.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4107 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Top-10-Indian-films-based-on-farmers-5.jpg\" alt=\"Foresting life (2013) Top 10 Indian films based on farmers (5)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Secondly, the Story of the biggest forest in the middle of the Brahmaputra river in Assam. Only one man created that forest. The Documentary also won the National award for the best agricultural film. The film had an IMDB rating of 9. This is purely one of the best documentaries or Indian movies based on farmers that will touch your heart.</span>\r\n\r\nWatch About the Motivation of this Man:\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HkZDSqyE1do[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So, that’s a wrap on this, we hope you like the content. Do hit like, share, comment your views on this. Also, follow for more content like this. Till then Goodbye. </span>','Best Indian/Bollywood Movies on Farmers and Their Problems','','publish','open','open','','best-indian-bollywood-movies-on-farmers-and-their-problems','','','2021-01-03 21:39:45','2021-01-03 16:09:45','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=4101',0,'post','',0),(4120,13,'2021-01-23 21:59:53','2021-01-23 16:29:53','<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Oscar category ‘Best Animation Feature’ started its journey in 2002. Till then 19 animation feature films have been awarded The Academy Awards. Anime movies are oscar-winning and have always been distinguished from other <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">animated films</a> because of their unique animation, art, character design, and plot.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">We always shortlist the movies to watch from oscar-winning movies because we want the quality stuff. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">These 6 oscar-nominated anime movies were so great that they even got nominations.</span>\r\n<h2><b>6. Mirai (2018) | Oscar Anime Movies</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>IMDb Rating: 7.0</li>\r\n <li>MyAnimeList Rating: 7.33</li>\r\n <li>Director: Mamoru Hosoda (Also Directed The Girl Who Leapt Through Time, Wolf Children, The Boy, and the Beast, Summer Wars)</li>\r\n <li>Voice Artists: Rebecca Hall, Victoria Grace</li>\r\n <li>Platform: Netflix</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4281 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/oscar-nominated-anime-movies-1.jpg\" alt=\"Mirai (2018) oscar \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">It’s not easy for an only child to accept the arrival of a new sibling. That is exactly what happens to Kun. He can not stand the existence of his newborn sister at all. He, who once was the center of his parent\'s attention, now feels neglected very often. And he fully blames his sister for that. What to do then? A little bit of imagination and a little bit of time travel will solve the problem fine.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Mamoru Hosoda is known for directing beautiful anime with great animation quality. And Mirai is no doubt one of his greatest creations.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6d-lsJZgmJs[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the first non-Ghibli anime movie to get an Oscar nomination.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">‘Mirai’ also is the first anime movie to get a </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Cannes Film Festival </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">premiere. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"><strong>5. </strong></span><b>When Marnie Was There (2014) | </b><b>Oscar Anime Movies</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>IMDb Rating: 7.7</li>\r\n <li>MyAnimeList Rating: 8.12</li>\r\n <li>Director: Hiromasa Yonebayashi (Also Directed The Secret World of Arrietty), James Simone</li>\r\n <li>Voice Artists: Hailee Steinfeld, Kiernan Shipka, John C. Reilly</li>\r\n <li>Platform: HBO Max</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4282 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/oscar-nominated-anime-movies-2.jpg\" alt=\"When Marnie Was There (2014\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Anna Sasaki is sent to her relative’s home for a change due to inconvenient health conditions and there she meets a young blonde girl named Marnie who will help her to reveal her unknown origin. ‘When Marnie Was There is a coming of age story of a 12-year-old girl about accepting her painful past and searching for the drive to move forward into the future. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Since 2014, no new anime has been released by Studio Ghibli which makes it the last known film of the legendary ‘film factory’. So I suppose, it’s hard not to feel a bit of melancholy while watching this movie.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jjmrxqcQdYg[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This film is the final work of the animator Makiko Futaki due to his death in 2006. (Rest in peace)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>4. The Tale of The Princess Kaguya (2013)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>IMDb Rating: 8.0</li>\r\n <li>MyAnimeList Rating: 8.24</li>\r\n <li>Director: Isao Takahata (Also Directed Grave of the Fireflies, Only Yesterday)</li>\r\n <li>Voice Artists: Chloe Grace Moretz, James Caan</li>\r\n <li>Platform: HBO Max</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4283 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/oscar-nominated-anime-movies-3.jpg\" alt=\"The Tale of The Princess Kaguya (2013) oscar nominated anime movies (3)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This anime is based on the 10th-century folklore of Japan called ‘</span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Tale of The Bamboo Cutter</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">’, where Kaguya, a resident of the moon, is exiled to the mortal world as a punishment. </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Reminds you of Mother Kaguya from Naruto Shippuden, right?</span></i>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Kaguyahime (Hime means princess in Japanese) is a legendary and very popular entity in Japanese mythology that has appeared in many other anime (both movies and series). And director Isao Takahata manifested this myth in the most beautiful and unique way possible.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W71mtorCZDw[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The run time of this film is the longest one made by Studio Ghibli (2 hours and 17 minutes).</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">With a budget estimated at 5 billion Yen, The Tale of Princess Kaguya is </span>the most expensive feature film made in Japan to this day.</li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Sadly this is the final work of Director Isao Takahata due to his death in 2018. (Rest in peace)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>3. The Wind Rises (2013)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li>IMDb Rating: 7.8</li>\r\n <li>MyAnimeList Rating: 8.13</li>\r\n <li>Director: Hayao Miyazaki (Also Directed Nausicaa of the Valley of the Wind, My Neighbor Totoro, Princess Mononoke)</li>\r\n <li>Voice Artists: Joseph Gordon-Levitt, Emily Blunt, Stanley Tucci, John Krasinski</li>\r\n <li>Platform: HBO Max</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4284 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/oscar-n