tch?v=F8peg4ACCj0[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In 2014, she was seen playing a small but significant part in the blockbuster Bollywood film </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ek Villain</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Ankita Lokhande | Actresses From Small Screen to Bollywood</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4228 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/3.jpg\" alt=\"Ankita Lokhande\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<strong><i>Pavitra Rishta</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> fame Ankita came in Bollywood in 2019 in Kangana Ranaut’s movie </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Manikarnika: The Queen of Jhansi </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">and gained immense appreciation for her amazing portrayal of the role of Jhalkari Bai. In 2020, she was seen playing a supporting character in </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Baaghi 3</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch her in Pavitra Rishta with <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/sushant-singh-rajput-facts-journey-to-bollywood/\">Shushant Singh Rajput</a>:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i7nzDqyhlIs[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We hope to see her playing more remarkable roles in movies in the future and enlist her name permanently in the list of ‘TV stars turned into movie stars’.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Prachi Desai | Actresses From Small Screen to Bollywood</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4229 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/4.jpg\" alt=\"Prachi Desai\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Among significant movie stars who started in television, another name that pops up is Prachi Desai. She started her journey as Bani (2006-08) in the soap opera <em><strong>Kasam Se</strong></em>. Her superior acting skills helped her make a Bollywood Debut soon with </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rock On!!</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in 2008.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch her in Kasam Se:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tNtRs2LSvYY[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Since then, she has appeared in some famous Bollywood movies like </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once Upon a Time in Mumbai, Azhar, Ek Villain, Rock On 2, Bol Bacchan,</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> etc. She was also one of the celebrities who appeared in TV shows after making her Bollywood debut. She appeared in </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Kapil Sharma Show</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and soap opera </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Naagin</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> to promote her film </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Aazhar</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Shubhi Mehta | Actresses From Small Screen to Bollywood</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4230 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/5.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Shubhi is one of those Bollywood celebrities who started on reality TV. She began her career as a participant in Roadies Season 3. Her performance in the reality show grabbed attention and she was given the role of Gunjan Lakhani in the Shah Rukh starrer, an all-time favourite Bollywood movie of </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chak De India</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, which she of course played amazingly. Later, she appeared in popular films such as </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mere Khwabon mein jo aaye, Aamras.</span></i>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pdrRNa-TyWo[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><i></i><strong>Mouni Roy</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4231 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/6.jpg\" alt=\"Mouni Roy\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This ravishing beauty from West Bengal is also one of those today’s movie stars. She also started in television before appearing in any Hindi film in a major role. The iconic soap opera </span><strong><i>Kyunki Saas Bhi Kabhi Bahu Thi</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> made Mouni a known face in every Indian household. She had done significant roles in numerous soap operas including </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do <strong>Saheliyan, Devon Ke Dev…Mahadev, Naagin 1, Naagin 2, Naagin 3</strong></span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, etc.</span>\r\n<h3>Watch Her Romance in Nagin:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1qAc_BPvUgs[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With her success as a model, dancer, and actress on the small screen, she made her appearance in the song </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Naachna Aaonda Nahi</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> from the film </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tum Bin II</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (2016). In 2018, she finally made her Bollywood debut as the female lead in the sports film </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Gold</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> opposite Akshay Kumar. Then she appeared in other movies like </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">KGF Chapter 1, Romeo Akbar Walter, Made in China.</span></i>\r\n<h2><i></i><strong>Ayesha Takia</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4232 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/7.jpg\" alt=\"Ayesha Takia\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In 2004, Ayesha Takia made her Bollywood debut with </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Taarzan: The Wonder Car</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and many other films following that, which gave her popularity in the Bollywood industry. She even won the award of Filmfare Best Debut Actress after her first movie. However, little do we know that, prior to working on the big screen, she had appeared in ad films like that of </span><strong><i>Complan</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and also worked in television shows such as </span><strong><i>Disney Hours.</i></strong>\r\n<h3>Young Ayesha:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MYP2niJUO14[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>Hina Khan</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4233 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/8.jpg\" alt=\"Hina Khan\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hina Khan is a known and in fact a very famous face in Indian television. From the female lead role of Akshara to the antagonistic role of Komolika Chaubey in soap operas, from being the first runner up of Fear Factor: Khatro Ke Khiladi 8 to the runner up of Big Boss 11, Hina received lots of praise from the audience.</span>\r\n<h3>Hina Khan Romance in Ye Rishta Kya Kahalata hai:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FBXOqzNNHGo[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She has already made her Bollywood debut with the movie ‘Hacked’ in 2020. She also appeared in another movie Suhani which also released last year in Zee5. We really wish to see more of her astonishing performances on the big screen.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Sakshi Tanwar | Actresses From Small Screen to Bollywood</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4225 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/9.jpg\" alt=\"Sakshi Tanwar Actresses From Small Screen to Bollywood\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sakshi Tanwar has always been one of the favourite soap opera actresses. She has been impressing us with her performances in serials like <em><strong>Kahaani Ghar Ghar ki</strong></em> and <em><strong>Bade Acche Lagte Hai</strong></em>. In the year 2016, she made her Bollywood debut with the blockbuster movie Dangal, opposite Amir Khan.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MZBKhOaY5VE[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So, these are some inspiring journeys of Actresses From Small Screen to Bollywood. Today, when everyone speaks of nepotism and says that only certain surnames and film backgrounds can make you earn a big name in Bollywood, these are some of our favourite actresses who aspire many youngsters to dream and work hard to achieve that. Hope you like the content. For more of such interesting updates about the entertainment industry, please subscribe to <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">Tv Freak</a>.</span>','From Small Screen to Bollywood – Inspiring Journey of Some Actresses','','publish','open','open','','actresses-from-small-screen-to-bollywood','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/sushant-singh-rajput-facts-journey-to-bollywood/','2021-01-31 17:10:39','2021-01-31 11:40:39','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=4223',0,'post','',0),(4238,13,'2021-01-22 11:57:21','2021-01-22 06:27:21','<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Fantasy has always been a fundamental genre when it comes to films, literature, or any kind of art. <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/reviews/\">Filmmakers</a> have always been fascinated by fairy tales, supernatural-magical creatures, unique storylines, and the chance to manifest something enchanting, distinguished, and at the same time enjoyable to the audience. Fantasy movies make us travel to a world that is so different from ours yet the emotions are so similar to those we possess. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">In this list, I will write about the top 30 fantasy movies that cinephiles should include in their watch-lists. </span>\r\n<h2>30. Season of The Witch (2011) | Best Fantasy Movies</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 5.4</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Dominic Sena (Also Directed Swordfish, Gone in 60 Seconds)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Nicolas Cage, Ron Perlman, Christopher Lee, Claire Foy</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Max Go, DIRECTV, Cinemax Amazon Channel</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4244 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/1-1.jpg\" alt=\"Season of The Witch (2011)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Two rough Knights from the Crusades go on a mission to exorcise a witch who is held responsible for the black plague. But at the ultimate moment, they realize what they are dealing with might be more than just a witch.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie was highly inspired by the 50s movie ‘The Seventh Seal’. ‘Season of The Witch’ tells the story of brave men dealing with their own demons side by side fighting with a real one.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i6QY5LOa6MM[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Fact:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Nicolas Cage had to learn horse-riding for this movie.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>29. The League of Extraordinary Gentlemen (2003)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 5.8</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Stephen Norrington (Also Directed Blade)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Sean Connery, Naseeruddin Shah, Shane West</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> VUDU</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4245 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2-1.jpg\" alt=\"The League of Extraordinary Gentlemen (2003)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Allan Quatermain, Captain Nemo, Mina Harker, Rodney Skinner, Dorian Gray, Tom Sawyer, Dr. Henry Jekyll— think about all these great fictional characters in a room. Sounds like a party, right? In the movie ‘League of Extraordinary Gentlemen’— all these characters are gathered together as a team to fight a mysterious villain called M. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The characters of this movie itself are an ultimate fantasy for everyone. Those who like to watch team-gathering fantastic movies will definitely enjoy it.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w3lwgm7ORM8[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts: </b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Last known feature film directed by Stephen Norrington.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the final live-action and only based-on-a-comic movie by Sean Connery. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>28. The Brothers Grimm (2005) | Best Fantasy Movies</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 5.9</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Terry Gilliam (Also Directed 12 Monkeys, Brazil)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Matt Damon, Heath Ledger, Lena Headey, Monica Bellucci</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> CBS, PlutoTV</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4246 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/3-1.jpg\" alt=\"The Brothers Grimm (2005)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The great Grimm brothers who are known as the greatest fairy tale collectors in history are portrayed as con-artists in this movie. On their journey, they come to encounter a village suffering from a curse.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie is practically a combination of several Grimm Brothers stories: The Red Riding Hood, Hansel &amp; Gretel, Snow White. And watching Lena Heady playing any other role than Cersei Lannister is very refreshing.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LfXQpg5m0iI[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The whole shooting of this movie was done in the Czech Republic.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Uma Thurman was offered the role that was later played by Monica Bellucci.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Johnny Depp was first selected for the role ‘Will Grimm’. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>27. The Great Wall (2016) | Best Fantasy Movies</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 5.9</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Yimou Zhang (Also Directed House of Flying Daggers, Curse of the Golden Flower)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Matt Damon, Tian Jing, Willem Dafoe</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> FuboTV, FXNow</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4247 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/4-1.jpg\" alt=\"The Great Wall (2016)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The plot is set in China about some alien monsters attacking the citizens and eating the citizens. William (played by Matt Damon) is a mercenary warrior, who helps the state army to defeat these monsters.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Remember on the 89th Oscars, host Jimmy Kimmel made fun of Matt Demon about how he gave away the leading role of ‘Manchester by The Sea’ to his best friend’s brother, and instead, he went to work on a movie in China? Well, this is the one. The Great Wall may not be as aesthetic as </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Manchester by The Sea</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> but as a Fantasy movie, it surely counts.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=avF6GHyyk5c[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Fact:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the most expensive Chinese feature film ever made.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>26. Percy Jackson &amp; The Olympians (2010, 2013)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 5.85 (Average)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Directors: </strong>Chris Columbus (Also Directed Home Alone (1 &amp; 2), Harry Potter (1 &amp; 2), Stepmom)\r\nThor Freudenthal (Also Directed Diary of a Wimpy Kid, Hotel for Dogs)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Logan Lerman, Alexandra Daddario, Brandon T. Jackson</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Disney Plus</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4248 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/5-1.jpg\" alt=\"Percy Jackson &amp; The Olympians (2010, 2013)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">When it comes to fantasy, what can be fancier than Greek Mythology? And ‘Greek Myth in Modern Times’ is the motto of </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Percy Jackson and The Olympians</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Percy is a Demigod who was unaware of the fact. After he found out who he was, he also came to know that there were many people like him and what’s more, there is a school for Demigods! After attending the school he made a few friends and came to face many possible problems and adventures.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The combination of myth, modern technology, and the new presentation of the characters take these two movies to a new level.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rNhV8dk6W2M[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Percy Jackson &amp; The Olympians: The Lightning Thief (2010) is one of the very few movies where Sean Bean doesn\'t die or go to jail. (Poor him)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Brie Larson auditioned for the role that Alexandra Daddario played in the movies.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>25. The Sorcerer’s Apprentice (2010) | Best Fantasy Movies</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 6.1</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Jon Turteltaub (Also Directed, National Treasure (1 &amp; 2), While You Were Sleeping)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Nicolas Cage, Jay Baruchel, Teresa Palmer, Monica Bellucci</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Disney Plus</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4249 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/6-1.jpg\" alt=\"The Sorcerer’s Apprentice (2010)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">A great evil has returned from the past and only Merlin’s true progeny can defeat him. What is special about this movie is the visual effect. It’s very clean, sharp and neat. The master-student chemistry between Balthazar and Dave is one of the best parts of this movie. There is humor, action, magic, and suspense— what’s more to ask for?</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v2uV0_1C4UM[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">A song by ‘One Republic’ is played in the movie. The title is called ‘Secrets’. (It’s a very nice song. Check it out on YouTube) </span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Brie Larson auditioned for the role that Theresa Palmer played in the movie.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>24. The Golden Compass (2007) | Best Fantasy Movies</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 6.1</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Chris Weitz (Also Directed The Twilight Saga: New Moon)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Nicole Kidman, Daniel Craig, Freddie Highmore, Ian McKellen, Eva Green, Christopher Lee</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> HBO Max, Hoopla</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4250 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/7-1.jpg\" alt=\"The Golden Compass (2007)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Think of a fantasy world where a person’s partial inner self exists in a form of an animal companion. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">‘The Golden Compass’ is no doubt one of the top fantasy movies of the 21st century. What is special about this movie is the plot is way darker and unpredictable than expected considering a child as the main protagonist. Also, the visual effects were awesome. It will give you the ultimate vibe of a fantasy movie.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LHYoOGfBObU[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The movie won the Academy Award for Best Achievement in Visual Effects in 2008</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">It was also nominated in the category of Best Achievement in Art Direction.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Fact:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Christopher Lee had only one line delivery in the entire movie.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>23. Rise of the Guardians (2012)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.3</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Peter Ramsey (Also Directed Spider-Man: Into the Spider-Verse)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Voice Artists:</strong> Chris Pine, Alec Baldwin, Jude Law, Isla Fisher, Hugh Jackman</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> HBO Max, HBO Now</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4251 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/8-1.jpg\" alt=\"Rise of the Guardians (2012)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Time for an animated feature. Rise of the Guardians gathers around all the guardians from our childhood bedtime stories— Santa Claus, Sandman, Toothfairy, Easter Bunny. Jack Frost is a trouble-some fellow (spreading ice here and there, making roads all slippery), but he is also chosen by the Moon Goddess as a guardian. Now, a new bad guy named Pitch Black enters the story with a lot of negative energy to make little children forget about these helpful guardians by spreading fear. So the Team Guardian must fight back and protect innocent children all around the world overcome their own fears.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aPLiBxhoug0[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts: </b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Roger Ebert wrote a review for this movie, and he rated it good. It was also his last Christmas movie review. (Rest in peace)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the last DreamWorks movie that was distributed by Paramount.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>22. Dorian Gray (2009)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 6.3</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Oliver Parker (Also Directed Johnny English Reborn)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Ben Barnes, Colin Firth, Rebecca Hall</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> FMovies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4252 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/9-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Based on the classic novel by Oscar Wilde, Dorian Gray is the story of a man named Dorian Gray who hides his age, inner demons, and ugly deeds in his self-portrait. The original sin is flowing through the human blood, given the perfect opportunity, a man can turn into the ugliest being on the inside no matter how handsome he looks on the outside.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YVbdd8oOwOY[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Ben Barnes was an excellent choice for this movie. With his handsome looks and good acting, he took this movie to another dimension.</span>\r\n<h2>21. Alice in Wonderland (2010)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 6.4</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Tim Burton (Also Directed Edward Scissorhands, Ed Wood, Charlie and the Chocolate Factory)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Johnny Depp, Mia Wasikowska, Helena Bonham Carter, Anne Hathaway</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Disney Plus</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4253 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/10.jpg\" alt=\"Alice in Wonderland (2010)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">It is impossible to create a list of fantasy movies and not include Alice in Wonderland in it. The name of this itself has now been a term for the genre of fiction where a person suddenly lands on a parallel or fantasy world. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">A movie directed by a Fantasy Master, Alice in Wonderland adds something more than the book. The movie is scary and unpredictable sometimes which makes it a must-watch for fantasy lovers.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9POCgSRVvf0[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The movie won two Oscars. One in the category of Best Achievement in Costume Design and the other in the category of Best Achievement in Art Direction.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">It was also nominated in the category of Best Achievement in Visual Effects.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Fact:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the 7th work of the Burton-Depp duo.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>20. The Spiderwick Chronicles (2008)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 6.5</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Mark Waters (Also Directed Freaky Friday, Mean Girls, Ghosts of Girlfriends Past)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Freddie Highmore, Seth Rogen</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Netflix</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4258 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/1-2.jpg\" alt=\"The Spiderwick Chronicles (2008)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">When the Grace family moves to an old house after Mr. and Mrs. Grace goes through a very bitter divorce, the kids learn that they are not alone in the house. And the forest behind the house is not an ordinary forest either. Then they discover a century-old secret about fairies, goblins, and many other magical creatures. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">‘The Spiderwick Chronicles’ is an underdog in the genre when it comes to fantasy movies. So the movie watchers will surely find a hidden gem watching this movie.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I99bp9SOhcQ[/embedyt]\r\n<h2>19. The Lovely Bones (2009)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 6.7</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Peter Jackson (Also Directed Lord of the Rings, King Kong)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Mark Wahlberg, Rachel Weisz, Susan Sarandon, Saoirse Ronan, Stanley Tucci</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Max Go, Cinemax Amazon Channel</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4259 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2-2.jpg\" alt=\"The Lovely Bones (2009)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Susie Salmon (played by Saoirse Ronan) was 14 years old when she was killed by a pedophilic serial killer. Now Susie is stuck in purgatory and can’t go to heaven because she feels like she has some unfinished business— that she can’t do anything about her father’s pain, that she never had her first kiss, and that her killer is still out loose.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">I must say, The Lovely Bones is a very unique movie on this list. Because other than fantasy, this movie also falls into the genre of Thriller, Drama, and Mystery. It’s also a big-all-star-cast movie. Most of the main characters are all Oscar-nominated actors and actresses.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s9PrQmcV81Y[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Stanley Tucci was nominated for The Best Actor in A Supporting Role in the Oscar for this movie.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Best Fantasy Movies | Fun Fact:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Ryan Gosling is selected for the role that Mark Wahlberg played in the movie. Ryan bailed just three days before the movie saying he was too young to play the father of a teenage girl. He was 26 at that moment. Wahlberg was finalized for the movie just the day before the shooting started.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>18. Miss Peregrine\'s Home for Peculiar Children (2016)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 6.7</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Tim Burton</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Asa Butterfield, Samuel L. Jackson, Eva Green</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> FXNow, Sling TV</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4260 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/3-2.jpg\" alt=\"Miss Peregrine\'s Home for Peculiar Children (2016)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Another movie by the Fantasy Master Tim Burton. Miss Peregrine\'s Home for Peculiar Children is based on the novel by Ransom Riggs. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Miss Peregrine (Played by Eva Adams) runs a home for children who have unique features and abilities. When Jacob\'s (Asa Butterfield, you definitely know him from Sex Education as Otis or from the movie The Boy in Striped Pajama) grandfather dies mysteriously, he starts to find connections between the Home and the sorrowful incident. With time traveling, a lot of monster-slayings, and Samuel L. Jackson as the villain, this movie is undoubtedly one of the best fantasy movies all the time.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tV_IhWE4LP0[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Fact:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Timothee Chalamet auditioned for the role that Asa Butterfield played in the movie.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>17. A Series of Unfortunate Events (2004)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 6.8</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Brad Silberling (Also Directed Casper, City of Angels)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Jim Carrey, Jude Law, Meryl Streep</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Netflix</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4261 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/4-2.jpg\" alt=\"A Series of Unfortunate Events (2004) \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Baudelaire siblings— what unfortunate kids! First, their parents are burnt to death along their house and then the foster parents they are being sent to are dying one by one as well. Who is behind this misfortune? It is the kids or someone else?</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">‘A Series of Unfortunate Journey’ is a dark fantasy playing with the fortunes and misfortunes of three siblings. With Jud Law’s amazing narration and Jim Carry’s amazing performance, this is one of the greatest movies in the fantasy genre.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4ErlhM1NaZA[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Best Fantasy Movies | Awards and Nominations: </b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Won the Oscar for Best Achievement in Make-up in 2005.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie was also nominated for Best Achievement in Art Direction, Best Achievement in Costume Design, Best Achievement in Music Written for Motion Pictures, Original Score.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the First Nickelodeon movie to ever win an Oscar.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Helena Bonham Carter and Dustin Hoffman made uncredited appearances in the movie.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>16. The Mummy (1999)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.0</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Stephen Sommers (Also Directed Van Helsing, G.I. Joe: The Rise of Cobra)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Brendan Fraser, Rachel Weisz</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Redbox</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4262 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/5-2.jpg\" alt=\"The Mummy (1999)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Now comes the fantasy with the ultimate adventure. A group of explorers awakens an ancient mummy while digging up archaeological treasures from the Pyramid. This movie is full of humor, adventure, drama, and suspense which will make your time worth watching this movie. Rachel Weisz was amazing in this movie by the way.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f7oKxlaUBac[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie was nominated for one Oscar in the category of Best Sound.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The movie was not shot in Egypt.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the first movie to be shown on the WB TV channel.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>15. Maleficent (2014)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.0</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Robert Stromberg</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Angelina Jolie, Elle Fanning</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Sling TV</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4263 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/6-2.jpg\" alt=\"Maleficent (2014)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Now is time for a Disney Fairy tale. ‘Maleficent’ is one of those few fantastic movies which are named after its villains. But truly speaking, Maleficent is not a villain at all. She is just a broken hero. The betrayal of a loved one at a very young age made Maleficent hate humans. But when it comes to a human baby who she, herself, has cursed to eternal sleep, motherly feelings can not stay away for very long.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">In this movie, a fairy tale villain has been portrayed in a way the world has never seen before. With the help of amazing costume design and make-up, Angelina Jolie’s acting looked so magnificent and enchanting that the movie won the critic\'s hearts. This is nonetheless one of the best Hollywood movies of that decade.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EYemY3xFsB4[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Maleficent was nominated in the category of Best Achievement in Costume Design at the 2005 Oscars.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Best Fantasy Movies | Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Lana Del Ray sang the OST for this movie.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is Angelia Jolie’s first Disney movie.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>14. Jumanji (1995)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.0</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Joe Johnston (Also Directed Honey, I Shrunk the Kids, Captain America: The First Avenger)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Robin Williams, Kirsten Dunst</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> FuboTV, Syfy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4264 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/7-2.jpg\" alt=\"Jumanji (1995)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Yes, there have already been two successful sequels and a prequel already, but nothing hits the heart harder than the original 1995s Jumanji. The 90s kids will surely be hit with a surge of nostalgia because this was a part of our childhood where there was no internet or Facebook.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">With Robin Williams as the central character, this movie is a classic fantasy movie. Though a few other actors were considered for the role, Robin Williams was specially chosen because of his power to improvise. And he absolutely stole the whole show with his amazing performance.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GrlMYIYt-SI[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Scarlett Johansson auditioned for the role that Kirsten Dunst played in the movie. Kristen Dunst later played the role of Mary Jane Watson in the classic Spider-man.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">A prequel of this movie is coming this January 2021. In this movie, it will be shown exactly where this Jumanji game came from all the adventures of the very first players.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>13. Sleepy Hollow (1999)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.3</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Tim Burton</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Johnny Depp, Christina Ricci, Michael Gambon, Christopher Walken, Christopher Lee</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Amazon Prime Video, FuboTV</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4265 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/8-2.jpg\" alt=\"Sleepy Hollow (1999) Fantasy movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">A young policeman is sent to the village where a headless horseman appears to look for his head and cuts down the heads of the townsfolk instead and takes them with him. (Sounds like a ghost in crisis)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Sleepy Hollow is one of the many great movies done by the Depp-Burton duo. This may be a horror fantasy movie but it’ll certainly give you the vibe of a detective movie too. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Before I first watched this movie, I had only seen Depp’s Pirates of the Caribbean before. So without the beard I hardly recognized him and that was really the first time I realized how handsome Johnny Depp is.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6RsKwn_Je1k[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Won the Best Art Direction-Set Decoration at the Oscars 2000.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The movie was also nominated in the categories of Best Cinematography and Best Costume Design.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Christopher Walken has no line in this movie.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Christopher Lee\'s only scene in this movie is before the opening credit.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>12. Stardust (2007)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.6</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Matthew Vaughn (Also Directed Kick-Ass, Kingsman(1 &amp; 2), X-Men: First Class)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Peter O\'Toole, Michelle Pfeiffer, Robert De Niro, Mark Strong</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> FlixFling, Netflix</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4266 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/9-2.jpg\" alt=\"Fantasy movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">A young man in search of his mother, a kingdom in search of an heirloom, a witch in search of a fallen star. And all these people are bound to meet at a final destination. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The plot of this movie is very exciting. The presentation, acting, and action scenes are marvelous. As always, Neil Gaiman’s writing left a timeless effect on this movie.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DbfLk8tfkQQ[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The book this movie is based on is written by Neil Gaiman.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Ian McKellen gave the narrating voice.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Henry Cavill and Ben Barnes have credited appearances in this movie.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>11. The Secret World of Arrietty (2010)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.6</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Hiromasa Yonebayashi (Also Directed When Marnie Was There)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Voice Artists:</strong> Saoirse Ronan, Tom Holland, Olivia Colman, Mark Strong</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> HBO Max</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4267 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/10-1.jpg\" alt=\"The Secret World of Arrietty (2010) Fantasy movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Borrowers’ happen to be four-inch-tall people of a fictional species who live secretly in normal people’s homes. Arriety is the only child of the Borrower Clock family. A girl from an endangered species and a normal kid who has been sick from his childhood bond overcoming their loneliness and fear.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The plot of this movie is really simple yet beautiful. The art and animation of this anime movie are as amazing as all other Ghibli movies. It’s a <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/hollywoods-top-10-feel-good-movies-you-must-watch/\">feel-good movie</a> with a fantastic ending.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VlMe7PavaRQ[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is Director Hiromasa Yonebayashi\'s debut film. He also happens to be the youngest director to ever work for Studio Ghibli.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>10. How to Train Your Dragon (2010)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 8.1</li>\r\n <li><strong>Directors:</strong> Dean DeBlois (Also Directed Lilo &amp; Stitch), Chris Sanders (Also Directed The Croods, The Call of the Wild)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Jay Baruchel, Gerard Butler, America Ferrera, Jonah Hill</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Amazon Prime Video</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4269 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/1-3.jpg\" alt=\"How to Train Your Dragon (2010) Fantasy movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Time for another animated feature. Let’s dive into a world where dragons and humans live under the same sky. Berk is a village that is frequently attacked by dragons. As a result, it has given birth to a culture of producing Dragon Slayer. But Hiccup is a young boy who can empathize with dragons. But this virtue of his will leads him to many secrets and dangers.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie has two other sequels and a spin-off series.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HqMYHjlBMUY[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This animated feature was nominated in two categories in the 2011 Oscars. The categories are Best Animated Feature Film and Best Achievement in Music Written for Motion Pictures (Original Score).</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the first animated feature film of DreamWorks to have a teenage boy as the protagonist. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>9. To the Forest of Firefly Lights (2011)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.9</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Takahiro Omori (Also Directed Durarara!!, Natsume\'s Book of Friends)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Voice Artists:</strong> Kouki Uchiyama, Ayane Sakura</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> 9Anime, GogoAnime</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4270 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2-3.jpg\" alt=\"To the Forest of Firefly Lights (2011)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This title is probably the most unheard one on this list. Anime watchers may know this movie but ‘To The Forest of Firefly Lights’ is an underdog in the anime community as well.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Hotaru was just a child when she first met Gin in the spirit forest. But Gin has a curse. He can not be touched by humans or else he will disappear from this world. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie is only 45 minutes long but it’s worth every second.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TFvezWFnaHw[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Fact:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">There is an AMV(Anime Music Video) on YouTube of this anime using the song ‘You can be King again’. That video has over 136 million views.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>8. The Neverending Story (1984)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.4</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Wolfgang Petersen (Also Directed Das Boot, Air Force One, Troy)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Barret Oliver, Noah Hathaway</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> HBO Max</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4271 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/3-3.jpg\" alt=\"The Neverending Story (1984)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">A lonely boy dives into the world of Fantasy while reading a book. (Well, they do say books are man’s best friend...) </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Unlike many mainstream fantasy movies, the main villain of this movie is not a demon, a dragon, or an evil witch. It’s the emptiness of the heart.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">‘The NeverEnding Story’ beholds a beloved novel and exhibits the warm kind nature of a child’s imagination.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UeFni9dOv7c[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<b>Fun Fact:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the first film directed by director Wolfgang Petersen in the English Language.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>7. Spirited Away (2001)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 8.6</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Hayao Miyazaki (Also Directed Nausicaa of the Valley of the Wind, My Neighbor Totoro, Princess Mononoke)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Voice Artist:</strong> Daveigh Chase, Jason Marsden, Suzanne Pleshette</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> HBO Max</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4272 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/4-3.jpg\" alt=\"Spirited Away (2001)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">When Chihiro’s parents unintentionally interfered in a spirit village, they were turned into pigs as a punishment. Now, Chihiro must do everything in her power to turn them back to normal.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Trust me, this is not half of the story. Spirited Away is a mystery gift box, you don’t know what to expect until you watch the whole movie. And it is nonetheless one of the best animated movies ever.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ByXuk9QqQkk[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<b>Awards and Nominations:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Won the Oscars for The Best Animated Feature in 2003.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Fun Facts:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">It was the highest-grossing movie in Japan until the Demon Slayer movie.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Miyazaki Hayao did not attend the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/5-great-movies-that-have-never-won-an-oscar-to-this-day/\">Oscars</a> in 2003 as a protest against the Iraq War. The presenter Cameron Diaz accepted the award on his behalf.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The first foreign animated movie to win an Oscar. Also, the only anime movie to win an Oscar.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Hayao Miyazaki made this film without any script.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>6. The Chronicles of Narnia Trilogy (2005, 2008, 2010)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 6.57 (Average)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Directors:</strong>\r\nAndrew Adamson (Also Directed Shrek)\r\nMichael Apted (Also Directed Rome)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Tilda Swinton, James McAvoy, Ben Barnes, Peter Dinklage</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Disney Plus</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4273 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/5-3.jpg\" alt=\"The Chronicles of Narnia Trilogy (2005, 2008, 2010)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Based on one of the all-time classic book series Chronicles of Narnia contains the 3 most fantastic movies in the fantasy genre. The adventure of four siblings in a strange world called Narnia, a big brave talking lion named Aslan, and a lot of magical creatures— Chronicles of Narnia is what you call an absolute Fantasy Universe. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">For the fanbase of this trilogy, a sequel and a prequel are on the way. </span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XqCJwpBxXwo[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Best Fantasy Movies | Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The trilogy has a total of 3 nominations and 1 Oscar win.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Liam Neeson voiced Aslan.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The book The Lion, The Witch, and The Wardrobe was dedicated to C.S. Lewis\'s God-Daughter Lucy.  </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>5. Wizard of Oz (1939)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 8.0</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Victor Fleming (Also Directed Gone with the Wind)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Judy Garland, Frank Morgan, Ray Bolger</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> HBO Max, DIRECTV</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4274 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/6-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Wizard of Oz is one of the best all-time classic movies. This movie is on the favorite list of many movie critics, filmmakers, actors, and actresses. It is a movie that people of all ages can see and enjoy the same. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Dorothy Gale and her dog get swept away by a tornado, and they land on a strange land of wizards. The story develops with fun adventures of Dorothy. This movie is a lot more than just a musical. The amazing cast and crew, set design, every small detail of this movie make it obvious how ‘Wizard of Oz’ can still hold appeal after 80 years since its release.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VNugTWHnSfw[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:    </b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The movie won Oscars in the category of Best Music, Original Song and Best Music, Original Score.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The movie was also nominated for four other categories including Best Picture.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Oscar-winning original song ‘Somewhere Over the Rainbow’ was almost cut off from the movie.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">There was a tributary event at the 86th Oscars celebrating the 75th anniversary of this movie. P!nk sang the song ‘Over The Rainbow’. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>4. The Hobbit Trilogy (2012, 2013, 2014)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.67 (Average)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Peter Jackson</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Ian McKellen, Martin Freeman, Richard Armitage</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform: </strong>HBO Max</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4275 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/7-3.jpg\" alt=\"The Hobbit Trilogy (2012, 2013, 2014)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The story before Lord of the Rings…</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">But aside from that let’s just say it’s the story of a calm peace-loving hobbit fellow who turned into all adventurous and brave with the influence of the right friends. It is a story of a journey that you will never forget.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YspUF04g1u4[/embedyt]   </span>\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nomination:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The trilogy has a total of 7 Oscar nominations but 0 wins.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Best Fantasy Movies | Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Benedict Cumberbatch voiced Smaug the Dragon. Another Sherlock duo!</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Eddie Redmayne auditioned for the role of Bilbo Baggins but failed terribly.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The actor (Lee Pace) who plays Legolas’s (Played by Orlando Bloom) father is actually 2 years younger than Bloom.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>3. Pan’s Labyrinth (2006)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 8.2</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Guillermo del Toro (Also Directed Blade II, The Shape of Water, Pacific Rim)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Ivana Baquero, Ariadna Gil, Sergi López</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Netflix</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4276 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/8-3.jpg\" alt=\"Pan’s Labyrinth (2006)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Time for a Spanish Fantasy. Pan’s Labyrinth is the greatest non-Hollywood fantasy movie ever. A fantasy of a young girl in wartime— Pan Labyrinth is visually outstanding with an enchanting storyline.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Guillermo del Toro gave his whole dedication and effort to this movie. He gave up his salary, refused all the Hollywood producers who offered him twice the budget, just to get this movie recognized. He finally created a labyrinth that the audiences won’t want to leave.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AcHasH-nLhU[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations: </b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The movie won 3 Oscars in the categories of Best Achievement in Cinematography, Best Achievement in Art Direction, Best Achievement in Makeup.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">It was also nominated in the categories of Best Writing (Original Screenplay), Best Achievement in Music Written for Motion Pictures (Original Score), Best Foreign Language Film of the Year(Mexico).</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie got 22 minutes-long standing ovation at Cannes.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>2. Harry Potter Film Series (2001-2011)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.69 (Average)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Directors:</strong>\r\nChris Columbus\r\nAlfonso Cuaron (Also Directed Y Tu Mamá También, Children of Men, Roma, Gravity)\r\nDavid Yates (Also Directed The Legend of Tarzan)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Daniel Radcliffe, Rupert Grint, Emma Watson, Maggie Smith, Alan Rickman</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Sling TV</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4277 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/9-3.jpg\" alt=\"Harry Potter Film Series (2001-2011)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Now, what to say about this franchise that has not already been said? Harry Potter is a film series consisting of eight fantastic movies. Based on one of the all-time best-selling novel series, Harry Potter is also very successful when it comes to the movies. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This film series is about an unfortunate orphan young boy Harry Potter, his wizardry school and two best friends, and many other people. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Harry Potter also has one of the biggest movie fanbases who like to call themselves ‘Potterheads’. It’s a fantasy world that every child, teenager, and adult wants to visit.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j4COmJN6GZM[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and nominations: </b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This film series has a total of 12 Oscar nominations but 0 wins.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Sir Ian Mckellen was offered the role of Dumbledore after Sir Richard Harris passed away. He was at the time playing Gandalf in LOTR. He refused to take the role because he thought it would be too much pressure on him to play two legendary characters one after another.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Ron Weasley and Rupert Grint both are arachnophobic. (Count me too.)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The actors who played Mad-eye Moody and Bill Weasley are father and son in real life.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>1. Lord of The Rings Trilogy (2001, 2002, 2003)</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 8.8 (Average)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Peter Jackson</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Elijah Wood, Ian McKellen, Christopher Lee, Orlando Bloom, Sean Bean, Cate Blanchett</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Hulu, HBO Max</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4278 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/10-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Yes, number one in our list is none other than the LOTR trilogy, one of the most successful trilogies in history, and of course, the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/some-of-the-best-trilogies-movies-worth-watching/\">best fantasy trilogy</a> ever existed. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Peter Jackson made this film with so much care and attention and honestly speaking, the filmmaking of this trilogy is way ahead of its time.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">With a huge cast and a huge script to cover, it takes a mastermind to pull off a trilogy like this.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Lord of the Rings provides us with a pure visual richness, stunning acting skills of the star cast, and the art of story-telling.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y2rYRu8UW8M[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Best Fantasy Movies | Awards and Nominations: </b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This trilogy has a total of 17 wins out of a total of 30 nominations.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Best Fantasy Movies | Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">I am pretty sure most people know it, Lord of the Rings: Return of the Kings is one of the three movies to win the most Oscars in history. What’s more, the movie was nominated in 11 categories and won every one of them.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Most Oscar-winning Movie Franchisee in history.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">All three movies are in the top 15 in the IMDb list of top 250 movies.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Sir Christopher Lee met Sir J. R. R. Tolkien(1892-1973) in real life!</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>Conclusion:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Few of the titles of this movie may seem very underdog. That’s because they are very underrated. But I can assure you, the movies are worth your time.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Please share your opinion about this list in the comment box.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Happy Watching!!! <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">The Tv Freak</a></span>','List of Top 30 Best Fantasy Movies for Cinephiles','','publish','open','open','','list-of-top-30-best-fantasy-movies-for-cinephiles','','https://www.thetvfreak.com/hollywoods-top-10-feel-good-movies-you-must-watch/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/5-great-movies-that-have-never-won-an-oscar-to-this-day/','2021-10-05 14:57:34','2021-10-05 09:27:34','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=4238',0,'post','',0),(4296,12,'2021-02-04 07:56:07','2021-02-04 02:26:07','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Films always need to have good stories to make them worth watching. But, more than the story itself, which creates a lasting impact on the audience in the making of a film. A Hindi film makes a remarkable mark in Bollywood and is remembered for years only when it can create a grip over the audience by its powerful making. It solely depends on the filmmaker, aka, the film Directors in Bollywood that how he makes and evolves the movie productions.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So, can we say who is the no 1 director in India or who is the most successful director in Bollywood? Bollywood is a treasure house of movie directors with great potential. We definitely cannot consider only one of them as the best Hindi film director. Some directors have slain in a certain genre while others may have earned fame by making films in some other genre. Some have made the best dark movies while some have impressed us with periodic dramas,</span><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/list-of-bollywood-biopics-and-upcoming-biopic-movies-in-2020/\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">biopics</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">,</span> <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-sports-movies-based-on-real-life-stories/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">sports</span> </a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">films, and so on.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hence the list of the best directors in Bollywood is long. Here Tv Freak presents to you some of our favourite and best movie directors in India:</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1. </span><b>Yash Chopra | Best Directors in Bollywood</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Let’s go a few decades back when the founding chairman of Yashraj films, Yash Chopra was a famous director in Bollywood. His films were the heart of the Hindi film industry.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4795 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/1-4.jpg\" alt=\"director - Yash Chopra\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His most loveable films which are even today appreciated by young generations include </span><b><i>Waqt</i></b><b> (1965), </b><b><i>Ittefaq</i></b><b> (1969), </b><b><i>Deewar</i></b><b> (1975), </b><b><i>Silsila</i></b><b> (1981), </b><b><i>Chandn</i></b><b>i (1989), </b><b><i>Lamhe</i></b><b> (1991), </b><b><i>Darr</i></b><b> (1993), </b><b><i>Dil To Pagal Hai </i></b><b>(19797), </b><b><i>Veer Zaara</i></b><b> (2004), </b><b><i>Jab Tak Hai Jaan</i></b><b> (2012)</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Being a 2000s kid in whose era love is all about right-swiping, </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Veer</span></i> <i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Zaara</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> will always be a personal favourite of mine for the tragic love story it shows and leaves the audience teary-eyed.</span>\r\n<h3>Amazing Veer Zaara Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OSaVImLnnsw[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">From illegitimacy to social drama, from musical dramas to extramarital affairs, from psychological thrillers to heart-warming romance, various fascinating and engrossing topics and genres have been covered by Yash Ji in his movies. This great filmmaker left us in the year 2012. But even today Bollywood, as well as the audience, never fails to honour him because of his lifetime precious contributions to Indian cinema.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2. </span><b>Sanjay Leela Bhansali</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4796 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/2-4.jpg\" alt=\"sanjay leela bhansali\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Winner of 11 Filmfare awards, Sanjay Leela Bhansali has given many superhits since the 1990s. But his two back-to-back award-winning blockbuster period films, </span><b><i>Bajirao</i></b> <b><i>Mastani</i></b><b> (2015) </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">and </span><b><i>Padmavat</i></b><b> (2018)</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, established him as one of the greatest movie directors all the time.</span>\r\n<h3>Amazing Scene of <b><i>Bajirao</i></b> <b><i>Mastani</i></b><b> (2015)</b>:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BSRUv2EyHrs[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bhansali used to work with Viru Vinod Chopra at the starting point of his career. His directorial debut was the 1996’s musical drama film </span><b><i>Khamoshi: The</i></b> <b><i>Musical</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> which despite being commercially flop earned critical acclamation. After that, he didn’t look back.</span>\r\n<h3>Devdar Romantic Scene:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QfTJoTZnzDI[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Some of his best works as a director include </span><b><i>Hum</i></b> <b><i>Dil</i></b> <b><i>De</i></b> <b><i>Chuuke</i></b> <b><i>Sanam, Devdas, Black, Saawariya, Golliyon</i></b> <b><i>Ki</i></b> <b><i>Rasleela</i></b> <b><i>Ram-Leela</i></b><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> His last film </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Padmavaat</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> which got severe backlashes and protests from Karni Sena and had a delayed-release earned 30 million dollars just within the first 4 days after release.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">3. </span><b>Rajkumar Hirani | </b>Best Directors in Bollywood</h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4797 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/3-4.jpg\" alt=\"Rajkumar hirani \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">According to a 2020 report, Rajkumar Hirani is still the richest director in Bollywood. Since his first film as a director, </span><b><i>Munna</i></b> <b><i>Bhai</i></b> <b><i>MBBS</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, his films have been blockbusters one after another. </span><b><i>Lage</i></b> <b><i>Raho</i></b> <b><i>Munna</i></b> <b><i>Bhai, 3</i></b> <b><i>idiots, PK, Sanju</i></b> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">are his works and in fact, his best works as a director.</span>\r\n<h3>Funny Moment in Munna Bhai MBBS:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PVyYGMa-dDo[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sanju</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in 2018 has been the 2nd highest-grossing film of the year after </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Padmavat</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. And </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">PK</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> has also beaten all box office records of 2014 and has earned the most that year. The list of his directed movies is not very long. Definitely, the director prefers quality over quantity.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">4. </span><b>Anurag Basu</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With his latest release of Ludo in November 2020, Anurag Basu has stolen our hearts once again. One of the best movie directors in India, Basu made his directorial debut with the John Abraham starrer </span><b><i>Saya</i></b><b> in 2003</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4798 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/4-4.jpg\" alt=\"Best Directors in Bollywood and Their Successful Movies of All Time Anurag Basu\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Since 2006 he has been making some of the best Hindi movies of all time, which have been both commercially as well as critically acclaimed. He is the one who launched today’s superstar Kangana Ranaut in his Bollywood movie </span><b><i>Gangster</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His 2012 release, </span><b><i>Barfi</i></b><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">!</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> can be called a treasure of Indian cinema and was even nominated for Oscar as India’s entry in the category of ‘Best Foreign Language film’. It won several awards in various categories including best film, best director, best cinematography, most entertaining director, most entertaining romantic film, and what not!</span>\r\n\r\nMost Emotional Touching Scene:\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xYCSOR0G53o[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Other notable films of Anurag Basu include </span><b><i>Kites, Life</i></b> <b><i>in</i></b> <b><i>a</i></b> <b><i>Metro</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. His 2017 film, </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jagga</span></i> <i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jasoos</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> was though a commercial flop it didn’t deserve to be so for its amazing making, cinematography, concept, and some brilliant performances by actors like Ranbir Kapoor, Katrina Kaif, Saswata Chaterjee.</span>\r\n<h3>Irfan Khan in Life in a Metro:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jz59GD8UW-M[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Da24I3IDnuM[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">5. </span><b>Rohit Shetty | Best Directors in Bollywood</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4799 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/5-4.jpg\" alt=\"Best Directors in Bollywood and Their Successful Movies of All Time Rohit Shetty\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Speaking of commercial Bollywood movies, the name that first comes to our mind is Rohit Shetty. He is undoubtedly the most successful and best Bollywood film director in the commercial action genre.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the case of most of his movies, what sticks the audience’s eyes to the screen is the mind-blowing dramatic action sequences. He has done several successful commercial movies with actors like Shah Rukh Khan, Ranvir Singh, Ajay Devgan.</span>\r\n<h3>Golmal Comedy Scene:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HloV55ttZqA[/embedyt]\r\n<h3>Full Movie:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_78eG9sB6vo[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Shetty’s most successful works include the </span><b><i>Golmal</i></b> <b><i>series, Singham, Chennai</i></b> <b><i>Express, Simba, Singham</i></b> <b><i>Returns,</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> etc. </span><b><i>Golmaal  Again</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> won the Zee Cine Best Film (Jury’s choice) award while </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chennai</span></i> <i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Express</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in 2013 also won a Best Film Award.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CL9ISdfZifk[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His latest directed film </span><b><i>Sooryavanshi</i></b> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">starring Akshay Kumar and Katrina Kaif was set to release in 2020 but due to the pandemic scenario, its release was postponed. It will now come up in theatres very soon. Let\'s keep our fingers crossed and wait eagerly for another action-packed Hindi film!</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">6. </span><b>Anurag Kashyap</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-4800 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/6-4.jpg\" alt=\"Best Directors in Bollywood and Their Successful Movies of All Time Anurag Kashyap\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of the gifted but underrated and best Hindi film directors Bollywood has right now is Anurag Kashyap. He has been entertaining us with his talents for years.</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Not at all hailing from a film background</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, Kashyap turned into film making only when he attended a film festival in 1993 and watched </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bicycle</span></i> <i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Thieves</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (1948).</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His first released movie, </span><b><i>Black</i></b> <b><i>Friday</i></b><b> (2007)</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, which was a political film about the occurrence 1993 Bombay bombings though didn’t receive much commercial success, gained a critical appreciation and today has an IMDB rating of 8.5. </span><b><i>Dev. D</i></b><b> (2009)</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> was his first commercial success.</span>\r\n<h3>Gangs of Wasseypur by Best Directors in Bollywood</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6OIGYTcVDjs[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400