:08','2021-02-11 07:33:08','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of the most important categories in any film award is undoubtedly the Best Director. The Director is what is considered to be the heart of a movie. With his/her direction a movie takes the form of art. A great director can even make a movie timeless. It is the vision and guidance offered by a director that makes every moment of a movie worth watching. So let\'s take a look at the Golden Globe Nominations for Best Director 2021.</span>\r\n<h2><b>5. David Fincher | Best Director nominations</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>Nominated For</strong>: Mank(2020)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast</strong>: Gary Oldman, Amanda Seyfried, Lily Collins</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform</strong>: Netflix</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5234 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Golden-Globe-Awards-Nominees-Best-Director-1.jpg\" alt=\"2021 Golden Globe Awards Nominees Best Director\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">David Fincher is a two-time Oscar-nominated director and when it comes to psycho-thrillers, it will not be exaggerating if I say, he is an auteur. His directorial debut was by the movie Alien³. Before that, he has directed countless music videos. His first breakthrough was by the movie Se7en which starred Brad Pitt, Morgan Freeman, Kevin Spacey, and <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/5-most-loved-movies-of-gwyneth-paltrow-shakespeare-in-love/\">Gwyneth Paltrow.</a></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mank is the 11th and the latest feature film directed by David Fincher. The script of this film was written by his late father Jack Fincher. It is a biographical film about the life of Herman J. Mankiewicz.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As I have mentioned before, psycho-thrillers are kind of his trademark, Mank as a drama-comedy biography is a very exceptional movie in his career and which he has pulled off smoothly with professionality and grace.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He is also the only veteran director in Best Director Nomination for Golden Globe Awards 2021.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">David Fincher has four previous Golden Globe nominations and one win in the category of Best Director.</span>\r\n<h3>Mank (2020) Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aSfX-nrg-lI[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>4. Chloé Zhao | </b><b>Best Director nominations</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>Nominated For</strong>: Nomadland (2020)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Frances McDormand, David Strathairn</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Hulu</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5235 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Golden-Globe-Awards-Nominees-Best-Director-2.jpg\" alt=\"2021 Golden Globe Awards Nominees Best Director\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Nomadland is about a woman who lost both her husband and job but is not ready to move on from the memories of either of them. But the reality is cruel and it forces her to move on nonetheless. This story is mostly about letting things go and adapting to a new life.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now let\'s talk about the director. Chloe Zhao is a Chinese movie director who made her directorial debut in 2015 with the movie </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Songs My Brothers Taught Me</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Nomadland is her third feature film and this is her first time being nominated at the Golden Globe. She is also a nominee in the category of Best Screenplay - Motion Picture for this film. </span>\r\n<h3>Nomadland (2020) Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6sxCFZ8_d84[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Fact:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She is the director of the coming MCU movie The Eternals. </span>\r\n<h2><b>3. Emerald Fennell | Best Director nominations</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>Nominated For:</strong> Promising Young Woman (2020)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Carey Mulligan, Bo Burnham, Alison Brie</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> VUDU, DIRECTV</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5236 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Golden-Globe-Awards-Nominees-Best-Director-3.jpg\" alt=\"2021 Golden Globe Awards Nominees Best Director\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">An actress turned director. Or shall I say, an actress turned into a very successful director with just one try? When you look up Emerald Fennell’s IMDb profile, you will see most of her credits are for acting.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She has played roles in various TV shows (The Crown, Call the Midwife) and movies (The Danish Girl, Pan). She has only two Directing credits, one is for a short film named </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Careful How You Go</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. The other one is the one she’s been nominated for the best director in the 78th Golden Globe Awards. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When I observe the concept of this movie, not just the plot also the making, I notice a strong chain of feminism. Women (referring to Margot Robbie and Carey Mulligan) helping a woman to make a film about a woman avenging her best friend who is also a woman.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Emerald Fennell\'s great directing capability comes from her way of storytelling. She has already written scripts for a Golden Globe-winning thriller Drama series Killing Eve. Now that I have mentioned that, Killing Eve is also a series with strong female leads. I guess strong female leads and feminism will be Director Emerald Fennell\'s trademark.</span>\r\n<h3>Promising Young Woman (2020) Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7i5kiFDunk8[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>2. Regina King | Best Director nominations</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>Nominated For:</strong> One Night in Miami (2020)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Kingsley Ben-Adir, Eli Goree, Aldis Hodge</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Amazon Prime Video</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5237 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Golden-Globe-Awards-Nominees-Best-Director-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another actress turned director. More likely, an Oscar, Golden Globe, and Emmy winning actress turned into a director. Regina King won both her Oscar and Golden Globe Award in 2018 for the movie </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If Beale Street Could Talk</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. But unlike Emerald Fennell, Regina King is not a total newbie director.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She previously has directed some well-known TV series like Scandal, Shameless, The Good Doctor, and This Is Us. She has also directed a documentary and a TV movie. But, yes, this is her first time directing a full-length feature film.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One Night in Miami is a fiction movie. But this fiction mixed up with reality and history. We are familiar with movies that unite famous fictional characters from different fictional universes within a common plot, like </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The League of Extraordinary Gentlemen</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> for example.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One Night in Miami is something similar to that, but the only difference is that instead of fictional characters, the protagonists in this movie are real historical figures. I am talking about Muhammad Ali, Malcolm X, Sam Cooke, and Jim Brown. Which makes this movie way more interesting than any fiction. And I would say, by directing a movie with such a unique plot and setting, Regina King proved herself to be a real visionary.</span>\r\n<h3>One Night in Miami (2020) Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZprXMxKg--w[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>1. Aaron Sorkin</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>Nominated For</strong>: The Trial of Chicago 7 (2020)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast</strong>: Joseph Gordon-Levitt, Eddie Redmayne, Sacha Baron Cohen</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform</strong>: Netflix</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5238 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Golden-Globe-Awards-Nominees-Best-Director-5.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Trial of Chicago 7 is based on a true event film portraying 7 victims of wrongdoings and judicial misconduct in the late 60s.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Aaron Sorkin is an Oscar Winning screenplay writer who won his Oscar in 2011 for the movie </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Social Network. David Fincher directs the Social Network</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, and this year Aaron Sorkin is competing against him in the same category at the 78th Golden Globe Award. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Trial of Chicago 7 is Aaron Sorkin\'s 2nd film as a director. If we look at some previous works by him (both as a writer and a director), we can see most of his films are biographical or based on true events. For Example- The Social Network, Molly\'s Game, Charlie Wilson\'s War, Steve Jobs. His upcoming movie ‘Lucy and Desi’ is also a biography movie. I guess we have found his speciality.</span>\r\n<h3>The Trial of Chicago 7 (2020) Trailer:</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IsFCZ_B2o5w[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Conclusion:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fi