r-biography-and-other-interesting-facts-7.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><b>The journey with theatre</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As mentioned, at a young age Kumar came to Bombay. Due to his talent, he got the chance to work with well-known actress Neena Gupta’s theatre productions </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sahej</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Darshan delivered many admirable stage performances during that time and proved his capability. He was in the group for about 5 years.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He also worked with another theatre group, </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Motley Productions</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> where he came in touch with actor Nasiruddin Shah. During those years, the senior and much–experienced actor Shah gave immense training to Darshan. It sharpened his acting skills and contributed a lot to Darshan being the outstanding entertainer he is today.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5471 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Darshan-Kumar-biography-and-other-interesting-facts-8.jpg\" alt=\"Darshan Kumar :The journey with theatre\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<blockquote><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">DK with Nasiruddin Shah</span></blockquote>\r\n<h2><b>Darshan Kumar Movies and Tv Shows</b></h2>\r\n<h3><b>TV shows</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Before beginning with a full-fledged film career, the actor tried his hands in well-known soap operas and was seen in important roles. He has been a part of famous serials like </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chhoti Bahu</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Devon Ka Dev...Mahadev</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Darshan was also seen in Imagine TV’s </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Baba Aiso Vaar Dhoondo</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> along with Vikrant Massey as well as in Colors’ drama </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Havan</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in 2012. He worked on the small screen till 2014.</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Watch Darshan in Baba Aiso Vaar Dhundo</span></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9zCHmgSGE-c[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Movies</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Success didn’t come in Darshan’s life in just one night. Hard work and determination have been the common characteristics of his journey. It was the year 2001 when we first saw him on the big screen, though we remember the least of it! His debut was with a small role in the Hindi film </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mujhe Kuch Kehena Hai</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. In the same year, he got a minor part in the Shah Rukh Khan starrer historical drama </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Asoka</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.  Later, in 2003 he was seen in the romantic tragedy </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tere – Naam</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> where he played a friend of the male lead, portrayed by Salman Khan.</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Darshan  Kumar in Tere Naam | Watch Now</span></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Hqydt7SLR5A[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Despite his initial appearances so long back, he had to struggle for another 10 years to gain a deserved project. In all these years, he involved himself with theatre and gained a lot of knowledge.</span>\r\n\r\n[irp posts=\"2779\" name=\"List of Top 10 Most Popular Salman Khan Dialogues Ever\"]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In 2014, his first Bollywood movie came into the audience. It was a sports drama, </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mary Kom</span></