m, A Perfect Murder, he grabbed a Best Actor Award.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">And for the iconic character of Bunty from Sacred Games, Sarna won the MTV IWM Award for Most Popular Supporting actor in a web series.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Jatin Sharma net worth</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As of 2020, his net worth is reportedly $1-$5 billion.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jatin Sarna is a very talented entertainer who has recently come in the limelight with his admirable on-screen performances. We wish to see him grow more as an actor in the upcoming times.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We, at <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">TV Freak.com</a>, try to present to you the inspiring journey of Indian artists. The journeys of chasing dreams! It’s high time when the audience should start appreciating underrated works and actors of Bollywood so that they get more opportunities to show their talents in various platforms.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is the content for today. Hope you had a happy reading. We are also there on Instagram and Facebook with the same name where you can follow us for regular updates about the entertainment industry. We will soon be back. Till then, have a safe and nice time.  </span>','Sacred Games Sensation Jatin Sarna Biography, Movies and Tv Shows','','publish','open','open','','sacred-games-sensation-jatin-sarna-biography-movies-and-tv-shows','','','2021-03-24 13:43:10','2021-03-24 08:13:10','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5475',0,'post','',0),(5489,13,'2021-03-03 11:20:59','2021-03-03 05:50:59','<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">It is such a shame to say, like any other workplace, Hollywood and other film industries are more or less biased with racism and sexism as well. It is the twenty-first century and still, women have to work twice as hard to prove their worth. That is why female directors in the movie industry are as rare as a four-leaf clover. And a </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">good</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> female director is even rarer.</span>\r\n\r\n<i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Oscars, </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The most prestigious film awards ever existed, had only 5 female directors to ever get a nomination in the category of <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/golden-globe-nominations-for-best-director-2021/\">Best Director</a> in the last 92 years. So <em><strong>this Women’s Day, let’s know and celebrate some of the best female directors of all time and the movies directed by them. </strong></em></span><em><strong> </strong></em>\r\n<h2><b>10. American Psycho (2000)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.6</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director</strong>: <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mary_Harron\">Mary Harron</a></li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Christian Bale, Reese Witherspoon, Jared Leto</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform</strong>: Amazon Prime Video, Hulu</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5493 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/1.jpg\" alt=\"American Psycho (2000)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">American Psycho is a psychological thriller. It is about the narcissist central character, who becomes so blind with jealousy that he turns into a serial killer. This movie is <strong>based on the novel by Bret Easton Ellis</strong>. The book is way gorier, to be honest.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">American Psycho is the first highlight of Christian Bale’s career. Many people told him not to do the movie. But their forbidding made him want to do the movie more.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Mary Harron has mainly directed TV series episodes and American Psycho is sadly her only well-known film.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=81mibtQWWBg[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Reese Witherspoon was three months pregnant when she was working on this film.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Leonardo DiCaprio was offered the role of </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Patrick Bateman</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">. He turned down the offer for several reasons. </span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">There is a TV series spin-off of this movie where Mila Kunis played the main lead. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<em><b>Personal recommendation: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">If you like this movie, you should watch <strong>The Machinist (2004)</strong> and<strong> Identity (2003). </strong></span></em>\r\n<h2><b>9. Winter’s Bone (2010)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.1</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director</strong>: Debra Granik (Also Directed Leave No Trace)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Jennifer Lawrence, John Hawkes</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform</strong>: Kanopy, DIRECTV</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5494 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2.jpg\" alt=\"Winter’s Bone (2010)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Winter’s Bone portrays the struggle of a young girl to support her mentally ill mother and two younger siblings. She has a missing father, whose presence causes more trouble than his absence. Ree Dolly must now find her father to save her house and prevent her family from being thrown into the forest.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\"><strong>Jennifer Lawrence</strong> was turned down for her role showing cause that she was too pretty for the job. But her tenacity won her the role and with amazing acting skills and flawless Ozark accent, she won the heart of everybody else.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">There are only 6 directorial credits in Debra Granik’s career. Winter’s Bone was her third film. <em><strong>She was nominated for Best Writing (Adapted Screenplay) for this movie</strong></em></span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bE_X2pDRXyY[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie was nominated for four Oscars.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Fact:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is one of the <strong>lowest-grossing movies</strong> to be nominated for the best picture at the Oscars.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"><strong>Jennifer Lawrence was only 19</strong> when she worked in this movie. She also got her first best actress Oscar nomination for this film. She was only 20 then which makes her one of the youngest best actress nominees in Oscar history. </span><b>   </b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>8. Monster (2003)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.3</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director</strong>: Patty Jenkins (Also Directed, Wonder Woman, Wonder Woman 1984)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast</strong>: Charlize Theron, Christina Ricci</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform</strong>: Tubi TV, Hoopla</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5495 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/3.jpg\" alt=\"Monster (2003)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the <strong>biopic of Aileen Wuornos, a female prostitute with a horrific childhood</strong>, who was raped and sexually abused countless times. A woman whom reality made a murderer. Charlize Theron’s performance in the character of Aileen Wuornos was awe-worthy. Maybe that’s because Charlize herself was a victim of child abuse growing up as well. Her mother had to shoot her father to death to protect Charlize and herself. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">People say women are women’s worst enemies. But it is also only a woman who can understand another woman so perfectly. Maybe that’s why together director <strong>Patty Jenkins </strong>and <strong>actress Charlize Theron</strong> could make it possible to turn the life of America’s first woman serial killer into an amazing feature film.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Maybe as women, they understood better than anyone else what made Aileen Wuornos snap and why she started to kill people.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vq70brIQP40[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Monster had one Oscar win.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Fact:</b></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The only Oscar nomination and win, which Charlize Theron received in the category of best actress in a leading role, took place on Aileen Wuornos’s birthday.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2><b>7. Little Women (2019)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.8</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director</strong>: Greta Gerwig (Also Directed Lady Bird)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Saoirse Ronan, Emma Watson, Timothée Chalamet, Laura Dern, Meryl Streep</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform</strong>: Starz, DIRECTV</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5496 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/4.jpg\" alt=\"Little Women (2019)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The time set up is after the Civil War, there were four sisters who had their own individual stories to tell, but their stories are also what made them wholesome.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Greta Gerwig has been working as an actress long before she started her directing career. Little Women is her second movie which was nominated for multiple Oscars. Her previous movie <em><strong>Lady Bird</strong></em> was also based on a plot featuring a young woman trying to live an individual life without anyone else’s influence or impact.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Greta Gerwig has only directed 3 movies and except for her directorial debut, <strong>the other two were very successful.</strong> We wish she will have a long and progressive career ahead of her and become one of the best female directors in Hollywood.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AST2-4db4ic[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie has a total of 6 Oscar nominations and one win, which is in the category of Best Achievement in Costume Design.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Fact:</b></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Greta Gerwig is the 12th woman to direct a Best Picture Oscar-nominated film.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">In 2018, Greta Gerwig was <strong>nominated for the best director at the Oscars</strong>, but she lost it to Guillermo del Toro (The Shape of Water).</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2><b>6. Boys Don’t Cry (1999)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.5</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director</strong>: Kimberly Peirce</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Hilary Swank, Chloë Sevigny, Peter Sarsgaard</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform</strong>: Vudu</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5497 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/5.jpg\" alt=\"Boys Don’t Cry (1999)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Brandon Teena was Teena Brandon once. After going through sex-change surgery she became a he and fell in love with a woman. But getting used to a new body is not easy, especially when society is completely against you. This is a story about adapting to a new life, a man born in the wrong body. <strong>It is based on a true actual event,</strong> the time set in the late 20th century when society was more biased and prejudiced than now.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">With <strong>18 directorial credits</strong>, it is sad to say, Boys Don’t Cry is the only highlight in Kimberly Peirce’s career. It was also her first feature film. Some other movies she gave directions are Stop-Loss, Carrie.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mYpUhVvfGeg[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie was <strong>nominated for 2 Oscars</strong>. Hilary Swank won her first Oscar for this movie.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Fact</b></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Hilary was paid only <strong>3,000 USD</strong> for her role.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<em><b>Personal recommendation: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">If you liked this movie, you can watch <strong>The Danish Girl (2015).</strong></span></em>\r\n<h2><b>5. I Am Sam (2001)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.7</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director</strong>: Jessie Nelson</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Sean Penn, Michelle Pfeiffer, Dakota Fanning, Dianne Wiest, Laura Dern</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform</strong>: HBO Max</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5498 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/6.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">I Am Sam</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> is what you call a perfect movie for Father\'s Day. A mentally challenged father who has the intelligence of an eight-year-old has a daughter of 7 years old. But that does not refrain him from being a good father or fighting for his daughter’s custody. So, when a cold-hearted female lawyer is forced to take his case, she learns something valuable from him about love and family.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">With amazing The Beatles song references, <strong>this movie will make you cry and laugh</strong> and the ending will definitely warm your heart. <em>This is undoubtedly one of the best movies directed by a woman.  </em></span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ir6_2EkhzAc[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Sean Penn was nominated in the category of Best Actor for the leading role for this movie</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Elle Fanning, Dakota Fanning\'s little sister, played her 3-year-old version.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is Elle Fanning’s debut movie. If you don’t know who Elle fanning is, she played Aurora in <em>Maleficent.</em></span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Shailene Woodley (Hazel Grace in The Fault in Our Stars) auditioned for the role of Lucy Diamond.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<em><b>Personal recommendation:</b> <strong>Miracle in Cell No. 7</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> is a South Korean movie also featuring a mentally handicapped father. If you like I am Sam, You will definitely like this one. </span></em>\r\n<h2><b>4. The Hurt Locker (2008)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.5</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director</strong>: Kathryn Bigelow (Also Directed, Zero Dark Thirty, Point Break)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Jeremy Renner, Anthony Mackie, Guy Pearce, Ralph Fiennes, Evangeline Lilly</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform</strong>: Amazon Prime Video, Hulu</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5499 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/7.jpg\" alt=\"The Hurt Locker (2008 Female Directors\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Hurt Locker is a hardcore war-action movie with a lot of gunfire and bombing scenes. The plot of this film is <strong>based on the Iraq war</strong>. When a new sergeant is assigned to an army bomb squad whose sole responsibility is to disarm bombs during combat, things start to get tense. In a hostile situation, Staff Sergeant William James has to also face his mates\' disloyalty because of his unorthodox technique to get jobs done.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Kathryn Bigelow is a woman who <strong>made history in the Oscars</strong> by being the first female director to win the Best Director Award. And The Hurt Locker is one of her greatest achievements.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AIbFvqFYRT4[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\"><strong>The Hurt Locker was nominated for 9 Oscars</strong> and scored 6 among them including the awards for Best Picture, Best Director, and Best Screenplay.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> </span>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Kathryn Bigelow was once married to </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"><strong>James Cameron</strong>,</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and he is the one to encourage her (his ex-wife) to direct this film. At the Oscars, The Hurt Locker competed against Avatar (Directed by James Cameron) in 9 categories and won in 6 of them. </span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie has <strong>6 Oscar wins.</strong> But oddly enough, this movie had <strong>3 Golden Globe nominations</strong> but did not win any.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the <strong>lowest-grossing movie to ever</strong> win the Best Picture.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the first movie directed by a woman to win the Best Picture.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Kathryn Bigelow is the <strong>first woman to win the Academy Award, the BAFTA, and the DGA for Best Director.</strong></span><strong>   </strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2><b>3. The Piano (1993)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.6</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director:</strong> Jane Campion (Also Directed The Portrait of a Lady)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Holly Hunter, Harvey Keitel, Sam Neill</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform</strong>: Amazon Video, Vudu</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5500 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8.jpg\" alt=\"Female Directors\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is a complicated romance movie. Ada used to be a mute young unmarried mother until her arranged marriage with Alisdair Stewart. So, when she moved in with her new husband in a new country she took two things that mattered to her the most— her daughter and her piano. But her husband heartlessly sold the piano to his friend George Baines, who happens to be lusting after Ada since the day he laid eyes on her (what a perv).</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Now, Ada is very attached to her piano and adamant to do anything to get it back. So, when Baines makes a negotiation to let Ada play the piano in exchange for letting him do to her the ‘things he likes’, Ada soon submits to lust and her passion for music.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Movies like these, most of the time finish with a tragic end, but hey, <strong>I am not giving any spoilers. You have to watch the movie for yourself to figure that out.</strong></span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cyTn4XIYH8M[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie was <strong>nominated in 8 Oscar categories </strong>and <strong>won in 3 of them</strong>, including best actress for both in the leading and supporting roles.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> </span>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Anna Paquin was<strong> 11 years old when she received her Oscar</strong> for best actress in a supporting role. She is one of the youngest people to ever win an Oscar. By the way, she later played Rogue in the earliest X-Men movies. </span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Jane Campion won the prestigious Palme d\'Or at the Cannes Film Festival with this film. She is the first female director to win one.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the debut film of Anna Paquin. </span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Jane Campion is the first woman to be Oscar-nominated for Best Director for directing the Best Picture nominee.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the last movie Kurt Cobain watched<strong> before he committed suicide. </strong></span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Jane Campion lost her Oscar to Steven Spielberg<em><strong> (Schindler\'s List)</strong></em> in the Best Director category. </span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2>2. Capernaum<b> (2018)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 8.4</li>\r\n <li><strong>Director</strong>: Nadine Labaki</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Zain Al Rafeea, Yordanos Shiferaw, Boluwatife Treasure Bankole</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform</strong>: Vudu</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5501 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/9.jpg\" alt=\"Capernaum (2018)Female Directors\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">It’s better not to be parents at all than being bad parents. After all, there is no excuse for that. When a 12-year-old Lebanese boy gets sent to prison for 5 years committing a violent crime, he sues his parents for their negligence, for giving birth to him in a poverty-stricken family. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Nadine Labaki, the director of this film, is a beautiful woman who was previously only known as an actress. Capernaum is her fourth and most successful film in her career. We wish to see her directing career become more vast so that she can gift us with more heart-touching movies like this one.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ULUo0048xZE[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie was nominated for <strong>Best Foreign Language Film of the Year (Lebanon).</strong></span>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Lost its Oscar to <em><strong>Roma</strong></em> (Mexico).</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The title, Capernaum, can mean \'chaos\' in Arabic.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the second Lebanese movie to get an Oscar nomination.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The film <strong>received a 15-minute standing ovation at Cannes.</strong></span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">78th in the IMDb Top 250 movie list.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">It is the <strong>highest-grossing</strong> Middle-Eastern film of all time.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The budget for this movie was only 4 million dollars.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2><b>1. The Matrix Trilogy (2008, 2013)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDb Rating:</strong> 7.57 (Average)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Directors</strong>: Lana Wachowski, Lilly Wachowski (Also Directed Cloud Atlas, Jupiter Ascending)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast:</strong> Keanu Reeves, Laurence Fishburne, Monica Bellucci, Carrie-Anne Moss, Jada Pinkett Smith</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform</strong>: HBO Max</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5502 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10.jpg\" alt=\"Female Directors\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is a <strong>cyberpunk trilogy</strong>, the first movie The Matrix (1999) is kind of a genre-defining movie as well. In the distant future, when Artificial Intelligence is a matter of course, the human race is confined in an illusion called the Matrix. But some people can get out of the matrix and to prevent them from causing any rebellion, Agent Smith pursues them to death. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Tell me honestly, how many of you actually knew that one of the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/some-of-the-best-trilogies-movies-worth-watching/\">greatest trilogies in Hollywood</a> history is actually exclusively directed by two women? The whole idea of this film came from the Wachowski Brothers.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\"><em>The story was so mind-bending that many of the famous actors turned down their offer to work in this movie because they could not understand the complexity of the plot. </em></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Now, you may wonder why I called them brothers when they are actually sisters. Both Lana and Lily were born as Larry and Andy. Yes, they are proud transwomen</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qPBuOAxOb2E[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The only <strong>first movie of this trilogy could enter the Oscar nominations.</strong> The Matrix (1999) was nominated in 4 categories and won in all of them. </span>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"><strong>Johnny Depp</strong> was Lana and Lilly\'s first choice for <strong>Neo</strong>.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Neo\'s name is an anagram for The One.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The <strong>special effects</strong> alone cost <strong>$100 million</strong> in The Matrix Reloaded (2003).</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Matrix Reloaded is <strong>Gloria Foster’s last film.</strong> (Rest in peace)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Matrix Reloaded is the highest-grossing film in the trilogy.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This trilogy has an anime spin-off named The Animatrix.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<em><b>Personal recommendation: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Watch <strong>The Blade Runner</strong> and <strong>The Blade Runner 2049</strong> if you like this trilogy. </span></em><b><em> </em> </b>\r\n<h2><b>Some Honorable Mentions:</b><b> </b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Why don’t we take a look at some more of the Best female directors and their movies—</span>\r\n<ol>\r\n <li><b>Sofia Coppola</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">— <em>The Virgin Suicides (1999), Lost in Translation (2003), Marie Antoinette (2006)</em></span></li>\r\n <li><b>Lina Wertmüller</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">— <em>Seven Beauties (1975)</em></span></li>\r\n <li><b>Amy Heckerling</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">— <em>Look Who\'s Talking (1989), Clueless (1995)</em></span></li>\r\n <li><b>Lynne Ramsay</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">— <em>We Need to Talk About Kevin (2011), You Were Never Really Here (2017)</em></span></li>\r\n <li><b>Nora Ephron</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">— <em>Sleepless in Seattle (1993), You\'ve Got Mail (1998), Julie &amp; Julia (2009)</em></span></li>\r\n <li><b>Lisa Cholodenko</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">— <em>The Kids Are All Right (2010)</em></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2><b>Conclusion</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">I am sure standing under the ‘Director Spotlight’ was not easy for either of these women. So, thanks to those men (especially) and women who gave these women a chance to prove themselves, believed in them, and encouraged them.</span>','Top 10 Movies Directed by Female Directors | Hollywood Female Directors','','publish','open','open','','top-10-movies-directed-by-female-directors-hollywood-female-directors','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/golden-globe-nominations-for-best-director-2021/','2021-10-05 15:00:06','2021-10-05 09:30:06','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5489',0,'post','',1),(5504,12,'2021-03-06 22:22:58','2021-03-06 16:52:58','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5509 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Amit-Sadh-Biography-and-other-interesting-facts-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Millions come to the Mayanagri every day to make it big in the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">Bollywood film</a> industry but only a few make it big and get the deserved fame. One such outsider is none other than Amit Sadh. Let us deep dive into his journey today and know how he made it big.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Early Life</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Amit’s early days were spent in the national capital of Delhi and sometimes in New York. His alma meter includes the prestigious La Martinere College, Lucknow from where he pursued his graduation.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, those days of Sadh were not at all spent with a silver spoon in his mouth as he faced many personal difficulties and struggles. As a 16-year-old guy, he had to take up petty jobs like that of a security guard and even at times worked at people’s residences washing dishes to earn money. Those dark days came in his life due to the unfortunate demise of his father.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Later, in an interview, Sadh revealed what he went through in those days and that he even attempted to end his life quite a few times.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, he didn’t lose hope and kept dreaming. He entered the universe of this industry and lastly, in 2010, he joined a film institute in NY to sharpen his skills and to produce himself as a better actor.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Amit Sadh age, physique, and other basic info</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5510 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Amit-Sadh-Biography-and-other-interesting-facts-2.jpg\" alt=\"Amit Sadh age, physique, and other basic info\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1983 born Amit Sadh is currently is 38.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sadh is a fitness fanatic and has a very charming appearance. This uprising superstar has a height of 5’9”. With a pair of dark black eyes, sharp facial features and black hair, he has a well-toned body. His well-groomed self has made him the heartthrob of many.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Amit Sadh family and friends</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With no connections with the Bollywood industry, Amit Sadh is from a rather simple family; though his father, Ram Chandra Dogra had a sports background and had played hockey at the national level.  He is not the only child of his parents and has a sister elder to him named Anu Gaur.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5511 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Amit-Sadh-Biography-and-other-interesting-facts-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">AS with his elder sister</span></em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Regarding his friends, Sadh is quite close to his Zidd co-actor Ali Gony.\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5515 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Amit-Sadh-Biography-and-other-interesting-facts-7.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He has friends from inside as well as outside the alluring world of entertainment.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5516 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Amit-Sadh-Biography-and-other-interesting-facts-8.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5517 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Amit-Sadh-Biography-and-other-interesting-facts-9.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>Beginning of the journey – Amit Sadh television shows</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sadh didn’t grab a film at the very first go and instead like many other actors, started his career by working in Hindi soap operas. He bagged the lead role of Aditya in the Star Plus serial, <strong><em>Kyun Hota Hai Pyar</em></strong> which was produced by the legendary actress Neena Gupta. The year was 2002.\r\n</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Watch Sadh in Kyu Hota hai Pyar title song</span></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SMZ9bQNrMnM[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His good acting skills made him grab a significant role in an anthology TV series <em><strong>Kya Hadsaa kya Haqeeqat</strong> </em>in 2003 itself. We saw him in the 5th story of the series Kalpanik.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He continued getting works and within a span of just 5 years (2002-05), he had acted 6 serials aired on different channels.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Some of his other major television works include<em><strong> Awaz – Dil Se Dil Tak, Guns and Roses, Kohinoor, Miss India Sakshi, Durgesh Nandini.</strong></em>\r\n</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Watch Sadh in Guns and roses</strong></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EnQY_m2Hd8I[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We also saw Amit Sadh in various famous reality shows like Nach Baliye where he participated with one of his ex-girlfriends. That tie, this power couple had won over the audience with their on-stage romantic, sizzling chemistry, dance steps and grooves.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Amit Sadh in Nach Baliye</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He was also a participant of <em><strong>Fear Factor: Khatro Ka Khiladi in the year 2007</strong></em> where we witnessed him performing various dangerous and difficult tasks.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Amit Sadh participated in hosted amazing and most popular reality show <strong>Bigg Boss</strong> but soon left it. He seemed to be not much impressed about any gaining from the show. Later on, he told that participating in it didn\'t turn out to be great and went on to say that such shows are \"hypocritical\".</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As per reports, he was banned by big influencers of TV industry. Hence, he left it and started trying luck on big screen.\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D7x2po-C358[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>The journey in Bollywood – Amit Sadh movies</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After a television career of roughly 6 years, Amit made it into the film industry. He began with the 2010 horror film <em><strong>Phoonk 2</strong></em>. That was just the beginning of a bright career in the industry.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Later in the decade, Sadh appeared in a numerous films like <em><strong>Maximum, Guddu Rangeela, Sultan, Akira, Running Shaadi</strong></em>. He had also played major supporting roles in iconic hits <em><strong>Sarkar 3, Gold, </strong></em>and<em><strong> Super 30.</strong></em>\r\n</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Watch AS in scene from Guddu Rangleela</span></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=izqa2AF_sIo[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Not to miss the most iconic character, Om Shashtri in a beautiful movie <em><strong>Kai Po Che</strong> </em>where he stole the lime light alongside Bollywood\'s new superstar Rajkumar Rao and breathtakingly amazing and most talented Sushant Singh Rajput. This movie is based on <strong>Chetan Bhagat\'s book, 3 Mistakes of my life.</strong>\r\n</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Watch Sadh in the BTS of Kaipoche</span></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hgvlUqd_weo[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Last year, during the lockdown situation when OTT platforms became synonymous to the whole industry and gained its peak, Sadh also appeared in Zee 5 originals such as <em><strong>Operation Parindey</strong></em> and Tigmanshu Dhulia\'s <em><strong>Yaara</strong></em>.\r\n</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Watch AS in Operation Parindey trailer</span></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QPqYGAG20uQ[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His last release was <em><strong>Shakuntala Devi</strong> </em>that came on Prime in 2020. Sadh was in Shakuntala Devi’s daughter, Anupama Banerjee’s husband in the movie.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Dominance in OTTs – Amit Sadh web series</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It can be well said that now his career is not just limited to big screens but also in our laptop and mobile screens. Amit Sadh is also gaining popularity for his lead roles in web series.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The actor was casted in the Amazon Prime thriller web show <em><strong>Breathe</strong></em> in its both seasons.\r\n</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Watch Sadh in a scene from Breathe</span></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IUpk_BeWs_4[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He was also seen in the main role of a major in Sony LIV Original <em><strong>Avrodh: A Seige Within</strong></em> where he delivered a very realistic performance and once again became highly praised. He is most recently seen in <em><strong>Jitt Ki Zidd</strong></em>. These last 2 roles of Sadh were showered with love by his fans. Thus, it can be truly said that 2020 was in favour of Amit Sadh.\r\n</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Watch this review and analysis of AS’ latest series Jeet Ki Zeed</span></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eu7wNv-2vXs[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>Other works</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At times, Sadh also impressed us with his brilliant acting in short films such as the<em><strong> Home Coming, Baarish Aur Chowmin.</strong></em>\r\n</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The short film <strong>The Homecoming</strong></span></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W1_eZln9qyg[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Baarish aur Chowmin trailer</span></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SzMtRpPoQIw[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Apart from these, we saw him in some beautiful and loving commercials too. These include the ads of Wildstone Deo, Maruti Suzuki Dzire, Platinum, One Plus.\r\n</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Watch AS in Maruti Suzuki dzire ad</span></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0Tks2ncEB_I[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>Achievements</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5512 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Amit-Sadh-Biography-and-other-interesting-facts-4.jpg\" alt=\"Amit Sadh Biography and other interesting facts (4)Achievements\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His character of Kabir Sawant from Breathe 2 gained immense popularity and gave him enough recognition. He went on to win the deserving title of Best Supporting Actor in Filmfare OTT awards for the same.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Amit Sadh net worth</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2020 had really been a turning point of Sadh’s career and he had an estimated net worth of about 6 million.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Relationship status</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When it comes to relationships or dating, many times the actor’s name got linked with various personalities, though until now he didn’t tie the knot with anyone.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5513 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Amit-Sadh-Biography-and-other-interesting-facts-5.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">About his date,<strong> Neeru Bajwa</strong> was a Punjabi actress whom he met on the sets of Star Plus soap opera, Guns and Roses and fell for each other. They seemed to be madly in love but not all love stories have happy endings. In 2010, due to some unfortunate reasons, the couple took different paths of life and got separated. Hard to believe that it was after their so many years of togetherness. Reportedly, Amit had a bad phase of life after the break -up.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He was then rumoured to be with the famous costume designer of Bollywood, Niharika Bhasin Khan who had worked for hit movies like Rock On! and Kaipoche. She had ended her long years of married life and then came in reports for being with Sadh.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, fans were surprised when he took on his social media and announced his official relationship with the Brazilian model, Annabel DaSilva. But once again, stars weren’t in favour of Sadh when it came to his love life. One year later the duo parted ways and Amit declared himself to be single. In 2019, there were news of his ex-lover getting married to Kabir Brah, a photographer.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5514 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Amit-Sadh-Biography-and-other-interesting-facts-6.jpg\" alt=\"Relationship status\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Post that, Amit had not engaged himself in any relationship, at least it’s not known to us. We really wish that he finds the true love of his life.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Some other interesting facts about him</strong></h2>\r\n<h3><strong>A traveler?</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The actor has a great passion for travelling. He often packs bags, goes to find solace in different destinations and yes...he often goes on such holidays without even carrying his cell phone. Maybe, the actor doesn’t want to distract himself in anyway while enjoying the world’s beauty.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>The kind of music he prefers</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">From his list of favourite songs, it can be rightly said that this guy is a sucker for country and rock music.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>The foodie in him</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Although we now know that he is a fitness freak, he never fails to deep dive when it comes to yummy dishes like Mutton Biryani, Cheese Cake and Hot Dog.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>A dog lover too and what else?</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The actor is quite active on Instagram from which we got to know about his love for dogs </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">too.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/CGxMUr4JG3c/?igshid=fr08wygqvlcf\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Also, Amit Sadh Instagram account has many posted motivational quotes indicating the motivational speaker the talented actor has in himself.\r\n</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/CHxuHkvJ1xH/?igshid=1v4vcwjxug458\r\n\r\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/CDrTSOqpVD7/?igshid=1tu4oup23qim0\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Amit Sadh is an extremely talented name in Bollywood, a name the demand for which is on the rise. It’s really good to see him gradually reach the peak of his career in recent years. We wish to see more of his versatility as an artist.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We at TV Freak.com try to present to you inspirational journeys of artists who made their dreams a reality. They work hard day and night to break our monotony, to entertain us. We are always thankful and appreciate their efforts and struggles. Their journeys behind reaching the goal are worth listening and hence we try to give you the maximum information.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is the content for today. Hope you had a happy reading. We are also there on Social Media with the same name where you can follow us for regular updates about the entertainment industry. We will soon be back. Till then, have a safe and nice time.</span>','Breathe Actor Amit Sadh Biography and other Interesting Facts','','publish','open','open','','breathe-actor-amit-sadh-biography-and-other-interesting-facts','','','2021-03-24 13:43:03','2021-03-24 08:13:03','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5504',0,'post','',0),(5574,13,'2021-03-16 10:27:30','2021-03-16 04:57:30','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5577 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Tahar-Rahim—-Biography-Movies-and-TV-Shows-1.jpg\" alt=\"Tahar Rahim— Biography, Movies, and TV Shows\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For a long time, he has been known as a French 