,0),(5627,12,'2021-03-23 23:34:59','2021-03-23 18:04:59','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5628 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Actor-competition-in-2021-1.jpg\" alt=\"Actor competition in 2021  (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When was the last time you went to a cinema hall to watch a <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/hollywoods-top-10-feel-good-movies-you-must-watch/\">good movie</a> which was totally worth the money and spent quality time with your friends and family? If you didn\'t go to watch Christopher Nolan\'s <em><strong>Tenet</strong></em>, then I guess it\'s been a year if I am not wrong.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now let me ask you when was the last time you watched a good movie or binge-watched a web series on a platform like <strong><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/16-best-bollywood-movies-of-2020-on-netflix-and-amazon-prime/\">Netflix</a>, Disney + Hotstar, Amazon Prime, </strong>or <strong>Zee 5</strong>? Today? Yesterday? Last week maybe? </span>\r\n<h2><b>The rise of OTTs</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The year 2020 has been a hell ride but one thing that gained its peak in this mostly digital/ online year is OTT platforms. By this time Indians aren\'t really alien to this term as they were almost 5 years back when entertainment was synonymous with TV and movie theatres. </span>\r\n<h2><b>The shows that increased the demand for digital content</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5629 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Actor-competition-in-2021-2.jpg\" alt=\"Actor competition in 2021  (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Although these OTT platforms like Netflix and Amazon Prime video has already entered the scene, it saw a major boom in its viewership in 2018 with the release of mainly two web series, namely </span><strong><i>Sacred Games </i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">starring Nawazuddin Siddiqui and Saif Ali Khan on Netflix and </span><strong><i>Mirzapur</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> starring Ali Fazal, Pankaj Tripathi on Amazon Prime Video. Since then, the OTT business set its sail and never turned back. </span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hoSijFjsMKM[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<strong><em>(watch this best compilation of Ganesh Gaitonde moments from Sacred Games and witness Nawaz’s lifelike acting)</em></strong>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BUIcp8dRvcI[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<strong><em>(watch these scenes from Mirzapur)</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5632 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Actor-competition-in-2021-5.jpg\" alt=\"Actor competition in 2021  (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The OTT platforms began curating and producing mainly content-driven shows. On the other hand, I don\'t think you will be surprised if I say that the Bollywood industry is mostly star cast driven rather than content. Where star-driven Bollywood keeps on increasing the list of 100 crore club movies, we have seen the OTT platforms bagging Emmy Nominations with shows like</span><strong><i> Made in Heaven </i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">on Amazon Prime video and </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Delhi Crime</strong> </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">on Netflix.  </span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tfnWRfnzta0[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<strong><em>(watch these scenes from Made in Heaven)</em></strong>\r\n<h2><b>The sudden pandemic and its impact</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5630 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Actor-competition-in-2021-3.jpg\" alt=\"Actor competition in 2021  (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Although people were enjoying both of these contents side by side, the year 2020 was kind of a game-changer in this duel. With the sudden Covid-19 pandemic and closing of the movie theatres and multiplexes, the star-driven Bollywood has faced a major setback. Big projects like Rohit Shetty\'s and Karan Johar\'s got postponed and we saw the rise of OTT platforms.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Prominent filmmakers like <strong>Anurag Kashyap, Vikramaditya Motwane, Shoojit Sircar, Hansal Mehta</strong>, etc. jumped into the scene now not with bankable glamorous faces but with versatile and promising actors, some new and others who had already claimed a share in the rise of OTT platforms. </span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WoytihkwgXM[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<strong><em> (If you missed this promising horror Netflix release Bulbul in 2020 starring an underrated actress like Tripi Damri, you really m9ssed something great)</em></strong>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5molN55chcg[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<strong><em> (Also don’t miss out on this Amazon Prime show-stealer from 2020, Bandish Bandits)</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now that the cinema halls are reopening and have started with their new charm and OTT platforms are launching back-to-back promising shows and movies, which will claim fame in 2021? The Actors or the Stars? Here I would like to focus on a few factors which might be helpful in further understanding this debate.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Content</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For the last two-three years, the various OTT platforms are bent on providing the viewers with all types of content you can think of spanning across all genres from documentaries, comedy, thriller, erotica, family drama and whatnot. This range is not only seen in the genres but from various languages all across the globe and for a country like ours, all across the country.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Recently a few weeks ago, Netflix brought out a list of all the upcoming movies and web series that they are going to release this year. Well, that list is enough for one to digest the fact that I am talking about. And the best part, you can enjoy all these in the comforts of your home.  </span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jx0_LOzWkJk[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<strong><em> (see what Netflix has in store for you in 2021)</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">No high-pitched dialogues, melodious songs, or such item dances and romance, but soon these OTTs grew addictive. Tell me the last time you came across people talking about larger-than-life actors and their mainstream films?</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Well, I guess it\'s when people were talking about how Akshay Kumar starred Laxmi was equally disliked by the audience and slammed by the critics at the same time. Somehow, somewhere the glamour of the mainstream industry doesn\'t quite fit well in the OTT platforms. </span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L_UMVPOBZjk[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<strong><em> (watch how a famous YouTube channel bashed Laxmi during giving its review)</em> </strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">People are surely changing their tastes but will the Khans, Kapoors, and Chopra\'s will be so easily forgotten?</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Somewhere deep inside you know that charm still exists and when talking about spending a good family time during Diwali or Eid, watching a good crime drama with curse words being uttered every 5 mins doesn\'t really add up.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Cost </b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What is it like to watch a big production house project starring the <strong>Khans, Kapoors,</strong> and<strong> the Chopras</strong> in air-conditioned halls with cushiony seats and an amazing sound system? Really amazing right? But you know it comes with a hole in your pocket and on weekends, it\'s even more. It\'s quite an experience. But do all movies that get released require such an ambience?</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>I don\'t think so.</strong> There are shows that you look to binge-watch during your weekends while biting a snack, sitting at the corner of your bed. There come to the OTT platforms to play. As the internet is getting cheaper day by day, so are the OTT platforms are coming up with cheaper and pocket-friendly plans. These plans are surprisingly cheaper than what you need to pay for a single movie ticket to watch a 2 hr show in a multiplex whereas you get hundreds of curated shows on these online platforms at even cheaper prices. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do you also now think twice before visiting a movie theatre</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Although cinema halls have opened up with proper sanitization and maintenance of social distance, and movies are being released every week, there\'s somehow still doubt when you question yourself when planning a day out to the multiplexes.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Conclusion</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Life may be short, but we can forever find comfort in the soothing image of SRK\'s widespread arms, Salman\'s Bhai-Giri, Aamir\'s charming humour, and that feeling to find ourselves. Stars are a source of joy, beauty, and pleasure and our obsession and relationship with these stars totally remain unapologetic!</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jAM5yeYYxuE[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<strong><em> (Let’s once again be a little nostalgic by seeing the iconic ‘spreading arm’ romantic gesture of King Khan)</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So as the clash between the stars and the actors has started, we are yet to see whether the charm and glamour or the content wins. Will the amazing <strong><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/pankaj-tripathi-biography-movies-tv-and-awards/\">Pankaj Tripathi</a>, <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/shweta-tripathi-biography-tv-shows-movies-and-commercial-ads/\">Shweta Tripathi</a>, <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/jitendra-kumar-life-biography-and-bollywood-journey/\">Jitendra Kumar</a></strong> or <strong>Criminal Justice, Kota Factory, Pataal Lok, Lootcase, Ludo,</strong> or <strong>Sir</strong> be able to match the glam and fame of mighty Khans and Kapoors or the to-die-for actors like Deepika, Kareena, and Katrina?</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Will content defeat glamour? And will realism defeat escapism? Will actors challenge stars?</span>\r\n\r\nThe game is on!\r\nThis is the content for today. Hope you had a happy reading. Don\'t forget to follow us on social media to get regular updates about the upcoming articles. Have a nice and safe time.','Is Bollywood going to face a tough Star vs. Actor competition in 2021? ','','publish','open','open','','is-bollywood-going-to-face-a-tough-star-vs-actor-competition-in-2021','','https://www.thetvfreak.com/jitendra-kumar-life-biography-and-bollywood-journey/\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/hollywoods-top-10-feel-good-movies-you-must-watch/','2021-03-24 13:42:32','2021-03-24 08:12:32','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5627',0,'post','',0),(5634,12,'2021-03-22 12:41:17','2021-03-22 07:11:17','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another outsider who is busy engraving his name in the world of Bollywood is none other than the talented actor Ali Fazal. From the boy next door to a favourite face of web shows and Hindi movies, the journey has not been really free from struggles.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Early life - Who is Ali Fazal</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ali spent his early life in the state of Uttar Pradesh. His birth was in the capital city of </span><b>Lucknow</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. However, the actor did not have a very peaceful childhood due to the not-so-good relationship with his parents who got divorced when he was an 18-year-old boy.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Firstly, Fazal’s schooling was from</span><b> La Martinere college </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">situated in Lucknow. But soon after, he shifted to his next alma meter, the well-known </span><b>boarding school of Dehradun</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, the Doon School. It was during those days when his passion for acting developed and reportedly he participated in many school plays, delivering admirable performances. Apart from this, the multi-talented Ali had also been a pro in basketball and dreamed of outshining in this field too.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After completing schooling from Dehradun, Fazal shifted to </span><b>Mumbai </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">to pursue his higher studies. He got himself admitted to St. Xavier’s college from where he pursued graduation and obtained a </span><b>bachelors’ degree in economics</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. However, his college days were not as enjoyable as that of us and at the age of 19, he had to take up a job at a call center just to pay his college fee. It used to pay him only </span><b>Rs. 8000 a month</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Last year, Ali tweeted about this which increased our love and respect for him a little more.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Other basic information – Ali Fazal age and physique</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1986 born Ali is currently almost</span><b> 35 years.</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> With a height of about</span><b> 5’10”</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and well-maintained body measurements, he has the perfect body of an actor that fits perfectly with his charming yet cute face.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Ali Fazal friends and family</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As mentioned before, Fazal didn’t grow up in a very happy family. In fact, his childhood had been spent with his grandparents at their house since this mom and dad separated at the time when he was a child. Much is not known about his parents but his father didn\'t live in India and worked in the Middle East. Last year in 2020 amidst the COVID-19 pandemic Ali’s mother passed away because of some health issues.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5637 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Ali-Fazal-biography-and-other-interesting-facts-2.jpg\" alt=\"Ali Fazal father\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>(With His father)</strong></em></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5638 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Ali-Fazal-biography-and-other-interesting-facts-3.jpg\" alt=\"Ali Fazal mother\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>(With His mother)</strong></em></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Regarding his friendships, it is known to many that during the shoots of his film Victoria and Abdul, the actor had developed a very sweet and affectionate bond of friendship with his senior co-actress, the legendary Judi Dench.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He has a very friendly nature and is friends with people from various backgrounds; at least this can be deduced from Ali Fazal Instagram.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5641 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Ali-Fazal-biography-and-other-interesting-facts-6.jpg\" alt=\"ali fazal friends\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5642 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Ali-Fazal-biography-and-other-interesting-facts-7.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5643 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Ali-Fazal-biography-and-other-interesting-facts-8.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><strong>New beginnings with Theatre</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">During his school and college days, the actor had very actively engaged himself in Theatre. It was one of such on-stage performances that grabbed attention and made him make his way to Bollywood. In fact, during his college days, he was a part of a play adapted from </span><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Tempest\"><b>William Shakespeare’s novel, </b><b><i>The Tempest</i></b><b>.</b></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Later the actor said that it was this play that finally urged him to take up acting as a full-time career. He had also been part of the famous Prithvi Theatres for some time.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>A small screen start – Ali Fazal TV shows</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Not any regular Hindi soap opera; in fact, Fazal at the very beginning of his career got the chance to act in a famous American TV miniseries, </span><b><i>Bollywood Hero</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. In 2009, the series aired on the famous American TV channel, IFC. We saw him in the character of an Indian director, </span><b>Monty Kapoor.</b>\r\n<h2><strong>The journey in Bollywood – Ali Fazal movies</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> It was the year 2008 when Ali Fazal started his journey with Hindi movies. His debut had been with a cameo role in the Indian American romcom, </span><b><i>The Other End Of The Line</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. However, it failed to create magic in the box office as well as with the audiences and did not give Fazal much recognition.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In 2009, he finally got the chance to be the lead of a Bollywood movie. It was an erotic thriller, </span><b><i>Ek Tho Chance</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> where we saw the talented actor sharing screen space with other eminent Bollywood personalities like </span><b>Amrita Rao</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><b>Saurabh Shukla</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Though it was basically his proper Bollywood debut and was premiered in a Film Festival in 2009 itself, it reached audiences in the year 2014 when it got released in theatres.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the same year, 2009 Ali first gave his first breakthrough performance in the iconic Raj Kumar Hirani-directed blockbuster comedy film, </span><b><i>3 Idiots</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Though he was cast in a cameo role, he had been highly noticed and received praises from the audiences.</span>\r\n<h3><strong> Watch Fazal’s scene from 3 idiots</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Being an outsider, Ali didn’t have a very smooth career and faced numerous ups and downs to reach the stardom he has today. His next film was released in 2011. It has been the gradually forgettable and box office flop film </span><b><i>Always Kabhi Kabhi</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. With negative reviews and backlashes from the audience Fazal could have stepped backwards and given up on his Bollywood career but he didn’t do so and then the turning point of his journey came in 2013.</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> <strong>Watch a young Fazal in this scene from Always Kabhi Kabhi</strong></span></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RikmHFgvkBY[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In 2013, he successfully gave his first hit </span><b><i>Fukrey</i></b> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">which had been both a commercial as well as a critical success. Even today, several years later, this comedy film is still a favourite among the masses, especially among the youths. It gained so much popularity that in 2017 its sequel </span><b><i>Fukrey Returns</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> was made and it was equally loved by the audiences.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Watch Fazal in this promo from Fukrey</strong></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5HnIMU3kV-w[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After that Ali did not have to look back and appeared in a number of films in lead as well as supporting roles. It is not that all of those films worked and all of his performances had received appreciations; but of course, the talent and potential he has as an artist cannot be at all denied today. Till 2021 he appeared in a number of firms including </span><i>Bobby Jasoos, Sonali Cable Khamoshiya, Happy Bhaag Jaigi, Happy Phir Bhag Jagi, Milan Talkies, Prasshthanaam, House Arrest.</i>\r\n<h3><strong>Watch Fazal in this Sonali cable scene</strong></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JW_WRWpz0cI[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>Brief but significant appearances in Hollywood too!</strong></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5639 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Ali-Fazal-biography-and-other-interesting-facts-4.jpg\" alt=\"ali fazal hollywood\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of those rare Indian actors, who behind leaving a mark in Bollywood by their extraordinary talent had also started working in the Hollywood industry is none other than this </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fukrey</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> actor.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5640 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Ali-Fazal-biography-and-other-interesting-facts-5.jpg\" alt=\"ali fazal hollywood1\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In 2015, he started to work in Hollywood with a cameo role in </span><b><i>Fast and Furious 7</i></b><b>.</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Though it is a cameo role and he had a very brief screen presence, the way Ali portrayed it always leaves a significant impact on the viewers.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Fazal’s scene from First and Furious 7</strong></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FGh1wFYQUWk[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Then he was cast in another British film named </span><b><i>Victoria and Abdul</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> where he was seen as the male lead. It later became an award-winning movie where Ali’s performance had been loved by all.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Watch Fazal in this scene from Victoria and Abdul</strong></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JrvHI1IJ07w[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He had also appeared in another 2015 Indian American film called </span><b><i>For Here Or To Go?</i></b><b>.</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another thriller English movie </span><b><i>Death On The Nile</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, starring Fazal in an important role will be releasing soon.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Some of the notable performances in web series – Ali Fazal web series</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now coming to one of the favourite platforms of today, the digital world where Ali Fazal has made a fanbase greater than many of his contemporary actors.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His first appearance in the web series was in the lead role of </span><b><i>Bang Baaja Baraat</i></b><b>,</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> a Yashraj Both audiences and critics had loved this miniseries which narrated how the two individuals from two different backgrounds fell for each other, decided to get married and how the family came in the way.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Watch Fazal in this Bang Baaja Baarat episode</strong></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lrv2b6KElDc[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Next in 2016, we saw him giving a cameo in the famous miniseries which you can always watch on YouTube and die out in laughter; yes, I am talking about </span><b><i>Sex Chat With Pappu and Papa</i></b><b>.</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Coming to his most loved performances, a performance that gave him the most recognition and proved his capability as a multi-faceted actor is in the Amazon prime series, </span><b><i>Mirzapur</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Words cannot describe how brilliantly Ali had portrayed the challenging role of Guddu Pandit, a character with several shades.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Watch Fazal in this scene from Mirzapur</strong></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KlAewRlNrY8[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In 2019 he appeared in another prime comedy web show </span><b><i>Mind the Malhotras</i></b> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">narrating the tale of a family. Ali had an episodic appearance in this series and had appeared as himself.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> In 2020 we witnessed a totally different version of Ali in the Zee 5 original film or miniseries </span><b><i>Forbidden Love</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. This series which showed the four different stories bound by one common connection-love. The actor had played the character of a gay man. The Storey has been the perfect epitome of current social issues and definitely, Ali’s portrayal of the character has been very life-like.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Lastly, in 2020 the sequel of </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mirzapur</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> was released. It had been the most anticipated series of the year and once again Ali’s performance had been showered with love by the audience as well as critics.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Other works</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In 2016 Ali made his first appearance in a music video </span><b><i>Pyar Maanga Hai</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.  In 2020 he appeared in another one </span><b><i>Aaj Bhi</i></b><b>.</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Also, little do we know but about the beginning of his acting career. He did various TV ads like those of Micromax mobile and Pizza Hut. Also, he was seen in the brand campaign of the online poker platform, Adda52 along with the famous rapper Badshah. He had also appeared in important roles in short films like </span><b><i>According To Plan A, Cheers,</i></b><b> And </b><b><i>The Blind Date.</i></b>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fazal’s A Blind date short film</span></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2XXJShLB76g[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong>A social activist too!</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Also, when it comes to social work and doing something for other people, Ali’s name has always been there. In 2015, he had been a part of the India TV and Fortis campaign. And he involved himself in spreading awareness about cancer. Later he also took part in a musical concert in order to gather funds for the sufferers of the devastating 2015 earthquake of Nepal that destroyed numerous lives.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Achievements</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">All through his career, Ali got lots of love and appreciation for his really praiseworthy works. In 2017, he had been the recipient of the ‘Various 10 actors to watch’ award in the famous Hamptons International Film Festival. For his iconic role of Guddu Pandit From </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mirzapur</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, he had also received a notable nomination in the ‘<a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/2021-golden-globe-awards-nominees-best-actor-in-a-motion-picture/\">Best Actor nomination in 2021</a>.</span>\r\n<h2><strong>Relationship status</strong></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ali Fazal is head over heels in love with the </span><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/pankaj-tripathi-biography-movies-tv-and-awards/\"><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Gangs of Wasseypur</span></i></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> actress </span><b>Richa Chadda.</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Two outsiders of Bollywood who made it big had fallen in love and are together now. The actor had since a long time fallen for her but it was only December 2019 when he proposed his lady love at a very beautiful destination, Maldives. Since then, they have been together and are giving us the major couple goals. The duo had planned to tie the knot last year. But the unfortunate pandemic became the greatest obstacle and thus they are still leading Bachelor lives.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">An uprising actor of Bollywood, Ali Fazal has the potential of being one of the great superstars of the industry one day. We wish to see more of his brilliant works in the upcoming times.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So, this is the content for today. Hope you had a happy reading. We will soon be back with a new update or anything interesting related to the entertainment industry. Don\'t forget to follow us on social media have a nice and safe time.</span>','Mirzapur fame Ali Fazal Bio, Wife, Age, Height, Movies and Tv Shows','','publish','open','open','','mirzapur-fame-ali-fazal-bio-wife-age-height-movies-and-tv-shows','','','2021-04-27 17:29:11','2021-04-27 11:59:11','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5634',0,'post','',0),(5646,12,'2021-04-30 11:43:05','2021-04-30 06:13:05','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The year was 2020 when the South Korean film industry gifted us with, \"Parasite\", one of the best thrillers of all times. A historical achievement it has been for the film as it received the Oscars. While accepting the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/golden-globe-nominations-for-best-director-2021/\"><strong>Golden Globe Awards in 2020</strong>,</a> director Bong Jong exclaimed how by overcoming just the barrier of subtitles or by being habitual in seeing the subtitles along with a movie, one can see some really amazing works of the world.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Till now only 11 international films have been nominated for the best picture in Oscars. Each of them is best and unique and deserves at least once a lifetime watch.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once you come out a bit of your comfort zone and start getting deeper into works of cinema beyond the confinements of Bollywood and Hollywood, you will know that how apt has been Bong Jong Hoo\'s remark. All credits go to the various online streaming platforms which makes these cinematic gems available to us. I am no critic, but we here at TVFreak will try to provide a to-watch guide to explore these international gems.</span>\r\n<h2><b>1. Parasite (2020) | Foreign Language Films</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Country: </b>South Korea</li>\r\n <li><b>Language: </b>Korean</li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 8.6</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on:</b> Amazon Prime Video</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5648 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10-foreign-films-to-watch-right-now-2.jpg\" alt=\"Parasite (2020): 10 foreign films to watch right now (2)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is the story of how the struggling Kim family sees an opportunity when the son starts working for the wealthy Park family. Soon, all of them find a way to work within the same household and start living a parasitic life.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This<strong> Korean movie</strong> Parasite has given Bong more global prominence than his English-language wannabe blockbusters like Snowpiercer making him stand out as one of the greatest directors of his time. From an anti-capitalist theme to everything that <strong>Bong Jong Hoo</strong> tries to project is worth watching and primitively thought-provoking. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">From social class division and climate change to exquisitely designed sets, and watching the ease with which a casual hangout scene mutates, first into a pressurized suspense set-piece and then into horror, and realize you’re in the company of a master filmmaker. His other works such as Memories to Murder, Okja, and Mother will prove how great a director he is.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SEUXfv87Wpk[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>2. Roma (2018)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Country: </b>Mexico</li>\r\n <li><b>Language: </b>Spanish</li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 7.7</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available: </b>on Netflix</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5649 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10-foreign-films-to-watch-right-now-3.jpg\" alt=\"Roma (2018): 10 foreign films to watch right now (3)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">“Roma\'\' shares its name with a neighbourhood in <strong>Mexico City</strong> where families live behind locked gates, and where maids, cooks, and drivers busily keep homes running. Set in the 1970s,<strong> it\'s about a maid</strong> who works in a middle-class white family which is somehow falling apart. Although this backdrop might sound small to some, Alfonso Cuaron uses a large canvas to paint this picture in a black and white tone.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you have seen Cuaron\'s other works like Children of Men and Gravity, you\'ll know that Roma\'s cinematographic excellence is not new but definitely, the panoramic style further enhances the depth of these <strong>\"larger than life\"</strong> characters.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie has <strong>won three Oscars</strong> for best cinematography, for foreign-language films, and the best director.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie is an <strong>intimate, expansive, </strong>and<strong> emotional</strong> portrait of life and definitely a true masterpiece.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OIClGSY5_tY[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>3. Amélie (2001) | Foreign Language Films</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Country: </b>France</li>\r\n <li><b>Language: </b>French</li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 8.3</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on: </b>HBO Max</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5650 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10-foreign-films-to-watch-right-now-4.jpg\" alt=\"Amélie (2001): 10 foreign films to watch right now (4)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is the story of Amélie is an <strong>innocent, introverted, </strong>and<strong> naive girl</strong> in Paris with her own sense of justice. She decides to help those around her and at times mischievous but makes sure to smile on our faces and, along the way, discovers love. So many intricate themes at play, it\'s wrong to call it just a rom-com.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The colours and visuals of this film are also very whimsical. We see paintings and photographs talking to the characters, telling them what they should do. We see green, red, and yellow-themed interiors and atmospheres throughout the film, which gives it a very warm feeling. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\"Amélie is one of those once in a decade comedy which shatters its charms like the pearls from a broken necklace, all more adorable because they are not real,\" wrote Times critic Barbara Ellen</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HUECWi5pX7o[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>4. Pan\'s Labyrinth (2006)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Country: </b>Spain</li>\r\n <li><b>Language: </b>Spanish</li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 8.2</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on:</b> Amazon Prime Video</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5651 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10-foreign-films-to-watch-right-now-5.jpg\" alt=\"Pan\'s Labyrinth (2006): 10 foreign films to watch right now (5)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Pan\'s Labyrinth is a fantasy movie based on historical events and a fairytale that explores fears and wonders, but the real meaning of the movie lies in its ability to bring to light these two human aspects together parallelly. Director Guillermo del Toro is well-known for his ability to combine the fantasy world with our ordinary lives maintaining a thin line that separates the two. Though dark, it is considered a cinematic masterpiece, is supposed to be the best example of his work.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3ARCBVIE_KQ[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>5. Incendies (2010)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Country: </b>Canada</li>\r\n <li><b>Language: </b>French</li>\r\n <li><b>IMDb 8.3</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on:</b> Amazon Prime Video</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5652 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10-foreign-films-to-watch-right-now-6.jpg\" alt=\"Incendies (2010): 10 foreign films to watch right now (6)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you are a mystery &amp; sci-fi movie bug, you are pretty much well accustomed to the works of the filmmaker Denis Villeneuve who has made some of the most visually stunning movies like Arrival and Blade Runner 2049 with a lurking theme of morality wrapped with mystery. Although this 2010 project is no sci-fi but based on the same theme. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">From its arresting opening to its shattering conclusion, the Canadian film Incendies is violent yet emotional film-making of the true sense with a captivating technical fineness, self-confidence without judging the characters. This movie is based on the stage play by Wajdi Mouawad which revolves around Nawal, a dying woman from Lebanon, living in Montreal who leaves separate letters to her twin children Jeanne and Simon to be read after she dies.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Jeanne is to deliver hers to the father who they thought was dead, and Simon is to give his to the brother about whom they never knew. The siblings travel to their mother\'s homeland, where they each experience acts of violence, come to know family history and have revelations about themselves.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XJ69WnwvZhE[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>6. A Separation (2011)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Country: </b>Iran</li>\r\n <li><b>Language: </b>Persian</li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 8.3</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5653 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10-foreign-films-to-watch-right-now-7.jpg\" alt=\"A Separation (2011)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A Separation is a 2011 Iranian drama film that won the Oscars Best International feature film in 2012.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The plot revolves around a married couple who are faced with a difficult decision that is either to improve the life of their child by moving to another country or to stay in Iran and look after a deteriorating parent who has Alzheimer\'s disease.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Background score is almost missing in the film, which makes viewers’ attention towards details in particular frames. The movie starts at a slow pace like any other Asghar Farhadi movie and then slowly picks up the pace and unstoppably races to the finish breaking you down into tiny little bits.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=58Onuy5USTc[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>7. City of God (2002)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Country: </b>Brazil</li>\r\n <li><b>Language: </b>Portuguese</li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 8.6</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on:</b> <a href=\"https://www.primevideo.com/?ref_=dvm_pds_amz_in_as_s_g_72|m_fQQR2NKbc_c386629063601\">Amazon Prime Video</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5654 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10-foreign-films-to-watch-right-now-8.jpg\" alt=\"City of God (2002)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Based on the real-life story, the movie is about two boys who are brought up in a violent neighbourhood of Rio de Janeiro. They adopt diverse professional paths, with one of them becoming a photographer and the other boy becoming a drug dealer.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie is beautifully narrated and presented in chapters. Initial chapters focus on the character build-up of every main character, the middle ones are based on the massive drug empire and how it affects the personal lives of each character, and the last ones include typical gang rivalry and the rise of the narrator of the movie as a daring &amp; successful photographer. Shot mostly in a documentary style it\'s one of the best in its genre and it\'s just a delight to watch.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dcUOO4Itgmw[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>8. Chungking Express (1994) | Best foreign films</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Country: </b>Hongkong</li>\r\n <li><b>Language: </b>Mandarin</li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 8.1</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on:</b> Criterion collection</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5655 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10-foreign-films-to-watch-right-now-9.jpg\" alt=\"Chungking Express (1994)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chunking Express is an interwoven love story about two policemen based in Hong Kong where one of them falls in love with a waitress and another with a drug dealer.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Directed by brilliant filmmaker Wong Kar Wai, this movie makes a long-lasting impression and focuses on the little moment that we often tend to ignore in our daily lives. Vibrant colours and the background score fit the movie perfectly also exploring the voidness experienced by the characters. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Also, watch In The Mood for Love by Wong Kar Wai.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bjd7PFf_TFw[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>9. Shoplifters (2018)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Country: </b>Japan</li>\r\n <li><b>Language: </b>Japanese</li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 7.9</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on: </b>Netflix</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5656 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10-foreign-films-to-watch-right-now-10.jpg\" alt=\"Shoplifters (2018)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Shoplifters, a Japanese Oscar nominee for the 2019 Best Foreign Language Film and winner of the Cannes Film Festival Palme d\'Or, is a complex and delicate movie that looks at how people manage the difficult project of simply getting through life. What at first look seems to be the story of an extended working-class poor family struggling to make ends meet with love and affection. Later it reveals the unlikely origins of how those people all ended up together. With clear-eyed compassion, the movie looks at human need, the law, murder, child abuse, and sex work. </span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rwcb5ki1f-4[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>10. Portrait of a lady on Fire (2019) | Foreign Language Films</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Country: </b>France</li>\r\n <li><b>Language: </b>French</li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 8.1</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on:</b> Amazon Prime Video</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5647 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/10-foreign-films-to-watch-right-now-1.jpg\" alt=\"Portrait of a lady on Fire (2019)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Firstly, This french masterpiece is based in 18th century France, on a remote island in Brittany, where a female painter is hired for a wedding portrait of a reluctant young woman by her mother. The young bride refuses to be painted as she isn’t willing to get married. The painter must observe her in secret to paint her without her knowledge.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Secondly, This movie is a slow-burn romance and slowly draws you in. It portrays a striking balance between silence and words, light and darkness, intimacy and distance. The brilliant screenplay allows you to observe two people as they slowly fall in love with each other.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R-fQPTwma9o[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Finally, With these, we end the list of the best foreign films – missing which you are gonna miss something really great in life. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So, this is the Foreign Language Films. Hope you had a happy reading. We will soon be back with a new update or anything interesting related to the entertainment industry. So, Don\'t forget to follow us on social media and have a nice and safe time.</span>','List Of Top 10 Best Foreign Language Films to Watch Right Now','','publish','open','open','','list-of-top-10-best-foreign-language-films-to-watch-right-now','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/golden-globe-nominations-for-best-director-2021/','2021-04-30 16:01:57','2021-04-30 10:31:57','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5646',0,'post','',0),(5660,13,'2021-03-24 17:20:16','2021-03-24 11:50:16','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Oscar Nominations 2021 announcement took place this 15th March and was hosted by </span><b>Priyanka Chopra Jonas</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><b>Nick Jonas</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Many of the Golden Globe nominees made it to the Oscars, many of them didn’t. Also, a lot of new faces have been nominated for this year’s Academy Award. So let’s take a look at some of the major categories and their nominees of the </span><b>93rd Academy Award</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. </span>\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/golden-globe-nominations-for-best-director-2021/\"><b>Best Director Nominees 2021</b></a></h2>\r\n<h3><b>5. David Fincher</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: Mank</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.0</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: The Game, Fight Club, Gone Girl</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5234\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Golden-Globe-Awards-Nominees-Best-Director-1-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"2021 Golden Globe Awards Nominees Best Director\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">David Fincher (58) is one of the well-known directors in Hollywood right now. Though </span><b>psycho-thriller</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is considered to be his trademark, he has directed two biography films in his career till now, including the one for which he is nominated in the category of best director this year. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mank is the biopic of </span><b>Herman J. Mankiewicz</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, the great visionary behind the timeless movie </span><b><i>Citizen Kane</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. The other biography movie that got Fincher nominated at the Oscar was </span><b>The Social Network</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (2010), a biopic of </span><b>Mark Zuckerberg</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and his story behind creating Facebook. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fincher was also nominated in the category of the best achievement in directing for the movie </span><b>The Curious Case of Benjamin Button</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (2008).</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He lost his first Oscar to Danny Boyle (Slumdog Millionaire) and the second one to Tom Hooper (The King\'s Speech). </span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aSfX-nrg-lI[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>4. <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/golden-globe-winner-chloe-zhao-career-movies-and-tv-shows/\">Chloé Zhao </a></b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: Nomadland</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.6</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: The Rider</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5235\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Golden-Globe-Awards-Nominees-Best-Director-2-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"2021 Golden Globe Awards Nominees Best Director\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chloe Zhao (38) is this year’s Golden Globe winner who also made it to the Oscars. Nomadland is her third feature film and the first one to have a well-known actress in the leading role. This is her first time getting nominations in the Oscar as well.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Other than the nomination for best director Chloe also has 3 other nominations in the 93rd Oscars. </span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6sxCFZ8_d84[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>3. Emerald Fennell </b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: Promising Young Woman</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.5</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5236\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Golden-Globe-Awards-Nominees-Best-Director-3-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"2021 Golden Globe Awards Nominees Best Director\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If Emerald Fennell (35) wins this year\'s Oscar, it will become history. Because Promising Young Woman is this actress-turned-director’s </span><b>directorial debut </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">which also has earned her 2 additional Oscar nominations. She is also the youngest nominee in this category this year.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eJ5DZ4Ny-rI[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>2. Lee Isaac Chung</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: Minari</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.7</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5692\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Oscar-Nominations-1-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"Oscar Nominations (1) Lee Isaac Chung\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Minari is an amazing coming of age story about family-bond, love, and hope.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Though Lee Isaac Chung (42) has directed several movies before, Minari is the most successful one in his career. He is one of the few directors of Asian descent to be nominated in the category of best director. He has also been nominated in the category of the best screenplay. </span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KQ0gFidlro8[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>1. Thomas Vinterberg</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: Another Round</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.8</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: The Hunt, Far from the Madding Crowd</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5693\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Oscar-Nominations-2-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"Thomas Vinterberg ; Oscar Nominations (2)\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Thomas Vinterberg (51) is a Danish director and this is his first Oscar nomination.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another world is a comedy-drama where</span><b> Mads Mikkelsen</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> unleashed his full acting power with the help of the director. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There is another movie of Thomas where Mads Mikkelsen starred. The movie is called T</span><b>he Hunt</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (2012).</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kAIOWPml_cc[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<b>Oscar Best Director Prediction: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So this is 2021’s Best director Oscar list of nominations. 3 of the Golden Globe Nominees made it to the Oscars, including the winner. This is the first time in Oscar history that two female directors and two directors of Asian descent got nominated in the best director category. Though I am rooting for David Fincher, my prediction is that One that won the Golden Globe will take the Oscar home as well. </span>\r\n<h2><b>Oscar-Nominated Actress in a Leading Role 2021</b></h2>\r\n<h3><b>5. Andra Day</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: The United States vs. Billie Holiday</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 6.3</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5428\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Golden-Globe-Awards-Nominees-Best-Performance-by-an-Actress-1-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"Andra Day 2021 Golden Globe Awards Nominees Best Performance by an Actress (1)\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Andra Day (36) is mostly known for her singing career. She has previously voiced a character in </span><b>Cars 3</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and played a minor role in </span><b>Marshall</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. So honestly speaking The United States vs. Billie Holiday is the first major film in her career. She has already won a Golden Globe for Best Performance by an Actress in a Motion Picture - Drama. We have to wait and see if she takes the Oscar home or not.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xdljv_PRZJs[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>4. Carey Mulligan</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: Promising Young Woman</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: An Education, Never Let Me Go, The Great Gatsby</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5429\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Golden-Globe-Awards-Nominees-Best-Performance-by-an-Actress-2-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"Carey Mulligan, 2021 Golden Globe Awards Nominees Best Performance by an Actress (2)\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Carey Mulligan (35) is a beautiful British actress who we mostly see playing, </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">how do I say this</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, rather placid characters. But in Promising Young Woman, we see a different side of Carey Mulligan which has won the hearts of both critics and audiences. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Carey Mulligan was previously nominated for an Oscar in the same category she is nominated this year for </span><b>An Education</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. She lost her Oscar to </span><b>Sandra Bullock</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (The Blind Side).</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eJ5DZ4Ny-rI[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>3. Frances McDormand </b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: Nomadland</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: Fargo, Mississippi Burning</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5430\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Golden-Globe-Awards-Nominees-Best-Performance-by-an-Actress-3-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"Frances McDormand 2021 Golden Globe Awards Nominees Best Performance by an Actress (3)\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Frances McDormand (63) is a 6-time Oscar-nominated and 2 times </span><b>Oscar-winning </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">actress. And this year, she has been nominated in the category of best leading actress for a movie that has 5 other Oscar nominations and already took home 2 Golden Globes including Best Motion Picture - Drama. Whether she wins this year or not, there is no denying that she is one of the best actresses of her generation. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Her previous two Oscar wins were both for the best performance by an actress in a leading role for </span><b>Fargo</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (1996) and </span><b>Three Billboards Outside Ebbing, Missouri</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (2017).</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6sxCFZ8_d84[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>2. Vanessa Kirby</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: Pieces of a Woman</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.1 </b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: Mission: Impossible - Fallout</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5431\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-Golden-Globe-Awards-Nominees-Best-Performance-by-an-Actress-4-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"Vanessa Kirby, 2021 Golden Globe Awards Nominees Best Performance by an Actress (4)\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Vanessa Kirby (32) is the youngest nominee in this category this year. The movie for which she got her nomination tells a tragic story of a mother who lost her child giving birth. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Venessa Kirby has previously won a BAFTA for Best Supporting Actress in the TV series </span><b>The Crown</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (2016).</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1zLKbMAZNGI[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>1. Viola Davis</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: Ma Rainey\'s Black Bottom</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.1</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: The Help, Fences</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5542\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Top-10-Highest-paid-Bollywood-Actresses-of-2020-10-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"Viola Davis  : Top 10 Highest paid Bollywood Actresses of 2020 (10)\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Viola Davis (55) is 4 times </span><b>Oscar-nominated</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and a one-time </span><b>Oscar-winning</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> actress. By her nomination of this year, she made a record by being the</span><b> most nominated black actress</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in Oscar History. She won her oscar in 2017 for the movie </span><b>Fences</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in the category of best supporting actress. This is her first nomination in the category of the best leading actress. She is also one of the two black actresses to ever get nominated in both the supporting and leading actress category. The other one is </span><b>Whoopi Goldberg</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ord7gP151vk[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Her previous two supporting actress nominations were for </span><b>Doubt</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (2008)— lost to </span><b>Penélope Cruz</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (Vicky Cristina Barcelona) and </span><b>The Help</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (2011)— lost to</span><b> Octavia Spencer</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (The Help)</span>\r\n\r\n<b>2021 Oscars best actress prediction: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">All 5 of the nominees are from the Golden Globes. Two </span><b>Triple Crown of Acting</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> winners, one two-time nominated, and two totally newbies. Each of these actresses has the potential to be the next Oscar winner. </span>\r\n\r\n<b>Jennifer Hudson</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> won both Golden Globe and Oscar in 2007 for </span><b>Dream Girls</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> by portraying a singer (it was in a supporting character though). Andra Day can be the same. </span><b>Frances McDormand</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> on the other hand lost all of her Oscars for supporting actress roles but never lost one in the Leading role. But considering the opinions of critics in famous magazines, my votes will be on Viola Davis and Carey Mulligan. </span>\r\n<h2><b>Oscar-Nominated Actor in a Leading Role 2021</b></h2>\r\n<h3><b>5. Anthony Hopkins</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: The Father</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 8.2</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: The Silence of the Lambs, Thor Trilogy</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5394\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/1-5-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"2021 Golden Globe Awards Nominees: Anthony Hopkins\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We mostly know him for his outstanding performance as </span><b>Dr. Hannibal Lecter</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Anthony Hopkins is 83 now, and he is still kickin’. This actor has </span><b>6 Oscar nominations</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in total including this year’s nomination. Though except the first time, he lost all of them. He was also nominated in the 92nd Academy Award in the category of best performance by an actor in a supporting role but lost to </span><b>Brad Pitt</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (fair enough).</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4TZb7YfK-JI[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>4. <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/chadwick-boseman-black-panther-star-dies-at-43biography-and-movies/\">Chadwick Boseman</a></b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: Ma Rainey\'s Black Bottom</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: Black Panther, 5 Da Blood</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5398\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/5-4-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"2021 Golden Globe Awards Nominees: Chadwick Boseman (1976-2020)\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It is very sad to see such a potential actor leave for good so early. Ma Rainey’s Black Bottom is Chadwick Boseman’s final work. In this film, he played a sort of anti-protagonist character, not like </span><b>King T’Challa</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> at all. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He has already won the Golden Globe Award. He is also the </span><b>7th actor</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><b>1st black actor</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> to get a posthumous nomination at the Oscar. </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">May he rest in peace.</span></i>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ord7gP151vk[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>3. Gary Oldman </b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: Mank</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: The Batman Trilogy, Léon: The Professional</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5395\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2-5-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"2021 Golden Globe Awards Nominees: Gary Oldman\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Gary Oldman (63) is the second oldest nominee in this category. He has played all sorts of characters in his career— a real-life figure, a police officer, a fantasy villain, a gangster mafia, from east to west and north to south he has done it all. And for his outstanding performance, he also won an Oscar for a leading acting role in 2018 for </span><b>Darkest Hour</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (2017). He was previously nominated in the same category in 2012 for the movie </span><b>Tinker Tailor Soldier Spy</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (2011) but lost to </span><b>Jean Dujardin</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (The Artist).</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aSfX-nrg-lI[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>2. Riz Ahmed </b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: Sound of Metal</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.8</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: Nightcrawler, Rogue One: A Star Wars Story</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5397\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/4-5-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"2021 Golden Globe Awards Nominees: Riz Ahmed\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Riz Ahmed (38) is a British actor of Pakistani descent. He has already taken part in one of the biggest movie franchisees— Star Wars. He is also one of the </span><b>Muslim actors</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> to get nominated at the Oscars. Sound of Metal is his breakthrough movie where he plays the role of a heavy metal drummer who is losing her hearing power because of chronic high-volume sound conditions. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Riz has won an Emmy in 2017 for Outstanding Lead Actor in a Limited Series or Movie in </span><b>The Night Of</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (2016).</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VFOrGkAvjAE[/embedyt]\r\n<h3><b>1. Steven Yeun </b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: Minari</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: Burning, Okja, I Origins</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5694\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Oscar-Nominations-3-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"Steven Yeun , Oscar Nominations (3)\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Steven Yeun (37) is the youngest man in this category. You may know him from</span><b> The Walking Dead</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> but he has appeared in many famous Korean movies like </span><b>Okja</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (directed by Bong Joon Ho) and </span><b>Burning</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is his first Oscar nomination. He is also one of the few Asian actors to get an Oscar nomination. </span>\r\n\r\n<b>2021 Oscars Best Actor Predictions: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">All of them were Golden Globe Nominees this year, except Steven Yeun. Among them, three are first-time nominees and the other two already have an Oscar. My prediction is that the Oscar will go to either Chadwick Boseman or Gary Oldman.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KQ0gFidlro8[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Oscar Nominations in Best Achievement in Cinematography 2021</b></h2>\r\n<h3><b>5. Sean Bobbitt </b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: Judas and the Black Messiah</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.6</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: 12 Years a Slave, Shame</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5695\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Oscar-Nominations-4-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"Sean Bobbitt  Oscar Nominations (4)\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sean Bobbitt seems like a </span><b>Steve McQueen</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> favorite. He has done several films with this famous director. This is his first Oscar nomination. </span>\r\n<h3><b>4. Erik Messerschmidt</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: Mank</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: Iron Man 2, Tomorrowland, Ant-Man</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5696\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Oscar-Nominations-5-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"Erik Messerschmidt  Oscar Nominations (5)\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Erik Messerschmidt (40), Mank is his third time working with director </span><b>David Fincher</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. His previous works with David were </span><b>Gone Girl</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><b>Mindhunters</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (TV Show). He also has worked in two MCU movies. This is his first nomination at the Oscars.</span>\r\n<h3><b>3. Dariusz Wolski</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: News of the World</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 6.8</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: The Mexican, Exodus: Gods and Kings, The Martian</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5697\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Oscar-Nominations-6-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"Dariusz Wolski , Oscar Nominations (6)\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dariusz Wolski (64) has worked in many films that starred </span><b>Johnny Depp</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, including three </span><b>Pirates of the Caribbean</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> movies. He is a Polish cinematographer who has worked in one of Eminem’s music videos, Stan. Though he has done many great movies in his career, this is his first Oscar nomination. </span>\r\n<h3><b>2. Joshua James Richards</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: Nomadland</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: The Rider</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5698\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Oscar-Nominations-7-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"Joshua James Richards, Oscar Nominations (7)\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Joshua James Richards is an American cinematographer. Nomadland is his fourth feature-length film. But he has another identity. He is married to the director</span><b> Chloe Zhao</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Looks like the husband and wife duo is on fire this year.</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> This is the first time getting Oscar nominations for both of them.</span>\r\n<h3><b>1. Phedon Papamichael </b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Nominated For: The Trial of the Chicago 7</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.8</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Other Notable Movies: Identity, The Pursuit of Happyness, Ford v Ferrari, The Huntsman: Winter\'s War</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-5699\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Oscar-Nominations-8-300x240.jpg\" alt=\"Phedon Papamichael , Oscar Nominations (8)\" width=\"300\" height=\"240\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Phedon Papamichael (59) is the only cinematographer in this category this year who has a previous Oscar nomination. Phedon was nominated in 2014 in the category of Best Achievement in Cinematography for the movie </span><b>Nebraska </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">(2013). He lost his Oscar to </span><b>Emmanuel Lubezki</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (Gravity). He is also the only one in this category who has got the nomination in the BAFTA this year.</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Oscar 2021 Best Cinematography prediction:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> No matter who wins this year’s Oscar, it’s gonna be history. But I will place my bet on Erik Messerschmidt (Mank).</span>\r\n<h2><b>Conclusion:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So this was 2021 Oscar Nominations. Oscar 2020 winners in these respective categories were— </span><b>Bong Joon Ho, Renée Zellweger, Joaquin Phoenix, and Roger Deakins</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (1917). They all more or less added new records to the history and we can expect the same from this year’s nominees as well. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So let us know about your Oscar predictions and for who you are rooting to win. </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">May the best person wins. </span></i>','Oscar Nominations 2021— Best Director, Actress, Actor and Cinematographer','','publish','open','open','','oscar-nominations-2021-best-director-actress-actor-and-cinematographer','','','2021-04-12 12:17:37','2021-04-12 06:47:37','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5660',0,'post','',0),(5662,12,'2021-07-03 22:15:59','2021-07-03 16:45:59','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Where mainstream Bollywood aims for the box office hits the regional non-Hindi-speaking film industry aims for cinematic excellence. When talking about the evolution of Indian cinema in the last decade, it will be wrong not to consider the contribution of the regional non-Hindi movies as they are way more progressive, thought-provoking, and content-driven rather than star-driven. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Thanks to the rise of OTT platforms and the lockdown that the millennials of today got to explore the regional cinema from Kashmir to Kanyakumari to truly appreciate its worth. Here I have tried to chalk out a list of few regional cinematic gems in the last few years (in no particular order). I know I will have missed a lot of great movies but I think that should be for you to explore!</span>\r\n<h2><b> Nagarkirtan (2017)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Language: Bengali</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 8.6</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on Hoichoi</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6589 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Best-Regionalmovie-10.jpg\" alt=\"Nagarkirtan (2017)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Acclaimed Bengali director Kaushik Ganguly\'s brutal love story between Puti and Madhu da played by Riddhi Sen and Ritwick Chakraborty has totally succeeded in showing the plight of the transgender community what they face in their day to day lives.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie is a true reflection of society and the ending leaves you shattered and hollow from inside. The story which is so different from the modern-day films about queer love shows how progressive is the Bengali Films Industry and truly deserves the National Award.</span>\r\n<h2><b> Village Rockstars ( 2017)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Language: Assamese</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 7.6</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on Netflix</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6580 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Best-Regionalmovie-1.jpg\" alt=\"Village Rockstars ( 2017)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This critically acclaimed and award-winning Assamese movie was India\'s official entry into the 91st Academy Awards. But, unfortunately, it didn\'t make it to the final nominations. With a backdrop of a small village of Chaygaon in Assam, it is the story of a ten-year-old girl Dhunu who wishes to own a guitar and make her own rock band despite the fact that she belongs to a very poor family where getting a square meal a day is quite a deal.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dhunu saves money to fulfill her wish but due to her financial and social constraints and crisis she has to set her priorities and forego her dream. Director Rima Das has single-handedly shown the life of real rural Assam and the hardships they face.</span>\r\n<h2><b> Super Deluxe ( 2019)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Language: Malayalam</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 8.3</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on Netflix</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6581 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Best-Regionalmovie-2.jpg\" alt=\"Super Deluxe ( 2019)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This Malayalee movie directed by Thiagarajan Kumararaja is an anthology thriller with four subplots all connected together at the end. What they have in common is the fact that they have committed a sin as perceived by society.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> With vivid colors, still, camera shots, wonderful casting including Fahaad Faasil and Vijay Setupathi the movie reflects a society with an amalgamation of subtle humor. Vijay Setupathi\'s role as a transwoman is something that will blow your mind! As you start watching the movie, it will take no time for you to get engrossed in the characters and empathize with them.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3-Xq_Zz3nPA[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b> Aamis ( 2019)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Language: Assamese</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 8</b></li>\r\n <li><b>( Currently unavailable in any major streaming platform)</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6582 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Best-Regionalmovie-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another Assamese film that deserves to be on this list is Bhaskar Hazarika\'s Aamis. The title means meat eater. This is one of those unique love stories you will encounter which is really dark and sensuous. It revolves around the sensuous relationship between Nirmali, a married doctor, and Sumon, a Ph.D. scholar, all centered around their love for unusual meat.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Filled with visual metaphors and psychedelic scenes and intense soundtrack, the movie dives deep into the human psyche with its art without letting us judge the characters.</span>\r\n<h2><b> Court (2014)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Language: Marathi</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB 7.7</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on Netflix</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6583 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Best-Regionalmovie-4.jpg\" alt=\"Court (2014)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chaitanya Tamhane\'s directorial debut is about a Dalit musician and teacher named Narayan Kamble who has been falsely accused as a sewer worker committed suicide after being inspired by his song.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This Mumbai<a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/courtroom-movies-based-on-real-life-stories/\"> courtroom drama</a> starts at a slow pace with but as it proceeds, it slowly engulfs you with its screenplay. The movie will make you question the tyrannical system as it showcases the endless delays of justice one has to suffer in this system.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4sc8z7zav9A[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b> \'96 (2018)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Language: Tamil</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 8.6</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on YouTube, MX player, Jio cinema</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6584 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Best-Regionalmovie-5.jpg\" alt=\"\'96 (2018) movie\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">C Prem Kumar\'s 96 is a warm story of two childhood friends Ram ( played by Vijay Setupathi) and Jaanu ( played by Trisha Krishnan). They parted from each other, led by their destiny. The two sweethearts meet after 22 years in the reunion of the batch of \'96 but still manages to spell their warmth and magic.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This melancholic tale is a tribute to unconditional love and taps into nostalgia to leave us with happy associations with our past and is definitely a delight to watch.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r0synl-lI4I[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b> Angamaly Dairies (2017)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Language: Malayalam</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 8</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on Netflix</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6585 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Best-Regionalmovie-6.jpg\" alt=\"Angamaly Dairies (2017)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Firstly, Lijo George Pellissery\'s one of the other gems is Angamaly Dairies which is about Vincent Pepe ( played by Anthony Varghese) who wants to be a powerful leader of a righteous gang in Angamaly.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With 86 new cast, this movie has received massive acclaim due to its strong portrayal of masculinity, action sequences, and small-town gang wars and even came to be known as Gangs of Wasseypur of the south. Lijo George Pellissery has gifted us with few exceptional cinematic gems like Ee Ma Yu and the most recent Jallikattu.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4yRBJCrjabU[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b> Sairat (2016)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Language: Marathi</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 8.3</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on YouTube</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6586 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Best-Regionalmovie-7.jpg\" alt=\"Sairat (2016)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Nagraj Manjule\'s both critically acclaimed and commercially successful love story. It is a proper take on the caste discrimination existing in our society. When a low caste fisherman\'s son, Parshya falls in love with Archi, who happens to be the daughter of a wealthy businessman, they are opposed by society. And they have no other option than to elope and lead a new life in Hyderabad until an unexpected turn.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Finally, the movie has drama, songs, and dance but will leave you shattered by the end of the movie and will make you think</span>\r\n<h2><b> Baishe Shrabon (2011)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Language: Bengali</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 8.1</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on Disney+Hotstar</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6587 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Best-Regionalmovie-8.jpg\" alt=\"Baishe Shrabon (2011)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">An extremely compelling and thought-provoking film from West Bengal that is going to leave you complex is Shrijit Mukherjee\'s Bishe Shrabon.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It focuses on several murders in Kolkata where notes left at the crime scene is the written verse of Bengali poets and these come as clues for the police and how they come to the bottom of the case is what will transfix you. Even though the film is pitched loud, its integration of Bengali poetry and crime thriller will truly excite you.</span>\r\n<h2><b> Kumbalangi Nights (2019)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Language: Malayalam</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDB: 8.6</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on Amazon Prime Video</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6588 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Best-Regionalmovie-9.jpg\" alt=\"Kumbalangi Nights (2019)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Firstly, The story of four brothers and their character dynamics vividly portrays the beauty of Kerala and stunning cinematography embedded with a soulful soundtrack, based on the fishing hamlet of Kumbalangi. The first half of the movie is more character-driven. And the latter half is when the story starts unfolding and picks up its pace.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3P4BFBSafF0[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Secondly, The tense and the surprising climax is dealt with in a comical tone. The broken house both metaphorically and literally ends up harboring lots of love while the opposite happens to the other family we see. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Still waiting for what…go and give these cinematic gems a watch and then suggest them to your friends and family. I bet by the time you complete this list, you will be in love with the diversity and horizon regional cinema possess.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So, this is the content for today. Hope you had a happy reading. We will soon be back with something more interesting about the entertainment industry.  </span>','10 Indian Regional movies you need to watch right now!','','publish','open','open','','10-indian-regional-movies-you-need-to-watch-right-now','','','2021-07-03 22:09:52','2021-07-03 16:39:52','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5662',0,'post','',0),(5665,12,'2021-03-31 09:00:43','2021-03-31 03:30:43','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of the most well-known Bollywood directors, Karan Johar is now all set to be the godfather of another star kid, Shanaya Kapoor. Seems like the director did not pay heeds to comments like ‘flag bearer of nepotism or the entire debate of <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/nepotism-and-favouritism-in-bollywood-star-kids-vs-outsiders/\">nepotism</a> that has arisen surrounding him after the unfortunate demise of the </span><i style=\"font-weight: inherit;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chichhore</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> actor Sushant Singh Rajput.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span><b>Who is this Shanaya Kapoor?</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Shanaya hails from the famous <strong>Anil-Bonney Kapoor</strong> clan of the Hindi film industry. She is the daughter of <strong>Sanjay Kapoor</strong>, a talented and known face from the glamorous world of Bollywood. He had been a debutant of 1995 and is known for movies like </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Prem, Julie, Kartavya, Lust stories, </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">and so on. She is the nephew of Bollywood biggies like <strong>Boney Kapoor</strong> and <strong>Anil Kapoor</strong> while other famous faces such as <strong>Sonam Kapoor, Arjun Kapoor, Jahnhvi Kapoor</strong> are her <strong>first cousins</strong>.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5668 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Shanaya-Kapoor-4.jpg\" alt=\"Shanaya Kapoor karan johar nepotism\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We have already seen her in the Recent Netflix reality TV series </span><strong><i>Fabulous lives Bollywood wives</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, a sneak peak in the personal and professional lives of the better halves of Bollywood stars like Sanjay Kapoor and Chunky Pandey. Technically, it has not been her debut as it has been more of a documentary or reality kind of thing where we saw the real Shanaya Kapoor and not the actress aspect of her. She had been seen sharing the screen along with her mother Mandeep Sandhu. </span>\r\n<h2><b>The announcement</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5667 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Shanaya-Kapoor-3.jpg\" alt=\"Shanaya Kapoor karan johar\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now, this pretty face is going to be launched in Bollywood. And this will be done by another of <strong>KJo’s Dharma film</strong> <strong>ventures</strong>, a debut of dreams that every aspiring star desires to get. On March 22 the director on his Instagram handle had made this announcement. He said about the star kid joining his agency and embarking upon her journey in the universe of Bollywood. <em>He also wrote that Shanaya will be starting to shoot for her film in July.</em></span><em> </em>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/CMtctiNp4xA/?igshid=o8wc6y3wbkmw\r\n<h2><b>Is Shanaya Kapoor going to have a successful debut?</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Karan Johar more than anything is famous for launching star kids. Many of them he launched like <strong>Alia Bhatt</strong>, <strong>Varun Dhawan, Ishan Khattar</strong> are eminent Bollywood actors of today who have proved their worth several times. But, on the other hand, star kids like <strong>Janhvi Kapoor</strong> and <strong>Ananya Pandey</strong> introduced by him though had received stardom are still often criticized for being just a nepotism product and not possessing sufficient acting skills.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> However, it cannot be denied that all of them had grand box-office hit debuts. But since last year the debates on nepotism have become more intense; the result being <strong>Alia Bhaat’s </strong></span><strong><i>Sadak 2</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> becoming the <strong>most disliked</strong> and hated movie of the year. Seems like audiences now are wishing to see and praise more content-driven stuff rather than movies with just glamorous and expensive sets and looks.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Till now we don’t know in what kind of movie Shanaya will be launched or opposite whom she is going to act. We are not here to speak more against or for nepotism. And with a neutral mindset, we wish the upcoming actress all the wishes and luck for her new beginnings. Only time will reveal the future now!</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span><b>Opposite whom?</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> As mentioned, there is still no official or confirmed report on which actors are going to share the screen space with <strong>Kapoor</strong>. But according to a report of Bollywood Hungama, her debut is going to be with another debutant actor <strong>Lakshaya Lalwani</strong> and the </span><strong><i>Guilty</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> fame </span><strong>Gurfateh Pirzada.</strong>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span><b>Public reactions for Shanaya Kapoor</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> The announcement has not gone very well with most of the netizens. There had been continuous trolling of Karan Johar for doing the same. The post became flooded with hate comments like </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bollywood se bahar bhi logo ko chance to, Chal nikal Karan Johar, She is beautiful but please search for true talent, Aur ek talentless kid, How much money do you get to launch star kids?</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and so on. People even started making memes for expressing dislike against it.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5669 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Shanaya-Kapoor-5.jpg\" alt=\" karan johar\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5670 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Shanaya-Kapoor-1.jpg\" alt=\" karan johar nepotism\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A comparatively very small proportion of the public reacted positively and wished the actress all the best for her new Bollywood career.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span><b>Shanaya Kapoor’s popularity</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">People may judge her for being a star kid. But by now she has definitely become a fashion icon with close to attaining <strong>600K followers on Instagram</strong> along with a blue tick on her account.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Conclusion</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Lastly, there is nothing more to say. As an audience, all I can say is, if the film’s concept is something really good or innovative instead of having a cringy storyline, no one can be stopped from loving or admiring it.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So, this is the content for today. Hope you had a happy reading. We will soon be back with something more interesting about the entertainment industry.</span>','The nest star kid in line – to be launched by KJo!','','publish','open','open','','the-nest-star-kid-in-line-to-be-launched-by-kjo','','','2021-03-30 22:39:36','2021-03-30 17:09:36','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5665',0,'post','',0),(5673,12,'2021-05-03 09:00:29','2021-05-03 03:30:29','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Biopics or biographical dramas have been one of the most favourite genres of Bollywood. From cricketer to the teacher, from Prime Minister to boxer, the inspirational stories of people from different backgrounds have always been narrated extraordinarily by Bollywood and naturally have been showered with love and appreciation from the audience.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Today Tvfreak.com</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> presents to you some of the best biopics ever made in Bollywood, missing which you will really miss out on something great in life.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Neerja | Biopics in Bollywood</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 7.7</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director</strong>:  Ram Madhvani</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Year</strong>: 2016</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available</strong> <strong>on</strong>: Disney+Hotstar</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5674 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/5-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What’s special about this biopic is that it’s the story of no celebrity or well-known personality but is the courageous tale of an ordinary girl, a flight attendant named <strong>Neerja Bhanot</strong> who sacrificed her own life to save the passengers of her flight that had been hijacked. It’s one of the best performances Sonam Kapoor has given in her entire career, making her win several accolades.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Deservingly, the movie has been the recipient of the best feature film award. Altogether it has been the recipient of around 31 awards in various categories. Every aspect of this Hindi film from direction to acting to the screenplay is praiseworthy and brings us tears every time we watch it.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hr0TjEHuZqE[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>The Legend of Bhagat Singh | Biopics in Bollywood</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 8.1</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director</strong>: Rajkumar Santoshi</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Year</strong>: 2002</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> MX Player</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5675 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/1-1.jpg\" alt=\"Some must-watch Bollywood biopics : The Legend of Bhagat Singh:\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The inspirational story of a 23-old-year <strong>freedom fighter Bhagat Singh</strong> who sacrificed his own life during the course of the struggle for freedom of the country is the perfect epitome of how a biopic should be and is still loved and admired by current generations.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">While <strong>Ajay Devgan</strong> looked perfect in the lead character, unblemished direction and execution make our eyes glued to the screen. From dialogues to action, from background scores to editing, the film grabbed about nine awards in the year 2003.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5RI3PrGgUMc[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Dangal:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong> – 8.4</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director</strong> – Nitesh Tiwari</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Year</strong> - 2016</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Netflix</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2834 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1-min-9.jpg\" alt=\"Dangal\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong> Haryana’s Phogat sisters</strong> mainly, <strong>Geeta Phogat</strong> and <strong>Babita Phogat</strong> are the best female wrestlers of India and have won gold and silver medals for the country in international championships. However, they did not receive the appreciation or love they deserve until their biopic was released.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dangal has been one of the best sports biopics of the decade. While<strong> Amir Khan</strong> in the role of <strong>Mahavir Singh Phogat</strong> stole the show, <strong>Sakshi Tanwaar</strong> as his wife, <strong><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/fatima-sana-shaikh-biography-controversiesawards-and-movies/\">Fatima Sana Sheikh</a>,</strong> and <strong><a href=\"http://Sanaya Malhotra\">Sanaya Malhotra</a></strong> as the Phogat sisters have been phenomenal throughout the film. It became the highest-grossing film of the year and went on receiving around 23 awards and several other nominations.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1QKwHWgMtIA[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Manjhi: The Mountain Man</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 8.0</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director</strong>: Ketan Mehta</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Year</strong>: 2015</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on</strong>: Netflix</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1472 size-large\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/1-1024x665.jpg\" alt=\"NAWAZUDDIN SIDDIQUI\" width=\"640\" height=\"416\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In this list next comes yet another extraordinary true story of an ordinary human being, a story that motivates us from many aspects, inspires us to dream, have a determination, and successfully reach it. It’s about a poor village labourer, <strong>Dasarath Manjhi</strong> from a small village in <strong>Bihar</strong>.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There was no proper way to reach the nearest town to access medical facilities except crossing a rocky mountain with great difficulties. When Majhi’s pregnant wife died while crossing the mountain he set out on an <strong>extraordinary 22-year-old mission</strong> to carve out a road through it and finally had been successful.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">While the legendary actor <strong>Nawazuddin Siddiqui</strong> has made the lead character appear more lifelike and realistic, the magic of <strong>Radhika Apte</strong>’s screen presence is no less. Overall, the film keeps the audience hooked to it till the end and leaves a great positive feel-good impact.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I9KAoTQlEWs[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>MS Dhoni: The Untold Story</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong> – 7.8</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director</strong> – Neeraj Pandey</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Year</strong> – 2016</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Disney+Hotstar</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-962 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/ms-dhoni-movie.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hardly today you can find any individual who has not watched this Bollywood movie. <strong>Mahendra Singh Dhoni</strong> has always been that successful cricket captain for us. However, the film beautifully narrates Dhoni’s journey from a child to the successful man he is today.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The struggling days, the days of success, stories of lost love, marriage, and friendships - everything has been narrated so beautifully and realistically in this biopic. And of course, there is nothing to mention separately about the late actor <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/sushant-singh-rajput-facts-journey-to-bollywood/\"><strong>Sushant Singh Rajput</strong></a> who brought tears and at the same time smiles on our faces by the amazing portrayal of Dhoni’s character. It has been the recipient of around 5 awards.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6L6XqWoS8tw[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Super 30 | Biopics in Bollywood</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 7.9</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director</strong>: Vikas Bahl</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Year</strong>: 2019</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Disney+Hotstar</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2837 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/4-min-1-1.jpg\" alt=\"Super 30 biopic movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A real-life inspiration from the field of academics, <strong>Anand Kumar</strong> is the centre of this film. It flawlessly captures the struggles of the <strong>talented mathematician</strong> whose passion and love for maths finally paid him off. While the drawbacks of the educational system of India and how the students from lower-middle-class backgrounds drop out of it due to lack of resources have been intactly shown in the film, at the same time the journey of an Anant Kumar from a papad seller to the greatest mathematics tutor of the country has also been beautifully narrated.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It is this movie from which many of us got to know about his educational <strong>Super 30 program</strong> where he teaches 30 deserving students to qualify for the difficult <strong>IIT exam.</strong> What adds to its legacy is it\'s receiving the best film award and <strong>Hritik Roshan</strong> winning the best actor award for it at the <strong>Dadasaheb Phalke International Film Festival.</strong></span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2-ag-Col13k[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Paan Singh Tomar:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 8.2</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director</strong>: Tigmanshu Dhulia</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Year</strong>: 2012</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Netflix</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1493 size-large\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/7-min-1024x665.jpg\" alt=\"Irrfan Khan\" width=\"640\" height=\"416\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> It a Unique and one of the most praised biographical dramas of all time it has been. The hero of this story was a national <strong>athlete turned dacoit,</strong> played by the iconic late actor<strong> Irfaan Khan.</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie unbiasedly has shown to us each shade of the central character. His early life in the army to his last days of rebelling against the landlord, each of the phases has been depicted in the film with the highest perfection. It went onto receiving around 8 awards in categories like acting, screenplay, and dialogues the following year.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_LhEryZCEww[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Dirty picture:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 6.6</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director</strong>: Milan Luthria</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Year</strong>: 2011</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Amazon Prime</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5676 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/2-1.jpg\" alt=\"Some must-watch Bollywood biopics : Dirty picture:\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A super-duper hit movie inspired by the real-life story of a South Indian actress named Silk Smitha, mainly known for her salacious or erotic roles, has been one of the best works by <strong>Vidya Balan</strong> in her career. Almost a decade old now, still while its song </span><strong><i>Ishq sufiyana</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> makes us feel hopelessly romantic, </span><strong><i>Ooo Lala</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> makes us grove whenever it is played.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> With versatile performances of the lead actress along with the other actors like <strong>Nasiruddin Shah, Tushar Kapoor</strong>, and <strong>Imran Hashmi,</strong> this film truly falls in our list of favourite biopics. From the actors to the lyricist, make-up artists, and costume designer, individuals associated with this Bollywood film and the film itself in total grabbed more than 40 awards.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=blxOKy7NTrY[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Mary Kom:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 6.8</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director</strong>: Omung Kumar</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Year</strong>: 2014</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on</strong>: Amazon Prime, Netflix</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5677 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/3-1.jpg\" alt=\"Some must-watch Bollywood : Mary Kom:biopics \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another biographical sports masterpiece that has been successful in impressing the audience, as well as critics, is the <strong>Priyanka Chopra</strong> starrer Mary Kom, based on the life of the <strong>famous boxer of the same name.</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The most important positive aspect of this film is the way Chopra prepared herself for the role and made herself look and act exactly like the legendary boxer which is not at all easy. From being the daughter of a struggling family to the daughter of India as well as the mother of two twins, the journey of this world champion boxer has been narrated very well in her biopic. Deservingly, the film received <strong>11 awards</strong> the following year.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UQH8zI92MFg[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Shahid:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 8.2</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Director</strong>: Hansal Mehta</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Year</strong>: 2012</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> SonyLiv</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5678 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/4-1.jpg\" alt=\"Some must-watch Bollywood biopics : Shahid\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One more impressive biographical film based on the life of a <strong>human rights activist cum lawyer, Shahid Azmi</strong> who has fought many cases voluntarily without any payment in consultation with many NGOs. From standing with the accused of Mumbai train bombings to Malegaon bombings, he had faced many backlashes in his career for supporting terrorists and ultimately shot dead in the year 2010.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It is then when <strong>Hansal Mehta</strong> decided to make a film on his life with <strong>Raj Kumar Rao</strong> playing the character of <strong>Shahid Azmi</strong>. We cannot say how Azmi really was as a person as we got to see many shades of him but we can definitely say that the best actor and best director awards received by Rao and Mehta have really been very deserving.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=X0U8sRis8uo[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is definitely not the end of the list. Many other biopics are admired and being talked about. Some notable of them include </span><i>Bandit Queen, Soorma, Bhaag Milkha Bhaag, Haseena Parker, Netaji Subash Chandra Bose the forgotten hero, Gandhi my father, Chhapak, Sarabjit, </i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">and so on.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">These are some of the biopics you must give a watch at least once a lifetime as these are cinematic gems in the true sense.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So, this is the Biopics in Bollywood we will soon be back with something more interesting about the entertainment industry till then have a safe and nice time.</span>','List of Top Best and Upcoming Biopics in Bollywood','','publish','open','open','','list-of-top-best-and-upcoming-biopics-in-bollywood','','','2021-05-10 12:49:59','2021-05-10 07:19:59','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5673',0,'post','',0),(5681,12,'2021-03-26 15:52:14','2021-03-26 10:22:14','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The </span><i style=\"font-weight: inherit;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Khiladi </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">of Bollywood is once again back with the announcement of his next film venture, </span><i style=\"font-weight: inherit;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ram Setu</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Let’s get to know a little more about this project.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Poster release on Social Media - Ram Setu</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Last year on the occasion of the Diwali, <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/akshay-khiladi-kumar-s-love-for-his-country/\"><strong>Akshay Kumar</strong></a> announced this film via uploading two of its posters on his Instagram handle. In both the posters we witnessed a very intense look of the actor wearing a mud-stained denim shirt and an orange scarf along with a bag hanging from his shoulder, thus giving the perfect look of a researcher or a student.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the background of the poster, there is an image of the sacred Hindu God, Lord Rama along with a phrase comprising of three words,<strong> ‘Myth or Reality.</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5685 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Ram-Setu-MOVIE-AKSHAY-KUMAR-NEWS-4.jpg\" alt=\"Ram Setu MOVIE AKSHAY KUMAR NEWS (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><b>Latest updates regarding the film - Ram Setu</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If we believe in the reports, this film will be having a grand theatre release on the occasion of Diwali in the following year 2022.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Consequently, we also got to know that the chief minister of the state of Uttar Pradesh, <strong>Yogi Adityanath</strong> had granted the actor and the entire team permission to shoot for this Hindi movie in <strong>Ayodhya</strong>, a sacred place for the Hindus known for being the<strong> birthplace of Lord Rama.</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">News had been surfacing that he will be starting to shoot for this film by the middle of this year. However, recently on March 18th he took to his Instagram account once again and announced the beginning of the film’s shooting along with the eminent and gorgeous actresses, Jacqueline Fernandez and Nusrat Bharucha. It was an auspicious day when the team started to shoot for this film.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5683 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Ram-Setu-MOVIE-AKSHAY-KUMAR-NEWS-2.jpg\" alt=\" AKSHAY KUMAR NEWS (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><b>Direction and production</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">First of all, Akshay Kumar’s own production house is going to co-produce the film. Apart from this, <strong>Abundantia entertainment, Lyca productions</strong> and <strong>Amazon Prime Video</strong> have also joined hands to carry out the production part of this film.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Secondly, <strong>Abhishek Sharma</strong> Known for Hindi films like </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tere Bin Laden, The Shaukeens</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is going to direct it.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Storyline</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With whatever is came till now, the concept or plot of Ram Setu seems to be quite distinctive. Still now not much is in news about it but it is quite possible, at least evident from the posters, that somewhere the film will lead to a blend of myth and reality.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As per the Hindu epic, Ramayana, the magical bridge or the Ram Setu had been constructed by none other than Lord Rama to rescue his wife from Lanka (present Sri Lanka) where she was abducted and kept by the evil demon named Ravana. Now while many devoted followers of Hinduism regard this as a historical reality, for many it is a myth. And hence we are all waiting to see how this adventure story from an Indian epic and other values link with the present.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Public reactions – are controversies going to arise?</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The situation is quite calm recently. But soon after when the actor had released the poster of </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ram Setu</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> on social media, netizens raised questions and expressed their anger as reactions. Mainly, speaking of the devoted Hindus, it has hurt their religious sentiments and according to many of them now the poster and next to the movie will try to question the existence of the Ram Setu and Lord Rama himself.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5684 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Ram-Setu-MOVIE-AKSHAY-KUMAR-NEWS-3.jpg\" alt=\" MOVIE AKSHAY KUMAR NEWS (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h3><strong>Phrase Myth or Reality - RAm Setu</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Most specifically, the phrase <strong>Myth or Reality</strong> did not do very well with the general public as the construction of Ram Setu which many Indians still stood today consider a notable historical event, questions are being raised on it.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once in the <strong><em>Good News</em></strong> movie, the actor’s one silly joke surrounding Lord Rama had made him get trolled. Now once again Hindu devotees suspected him of trying to defame Rama.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Donations to the construction of Ram Temple</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Soon after, in January, Akshay Kumar made a video claiming donations to the construction of the Ram temple in Ayodhya. Once again, he faced backlashes. And he was accused on grounds that such stunts were being done by him only on account of his upcoming movie.</span>\r\n<h2>Finally</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Whatever be the case, only time will tell whether the movie will really be something unique or something new in the world of Bollywood or will become something rather forgettable. It may give rise to controversies and hurt the sentiments of certain sections of people. But trust me, if the content is really good, no one can stop the </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rowdy Rathore</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> from giving another box-office hit.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So now, all fingers crossed for the next Diwali of 2022 when the film will come. We wish all the luck to Akshay Kumar and the entire team for their success in this project.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is the content for today. We will soon be back with something more interesting about the entertainment industry. Till then, have a nice and safe time.</span>','All that you need to know about the Upcoming Movie Ram Setu','','publish','open','open','','all-that-you-need-to-know-about-the-upcoming-movie-ram-setu','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/akshay-khiladi-kumar-s-love-for-his-country/','2021-04-17 11:32:41','2021-04-17 06:02:41','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5681',0,'post','',0),(5704,12,'2021-04-12 22:00:59','2021-04-12 16:30:59','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5707 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Bunty-Aur-Babli-2-1.jpg\" alt=\"Bunty Aur Babli 2\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n2021 has brought us the good news of opening up our nearest movie theatres so that we can once again go and see our favourite stars performing on screen. Indian audiences have been highly expecting the release of one such big banner Bollywood film <em><strong>Bunty Aur Babli 2</strong></em> in their nearest cinema halls on <strong>23rd April 2021</strong>. But is it happening or once again the rising Covid cases are creating obstacles in the release of the film?\r\n<h2><strong>Bunty Aur Babli 2 | The anticipated release and the delay</strong></h2>\r\nThis Hindi movie was all scheduled for a grand theatrical release on the 26th of June 2020. However, we are aware of the then countrywide situation when there had been a severe spike in the COVID-19 cases leading to the loss of numerous lives. The theatres were not open. As a result, the release of Bunty Aur Babli 2 also got postponed.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5709 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Bunty-Aur-Babli-2-3.jpg\" alt=\"Bunty Aur Babli 2\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nLater the release date come again of the film and it was on April 23rd, 2021. However, in the context of the current situation when once again the COVID cases are rising and lockdowns are newly imposed in different parts of the country, mainly in Maharashtra, the decision has been taken to delay the release of the film yet again. <strong>When it will be released has not yet been announced.</strong>\r\n<h2>Bunty Aur Babli 2 | Teaser or trailer release?</h2>\r\nThe official teaser or trailer of this film is not in news and don\'t know when we will see it. However, on 18th February 2020, a small 27 seconds’ video came on <strong>Yash Raj Films </strong>official account. However, it was not a teaser and we didn’t see any of the actors’ faces. It was just to increase the excitement regarding it.\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qmXbi6AkCuo[/embedyt]\r\n<h2>A Sequel?</h2>\r\nThe Bollywood blockbuster, Bunty Aur Babli is still a lovable film of the current generation. So, keeping the popularity and fame of the former movie in mind the team has come up with its sequel, Bunty Aur Babli 2.\r\n<h2>The Star cast of Bunty Aur Babli 2</h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5708 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Bunty-Aur-Babli-2-2.jpg\" alt=\"Bunty Aur Babli 2\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThe lead pair of Bunty Aur Babli played by <strong>Rani Mukherjee</strong> and <strong>Abhishek Bacchan</strong> just stole the show. And this time while Mukherjee is still there in the character of one of the female leads, Abhishek Bachchan is no longer a part of the new project.\r\n\r\nIn an interview, she revealed this. She said that both she and Abhishek had been approached for the film. Due to some unfortunate issues, he was not able to manage to be a part of this sequel. And hence, in this part, we are going to see the Bollywood nawab <strong><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/saif-ali-khan-said-about-his-autobiography-reactions-on-twitter/\">Saif Ali Khan</a>.</strong>\r\nAlso, in the character of another lead pair here we are going to see the Gully Boy fame <strong>Siddharth Chaturvedi</strong> and the Prime series The forgotten army: Aazadi Ke Lie actress<strong> Sharvari Wagh.</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5710 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Bunty-Aur-Babli-2-4.jpg\" alt=\"Sharvari Wagh hot pic\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2>Direction</h2>\r\nWhile the prequel was directed by the <em>OK Jaanu</em> and <em>Soorma</em> fame, <strong>Shad Ali</strong> it is pretty sure that it has been his filmography and direction that has been one of the major causes behind making it one of the successful big box office hits.\r\n\r\nHowever, it is a matter of grief that Shaad Aali has not returned to direct the sequel Bunty Aur Babli 2.\r\nInstead, this time the responsibility of direction went to the one who had written the script. So yes, the sequel is in direction of <strong>Varun V.</strong> Sharma, a debutant director.\r\n<h2>Production</h2>\r\nThe film is in the production of none other than the <strong>husband of Rani Mukherjee</strong>, <strong>Aditya Chopra</strong> under the banner of <strong>Yash Raj Films.</strong>\r\n<h2>Story so far</h2>\r\nSo, the prequel basically narrated the tale of 2 small village people dreaming to make it big in their lives. Their paths crossed. Finally, they entered the world of conning people to make money as it seemed to be the easiest way. In the backdrop of their Love Story and giving birth to a child, their criminal career finally comes to an end when JCP Dasrath Singh finds his way to the duo and arrests them.\r\n\r\nHowever, they were released from custody soon. And a few years later the policeman offered them to work for the nation by stopping or preventing the activities of other such scammers. With this, the story ended.\r\n<h2>Bunty Aur Babli 2 Storyline</h2>\r\nMuch is not open yet about the sequel’s storyline. However, it is very sure that it’s definitely going to be a continuation of the previous story. Reportedly, the story is going to be narrated in the backdrop of 2 such scammer couples, played by and<strong> Rani - Saif </strong>and <strong>Siddharth - Sharvari.</strong>\r\n\r\nBy a leap of 10 years, the sequel is most probably going to start. Definitely, we are wishing for another mind-blowing, ‘dying out of laughter’ comedy-type movie Bunty Aur Babli.\r\n\r\nWe all really hope that the movie gets released soon and achieves success by becoming a super-duper hit like its prequel. We wish the entire team of Bunty Aur Babli 2 all the luck for their soon-to-be-released project.\r\n\r\nHere at TVFreak.com, we try to provide you with regular updates about the entertainment industry as we are a website solely dedicated to the purpose of entertainment. Besides these, we cover different topics about the glamorous worlds of acting, be it movie reviews or the biography of your favorite star. To know more, don\'t forget to go through our rest of the articles.\r\nSo, this is the content for today. Hope you enjoyed the reading. See you in the next article. For regular updates, you can definitely follow us on social media.','Crime comedy Bollywood movie, Bunty Aur Babli 2, Storyline & Watch Trailer','','publish','open','open','','crime-comedy-bollywood-movie-bunty-aur-babli-2','','','2021-04-12 12:39:46','2021-04-12 07:09:46','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5704',0,'post','',0),(5712,12,'2021-03-28 22:05:50','2021-03-28 16:35:50','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After a delay due to the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic, Netflix has finally released its original Hindi language light-hearted yet dark comedy movie </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pagglait.</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6194 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Netflixs-Pagglait-Movie-Sania-Malhotara-1.jpg\" alt=\"Netflix’s Pagglait Movie Sania Malhotara (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><b>Pagglait Storyline</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This<a href=\"https://www.scoopwhoop.com/entertainment/women-centric-films-that-made-a-greater-impact-than-manikarnika/\"><strong> female-centric movie</strong></a> shows the journey of a young widow whose husband has faced an unfortunate demise due to some unknown cause within six months of marriage. Amidst when the entire Giri family was grieving the loss of their son Astik and was busy executing the various traditions to ensure the peaceful departure of his soul, our protagonist set out on her own journey of freeing herself from the familial or societal shackles to find her true identity.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0xVqPbvLzX4[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Pagglait</b><b> Star Cast</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The girl who has been winning hearts since the time of Dangal, and gave some appreciable performances in films like </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Patakaa</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ludo</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/sanya-malhotra-story-biography-and-movies/\"><strong>Sanya Malhotra </strong></a>plays the lead, named Sandhya in the film. She has been very natural while her non-makeup looks perfectly complemented her performance throughout the movie.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6195 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Netflixs-Pagglait-Movie-Sania-Malhotara-2.jpg\" alt=\"Netflix’s Pagglait Movie Sania Malhotara (1) cast\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The supporting cast is the second strongest point of </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pagglait</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Frankly speaking, the credit goes to them for this extraordinary narration of an ordinary story. Some of the amazing performances have been delivered by actors like <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/the-four-more-shots-please-girl-sayani-gupta-hot-pics-nude-movies-tv-shows/\">Sayani Gupta</a>, Shruti Sharma, <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/gorgeous-sheeba-chaddha-biography-husband-movies-tv-shows/\">Sheeba Chadda</a>, Ashutosh Rana, Aasif Khan, Raghuvir Yadav, Meghna Malik, Natasha Rastogi, Jamil Khan, and so on.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6196 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Netflixs-Pagglait-Movie-Sania-Malhotara-3.jpg\" alt=\"Star cast\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><b>Performances</b></h2>\r\n<h3><b>Pagglait </b><b>Actress Sanya Malhotra</b></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6197 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Netflixs-Pagglait-Movie-Sania-Malhotara-4.jpg\" alt=\"Netflix’s Pagglait Movie Sania Malhotara (1) cast\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Starting from </span><b>Sanya Malhotra</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, the way she portrayed her transformation from a dependent-on-husband girl to overcoming different situations and finding her true self is the perfect epitome of graceful acting talent.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> From Sandhya’s ‘I am not affected much from Astik’s death’ attitude to the always-angered </span><b>Tau ji</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">’s (Raghuvir Yadav) annoying, irritating, and hypocritical comments as well as another uncle named </span><b>Ghanashyam</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">’s (Jamil Khan) seems-so-fake intellectualness at times add a veil of comic flavour in the film.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Sheeba Chadda – Ashutosh Rana</b></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6198 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Netflixs-Pagglait-Movie-Sania-Malhotara-5.jpg\" alt=\"Netflix’s Pagglait Sheeba Chadda – Ashutosh Rana\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">But at the same time, the </span><b>Sheeba Chadda – Ashutosh Rana</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> duo was seen in the character of Astik’s parents stole the show by the portrayal of how they had been carrying the emotional baggage of their son’s death throughout the film. Along with mourning about Astik’s death, stressing about clearance of house loans in the future. The dead son was managing that when he was alive. All the emotions were there with so much perfection by these 2 natural actors.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Sayani Gupta</b></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6199 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Netflixs-Pagglait-Movie-Sania-Malhotara-6.jpg\" alt=\"Sayani Gupta\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<b>Sayani Gupta</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">’s small screen time presence in which she was mostly seen sharing the screen space with Sanaya Malhotra also grabbed the spotlight. It was really heartbreaking to see a strong ambitious successful woman like Akanksha Roy (the name of her character) emotionally breaking down when accused by Sandhya of sleeping with her husband.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Both of these phases – firstly, a strong economically independent woman living alone in a house. Secondly, this soft-hearted who sobs on bring sadness. Both of them have been carried by Gupta on her shoulders perfectly.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Shruti Sharma</b></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6200 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Netflixs-Pagglait-Movie-Sania-Malhotara-7.jpg\" alt=\"actress Shruti Sharma\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Not to forget </span><b>Shruti Sharma</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> who played the role of Nazia, a best friend we all want. She’s the one, in fact only one, who stood by Sandhya irrespective of everything, from eating Golgappas in the first 13 days of her husband’s death to supporting her life-changing decision at the end of the film. She seemed very realistic and a perfect complement to the character of Sandhya.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Besides, the characters of </span><b>Meghna Malik </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">and </span><b>Yamini Singh</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> were very life-like in their roles of relatives whom family members try to avoid. Their back bitching about each other as well as about the other members and putting forward useless accusations of different kinds make all of us at least once feel that we all have these kinds of aunties in our family.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Pagglait </b><b>Direction</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another aspect that takes this film to altogether greater heights is the amazing direction and filmography by Umesh Bisht. From the irony to the contrasts to a perfect societal message, he managed to deliver everything with so much flawlessness and magnificence. </span>\r\n<h2><b>Pagglait </b><b>In-depth analysis</b></h2>\r\n<h3><b>Inner meaning:</b></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6201 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Netflixs-Pagglait-Movie-Sania-Malhotara-8.jpg\" alt=\"Netflix’s Pagglait Movie Sania Malhotara (8)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Behind what just seems just like a story full of emotions, what makes this film different is the way it tries to show the empathizing conditions of many women in India; especially, the dependent women who do not remain in a position to make decisions for themselves. They acted in the way society wants them to. This clearly reflects in Sandhya’s dialogue mentioning how women were considered Pagglaits once they try to act a different way.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sandhya’s mother is a reflection of many such Indian mothers. She only makes their daughters educated to make her capable of finding a groom earning huge packages.</span>\r\n<h3><b>The irony: </b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Also, definitely, the ironies that have been used in the film are something that cannot be missed out. First of all, the residence of the Girls was shown to have the name, </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Shanti Kunj</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> which is very ironic in the context that there had been hardly any </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Shanti</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> or peace in the house. The relatives are mostly busy showing each other down and highlighting their own respective achievements, often leading to arguments. </span>\r\n<h3><b>The contrasts:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Moreover, the film in itself is a contrast. Considering the current situation of the Giri residence where the family members are busy mourning, the film itself unfolds as a light-hearted comedy with a twist in the end.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The contrasts in various situations have been portrayed very significantly all through the film. First of all, in the context of maintaining purity in the house the Muslim friend of the protagonist was ordered to eat from somewhere outside. However, at the same time, we witnessed members of the house breaking the 13 days’ rule and smoking and drinking alcohol on the terrace.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Again, the dull situation of the house is often interrupted with the sound of a doorbell which while ringing plays the loud Bollywood song </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ohh La La</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> which is in complete contrast with the house’s grief.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">These show that the film itself is in no mood to go by the storyline. It tries to attain a mood of itself.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Pagglait Reviews</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With a current IMDB rating of 7.2, the film is one of the favourites of the audience. However, some of the film critics called it boring. But personally speaking, it is a real feel-good movie. And to understand it you need to dive yourself deep into the characters instead of just judging the plot. Overall, it’s worth a watch at least once.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Conclusion</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Films like </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pagglait </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">make us feel that Bollywood has still not lost its essence and how character-driven movies can actually lead to the creation of a cinematic gem.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So, this is the Pagglait Reviews. Hope you enjoyed the reading. You can let us know in the comment if something is missing. See you in the next article. Till now you can check our movie collection. You can find Hollywood and Bollywood lists in every category. These are some lists on every mood. Enjoy!!</span>','Review: Netflix’s Pagglait is full of surprises! Know more of its cast, synopsis, review, analysis and many more','','publish','open','open','','netflixs-pagglait-start-cast-reviews-analysis-storyline-watch-now','','','2021-05-06 10:24:54','2021-05-06 04:54:54','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5712',0,'post','',0),(5811,13,'2021-04-05 08:59:16','2021-04-05 03:29:16','<strong>Chloe Zhao,</strong> you may not have heard this name before. But this year this specific name has appeared in many award shows in the category of best director and screenplay. Chloe Zhao is a <strong>Chinese film director,</strong> her base of interest in Indie-films. She is also one of the few female directors to <strong>get nominations in Oscar, <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/golden-globe-nominations-for-best-director-2021/\">Golden Globe</a>, and BAFTA</strong>— all at the same time.\r\n<h2>Early Life</h2>\r\nGrowing up Chloe was a rebellious person. She was not very attentive at school and liked to get lost in the <strong>world of fantasy and fiction via books and films.</strong> She was 15 when her parents sent her to a boarding school in the United Kingdom. As a Chinese native and not knowing English, I reckon adapting to the educational system was not easy for her.\r\n\r\nBut anyway, because of her love for western movies, she was influenced by western pop culture as well. Later she moved to Los Angeles to pursue higher education.\r\nIn 2015 Chole Zhao directed her <strong>first feature-length film </strong>named <strong>Songs My Brothers Taught Me</strong>. This movie portrays the relationship between siblings. Chloe was 33 years old at that time. Before this film, she also directed 4 short films.\r\n<h3>Songs My Brothers Taught Me (2015)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>IMDB Rating:</strong> 6.9 (1,107 votes)</li>\r\n <li><strong>Star Cast</strong>: John Reddy, Jashaun St. John, Irene Bedard</li>\r\n <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Hoopla, Kanopy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Check out The Trailer:</strong>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VChWnJUButI[/embedyt]\r\n<h2>Some Basic Information | Chloé Zhao</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><strong>Full Name:</strong> Zhao Ting</li>\r\n <li><strong>Date of Birth:</strong> March 31, 1982</li>\r\n <li><strong>Birth Place:</strong> Beijing, China</li>\r\n <li><strong>Zodiac Sign:</strong> Aries</li>\r\n <li><strong>Hair Color:</strong> Black</li>\r\n <li><strong>Eye Color:</strong> Black</li>\r\n <li><strong>Height:</strong> 5 feet 5 inch</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Family:</h2>\r\n<h3>Parents:</h3>\r\n<strong>Yuji Zhao (father)</strong>, a steel company manager. Information about her mother is nowhere to be found. But she was a <strong>hospital worker</strong>. Chloe’s parents got separated later and her father remarried the Chinese actress <strong>Song Dandan.</strong>\r\n<h3>Husband:</h3>\r\nShe has not married yet. But she is currently dating cinematographer <strong>Joshua James Richards.</strong>\r\n<h3>Chloe Zhao <strong>Net Worth:</strong> $200,000 approx</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Chloe Zhao Movies and TV Shows</h2>\r\nZhao has been active in the film industry since 2015. Till then she has directed 3 movies including her debut film. The other two movies are <strong>The Rider (2017) </strong>and <strong>Nomadland (2020).</strong>\r\nBoth of these films are driven by their characters and tells the story of very personal yet relatable problems.\r\nChloe Zhao is also directing the new MCU movie <strong>Eternals</strong> (starring <strong>Angelina Jolie</strong>). She is now one of the four female directors who are directing big-budget superhero movies.\r\n<h3>Chloe Zhao Nomadland Trailer:</h3>\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6sxCFZ8_d84\r\n<h3>Chloe Zhao On Her Historic Golden Globe Win</h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AMjFTiRh8wA[/embedyt]\r\n<h2>Chloe Zhao Awards and Achievements</h2>\r\nNow in this section, Chloe does not lack any. She has accustomed herself to various awards and achievements in just 5 years of her career. In 2017, Chloe won the <strong>C.I.C.A.E.</strong> Award at <strong>Cannes</strong> for the movie The Rider. She won her first <strong>Golden Globe</strong> this year in the category of <strong>Best Director - Motion Picture for Nomadland.</strong> She was also nominated in the category of the best screenplay but lost to <strong>Aaron Sorkin</strong> (The Trial of the Chicago 7).\r\nAnd in the 93rd Academy Award Chloe has scored nominations in four categories— Best Achievement in Film Editing, Best Adapted Screenplay, Best Achievement in Directing, and Best Motion Picture of the Year (Producer).\r\n<h2>Some Fun Facts About Chloé Zhao</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n <li>Chloe Zhao’s boyfriend Joshua James Richards has also been nominated for an Oscar this year in the category of Best Cinematography.</li>\r\n <li>Growing up she used to draw manhua (Chinese comics) and write fanfiction.</li>\r\n <li><strong>Happy Together</strong> by<strong> Wong Kar-wai</strong> is her favourite movie.</li>\r\n <li>She has 3 chickens and 2 dogs.</li>\r\n <li>She was a student of<strong> Spike Lee.</strong></li>\r\n <li>Her stepmother is a very famous Chinese actress.</li>\r\n <li>She has no accounts on Facebook, Instagram, or Twitter.</li>\r\n</ol>','Golden Globe Winner Chloé Zhao— Career, Movies and Tv Shows','','publish','open','open','','golden-globe-winner-chloe-zhao-career-movies-and-tv-shows','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/golden-globe-nominations-for-best-director-2021/','2021-04-17 11:32:23','2021-04-17 06:02:23','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5811',0,'post','',0),(5813,14,'2021-05-10 09:10:21','2021-05-10 03:40:21','<h2>Who is Regina King</h2>\r\nAn actress of African – American root, Regina King or Regina Rene King is additionally a skilled executive. She is known for the depiction of numerous interesting comedic and sensational roles. And the awesome profundity in her versatile acting is exceedingly respected.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6185 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Regina-King-Biography-movies-and-tv-shows-2.jpg\" alt=\"Regina King movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nWith her commitment to the Hollywood industry and her overgrowing acclaim and ubiquity, <a href=\"https://time.com/\">Time magazine</a> recorded her among 100 world’s most powerful individuals as of the year 2019.\r\n<h2>Early Life</h2>\r\n1971 born King, was from a totally non – dingy family. Her days of developing up had been in Los Angeles. Her father utilized to work as an electrician whereas her was mother was a teacher. They were together for some time and then got separated when Regina was still a child.\r\n\r\nWhen young, King took acting classes and appeared and showed great skill. Her scholastic accomplishments are also quite prolific.\r\n\r\nWithin the year 1988, she completed her graduation. Afterwards, she moreover joined the celebrated College of South California for higher studies.\r\n<h2>Hot Regina King Physique</h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6186 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Regina-King-Biography-movies-and-tv-shows-3.jpg\" alt=\"Regina King Bio