ster came in 2012. Filmmaker </span>Kimbie Rendall\'s films can be considered a near to perfect amalgamation of disaster and horror. The story revolves around a group of people stuck in a supermarket by the sea during a tsunami.\r\n\r\nThe real thrill comes when a Great White Shark attacks! Added with some comical elements and gruesome scenes and often described as \'Realistic\' and \'scary\' by the fans, this movie will keep you at the edge of your seats.\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sDKRvbVjlRc[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>8. Noah (2004) | Movies on Tsunami</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb: </b>5.7/10</li>\r\n <li><b>Director: </b>Darren Aronofsky</li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: </b>Russell Crowe, Emma Watson, Anthony Hopkins</li>\r\n <li><b>Available on Amazon Prime Video</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5943 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Tsunami-survival-water-disaster-Movies-3.jpg\" alt=\"Noah (2004): Tsunami, survival, water, disaster Movies (3)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Phenomenal and well-known filmmaker </span><b>Darren</b> <b>Aronofsky</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\'s Biblical movie on the story of Noah\'s Ark is the premise of this movie. The movie stars some popular faces like </span><b>Anthony Hopkins, Emma Watson,</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><b>Russell Crowe</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With some spectacular visual effects and strong scenes, this Old Testament adaption shows how skilled Aronofsky is. Due to some shifts from the actual story, the movie did face some backlash but if you are someone who has a thing of historical drama along with perfect thrill elements, this movie is a must-watch. </span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FFCXHr8aKDk[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>7. Geostorm. (2017) | Movies on Tsunami</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>I