ch of the family members is searching for the other members just with the hope that they are still breathing. This movie proves successful in bringing to you the emotions, tragedy, and physical and mental pain that the victims of such natural disasters cause to them. The tragedy of the families will surely shake you to the roots. This movie is surely a must-watch!</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UV5zCTfvurQ[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>1. Deep Impact (1998)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb:</b> 6.2/10</li>\r\n <li><b>Director: </b>Mimi Leder</li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: </b>Elijah Wood, Morgan Freeman, Robert Duvall</li>\r\n <li><b>Available on Netflix</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5950 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Tsunami-survival-water-disaster-Movies-10.jpg\" alt=\"Deep Impact (1998\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Firstly, When a movie has its name attached to </span>Steven Spielberg (the producer of Deep Impact), you know it\'s something different and will surely amaze you with its exceptionally brilliant writing and making.\r\n\r\nSecondly, An extraordinary cast like Morgan Freeman, amazingly matriculated special effects, phenomenal performance, and an asteroid attack leading to a great tsunami is all here in this movie. With the perfect blend of emotional drama and suspense, this movie will surely keep you at the edge of your seat.\r\n\r\nThe scenes of Sarah leaving her family, Oran bidding his wife and child, goodbye and Jenny settling her issues with her father make your heart fill with tears. This movie is high in the recommendation and surely deserves to be on the best disaster movies list at the top.\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VNtsVP42bOE[/embedyt]\r\n\r\nFinally, Thus here was the list of the greatest films about tsunami by <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">TheTvFreak.com</a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Hope you had a great time reading this and let us know the best tsunami films that you have watched in the comment section below! </span>','Top 10 Best Movies on Tsunami all the time | Watch right now! ','','publish','open','open','','top-10-best-movies-on-tsunami-all-the-time','','','2021-05-10 12:51:05','2021-05-10 07:21:05','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5939',0,'post','',0),(5952,12,'2021-04-13 12:41:00','2021-04-13 07:11:00','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Since last year, OTTs have been gifting us with some significant works. While Hindi movies like the Netflix original, Anurag Kashyap’s </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ludo</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> gripped us with its magic, the Hansal Mehta directorial Sony Liv original web series, </span><strong><i>Scam 1992</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong> based on the life of the fraud stockbroker of 80s and 90s named Harshad Mehta,</strong> <strong>became the best, award-winning web series of the year</strong> and is in fact, a gem in itself.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Call it a coincidence or something else, but within one year of this unforgettable web series’ release, we got to witness a movie loosely based on the life of the same person, Harshad Mehta…Yes, I’m talking about the recently released Kookie Gulati crime drama <strong>Big Bull</strong> which is streaming on <strong>Disney+Hotstar</strong>.</span>\r\n<h2>The Big Question:</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Has Big Bull been successful in outshining </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Scam 1992</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> or it’s already out of the way of leaving any mark? Read to know more.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-3038 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/1-5.jpg\" alt=\"SCAM 1992 : Behind the Hype\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><b>The Big Bull Release</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Firstly, due to the ongoing pandemic, the decision of releasing this Hindi film theatrically was called off. Later the makers pushed the release more backwards. This is to give the audience the time to get over the hype that has been created surrounding Scam 1992. But it is true that iconic and unique creations are not easily forgotten.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hence, soon after the </span><b><i>Big Bull</i></b><b> trailer release</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, the public started to react. The </span><b><i>Big Bull</i></b><b> trailer release date</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> was three weeks ago before releasing of the film on 8</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">th</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> April 2021. Post its release, netizens, especially the Scam 1992 fans, and critics have been comparing the two and consequently, the film is receiving backlashes on grounds of unstructured writing, rushed screenplay, overdramatic dialogues, etc.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bw6I-KgCSP4[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Ineffective Writing and overdramatizing of the story</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5858 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/April-movire-released-this-week-2021-4.jpg\" alt=\"The Big Bull, April movire released this week 2021 (4)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the case of </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Big Bull,</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong> it has been unnecessarily tried to make the film typically Bollywoodish</strong> and this is one of the main reasons why it turned out to be so <strong>underwhelming</strong>. One of the major instances of this is the lead character’s love story that has been unnecessarily and forcefully dragged into the plot.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">While<a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/scam-1992-the-harshad-mehta-story-behind-the-hype/\"><strong> Scam 1992 had a more realistic approach in showing the journey and determination</strong></a> of an individual, no idea why Big Bull was so keen to show that the protagonist’s setting out on his journey was just motivation of winning over his love interest</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Also, not to miss out on the protagonist’s demonic laughter and the background score accompanied the entry of a corrupt MLA. All these seem to be quite hilarious at some point, particularly when you realize that it is 2021 and the audience no longer admires such over-the-top and over-dramatic portrayals of characters.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Rushed screenplay</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Well…Scam 1992 has captured in detail the rise and fall of Harshad Mehta in its 10 long episodes. But for Big Bull, I would like to say that despite being 2 hours 30 minutes long episodes, <strong>the audience failed to connect with the characters</strong>, the main reason being the rushed and too first screenplay.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>It failed to show how the protagonist established himself successfully</strong> in the world of fraud. And hence the storytelling lacked the required depth. It feels like things are happening too fast and we are missing out on information.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Big Bull Performances</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The central character of this film, inspired by the real-life Harshad Mehta, is named Hemant Shah and has been played by none other than the phenomenal and versatile actor <strong>Abishek Bacchan</strong> who has many times proven himself in films like </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bunty Aur Bubly, Dostana, Ludo,</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and so on. But have the </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Scam 1992</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> fans really able to forgot the breakthrough performance delivered by the Gujarati superstar <strong><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/pratik-gandhi-from-scam-1992-biography-movies-and-web-series/\">Pratik Gandhi</a> </strong>in his debut web series? Absolutely not. However, judging by only the performances both have been ideal in their places and later on. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> But considering the faulty over-the-top writing and screenplay, it is not possible for a single actor to make a film masterpiece on his single shoulder. Abhishek has genuinely and energetically tried to give his best but <strong>failed to touch the expectation.</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Similarly, in the case of <strong>Sohum Shah</strong>, who has played Hemant Shah’s brother in the film. Again due to the writing, he appeared quite insignificant, particularly, if we compare him to his counterpart, Hemant Kher in Scam 1992. His emotions and the other acts appeared very <strong>unrealistic</strong>.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5953 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong> Ileana D Cruz</strong> has been seen in the character of the news reporter in the journey of revealing Hemant Shah’s fraud business. Ileana definitely does justice to her character. But again some of her character’s on-screen doings like barging anytime anywhere without any permission makes us question the authenticity of the film. However, both <strong>Shreya Dhanvantari </strong>and <strong>Ilena</strong> did quite good jobs in portraying the role.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> And then there are other efficient actors like Nikita Dutta, Mahesh Manjrekar, Ram Kapoor, Sumit Vyas, Shishir Sharma, Saurabh Shukla in different roles. However, in most cases, their efforts have gone unnoticed due to the lack of strength in the writing.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Background score</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>The BGM of Scam 1992 still buzzes in our ears.</strong> On the contrary, while the romantic song </span><strong><i>Ishq Namaz</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> seemed to be forcefully fitted in the financial setting of the story, <strong>Carry Minati’s rap</strong> song </span><strong><i>Yalgar</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> seemed to be more of a marketing strategy to hype the film. Of course, it is appreciable that finally, Bollywood is acknowledging the efforts of <strong>Indian YouTubers</strong>. But at the same time, it feels like the vibe of Yalgar too doesn’t somewhat match with the environment. Overall the BGM of Big Bull is far beyond touching the level of Scam 1992’s BGM.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-1LAtT9u3ag[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Lastly, we can say that the film<strong> Big Bull has kinda lost its track</strong> in the way of integrating excessive unnecessary angles like the aspects of romance and over-dramatic emotions. It seems more like half-baked stuff. On the other hand, </span><strong><i>Scam 1992</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong> is a gem</strong> from every aspect – storytelling, acting, directing screenplay, and whatnot.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Of course, if you are a Scam 1992 fan, it is quite natural for you to compare the two and conclude the superiority of the web series over the film. Hence, from making aspects, of course, the series is better. But if you haven’t watched it till now, Big Bull is definitely your cup of tea as of now and will not disappoint you. You can give it a one-time watch.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Where can you watch it? – Big Bull movie watch online free</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If you are having a Disney+Hotstar subscription, you can definitely watch the </span><b>Big Bull Full Movie</b><