e character of the creepy teenage guy having hots for Indu. Besides these, the on-screen creepy old uncles delivered very realistic performances as well. </span>\r\n<h2><b>Direction and production</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Abir Sengupta, a new director, debuted in Bollywood with this movie. Some of the famous production houses, including T-Series, Electric Apples, and Emmay Entertainment have produced this one.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Has it been a success or a gradually forgettable film? - Indoo ki Jawani analysis</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Okay, so the question here arises,<strong> ‘Should you spare your 2 hours to watch this supposedly carefree or light-hearted Bollywood movie?</strong>’ With small towns in the backdrop, romantic films like Chaalang or Baireley ki Barfi have been appreciated by the Indian audience and hence it has been thought that Indu Ki Javani would also leave no stone apart in making us point it out as a feel-good film.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Unfortunately, that hasn’t been the case. While the debutant director has tried to cover various aspects including dating apps, the typical narrow mentality of small-town people, terrorism, India-Pakistan debate the potential actors also tried to make the film likable; but that’s not enough.</span>\r\n<h3>What\'s More?</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In today’s era of right-swiping in order to find soulmates, the plot presenting a modern seems to be quite relevant and promising. However, it has not reached our expectations due to faulty and messy writing. In the quest of making, it a full-fledged adult comedy, numerous dialogues on sex, porn, virginity have been incorporated. But the purpose of entertainment of such dialogues have been somewhere lost as most of them seemed to be written with an asinine treatment as well as with a socially debatable or unacceptable perception.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Sonal advises Kiara</strong></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For instance, the fictional character, Sonal continuously advises Kiara’s character that the only way to make a boy fall for her is to have sex with him. Hurts your ears, right? While generally, youths watch such movies, I wonder how badly such lines can influence them. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At the same time, while the film’s female-centric approach or the message it gives that how a woman’s sexual desires matter too, it didn’t step back to stereotype UP’s men (be of any age) as those having nothing in life except for sexual desires or hots for a young girl. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Moreover, the chemistry between the lead pair seems to be quite weak and hence even the last twist fails to leave any mark in the audience’s hearts. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A film that had the potential to be a strong comic spy thriller with masalas of romance, as well as an essence of a small town, turned out to be an unfunny mess trying to touch on so many interesting topics but at last, trying to attract the audience with what? Casual sex. Yes, that’s the truth of this film – trying to sell casual sexism in the name of comedy. It could really have been better to devote more budget into the writing of the film, rather than just spending on the shooting of music videos in such expensive sets.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Oh yes! The songs are appealing, one cannot deny. It’s a treat to the eyes to see Kiara grooving in Sawan Mein Lag Gayi Aag.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NwzlUahlfQk[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Indoo ki Jawani IMDB and reviews</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So, in all, the film got mostly negative reviews from the critics. The performances, incorporation (though not much successful) of a subplot with thrill and mystery, the songs have been considered a few of the positive aspects of the film. It has got an IMDB rating of 2.6. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As it’s on an OTT now, you can go and give it an easy watch once. But of course, if you are a viewer of much better content OTTs are producing these days, you will be quite disappointed by this film.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So, this is the content for today. See you in the next article. </span>','Indoo ki Jawani – read to know it’s worth watching or not','','publish','open','open','','indoo-ki-jawani-read-to-know-its-worth-watching-or-not','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/16-best-bollywood-movies-of-2020-on-netflix-and-amazon-prime/','2021-05-26 22:08:14','2021-05-26 16:38:14','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=6226',0,'post','',0),(6231,13,'2021-05-13 22:00:03','2021-05-13 16:30:03','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sometimes actors play some larger than life characters that become more than their real identity. The audiences and fans then know that actor by the character’s name. Tell me if I say the name </span><b>Phoebe Buffay</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><b>Lisa Kudrow</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, which one will you recognize first? But you see, there is no art without an artist. And similarly, there is no Phoebe Buffay without Lisa Kudrow.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Early Life</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6236 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Lisa-Kudrow—-Early-Life-Movies-TV-Shows-and-Some-Interesting-Facts-4.jpg\" alt=\"Lisa Kudrow— Early Life, Movies &amp; TV Shows and Some Interesting Facts\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Lisa Kudrow was born in a middle-class </span><b>Jewish family</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. She even had a </span><b>Bat Mitzvah</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> ceremony. Lisa was born and raised in California. She went to </span><b>Portola Middle Schoo</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">l in Tarzana, California. And 