times and gifted us with some of the evergreen trios, depicting or defining the essence of friendship in unique ways. Today, let’s go down the memory lane and revisit the </span><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-15-movies-on-friendship-that-you-must-watch/\"><b>best friendship movies</b></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, Hindi cinema’s best onscreen trios</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">who have never left any stone apart to entertain us.</span>\r\n<h2><strong><i>1. Dil Chahta hai</i> </strong></h2>\r\n<b>Akshay – Sameer – Siddharth:</b> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The name itself is enough to reveal which of the </span>Bollywood friendship movies<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> we are talking about. The heart-touching iconic film of 2001 </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dil Chahta hai</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is still a favourite of many. A perfect movie to watch with your friends if you are uniting with them after a long time. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The plots beautifully show how after college, circumstances made three friends get separated from each other but ultimately the inevitable force of friendship brings them all together back again. Eminent actors like Amir Khan, Akshay Khanna, and Saif Ali Khan have so realistically played the roles that for every single moment as the movie progresses, we feel like we are also a part of their journey.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OBAcYSSUf6o[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong><i>2. 3 idiots | Bollywood friendship movies</i></strong></h2>\r\n<b>Rancho – Raju – Farhan:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Another one of the lovable </span>best Bollywood movies on friendship<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> has been this 2009’s award-winning film </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">3 idiots</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> where the worth remembering characters of Rancho, Farhan, and Raju portrayed by Amir Khan, R. Madhavan and Sharman Joshi respectively in.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Despite having lots of differences, these three friends, throughout the movie, always stick to each other no matter what. Indeed, a must-watch for today’s generation which never thinks even once to leave their friends behind to be a part of the competitive rat race. It’s admirable to see how Rancho always tops in the college while Farhan and Raju despite failing never leaves each other’s back.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Of course, it is finally their friendship that motivated them to follow their passion and become successful in their respective lives. The last scene of the film where the three friends reunite and Rancho kisses his ladylove makes us emotional every time we watch it.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K0eDlFX9GMc[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong><i>3. Kiapoche</i></strong></h2>\r\n<b>Ishaan – Omi - Govind: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of the Hindi</span> movies about 3 friends <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">enough to make us cry is this 2013’s unforgettable cinematic gem, </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Kiapoche.</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> A group of three friends who have been always with each other through thick and thin starts a business venture together, faces a tragic ending when religion and politics come in the way of their friendship and they have to sacrifice one of them, the regret of which stays forever.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Ishaan, played by the legendary late actor Sushant Singh Rajput, loses his life in the hands of Omi (portrayed by Amit Sadh). The film ends as Omi and Govind, after years, discuss their old days with Ishaan whose spirit smiles from heaven as their dream of seeing their neighbourhood kid Ali getting into the Indian cricket team finally gets fulfilled.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nGSyqEOo8k8[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong><i>4. Dostana | Bollywood friendship movies</i></strong></h2>\r\n<b>Sam – Neha – Kunal: </b><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jaane Kyun</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is still one of the top songs on our playlist. While the song buzzes in our ears, the music video is also one of our favourites because of the way it portraits the chemistry between three friends, played by Priyanka Chopra, Abhishek Bachchan, and John Abraham. By now you must be knowing that we are talking about the movie </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dostana</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> which beautifully narrates the tale of how three people from different spheres of life met and got along with each other and finally became the best of friends.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It is one of those </span><a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/best-bollywood-romantic-movies-to-watch-on-valentines-day-2021/\"><b>Bollywood movies about best friends falling in love</b></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> which distances them from each other. However, in the end, all of them reconcile and the two guy friends apologize to their girl bestie they once fell for; the film ends with a happy note that whatever comes in the way, a true bond of friendship can never be broken.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PYNpmI_MHXc[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong><i>5. Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara</i></strong></h2>\r\n<b>Arjun – Kabir – Imran:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Don’t lie, but every one of us wants to go on that fantasized trip with our squad just like this trio from </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. The adventurous, as well as the funny journey of three young friends who set out on a road trip to Spain, is indeed a happy watch. Having the best times of their lives, undertaking all the fun sports, meeting some amazing persons, and finally having some self-realizations as well as understanding the value of the bond they share form the main plot of the story. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">All happens in the course of the trip. Love, comedy, friendship, drama, adventure – a mixture of all these elements, ZNMD is truly one of the best movies of all times, one of the </span>best Bollywood movies about friendship<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">; of course, we shouldn’t miss out on the cast, Hrithik Roshan, Farhan Akhtar and Abhay Deol who are its shining stars.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FJrpcDgC3zU[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong><i>6. Hera Pheri</i> </strong></h2>\r\n<b>Raju – Shyam – Baburao:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Name a trio better than this and I will wait. A cult classic, a blockbuster, and an evergreen movie of all time, </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hera Pheri</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> which released in the year 2000 gifted us with this unforgettable trio, played by Akshay Kumar, Sunil Shetty, and Paresh Rawal. Even after 21 years, we can still say that each scene of this film is better than the previous one and will always make you die out of laughter. The story is about the trio\'s quest to become rich.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Nj4H-X3FAWU[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong><i>7. Pyar Ka Punchnama 2</i> </strong></h2>\r\n<b>Gogo – Thakur – Chauka:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> One of the most entertaining buddy dramas and in fact, one of the favourites among today\'s youths is this Luv Ranjan-directed film </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pyar Ka Punchnama 2</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> where we saw Kartik Aryan, Sunny Singh, and Omkar Kapoor in the lead characters of three best friends. This film is the perfect epitome of how friendship is over everything our friendship and is the best gift we have ever received, how in the most distressing days it is only those friends who can make us feel happy and good about ourselves; in fact, while the loves of their lives walked away it has been just three of them in the bar chilling out with each other, thus showing that no matter how many people come and leave, their friendship is going to remain the same forever.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tC-HGUhxyyc[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong><i>8. Stree</i></strong></h2>\r\n<b>Vicky – Bittu – Jaana:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Raj Kumar Rao, Aparkashti Khurana, and the Patal Lok sensation Abhishek Banerjee played the trio in this comedy-horror </span>friendship Hindi movie <i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Stree</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. As one of them, Jaana, the character portrayed by Banerjee, gets possessed by a witch, called </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Stree, </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">the other two of them set out to dig up all the mystery and save their friend from the hands of the spirit. Full of comedy sequences as well as horror ones, the film also showcases the extent to which buddies can go in order to protect or save each other from anything and anyone. After all, that’s what friends are for.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gzeaGcLLl_A[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><strong><i>9. Yeh Jawani Hai Deewani</i></strong></h2>\r\n<b>Bunny – Aditi – Avi:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Well, while the romance between Bunny (Ranbir Kapoor) and Naina (Deepika Padukone) is going to make you emotional, the friendship shared between Bunny, Avi, Aditi portrayed by RK, Aditya Roy Kapoor, and Kalki Koechlin respectively, is also something that we can never get over from Ayan Mukherjee’s </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Yeh Jawani Hai Deewani</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">From food to happiness and pain the squad shared it all. Life happened which did separate them from each other, but finally years later when the trio met, they cleared out all the misunderstandings, embraced each other, and became best buddies once again.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rbp2XUSeUNE[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><i>10. Mitron</i></h2>\r\n<b>Jai – Raunak – Deepu:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Though the main focus of this 2018 film remains on the love story of Jai and Avni, it also portrays the strong bond the main character shares with two of his buddies Raunak and Deepu, played by the Scam 1992 actor Prateik Gandhi and Shivam Parekh respectively.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jai, who is considered as a ‘good for nothing’ guy by his dad always got his friends’ moral and financial support, without which it would surely be not possible for him to think positively about life. Raunak and Deepu stayed with Jai throughout his good as well as bad days and the trio has really given us friendship goals in a true sense.</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-7oSVaQp6CM[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> So, these are some of the </span>3 friends movies in Bollywood<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> you should of course not miss out on. And if you are a movie buff, you are just going to love these films.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Finally, this is the content for today. Hope you had a happy reading. See you in the next article.</span>','Top 10 Memorable Bollywood Trios | Friendship Movies | 3 Idiots & More','','publish','open','open','','memorable-bollywood-trios-friendship-movies','','','2021-05-18 22:24:44','2021-05-18 16:54:44','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=6272',0,'post','',0),(6279,12,'2021-05-24 22:09:23','2021-05-24 16:39:23','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Despite being aware of the thrill and fear horror movies put us through, we watch them. Many of the Bollywood horror Movies are indeed terrifying but still, it’s fun for us to get goosebumps because we believe all the happenings are fictitious and can’t happen in real life. But, will you be able to remain in your normal state of mind if I tell you that some of your favourite Hindi horror films are based on true events? Spine chilling enough.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So today, TV Freak.com presents to you a </span><b>list of Bollywood horror movies based on true stories. </b>\r\n<h2><b></b><strong>1. Ragini MMS | Bollywood Horror Movies</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 4.9</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> Pawan Kripalani</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> YouTube</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6292 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10-Bollywood-horror-movies-on-true-stories-1.jpg\" alt=\"10 Bollywood horror movies on true stories (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In this 2011 horror Bollywood movie</span><b>,</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> we saw that a couple went to a deserted bungalow for spending a night, got stuck inside, and was attacked by some unknown force. And finally, they met with very disastrous consequences.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> This plot is inspired by an incident, the victim of which has been a Delhi girl named Deepika. She went with her boyfriend to an abandoned strange house away from the city and while the duo was having sex, the guy suddenly got possessed started blabbering in Marathi\'s language. It made the girl unconscious in fear.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Later that night, she was rescued but her bf was never traced again. However, as they were recording the love-making session, she had the footage of everything that happened, based on which later this film was made.</span>\r\n<h2><b></b><b>2. Bhoot Part 1: The Haunted Ship</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 5.4</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> Bhanu Pratap Singh</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Amazon Prime Video</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6293 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10-Bollywood-horror-movies-on-true-stories-2.jpg\" alt=\"10 Bollywood horror movies on true stories (8)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">National crush Vicky Kaushal played a surveying officer in this movie where his efforts to find the truth behind a mysteriously found ship abandoned at a port lead to various spooky happenings like encountering a wicked spirit.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> The movie’s crew had themselves confirmed that the story had been inspired by a cargo ship that suddenly washed ashore along Mumbai’s Juhu beach under mysterious circumstances. It was June 2011.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A month later another oil tanker was discovered abandoned along the same beach after it was untraceable for many days. These two bizarre incidents inspired the making of this movie. The addition of the horror on a haunted angle along with elements like thrill and suspense has indeed made it scary.</span>\r\n<h2><b>3. Stree | </b><strong>Bollywood Horror Movies</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 7.6</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> Amar Kaushik</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Disney+Hotstar, Netflix</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6301 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10-Bollywood-horror-movies-on-true-stories-10.jpg\" alt=\"10 Bollywood horror movies on true stories (8)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Speaking of Bollywood horror films based on real incidents, here comes 2018’s Stree which had petrified the audience with its plot dealing with a female ghost preying on men at night. Though the approach to this film has been entertaining and full of comedies, the trailer itself revealed that the story is based on a ‘ridiculously true phenomenon</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> We don’t know if such a witch exists in real or not, but a similar legend snatched away the night’s sleep of 1990’s Bangalore city. People reported that there used to be knocks on the door at night and many unfamiliar killings or murders took place as well. As per folklore, a witch comes out at night and calls men from outside their houses in someone’s voice they love. And then the man would die within the next 24 hours. The residents of the city gradually found a solution to this - Naleba which means ‘come tomorrow’. They used to write this outside their doors so that spirit would go away every night.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The people’s fears are quite evident from the fact that even today the 1st of April is celebrated as Naleba body. Similarly, the film also made us witness how residents of the Chanderi town of Madhya Pradesh were traumatized by Stree’s presence and as a solution wrote ‘oi Stree kal aana’ (come tomorrow) outside their houses every night.</span>\r\n<h2><b>4. ?: A Question mark:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 5.6</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> Allyson Patel, Yash Dave</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> YouTube</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6294 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10-Bollywood-horror-movies-on-true-stories-3.jpg\" alt=\"10 Bollywood horror movies on true stories (8)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Reportedly, this blood-curdling award-winning horror film is also partially based on a true incident. The narration of the film is as scary and realistic as hell. It’s about a few friends who went to a house for some shoot but never returned. Later, their camera was discovered which had the footage of everything that happened with them. Actors like <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/hot-maanvi-gagroo-bio-nude-pics-instagram-movies-and-tv-shows/\">Maanvi Gagroo</a>, Akhlaque Khan, Sonam Mukherjee delivered some best performances of their careers. So, whatever is shown in the movie is a collection of the found footage. The film makes sure to make numerous of your nights sleepless.  </span>\r\n<h2><b></b><b>5. Bhool Bhulaiya | </b><strong>Bollywood Horror Movies</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 7.3</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> Priyadarshan</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Amazon Prime Video</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6300 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10-Bollywood-horror-movies-on-true-stories-9.jpg\" alt=\"bhoolbhulyiya\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This iconic 2007’s remake movie isn’t essentially a horror film till the end but has many psychological, comic as well as scary elements. One of the central characters, Avni played by Vidya Balan was thought to be possessed by a spirit named Manjulika but in reality, she had Dissociative Personality Disorder which resulted in her developing multiple personalities.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">These events have been inspired by incidents that have indeed occurred around 1988. Also, the back story of Manjulika is believed to have actually taken place about 200 years ago from today. As per sources she used to be a poor Bengali dancer who was kidnapped and brought to India. She met a male dancer named Shashidhar and the duo fell in love. However, the king killed Shashidhar to be with Manjulika himself.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She later committed suicide but in the suicide note promised to take revenge. Avni had heard this story numerous times in her childhood which had made her believe herself as Manjulika and take revenge from the king.</span>\r\n<h2><b></b><b>6. Trip to Bhangarh:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 2.4</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> Jitendra Pawar</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> YouTube</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6295 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10-Bollywood-horror-movies-on-true-stories-4.jpg\" alt=\"10 Bollywood horror movies on true stories (8)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There is nothing new regarding the spookiest incidents related to this worldwide known Bhangarh fort located in Rajasthan. Visiting this historical site after sunset and before sunrise is prohibited. However, many squads have gone there till date during nights to have the best adventures of their lives but had some scariest experiences including hearing screams of some women or someone’s voice from behind or witnessing some frightening man staring at them. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The film has been inspired by the amalgamation of all such events. It narrates the journey of five friends who visited the fort just having fun, but then the visit supposedly started making negative impacts on their lives.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 7. </span><b>Phoonk:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 3.9</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> Ram Gopal Verma</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> YouTube</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6296 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10-Bollywood-horror-movies-on-true-stories-5.jpg\" alt=\"phook\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> India’s so-called progressive society every year witnesses many cases of black magic. Mainly women become the victims of this and either suffer or are killed. Mainly in the rural areas, such incidents are quite regular occurrences where people confide in such things to take revenge for simple matters.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Being inspired by those events and to create more awareness regarding black magic, this film was made in the year 2008. It takes you to a petrifying ride of witnessing the dark side of magic and how it works on people. It is about a couple who performs black magic on the child of a family. Go and give this ‘Hindi horror film based on real life’ a watch.</span>\r\n<h2><b>8. Bhoot:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 6.5</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> Ram Gopal Verma</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Amazon Prime Video, Voot</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6297 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10-Bollywood-horror-movies-on-true-stories-6.jpg\" alt=\"bhoot\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This Hindi film is based on a very common plot of a couple moving into a new house where they start to witness various eerie happenings. This incident has occurred to many of us if we have moved to a new apartment or even a hotel room with a dark past. The movie has been highly inspired by such real-life occurrences. Urmila Matondkar’s performance as the possessed wife Swati is the film’s most appreciable aspect.</span>\r\n<h2><b></b><b>9. 3 AM:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 5</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> Vishal Mahadkar</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Amazon Prime Video, YouTube</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6298 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10-Bollywood-horror-movies-on-true-stories-7.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another horror film based on a true story is this Ranvijay Singh starrer. It revolves around the real concept or fact of witching hour or 3 am when all negative energies or souls and spirits are supposed to become the most powerful to cause harm. The film is about a mysterious man who narrates the fateful incidents that had happened to him and his dead girlfriend to a group of college students and prevents them from entering a haunted site. The twist, in the end, will make you shake in fear.</span>\r\n<h2><b></b><b>10. Darna Zaroori hai:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 5.4</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> JD Chakravarthi, Manish Gupta, Sajid Khan, and others</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Amazon Prime Video, YouTube</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6299 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10-Bollywood-horror-movies-on-true-