</i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She also looked no less than a goddess in the red-coloured lehenga in which she was also seen in one of the movie posters sharing a romantic pose with co-actor Ranvir Singh. Lastly, the traditional Marathi look completed with the maroon saree and jewellery during the Pinga dance can’t be missed out. Anju Modi is indeed a brilliant designer.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6342 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/1-Deepika-Padukone-in-Bajirao-Mastani-1.jpg\" alt=\"1 Deepika Padukone in Bajirao Mastani (2)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6344 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/1-Deepika-Padukone-in-Bajirao-Mastani-3.jpg\" alt=\"1 Deepika Padukone in Bajirao Mastani (2)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<b style=\"font-size: 1.7em; font-style: inherit;\">Alia Bhatt in </b><b style=\"font-size: 1.7em; font-style: inherit;\"><i>Kalank</i></b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A film that tried to narrate a heart-breaking tale of love from the pre-independence era did not do well with the audience. However, no one can bet on the expensive sets and gorgeous costumes that have been designed for it. Alia Bhatt radiated royalty as she played the female lead character of Roop in the film.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6345 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/2-Alia-Bhatt-look-in-Kalank-1.jpg\" alt=\"2 Alia Bhatt look in Kalank (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In fact, This was the very first look at the movie. In it, the actress had made us spellbound with her iconic red dupatta ‘attired-with-all-the-jewellery’ royal bridal look. Also, when she danced as </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ghar More Pardesiya</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> played in the background, her white-coloured full-sleeved lehenga made us fall in love with her beauty. Even the minimal makeup complemented with just a bindi and a pair of earrings made Bhatt look like a fairy. All credits to the all-time-favourite fashion designer Manish Malhotra, the creator of </span><b>best costumes in Bollywood movies.</b>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6346 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/2-Alia-Bhatt-look-in-Kalank-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6347 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/2-Alia-Bhatt-look-in-Kalank-3.jpg\" alt=\"2 Alia Bhatt look in Kalank (3)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><b>Aishwariya Rai Bacchan in </b><b><i>Jodha Akbar </i></b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Speaking of </span><b>iconic Bollywood characters costumes</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, now let’s go back to 2008 when Ashutosh Gwarikaer created on-screen magic in the film </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jodha Akbar</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and indeed took us to the Mughal era. The evergreen diva Aishwarya Rai played the role of a Rajput Princess who gets married to emperor Akbar as a result of an alliance.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6350 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/3-Aishwariya-Rai-Bacchan-in-Jodha-Akbar-3.jpg\" alt=\"3 Aishwariya Rai Bacchan in Jodha Akbar  (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> The story moves forward as the duo falls in love. Coming back to Aishwariya, she was the epitome of royalty throughout the movie. The actress looked drop-dead gorgeous in the light makeup along with the heavy jewellery she wore for most of the scenes. The royal Rajasthani essence that her look generated is worth appreciable. Thanks to well-known designer Neeta Lulla for giving us such royal outfit goals.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6349 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/3-Aishwariya-Rai-Bacchan-in-Jodha-Akbar-2.jpg\" alt=\"3 Aishwariya Rai Bacchan in Jodha Akbar  (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6348 size-full\" style=\"font-weight: inherit;\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/3-Aishwariya-Rai-Bacchan-in-Jodha-Akbar-1.jpg\" alt=\"3 Aishwariya Rai Bacchan in Jodha Akbar  (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><b></b><b>Kangana Ranaut in </b><b><i>Manikarnika: The Queen of Jhansi</i></b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A blend of royalty, power, and courage has been flawlessly portrayed by Ranaut as she played the character of the great freedom fighter Rani Laxmi Bai, aka Queen of Jhansi, one of her major successful projects now. Even in such a fierce avatar, she made us impressed with her ethnic royal looks every time she appeared on the screen.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6351 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/4-Kangana-Ranaut-in-Manikarnika-The-Queen-of-Jhansi-1.jpg\" alt=\"4 Kangana Ranaut in Manikarnika The Queen of Jhansi (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Firstly, in the whitish-golden coloured outfit. The beauty generated by this </span><b>Bollywood actress in a salwar suit</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> can’t be explained in words. And then the most favourite of all is the one in which she was wearing a red colour saree with a lining of green. It was decked up in all the ornaments. Just like in </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jodha Akbar</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, the magical </span><b>famous Bollywood costumes</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> had been made by none other than Neeta Lulla.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6352 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/4-Kangana-Ranaut-in-Manikarnika-The-Queen-of-Jhansi-2.jpg\" alt=\"4 Kangana Ranaut in Manikarnika The Queen of Jhansi (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><b></b><b>Hema Malini in </b><b><i>Razia Sultan</i></b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This period biopic, made in 1983, is based on the life of the only woman sultan of Delhi. The titular character was portrayed by the dream girl of Bollywood, Hema Malini. It traces the epic story of the romance between her and her slave.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6353 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/5-Hema-Malini-in-Razia-Sultan-1.jpg\" alt=\"5 Hema Malini in Razia Sultan (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Despite being a film of that era, this cult classic never fails to give all the vibes of the sultanate era. While the cinematography and direction are worth praising, Hema Malini’s royal outfits made us feel as if Razia Sultan had indeed come alive from the pages of history. The royal </span><b>celebrity Anarkali suits</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and the turban were perfect to create that sultanate look and make us admire the </span><b>old Bollywood fashion</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in a true sense.</span>\r\n\r\n<b> <img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6354 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/5-Hema-Malini-in-Razia-Sultan-2.jpg\" alt=\"5 Hema Malini in Razia Sultan (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" /></b>\r\n<h2><b></b><b>Kajol in </b><b><i>Tanhaji The Unsung Warrior</i></b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Kajol’s Maharashtrian look is worth mentioning in this list. Her ethnic traditional outfits combined with superior acting made it look as if she was the only one made for the character of Savitribai Malusare, the wife of the titular character played by Ajay Devgan. She was not a queen or princess in the film; instead, she was the better half of a Sardar; still, she managed to look breathtakingly beautiful even in the simple sarees.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It was the light ornaments that indeed did a great job of giving an ancestral royal touch to her entire look. All credits go to designer Nachiket Barve for such brilliant styling of the actress.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6356 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/6-Kajol-in-Tanhaji-The-Unsung-Warrior-2.jpg\" alt=\"6 Kajol in Tanhaji The Unsung Warrior (2)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6355 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/6-Kajol-in-Tanhaji-The-Unsung-Warrior-1.jpg\" alt=\"6 Kajol in Tanhaji The Unsung Warrior (2)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><b>Zarine Khan in </b><b><i>Veer</i></b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hot and beautiful actress Zarine Khan made her debut with this Salman Khan. This was a period action Bollywood film in the year 2010. And in her very first project, she successfully gave us some major royal outfit goals.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I must say that she carried those looks very sportingly. Hence despite her not-so-impressive acting, we can’t stop ourselves from admiring her character of Princess Yashodhara. One of the most favourite looks is the bridal look of hers. She was wearing a red lehenga with the dupatta covering her head while wearing beautifully made jewellery.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In another scene, she was seen in a yellow-coloured royal outfit in which she managed to look equally gorgeous. In this way, more of her looks just stole away our gazes.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6357 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/7-Zarine-Khan-in-Veer-1.jpg\" alt=\"7 Zarine Khan in Veer (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6359 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/7-Zarine-Khan-in-Veer-3.jpg\" alt=\"7 Zarine Khan in Veer (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6358 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/7-Zarine-Khan-in-Veer-2.jpg\" alt=\"7 Zarine Khan in Veer (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><b>Priyanka Chopra in </b><b><i>Bajirao Mastani</i></b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, while everyone praises Deepika’s look from the film, we hardly talk about PC’s portrayal of Kashibai as well as the strong royal Marathi queen look she carried out. For the character, this global icon developed a powerful personality trait that suited perfectly with the traditional royal sarees and jewellery she was made to wear. Her dresses were also designed by </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Anju Modi and are truly one of the worth remembering </span><a href=\"https://www.limeroad.com/bollywood-collection\" rel=\"nofollow\"><b>Bollywood outfits</b></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> ever designed till now.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6360 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/8-Priyanka-Chopra-in-Bajirao-Mastani.jpg\" alt=\"8 Priyanka Chopra in Bajirao Mastani\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><b></b><b>Kareena Kapoor Khan in </b><b><i>Asoka</i></b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bebo is famous for carrying out ravishing looks in Hindi movies efficiently. From being the influencer Poo of Kabhi Khushi Kabhi Gham to being the simply dressed journalist of Satyagraha, the actress has always slain the outfit game of Bollywood. In this period biographical movie, which narrates how the war of Kalinga changed emperor Asoka’s life, she played the character of Princess Kaurwaki of Kalinga, opposite Shah Rukh Khan.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, unlike other princesses or queens, she was not draped in jewellery. Though she had worn the least ornaments, it has been her body art and out-of-the-box refreshing outfits that created the magic of royalty. Manish Malhotra and Anu Vardhan designed the dresses.  </span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6361 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/9-Kareena-Kapoor-Khan-in-Asoka.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><b></b><b>Karishma Kapoor in </b><b><i>Zubeidaa </i></b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Karishma Kapoor’s titular character in this film falls for a maharaja, played by Manoj Bajpayee and marries him. So, in that manner, she plays a queen in the movie. She represented royalty as Zubeidaa in the most elegant way and that’s the best part of the movie. Her chiffon sarees and jewellery indeed made her look ravishing.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6362 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/10-Karishma-Kapoor-in-Zubeidaa-.jpg\" alt=\"10 Karishma Kapoor in Zubeidaa \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><b></b><b>Deepika Padukone in </b><b><i>Padmavat</i></b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The beginning and ending are definitely perfect with the queen of Bollywood. As the legend says, Rani Padmavati of Chittor was a symbol of beauty. And she had been one of the most gorgeous queens of history.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6364 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/11-Deepika-Padukone-in-Padmavat-2.jpg\" alt=\"11 Deepika Padukone in Padmavat (2)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Deepika Padukone recreated her look for the film. She has awestricken us by the way she handled the challenging character as well as the heavy dresses and jewellery. She was mostly in traditional Rajasthani ghagra. The best one has been the red coloured ghagra with golden embroidered designs all over it, i.e., the one she wore for the </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ghoomar </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">dance.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6363 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/11-Deepika-Padukone-in-Padmavat-1.jpg\" alt=\"11 Deepika Padukone in Padmavat (2)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Indeed, the actress looked ethereal in those dresses and ornaments consisting of bangles, nose rings, chokers, etc. The dresses were designed by the super talented Rimple and Harpreet Narula.</span>\r\n<h2>Finally</h2>\r\n<b>Costume designing in Indian movies </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">by renowned designers is a major way to make the audience hype about the films. And these are some of the instances when our favourite Bollywood actresses just rocked in royal dresses.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hope you liked today’s content. See you in the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">next article</a>.</span>','Actresses Royal looks in Movies | Bollywood outfits | Costume movies','','publish','open','open','','actresses-royal-looks-in-movies-bollywood-outfits-costume-movies','','','2021-05-28 19:09:38','2021-05-28 13:39:38','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=6341',0,'post','',0),(6370,11,'2021-05-28 22:25:31','2021-05-28 16:55:31','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6372 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Drishyam-2-The-Resumption-review-1.jpg\" alt=\"Drishyam 2 The Resumption review (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nDrishyam 2: The Resumption could not be released in theatres because of the pandemic situation. It was released on the<a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/16-best-bollywood-movies-of-2020-on-netflix-and-amazon-prime/\"> OTT platform</a>. It is a sequel of Drishyam which was a blockbuster in the year 2013.\r\n<h2>Director, Cast of Drishyam 2</h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6373 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Drishyam-2-The-Resumption-review-2.jpg\" alt=\"Drishyam 2 The Resumption review (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nIt was written and directed by Jeethu Joseph. The movie was based on a crime thriller. In this movie, we can see Mohanlal, Meena, Asha Sharath, and Siddiqui sharing the screen space. It was a super hit blockbuster movie that attracted the audience to the theatre.\r\n<h2>Language of Drishyam 2</h2>\r\nFor this outstanding box office collection, this movie was remade in Tamil, Telugu, Hindi, Kannada by some of the biggest male stars of those industries.\r\n<h2>Trailer:</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0f-nd1uGsjQ\r\n<h2>What\'s So Special</h2>\r\nIn recent times, Malayalam crime thrillers are becoming the talk to the town. The director of this movie Jeethu Joseph is the actual hero in these two sequels. He proved once again and showed his master class in the Sequel Drishyam 2: The Resumption. Right from the opening scene, each frame was well connected to the first version.\r\n\r\nThe detailing for each scene was simply mind-blowing to watch. Most of the characters played in the first version were retained and only a few new faces played their part in the sequel. But everything was perfectly synced with the plot.\r\n<h2>The Ultimate Suspense</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6374 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Drishyam-2-The-Resumption-review-3.jpg\" alt=\"Drishyam 2 The Resumption review (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\nThis movie is a complete build-up of suspense and thrill keeping you at the edge of your seat. Mohan Lal played the protagonist in this movie. He himself proved again how talented and good an actor he is who is always ahead of everyone in every possible way and he proves it towards the climax just gives you a rush of adrenaline out of the surprising excitement.\r\n\r\nThis film has really uplifted the name “Drishyam” to another level, which was already a mega hit-making way for multiple remakes. If the sequel to a movie fails, then it actually affects the legacy the former had created. But to be frank, there is a huge expectation for every sequel, and this one has really fulfilled everyone\'s expectations.\r\n<h2>So, What\'s about the Interest?</h2>\r\nFrom the start, this movie was very much engaging. Be it the screenplay, the twist here and there, and the ultimate climax which is one of the special elements in Jeethu\'s movie, all we’re so well written and beautifully executed.\r\n\r\nEvery night scenes were literally bringing in that cold feeling within and all the scenes perfectly kept building up the castle, making us wait for the final reveal. There is a line in the movie stating, “ so he has begun his game.” This could have definitely been one of the best theatrical moments, but nevertheless, it was amazing.\r\n\r\nIt was also a family drama and of an ordinary man rising to the occasion.  I think all movie lovers were amazing. The first one hour or so is pretty boring but wait. Hold on to your patience because all these boring moments lead to a massive shocking twist that literally skyrockets the pace of this movie.\r\n<h2>The plot of Drishyam 2</h2>\r\nThe main plot is that in Drishyam,  the police had challenged that they would find the dead body and George Kutty confidently accepted it knowing that they wouldn\'t find it under the police station.\r\n\r\nHowever, in Drishyam 2,  it is revealed that George\'s acts had a witness. since the witness got jailed immediately for his own crime, the investigation did not have a witness. Now 6 years later, the witness is out of jail, and George is in deep trouble when the witness reveals and the dead investigation gets a massive boost.\r\n<h2>Let\'s know a little about Story:</h2>\r\nPart one continues and this sequel shows the routine life of the accused family where Georgekutty becomes a theatre owner from being a cable operator. He writes a book on his own story which he wants to show the same story in a feature film also produced by him. He finds out about the film industry guys and starts working with them. As well as release a book with limited edition copies in only local areas.\r\n\r\nA couple stays just beside their house and the wife accompanies Georgekutty\'s wife as her husband keeps torturing. And there the movie takes all the turn, the couple is shadow police.  And the case is reopened. Varun was killed and her mother is IG And DSPs.\r\n<h3>The personal war Scene</h3>\r\nThere is a scene where he says that it is not about the police department but it is many times about the personal war and this is my war also that how a stupid man can fool the whole police department. How a man can be so much clever and intellectual that he reaches this extent to save his family. The police family comes to know that the dead body is buried under the police station.\r\n\r\nVarun\'s mother and father can become so rebel forgetting the past and their own deeds, as well as they, get one eye witness against Georgekutty. But in this part also, the game by Georgekutty continues and the movie connects the first half and second half strings attached together and shows all dramas.\r\n<h3>The Ultimate End</h3>\r\nThe story ends with a happy ending as the Court releases the full family due to lack of evidence against them. It proves the accused NOT GUILTY. But the how, that is the magic of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jeethu_Joseph\" rel=\"nofollow\">JEETU JOSEPH</a> and Drishyam 2. If you like Drishyam 1, you would love Drishyam 2 more.','Drishyam 2: The Resumption review | Star Cast, Trailer, Language','','publish','open','open','','drishyam-2-the-resumption-review-star-cast-trai