\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Gajraj-Rao-with-Manoj-Bajpai.jpg\" alt=\" Gajraj Rao with manoj bajpayi\" width=\"800\" height=\"365\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>(Gajraj Rao during theatre days)</strong></em></p>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once Rao shared that while being a student of the Delhi university, he went to watch a play with one of his friends and that was when he took this decision of entering this world of entertainment. However, his path to enter the film industry was not easy. After graduation, he went on doing theatre along with some odd jobs, firstly as a tailor and then as a worker in some garment company. He went on changing jobs but always found solace in theatre. His talent made him get the opportunity to work as a freelance writer for well-known newspapers like Navbharat and Hindustan times and as a script writer for Doordarshan. Lastly, he got the break when famous Hindi film director Pradeep Sarkar gave him a fabulous offer to write for his ad-films. After a few years, in 1994, Gajraj Rao finally got his dream fulfilled when director Shekhar Kapur offered him a role in the biopic </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bandit queen.</span></i>\r\n<h2><b>Gajraj Rao family and friends</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rao’s family has completely been a non-filmy one, with no connections in the world of Bollywood. After his birth in a simple middle-class family of Rajasthan, he spent his later days in Delhi. As per sources his dad was a staff in Indian Railways. Hence, long with his parents, the actor used to reside in a railway colony of Delhi.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Right now, he is leading a happy marital life with his wife Sanjana Rao and the couple is also the parents of two sons. The elder one is reportedly pursuing a career in graphic designing.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Regarding friendships, Rao shares a really good bond with his co-actress Neena Gupta with whom he has shared the screen quite a few times and as a pair they have always delivered amazing performances. Besides work, they are at times spotted together and even post pictures with each other on social media. Gajraj Rao Instagram gives an instance of that. He also shares a good relation with Manoj Bajpai since theatre days.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6571 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Bollywood-actor-Gajraj-Rao-biography-2.jpg\" alt=\"Gajrat Rao with Neena Gupta\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>(Gajrat Rao with Neena Gupta)</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><b>Gajraj Rao age and physique</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The actor’s birth was in the year 1971. He is currently 50 years old. With an amazing height of around 5’9”, he looks handsome and charming even at this age.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Journey in Bollywood – Gajraj Rao movies</b></h2>\r\n<h3><b>Before 2000s:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In Gajraj Rao biography, his journey begins in Bollywood with </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bandit queen</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in the year 1994 where he played a minor character.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1995 he was a part of the Dimple Kapadia starrer Hindi film </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pathreela Raasta.</span></i>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In 1998 he was seen as an investigating officer in the hit Sharukh Khan-Preity Zinta film </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dil Se</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Next, we witnessed him in the character of Tiwari ji in the 2000’s Bollywood movie </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dil Pe Mat Le yaar i</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">n which he shared the screen with other eminent actors like Manoj Bajpai and Tabu.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6572 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Bollywood-actor-Gajraj-Rao-biography-3.jpg\" alt=\" Gajraj Rao with manoj bajpayi\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong> (Gajraj Rao in Dil Pe mat Le yaar alongside Manoj Bajpai)</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><b>2000-2010:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After 2000, Rao became more frequent on screen and was seen in many of the versatile characters. </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dil Hai Tamara, Yeh Kya Ho Raha Hai?, Black Friday, No smoking Aamir</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are his major releases in this decade. However, he was still to achieve the stardom he deserves.</span>\r\n<h3><b>After 2010</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His career attained greater heights mainly after 2010. After 2008, Rao was absent from the big screen up to almost 2014 and then made a comeback with the 2014 Amitabh Bachchan starrer </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bhootnath returns</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. He played the character of Baade Sahab, a ghost officer in the film.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His big breakthrough performance was in the year 2015 when he portrayed a negative character of an inspector in the critically acclaimed thriller film </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Talvar</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Post that he became a more demandable face in Bollywood and went on delivering more and more challenging roles.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6573 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Bollywood-actor-Gajraj-Rao-biography-4.jpg\" alt=\" Gajraj Rao \" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>(Rao in Meghna Gulzar’s film Talvaar)</strong></em></p>\r\n