ow. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The pain of Aman, the struggle of Naina and the helplessness of Rohit and every and every emotion of the movie has been beautifully captured by the theme of heartbeats which will definitely hit you at the heart.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Javed Akhtar\'s lyrics fit perfectly with </span><b>Shankar Ehsaan Loy\'</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">s soulful vocals and </span><b>Sonu Nigam\'s</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> melody. Even after so many years, the title track which is in IMDb top Bollywood songs is definitely everyone\'s favourite and surely makes one nostalgic for the old days of SRK\'s romance. Definitely worth placing it among the best Bollywood soundtracks in the 2000s.</span>\r\n<h2><b>6. Lagaan (2001)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb: 8.1</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Ashutosh Gowarikar</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Music Director: A R Rahman</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Cast: Aamir Khan, Gracy Singh</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on Netflix</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6487 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Top-10-bollywood-movies-with-best-soundtracks-list-5.jpg\" alt=\"Lagaan, bollywood movies with best soundtracks list\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Considered among the best movies in Indian history, Lagaan directed by Ashutosh Gowariker has Aamir Khan in lead roles with an excellent support cast. From British Raj to poverty, the burden of taxes to the game of cricket, and many other facets of the movie, </span><b>A R Rahman</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> captivates this with a calm soothing soundtrack which then transforms into a powerful track that signifies the battle against the British. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For the composition of timeless songs like </span><b>Mitwa</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><b>Radha Kaise Na Chale,</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> one can easily say that </span><b>A R</b> <b>Rahman</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is truly a genius.</span>\r\n<h2><b>5. Swades (2004)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb: 8.2</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Ashutosh Gowarikar</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Music Director: A R Rahman</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Cast: Shahrukh Khan, Gayatri Joshi</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on Netflix</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6488 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Top-10-bollywood-movies-with-best-soundtracks-list-6.jpg\" alt=\"Swedesh, bollywood movies with best soundtracks list\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fifth on the list we have </span><b>Swadesh</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. It should be a crime that this </span><b>Shahrukh Khan</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> starrer film didn\'t get its due credit and craze. Another masterpiece by </span><b>Ashutosh</b> <b>Gowariker</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is one of the most underrated films in Bollywood. The quest to find someone\'s true self and identify their roots, and work in unison for a greater cause is beautifully captured in the movie. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In sequences, the instrumental of Yeh Jo Des Hai Tera plays, and it only shows us what a  genius A R Rahman is. The music here really touches you in every shape and form. </span>\r\n<h2><b>4. Black (2005)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb: 8.2</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Sanjay Leela Bhansali</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Music Director: Monty Sharma</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Cast: Amitabh Bachchan, Rani Mukherjee</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on YouTube</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6489 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Top-10-bollywood-movies-with-best-soundtracks-list-7.jpg\" alt=\"Black, bollywood movies with best soundtracks list\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Next on the list, we have the movie, Black. It is A extremely beautiful and emotional film directed by </span><b>Sanjay Leela Bhansali</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, starring Amitabh Bachchan and Rani Mukherjee in lead roles. Black revolves around a deaf and blind girl and her relationship with her teacher, who later develops Alzheimer\'s disease. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The movie draws inspiration from Helen Keller\'s life and struggle. The music which was composed by Monty Sharma was extremely well crafted, especially Michelle\'s Theme - a score that had the power and quality and warmth which touched everyone\'s soul.</span>\r\n<h2><b>3. Life in a Metro (2007)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb: 7.4</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Anurag Basu</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Music Director: Pritam</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Cast: Rajat Shiney Ahuja, Irfan Khan, Shilpa Shetty, Kangana Ranaut, Konkona Sen Sharma, Sharman Joshi, Dharmendra, Nafisa Ali</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on Netflix</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6490 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Top-10-bollywood-movies-with-best-soundtracks-list-8.jpg\" alt=\"Life in a metro, bollywood movies with best soundtracks list\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie with an ensemble cast is definitely among the most celebrated movies of Bollywood in the last two decades, thanks to the amazing duo behind the success of this movie - </span><b>Anurag Basu</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><b>Pritam</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. The musical craftsmanship of Pritam is beyond words.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The characters are interesting with their own stories to follow through this film, and somehow their lives are connected.  Each actor has done a brilliant job portraying their characters, </span><b>Dharmendra</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><b>Nafisa\'s</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> love story was so beautiful and sad too. It was actually good to see them share a tender kiss, which shows the actors and directors have moved with the times. Thank god. Above all, this film touches upon the lives of 9 people, who struggle with life in the city, the highs, and lows of finding work, and finding love.   </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With songs like </span><b>Alvida, In Dino,</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><b>Baatein Kuch</b> <b>Ankahee Si</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> will surely take you to those early days and it\'s among the Bollywood movies with the best songs.</span>\r\n<h2><b>2. Gangs of Wasseypur 1 and 2. (2012)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb: 8.2</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Anurag Kashyap</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Music Director: Sneha Khanwalkar</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Cast: Manoj Bajpai, Pankaj Tiwari, Nawazuddin Siddiqui, Raj Kumar Rao, Huma Qureshi, Richa Chadda.</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on Netflix, Amazon Prime Video</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6491 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Top-10-bollywood-movies-with-best-soundtracks-list-9.jpg\" alt=\"Gangs of waseypur, bollywood movies with best soundtracks list\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">By now, if you haven\'t seen this movie, you have definitely committed a crime. One of the best of modern-day Indian cinema, this movie features some of the most talented and experienced actors of Bollywood today. From </span><b>Manoj Bajpai to Pankaj Tiwari to Nawazuddin Siddiqui and Raj Kumar Rao</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, they have all. Moreover, the plot focuses on Faisal Khan\'s taking revenge for all the harmful murders that have plagued his family.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Gangs of Wasseypur has definitely the coolest soundtrack in modern-day Bollywood. Courtesy to geniuses like </span><b>Amit Trivedi</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><b>Sneha Khanwalkar</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. The Dubstep track titled \"kkl\" from the scene where Faisal Khan brutally kills Ramadhir Singh will surely blow your mind.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It\'s a perfect blend of folk music from rural Bihar and UP and the studios of Mumbai. Sometimes, we forget about just how great the music from Wasseypur is, given the multitude of things that stand out when you\'re watching these films but that\'s okay. </span>\r\n<h2><b>1. Dev D (2009)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb: 8.2</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Anurag Kashyap</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Music Director: Amit Trivedi</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Cast: Mahie Gill, Abhay Deol, Kalki Koechlin</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Available on Netflix</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1990 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/7-min.jpg\" alt=\"Dev D, movie with best soundtrack \" width=\"750\" height=\"480\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">At the top of the list, we have the best soundtrack of Bollywood - a brainchild of the mastermind </span><b>Amit</b> <b>Trivedi</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A perfect movie that shows what a toxic man can actually be because a story revolving around finding redemption and in its core about second chances and it nails right in the core. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Firstly, The creators of this movie did a great job of connecting the then-present social dilemmas and issues to the plot of this movie and executed it so profoundly that when this movie ends you really start thinking about the society we live in. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Secondly, This story that </span><b>DevD</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">’s soundtrack tells draws in and traps the listener into a state of mind for 60 straight minutes. This is the Devdas state of mind. Devdas, over the years, had ceased to become a character, a book, or a film, </span><b>Kashyap</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> had said in 2009. “It has become an adjective and my movie is about that adjective.” If the film is an elaborate thesis on this adjective, the soundtrack is an incantation woven around it. This truly deserves the title of best Indian soundtracks of all time. </span>\r\n\r\n<b>Some Honourable Mentions: Aashiqui 2, Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara, Kahaani, Devdas, Earth, Rock On</b>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Here was the list of Bollywood movies with best soundtracks.</span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So, this is the content for today. We at The</span><b>TvFreak.com</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> attempt to wake you up to the ennobling journeys of our favorite artists. For future movie trailers, movie reviews, and movie updates on the latest Bollywood and Hollywood movies. Stay safe, maintain social distance, and do not forget to check The</span><b>TvFreak.com</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> for more!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hope you had a cheerful reading. See you within the next article!</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWant to have more fun. Watch <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/kiara-advani-bio-movies-tv-shows-ads-hot-pics-upcoming-movies/\">Kiara Advani</a> latest news!','Top 10 bollywood movies best soundtracks of all time','','publish','open','open','','top-10-bollywood-movies-best-soundtracks-of-all-time','','','2021-07-15 08:27:49','2021-07-15 02:57:49','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=6481',0,'post','',0),(6497,12,'2021-06-25 23:45:25','2021-06-25 18:15:25','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Gossips and news about the B-town always interests us. Afterall, who doesn’t want to be updated about their favorite stars’ personal and professional lives? So, today TVfreak.com presents to you the top 25 Bollywood news of last week.</span>\r\n<h2>1. <b>Chandrasekhar Vaidya’s demise</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6506 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/1.jpg\" alt=\"Chandrasekhar Vaidya\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bollywood lost a talent yet again! Chandrashekhar Vaidya, mainly known for playing supporting roles in well-known movies as well as for portraying the character of Sumatra in the iconic television series Ramayana, breathed his last on 16th June 2021. At the age of 97, this veteran actor passed away peacefully in his sleep.</span>\r\n<h2>2. <b>Minisha Limba opened up about her relationship status</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6507 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/2.jpg\" alt=\"Minisha Limba\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Coming to the next recent Bollywood news, the </span><strong><i>Bachna Hai Haseeno </i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>actress Minisha Limba</strong> tied the knot in the year 2015 with someone from outside the entertainment industry. However, in 2020, the duo got separated. In a very recent interview, when asked about the current circumstances in her life, the actress gladly opened up about how she has moved on and also claimed that she is happily in a relationship with someone.</span>\r\n<h2><b>3. Arjun Rampal’s new look</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6508 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/3.jpg\" alt=\"Arjun Rampal’s new look\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Handsome actor Arjun Rampal has startled everyone by sharing his new glamorous look on Instagram. In the pictures, this 48 year old was seen with platinum blonde hair complemented by black moustache and beard, black shades and a white t-shirt. From the caption, fans got to know that this look is a part of his upcoming project </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dhakkad </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">starring Kangana Ranaut. Rampal’s playing a negative role in the film is one of the most discussed news of B-town currently.</span>\r\n<h2><b>4. Sonu Sood – the savior</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6509 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/4.jpg\" alt=\"Sonu Sood\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So, here comes the next update in the list of Bollywood news. Since the beginning of the COVID-19 pandemic, actor Sonu Sood has engaged himself in all sorts of generous activities starting from helping labourers to go back to their homes. <strong>Last Friday, this actor once again won many hearts by booking an urgent surgery for a baby of only 6 months</strong>. He took the entire responsibility for it once the father of the infant approached him via <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sonu_Sood\">social media</a>.</span>\r\n<h2><b>5. SSR’s sister heartfelt note on the actor’s 1</b><b>st</b><b> death anniversary</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6510 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/5.jpg\" alt=\"SSR death anniversary\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">14th June, 2021 has been the black day for Indian cinema as last year on the same day the film industry lost one of its gems, Sushant Singh Rajput who died by suicide. Investigation went on for months to find out the conspiracy behind his unfortunate demise. This year on this very day, on the saddening occasion of the actor’s first death anniversary, his sister Meetu Singh has shared a heartfelt note along with pictures from the havaan and assured justice to her dead brother. In the pictures, she was seen along with the two other sisters.</