></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in the movie.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nhttps://youtu.be/QmOAIIrQK80\r\n<h2><b>9. Gone Girl (2014)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb: </b>8.4/10</li>\r\n <li><b>Director: </b>David Fincher</li>\r\n <li><b>Cast: </b>Ben Affleck, Rosamund Pike, Neil Patrick Harris</li>\r\n <li><b>Genre:</b> Drama, Mystery, Thriller</li>\r\n <li><b>Available on Netflix</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When you know it\'s a movie by </span><b>Fincher</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, you know the type of gem you are about to experience. </span><b>Adapted from a book </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">with a matching title, it has successfully delivered the suspense and thrill of the novel.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Set in a suburban American country side, when a popular young lady </span><b>goes missing</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> suddenly on her wedding anniversary, fingers starts pointing to her husband. Blended with strong aspects of psychothriller, this movie is also a cynical take on the current day media. Surely a </span><b>late night watch</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and among the movies for snowy weather.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Facts and Trivia:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It\'s the Highest grossing </span><b>David</b> <b>Fincher</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> film.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nhttps://youtu.be/cFGLBQLUuUU\r\n<h2><b>8. Little Things (2021)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb: </b>6.3/10</li>\r\n <li><b>Director: </b>John Lee Hancock</li>\r\n <li><b>Cast: </b>Denzel Washington, Rami Malek, Jared Leto</li>\r\n <li><b>Genre: </b>Crime, Drama, Thriller</li>\r\n <li><b>Available on YouTube</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie is a murder mystery about a serial killer in an American country side. This </span><b>who-dunnit</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> suspense thriller features some most popular faces