ion, Adventure, Drama</li>\r\n <li><b>Available on Netflix</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This survival drama is about a tribe leader who gets attacked by a bear and is isolated by his crew. The determination of survival and take revenge in such a drastic weather conditions forms the plot of the movie. The performance delivered by </span><b>Di Caprio</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><b>Hardy</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is beyond words. The </span><b>cinematography</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> of this films is simply a </span><b>visual treat</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> for the eyes. The movie is shot entirely in </span><b>natural light</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> which makes it more realistic. Also you may require subtitles for this one because of the mumbling dialoges in emotional scenes which adds emphasis to the acting part and conveys </span><b>complex</b> <b>emotions</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> better. This movie is surely a must watch and among the best of the last decade. This is best <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/11-amazing-best-crazy-and-funny-hollywood-facts/\">snowy thriller movie</a>.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Facts and Trivia</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">:</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Di Caprio</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> ate the real lever of a horse to make the scene more realistic. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nhttps://youtu.be/6h6avrP_vt0\r\n<h2><b>2. Memories of Murder (2003)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb: </b>8.3/10</li>\r\n <li><b>Director: </b>Bong Jong Hoo</li>\r\n <li><b>Cast: </b>Kang Ho Song, Kim Sang Kyun</li>\r\n <li><b>Genre: </b>Crime, Drama, Mystery</li>\r\n <li><b>Available on YouTube</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One of the early movies of </span><b>Bong Jong Hoo</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> it\'s about a serial killer who targets and mercilessly kills women in a small town near </span><b>Seoul</b><