ost loved as well as critically acclaimed award-winning Bollywood horror fantasy movies of all time is this 2018’s frightful period drama. Not a regular horror movie that will scare you from turning back at night, but its setting, a thread linking myth and fantasy with horror and reality, has the capability of messing up with your mind. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A tale that intrigues morality narrates the story of how the characters get cursed (turns into monsters or trees – the most captivating scenes) due to their greed.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A mythological story about Hastar, a greedy deity saved by his creator from other gods only on condition of not being worshipped by anyone forms the backdrop of the film. Problems arise when humans build a temple for him to obtain the wealth he has. With such an out-of-the box storyline, this film will keep your eyes glued to the screen till the end.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Direction, screenplay, cinematography - is indeed the best from many aspects. Also hats off to actors like Sohum Shah, Jyoti Malshe, and Ronjini Chakraborty as well as to child actor Mohammad Samad who portrayed such challenging characters flawlessly.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> I can bet that masterpiece </span>movies like Tumbbad in Hollywood<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> also rarely exist.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sN75MPxgvX8\r\n<h2><b>2. Raat:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB:</strong> 7.1</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> Ram Gopal Verma</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> YouTube</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This 1992 film, one among the </span>Bollywood old horror movies<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, is another highly rated cinematic gem which has indeed proved the worth of the </span>horror genre in India.<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> A cult classic that you are going to enjoy even if you are not a fan of 90’s films- that’s my guarantee.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This horrifying tale is about a kitten which gets killed and its spirit possesses the lead female character, a girl named Manisha played by famous Tamil actress Revathy. Warning! if you are a cat lover don\'t go for this Hindi film. Your love for these creatures can change into fear and terrifying screams whenever you see them.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://youtu.be/Ar5RHRCl6ks\r\n<h2><b>3. 13 B | </b><b>Best Bollywood horror movies</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 7.3</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by</strong>: Vikram K. Kumar</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on</strong>: Disney+Hotstar.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Speaking of the must watch Bollywood movies made by Bollywood, this supernatural thriller is definitely worth mentioning. Like any other horror story, it starts with a picture-perfect family moving into a new house which is supposedly haunted. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now you will say, what’s new in that plot? But the way the story has been presented with the mind blowing twists and turns incorporated at the correct timings do deserve an applause. The tale will take a grip on you with the beginning of scary events like the spirit trying to communicate with the family via a TV, thrilling enough right? Madhavan who delivers an outstanding performance plays the lead character. It is really one of the </span>best Hindi horror movies on OTT like Netflix and amazon prime, <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-ullu-web-series-online-that-you-must-watch/\">ULLU web series</a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://youtu.be/-eWl5M-jqxs\r\n<h2><b>4. Pari:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 6.6</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> Prosit Roy</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Amazon Prime Video</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">An underrated work of Bollywood and undoubtedly the best performance of Anushka Sharma so far is in this 2018’s horror movie. A treat for all the scary film buffs, the film shows two parallel storylines, one of the Ifrith satanic cult of Bangladesh and another of a gentleman named Arnab who falls for a mysterious girl named Ruhksana.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A totally different approach Indian cinema has ever applied in the horror genre, the film has the capability to redefine it. Its song </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Meri Khamoshi Hai</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> still tops our playlist. While some scenes will surely give you goosebumps, the ending is going to make you cry.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://youtu.be/PQKu78NnyvU\r\n<h2><b>5. Stree | </b><b>Best Bollywood horror movies</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB:</strong> 7.6</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> Amar Kaushik</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Disney+Hotstar.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2018 has indeed been Bollywood’s best year of exploring the horror genre. While we got paranormal thrillers with elements of mythologies or folklores in masterpieces like </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tumbbad</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pari</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Stree </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">has been a perfect combination of horror and comedy.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It is the story of a female witch who used to pray on men during nights. The central character Vicky, played by Rajkumar Rao sets out on a struggle along with his squad to save their friend, Jaana as he had supposedly been possessed by the ghost. Rao’s perfect comic timings as well as Shraddha Kapoor’s impressive performance in a mysterious character along with the supporting cast and some horrifying sequences have made the movie receive lots of appreciation.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://youtu.be/hR9Uyp6a68Y\r\n<h2><b>6. Veerana:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 6.7</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> Shyam Ramsay and Tulsi Ramsay</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Youtube</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This movie made in 1988 is enough to haunt you for nights. After this, many attempts have been made with this combined genre of eroticism and horror, but not a single movie can mark the heights of </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Veerana</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It is about a witch that goes into a body of a young woman named Jasmine and seduces some men, kills some and in this way sets out on a murder spree. With well-woven characters, this one is indeed a great watch where its creepy looking creatures are going to scare you the most.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://youtu.be/ZArMTDk0fuk\r\n<h2><b>7. Bhoot:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 6.5</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by</strong>: Ram Gopal Verma</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Netflix</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another of </span>great Indian horror movies<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is this 2003’s Ajay Devgan-Urmila Matondkar film has not only been a box office success but has also been also greatly loved by masses and is considered a really appreciable work in the world of horror films.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It’s about a newly married couple who moves into an apartment with a dark past - a woman committed suicide after killing her own child. Gradually the wife starts getting affected by all these past happenings, started hallucinating or has she been possessed by the spirit? Of course, you need to watch the film to know more.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://youtu.be/BS41ajS4wYc\r\n<h2><b>8. Bulbul:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 6.6</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> Avnita Dutt</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Netflix</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The most recent and appreciated works of Bollywood has been this 2020’s Netflix original film starring Tripti Damri, Parambrata Chatterjee, Paoli Dam, Rahul Bose and others. It has presented to us totally refreshing content.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Unlike other horror films, it is not the story of any witch or ghost, rather it narrates the journey of a girl named Bulbul, the crimes of which she had been a victim of in a male-dominant setting and shows how powerful and scary a woman can become to raise her voice against oppression and injustice.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">More than making you scared, this Bollywood film is going to make you appreciate the film industry’s encouraging attempt in experimenting with a concept much relevant to today\'s times where a woman faces all kinds of harassment from the society.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://youtu.be/4MGReT9-cAg\r\n<h2><b>9. Go Goa Gone:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 6.7</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> Krishna DK, Raj Nidimoru</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Available on:</strong> Jio Cinema</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The concept of zombies in itself is too much spine chilling. Zombie movies are very rare in Bollywood. But the year of 2013 offered a tale of zombies in a hilarious way in this Safe Ali Khan, Kunal Khemu and Vir Das starrer box-office success horror comedy.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It’s about four friends who get stuck on an island in Goa infested by zombies. Well, some may find few flaws in the script. But that can easily be ignored by the way horror, fun, adventure, action has been amalgamated in it. If you want to have an entertaining weekend or spend a lazy afternoon, it’s really suggestable to give this film a watch.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://youtu.be/gwhsuOljaxQ\r\n<h2><b>10. Ek Thi Dayaan:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>IMDB</strong>: 5.7</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Directed by:</strong> Kannan Iyer</span></li>\r\n <li><strong>Available on: </strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jio cinema</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This is one of the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-adult-and-hot-movies-of-bollywood/\">hot hit movies</a>. Even the thought of witches and dayaans is enough to give us all the spooky feels. All the fantasies and mysteries that have always kept us engulfed have been perfectly put up in this Imran Hashmi starrer film.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A film where magic, thrill and horror meet, narrates how the central character, a magician named Bobo encounters witches in various phases of his life (firstly, as his father’s wife and then…. Well, the rest is a mystery!) and deal with them.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://youtu.be/UN5Ss-EV_qc\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Some of the blood-curdling sequences will surely give you some sleepless nights. Also, not to miss out on the eminent actresses like Konkona Sen Sharma, Kalki Koechlin, Huma Quereshi as they carried out their respective roles with such an ease. It’s worth watching and don’t let IMDBs fool you every time.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With this, we complete our list of the </span>Bollywood best horror movies<b>.</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Hope you liked the content. See you in the next article.</span>','Top 10 Best Bollywood Horror Movies Which Can Not Be Seen Alone','','publish','open','open','','top-10-best-bollywood-horror-movies','','','2021-07-01 10:40:48','2021-07-01 05:10:48','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=6592',0,'post','',0),(6625,12,'2021-07-06 05:58:23','2021-07-06 00:28:23','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Be it an update about an upcoming film, pictures of our favorite star holidaying or rumor of a celebrity dating, Bollywood news indeed arouse our interests. In the monotonous days when we are tired of maintaining our regular work schedule, </span><b>Bollywood hot gossips</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are one of those things which act as a catalyst in keeping us somewhat relaxed and entertained. So, today tvfreak.com presents to you the top 25 Bollywood news of this entertainment industry from last week. </span>\r\n<h2><b>End of the Amir Khan – Kiran Rao love story</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A blissful journey of love and 15 years of marital life is what this Bollywood power couple had witnessed. Their recent announcement of separation has come as a shock and surprise to their fans and admirers. An official statement was released by the duo this Saturday regarding this <a href=\"https://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/ira-khan-shares-first-instagram-post-after-aamir-khan-k