Games </b></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">(Effie Trinket) and </span><b>Pitch Perfect</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> (Gail). </span><b>Pitch Perfect 2 </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">is the movie that she directed exclusively and that movie was a hit at the box office. </span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d0b0owXWGdo\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is </span><b>Ella Balinska</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">’s debut feature film as an actress.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>19. Larry Crowne (2011)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 6.1</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Tom Hanks (Also Directed That Thing You Do!)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: Tom Hanks, Julia Roberts, Randall Park, Bryan Cranston, Rami Malek</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: Amazon Prime Video</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6738 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"Larry Crowne (2011)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Well, </span><b>Julia Roberts</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> is an actress who has chemistry with almost all Hollywood actors— George Clooney, Richard Gare, Hugh Grant. You name it. And why would Tom Hanks be left out? </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The story of Larry Crowne is very simple and sweet. Larry is a middle-aged man who is only a high school graduate. After an unfortunate turn in his life, he had to get admitted to a college to start anew. There he meets Mercedes, who is his economic teacher in college. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is a romance story between a student and a teacher. If you are looking for movies that were directed by the star of the movie, you can pick this one.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x_-tWhlcQok\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The story of this film is loosely based on the life of </span><b>Jim Chandler</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">. He is Tom Hanks’s friend.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Tom Hanks has also directed an episode of </span><b>Band Of Brothers (2001)</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The first movie that Tom Hanks directed</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400\">was That</span><b> Thing You Do!</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> (1996) was nominated for an Oscar in the category of Best Music, Original Song (For the song \"That Thing You Do!\") but lost the award to </span><b>Evita (</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">For the song</span><b> \"You Must Love Me\").</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>18. The Invisible Woman (2013)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 6.1</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Ralph Fiennes (Also Directed Coriolanus, The White Crow)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: Ralph Fiennes, Felicity Jones, Kristin Scott Thomas </b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: The Roku Channel</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6739 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/3Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"The Invisible Woman (2013)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Invisible Woman is a biography film about the famous Novelist </span><b>Charles Dickens</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and his extramarital love affair. But anything good hardly comes from this kind of relationship. We just have to watch the film to know if this forbidden love destroys three lives or not. </span>\r\n\r\n<b>Ralph Fiennes</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, you may know him better as </span><b>Voldemort</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> from </span><b>The Harry Potter Franchisee</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> is an English film director-actor. He played the role of Charles Dickens in this film. The Invisible Woman is his second movie as a director. </span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WDMHb3GetIc\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Invisible Women (2013) was nominated in the category of Best </span><b>Achievement in Costume Design</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> at The Oscars 2014. The movie lost the award to </span><b>The Great Gatsby</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>17. The Interview (2014)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 6.5</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Directors: Evan Goldberg, Seth Rogen (Also Directed This Is the End)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: James Franco, Seth Rogen, Randall Park, Lizzy Caplan </b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: HBO Max</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6740 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/4Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"The Interview (2014)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Dave is the host of a famous talk show and Aaron is his producer. Most of the topic of the job is mainly involves in talking and bringing out the most scandalous news of celebrities. This makes Aaron think if the show is actually making a difference in the real world. So when he hears that </span><b>Kim Jong Un</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, the dictator of North Korea, is a fan of his show, he and Dave decide to interview him. But it will not be as easy as it sounds because the CIA also wants this as an opportunity to kill Jong Un using this interview. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie is pure entertainment. You will laugh your heart out, I promise.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Seth Rogan is one of the actors who directed themselves. This movie is the </span><b>6th collaboration</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> between </span><b>Seth Rogen</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and </span><b>James Franco</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and they do make a nice duo.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BObCk4wKLn0\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The total budget of this film was </span><b>$44 million</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and Seth Rogen alone was paid</span><b> $8 Million</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><b>Eminem</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> made a cameo in this movie.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>16. Money Monster (2016)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 6.5</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Jodie Foster (Also directed Little Man Tate, The Beaver, Home for the Holidays)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: George Clooney, Julia Roberts, Dominic West</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: Amazon Video</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6741 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/5Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"Money Monster (2016)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Money Monster is the name of a TV Talk Show that talks about finance. Lee Gates is the host of the show and Patty Fenn is the studio director. On a particular day, everything was going right until a man entered the show with a gun and took everybody hostage on live worldwide national TV.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qr_nGAbFkmk\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><b>Jodie Foster</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> has also given direction in some famous TV series like</span><b> Black Mirror</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, </span><b>House of Cards</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, and </span><b>Orange Is the New Black</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>15. The Good Shepherd (2006)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 6.7</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Robert De Niro (Also directed A Bronx Tale)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast:  Matt Damon, Angelina Jolie, Robert De Niro, Lee Pace, Joe Pesci, Alec Baldwin, Eddie Redmayne</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: DIRECTV</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6742 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/6Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"The Good Shepherd (2006)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Good Shepherd is one of the movies directed by famous actors. Edward Wilson (played by Matt Damon) was greatly shaken by his father’s suicide. Since then he had grown a will within himself to work for his country. But you know some people who are so good at making wrong choices one after another? Yup, that’s our Edward! But he does get the opportunity to work for his country in the cold war. Will he be able to do it? Or his father’s suicide will hold him back?</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is Robert De Niro’s second feature film. The first one was </span><b>A Bronx Tale</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> (1993, IMDb Rating 7.8)</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wkKFBJG3Oes\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Good Shepherd was nominated for an Oscar in the category of</span><b> Best Achievement in Art Direction</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> but lost the award to </span><b>Pan\'s Labyrinth</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">. (Fair enough)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the theatrical film debut of </span><b>Eddie Redmayne</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>14. Tropic Thunder (2008)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.0</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Ben Stiller (Also Directed Reality Bites, The Cable Guy, Zoolander I &amp; II, The Secret Life of Walter Mitty)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: Ben Stiller, Robert Downey Jr., Jack Black, Jay Baruchel, Matthew McConaughey, Tom Cruise</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: Amazon Prime Video</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6743 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/7Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"Tropic Thunder (2008)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Tropic Thunder is a war-comedy starring a lot of famous Hollywood stars. It is also a movie acted and directed by the same person.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The movie starts with the shooting of a war movie. Noticing no cooperation among the star cast, the director schemes to set the actors in a survival situation. But quite quickly the situation goes south because the location he chose is actually the operation area of a huge drug dealer gang. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Had a bad day, need to shrug off depression? Watch Tropic Thunder.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Also for your information, this is the </span><b>fifth film</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> that Ben Stiller directed. His directorial feature film debut was </span><b>Reality Bites</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> (1994) starring </span><b>Winona Ryder</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and </span><b>Ethan Hawke</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ASJvlHExnMA\r\n<h3><b>Award and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><b>Robert Downey Jr.</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> was nominated in the category of Best Performance by an </span><b>Actor in a Supporting Role</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> at the Oscars 2009. He lost the award to </span><b>Heath Ledger</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> in The Dark Knight. (Fair enough)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun facts: </b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><b>Justin Theroux</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> is one of the co-writers of this film. </span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><b>Tobey Maguire, Jennifer Love Hewitt, Jon Voight, and Jason Bateman</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> made cameos in this movie.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">If you don’t know who </span><b>Jay Baruchel</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> is, he voiced Hiccup in </span><b>How to Train Your Dragon.</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>13. The Water Diviner (2014)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.0</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Russell Crowe </b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: Russell Crowe, Olga Kurylenko</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: Tubi TV</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6744 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/8Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"The Water Diviner (2014)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Joshua is an ordinary Australian man who has sent three of his sons to war in Istanbul, Turkey. Four years after that, Joshua goes on a quest to search for his sons. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Water Diviner is a heart-touching story of a father. It is a story of a father keeping his promise to his sons.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The plot is very tragic and all, but the end was satisfying. You will cry both in sadness and happiness while watching this movie.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=grIiiHuetis\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the</span><b> directorial debut</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> of the </span><b>Oscar-winning</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> actor Russell Crowe.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the final work of cinematographer </span><b>Andrew Lesnie</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">. He was the cinematographer in all of the Lord of the Rings movies and won an Oscar in the category of Best Cinematography in 2002 for The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring (2001). (Rest in peace)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>12. One Night in Miami... (2020)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.1</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Regina King</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: Kingsley Ben-Adir, Eli Goree, Aldis Hodge </b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: Amazon Prime Video</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6745 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/9Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"One Night in Miami... (2020)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Fiction with the hint of reality is the best kind of fantasy. Yeah, I made up this quote to best describe Regina King’s One Night Miami. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">You know I always wondered what would happen if Sherlock Holmes and Hannibal Lecter were set in the same universe. It would be like an unstoppable force hitting an immovable object. But enough of my imagination. What </span><b>Kemp Powers</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> have put into writing is even greater than this paradox.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Just think about it. </span><b>Muhammad Ali, Malcolm X, Sam Cooke, and Jim Brown</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, all in the same time and same place, raising their voices against the rights of general people in the late 60s. Now that made me feel shivers down my spine. </span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=onX-F41ej6o\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><b>One Night in Miami</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> was nominated for </span><b>3 Oscars</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> but did not win any.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Regina King has given direction in some popular TV series like </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Scandal</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, </span><b>This Is Us, Shameless, The Good Doctor</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, etc.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>11. Unbroken (2014)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.2</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Angelina Jolie (Also directed By the Sea, First They Killed My Father)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast:  Jack O\'Connell, Miyavi, Domhnall Gleeson</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: AMC Plus</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6747 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/11Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"Unbroken (2014)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Unbroken is a war biography movie about </span><b>Louis Zamperini</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> who had to suffer a lot for unfortunate turns of events. Louis Zamperini was an Olympic athlete. During the second world war, he fell victim to a plane crash and his survival from that accident was not easy at all. He had to fight against nature and then he was taken as a war prisoner. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is Angelina Jolie’s second movie as a director. Her directorial debut was In the </span><b>Land of Blood and Honey </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">(2011).</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OT4fy2ed1So\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie was nominated in </span><b>3 categories at the Oscars</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> in 2015 but lost in all of them.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The screenplay of this movie is written by the Oscar-winning director duo </span><b>The Coen Brothers. </b></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Did you know Angelina Jolie’s father was an Oscar winner as well? </span><b>Jon Voight </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">won his Oscar in the category of Best Actor in a Leading Role for </span><b>Coming Home </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">(1978).</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>10. Fences (2016)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.2</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Denzel Washington (Also directed Antwone Fisher, The Great Debaters)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: Denzel Washington, Viola Davis</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: Amazon Video</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6748 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/12Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"Fences (2016)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Fences is a story of many unfulfilled dreams, the gap between two generations, and the fridge between a father and a son. Troy is an African American man raising his son in a world that reeks of white supremacy. The story is set in the 50s. Troy had a dream to be a basketball player which for many reasons did not come true. But when his son Cory wants to join the college football team, Troy refrains him from it. This led to a great conflict among the family.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Denzel Washington is one of the actors who are also directors. He is a</span><b> two-time Academy Award winner</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and Fences is his 3rd film as a director. His directorial debut was in the movie </span><b>Antwone Fisher</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> (2002).</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=spCxVd9ctFs\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie was nominated in the 4 major categories including the best picture and Best Performance by an Actor in a Leading Role. But the only Oscar win for this film is by </span><b>Viola Davis</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> in the category of Best Performance by an Actress in a Supporting Role.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Denzel Washington directed an episode of </span><b>Grey’s Anatomy</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> (Season 12, Episode 9). </span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><b>August Wilson</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> (who passed away in 2005) received a posthumous Oscar nomination for his \'Fences\' screenplay, adapted from his own play in 2017.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>09. Good Night, and Good Luck. (2005)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.4</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: George Clooney (Also directed Confessions of a Dangerous Mind, The Ides of March, The Monuments Men, Leatherheads)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: George Clooney, Jeff Daniels, Robert Downey Jr.</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: Tubi TV</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6749 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/13Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"Good Night, and Good Luck. (2005)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is another biography movie. But you can say it is a movie that shows the purpose and power of good journalism. The early 50s was a paranoid time with all the tension from communism. The man who was actually responsible for this was Senator </span><b>Joseph McCarthy</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">. Being a political body, he had all the power. That is why CBS reporter </span><b>Edward R. Murrow</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and his producer </span><b>Fred W. Friendly</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> took the matter into their hand and decided to expose the real culprit. Both of them had to go through immense difficulties and inconvenience. But they stood their ground because their morale was as strong as steel.  </span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1Qg9ZahBu8c\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie was nominated in 6 major categories at the Oscars 2006 including Best picture. Unfortunately, it did not win any.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">George Clooney the film director-actor was paid a total of </span><b>3 dollars</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> for his job in this movie, including writing, acting, and directing— one dollar for each job. (Yup, It’s true). He is also one of the few actors who wrote and starred in their own movies.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The budget for this film was </span><b>$7.5 million</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>08. A Quiet Place (2018)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.5</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: John Krasinski (Also directed A Quiet Place Part II, The Hollars)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: Emily Blunt, John Krasinski</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: fubo TV</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6750 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/14Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"A Quiet Place (2018)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">A Quiet Place is a post-apocalyptic dystopian movie. The earth is suddenly infiltrated by these monsters who are blind but very sensitive to sound. So to survive, humankind must stay as silent as possible. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The story is very interesting. And the suspense is almost unbearable.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The movie was a huge success and so they made a sequel to this movie—</span><b> A Quiet Place 2</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">. </span><b>Cillian Murphy</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and </span><b>Djimon Hounsou</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> starred in the movie.</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Personal Recommendation:</b> <b>Bird Box </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">(2018) is a very similar film to this one. It has </span><b>Sandra Bullock</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> in the leading role.  </span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BpdDN9d9Jio\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie was nominated for an Oscar in the category of Best Achievement in Sound Editing but lost the award to </span><b>Bohemian Rhapsody</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">John Krasinski also directed 3 episodes of </span><b>The Office</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> (US).</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This film is highly praised by the </span><b>Horror God Stephen King</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">John Krasinski and </span><b>Emily Blunt</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> are married in real life.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie has references from many classic horror films like </span><b>Vertigo, Psycho, Rosemary’s Baby, Jaws, Alien</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, etc.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>07. Dead Man Walking (1995)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.5</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Tim Robbins (Also directed Bob Roberts)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: Susan Sarandon, Sean Penn</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: Max Go</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6751 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/15Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"Dead Man Walking (1995)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<b>Susan Sarandon</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and </span><b>Tim Robbins</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> were a legendary couple until they ended their 23 years of relationship. Dead Man Walking is one of the best movies of this duo.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Matthew Poncelet is a convicted murderer who has been sentenced to death. He seeks the help of a nun to find some legal help. But it becomes hard for the nun to decide when she hears the story of both sides.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">By the way, if you don’t know who Tim Robbins is, he played </span><b>Andy Dufresne</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> in </span><b>The Shawshank Redemption</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">. </span>\r\n\r\n<b>Personal Recommendation:</b> <b>Infamous (2006)</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">. It is a very underrated movie starring </span><b>Daniel Craig, Sandra Bullock, </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">and </span><b>Toby Jones</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">. </span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kgvbfLNYumU\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Susan Sarandon won the Oscar for </span><b>Best Actress in a Leading Role</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The movie was also nominated in 3 other categories including Best Picture.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><b>Bruce Springsteen </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">sang the OST of this film. The song title was Dead Man Walking. He was also nominated for an Oscar for this in the category of Best Music (Original Song) but lost the award to </span><b>Pocahontas</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> (For the song \"</span><b>Colors of the Wind</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">\").</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the debut feature film of </span><b>Peter Sarsgaard</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">‘Dead Man Walking’ is actually a slang word for </span><b>Death Row inmates</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>06. A Star Is Born (2018)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.6</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Bradley Cooper</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: Lady Gaga, Bradley Cooper, Sam Elliott, Alec Baldwin</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: HBO Max</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6752 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/16Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"A Star Is Born (2018)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Jack used to be a famous singer. But age and his other bad habits were the root cause of the downfall of his career. Then he meets a very talented female singer. Instead of trying to regain his glorious career, he helps the girl to become famous. And in the process, he falls in love with her. But will that be the final nail in the coffin?  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">It is actually a remake movie. I think it got most of its success thanks to </span><b>Lady Gaga</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">. </span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nSbzyEJ8X9E\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This film only won one Oscar in the category of Best Achievement in Music Written for Motion Pictures (Original Song) for the song </span><b>Shallow</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The movie was also nominated in 7 other Oscar categories including Best Picture.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><b>Lady Gaga</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> won the Oscar for this film but she was also nominated in the category of Best Performance by an Actress in a Leading Role.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The award for the Best Achievement in Music Written for Motion Pictures (Original Song) was given to four people for the song Shallow. Two among them were </span><b>Mark Ronson</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and </span><b>Andrew Wyatt</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">. These two men also wrote the super hit song </span><b>Uptown Funk </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">performed by </span><b>Bruno Mars</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The song Shallow has over </span><b>1.1 Billion views</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> on Youtube.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the directorial debut of </span><b>Bradley Cooper.</b></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This film is actually a remake of </span><a href=\"https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0075265/\"><b>A Star Is Born (1976)</b></a><b>.</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>05. Argo (2012)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.7</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Ben Affleck (Also directed Gone Baby Gone, The Town, Live by Night)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: Ben Affleck, Bryan Cranston, Alan Arkin  </b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: HBO Max</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6753 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/17Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"Argo (2012)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Argo is a biography thriller movie set in the late 70s. In 1979, some terrorists attacked the US embassy in Tehran, Iran, and took 6 Americans hostage. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">A CIA agent in disguise as a film producer and a former CIA agent who is now a film makeup artist make a team to rescue the hostages. It is a dangerous mission and they are dangerously desperate as well.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T29kIOXpj6o\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Argo was nominated in a total of 7 categories at the Oscars 2013 and won in 3 of them. The winning awards are for </span><b>Best Motion Picture</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, Best Writing (Adapted Screenplay), and Best Achievement in Film Editing.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><b>George Clooney</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> is one of the three producers of this film.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Yeah, You should watch Quentin Tarantino’s reaction when he lost the best director to Ben Affleck award at the 70th Golden Globe. Here is the link: </span><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S4YdbFwlYLo\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Real Golden Globes</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>04. Ordinary People (1980)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.7</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Robert Redford (Also directed A River Runs Through It, Quiz Show, The Legend of Bagger Vance, Lions for Lambs)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: Donald Sutherland, Mary Tyler Moore, Adam Baldwin</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: Amazon Prime Video</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6754 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/18Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"Ordinary People (1980)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">After the accidental death of the eldest son, the Jarrett family is on the brink of falling apart. The parents don’t know how to deal with the grief, and the youngest son is miserable with survivor’s guilt. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Ordinary people is a family drama that shows how to cope with reality after a sudden loss of a family member. Maybe it is better to be happy apart than being miserable together.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HQKEdiQ79OM\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The movie was nominated in 6 major categories and won in 4 of them, including best picture, best director, Best Actor in a Supporting Role, Best Writing, Screenplay Based on Material from Another Medium (Yeah, it was 1981. The name of the categories were slightly different)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><b>Mary Tyler Moore</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> was nominated in the category of Best Actress in a Leading Role but lost the award to </span><b>Sissy Spacek</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> (</span><b>Coal Miner\'s Daughter</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">). This was the only Oscar nomination in her career. (Rest in peace)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><b>Judd Hirsch </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">was nominated in the category of Best Actor in a Supporting Role but lost the award to </span><b>Timothy Hutton</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> for the same movie. Sadly this is the only Oscar nomination in his career till now. (No, he is not dead)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is the debut film of </span><b>Timothy Hutton</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and the </span><b>directorial debut</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> for Robert Redford. Both of them won Oscars on the first try. (Lucky lucky people)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>03. Jojo Rabbit (2019)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 7.9 </b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Taika Waititi (Also directed What We Do in the Shadows, Thor: Ragnarok, Hunt for the Wilderpeople)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: Sam Rockwell, Scarlett Johansson, Taika Waititi, Alfie Allen, Rebel Wilson</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: HBO Now Amazon Channel</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6755 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/19Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"Jojo Rabbit (2019)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Johannes \"Jojo\" Betzler is a young 10-year old who is very eager to join the German Youth Organization. He idolizes Hitler very much and is ready to do anything for him. But when he gets to know his mother is hiding a young Jewish girl from the Nazzis, he is torn apart to make the decision of which side to choose.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Jojo Rabbit is a war comedy suitable even for children. Taika Waititi is known for starring and directing comedy movies that are exceptional and have quality. And this movie is one of his greatest creations.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tL4McUzXfFI\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The movie was nominated for 6 Oscars including Best Picture, Best Performance by an Actress in a Supporting Role but won in only one category— Best Adapted Screenplay, </span><b>Taika Waititi.</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Fun Facts:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Taika Watiti has also directed the TV Show </span><b>Flight of the Conchords</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and an episode of the Star Wars spin-off </span><b>The Mandalorian</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Taika Waititi, who plays the role of Adolf Hitler in the film, is actually Jewish in real life.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>2. Into the Wild (2007)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 8.1</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Sean Penn (Also Directed The Pledge, The Crossing Guard)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: Emile Hirsch, William Hurt, Jena Malone, Kristen Stewart</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: Netflix</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6756 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/20Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"Into the Wild (2007)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This is another biography movie based on the book of </span><b>Jon Krakauer</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">. Christopher McCandless, who had an outstanding academic life and result gave away all his savings to charity and went on a journey to find the meaning of life. On his journey, he had very bizarre and different experiences. And finally, he finds solace in the arms of nature.</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Sean Penn</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> who is the director of this movie is a two-time Oscar-winning actor. He made his directorial debut in 1991 with the movie </span><b>The Indian Runner </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">(IMDb rating 7.0). This is one of the best movies directed by an actor.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XZG1FzyB8DI\r\n<h3><b>Award and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Into the wild got the nomination in 2 categories at the Oscars 2008— Best Performance by an Actor (Hal Holbrook) in a Supporting Role and Best Achievement in Film Editing. Hal Holbrook lost his Oscar to </span><b>Javier Bardem</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> (No Country for Old Men).</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>01. Braveheart (1995)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating: 8.5</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: Mel Gibson (Also directed The Passion of the Christ, Apocalypto, Hacksaw Ridge)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: Mel Gibson, Sophie Marceau, Patrick McGoohan</b></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform: Starz</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6757 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/21Movies-directed-by-Hollywood-Actor-or-Actress.jpg\" alt=\"Braveheart (1995)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Braveheart is the story of William Wallace who leads an army to save his wife from the tyranny of King Edward I of England. Though IMDb has marked it as a biography movie, there are a lot of scenes in the movie which are not historically accurate. Nonetheless, it is one of the greatest historical movies of all time.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Braveheart is one of the most successful movies of the mid-90s. Mel Gibson really proved to be a successful multitasker. He produced, directed, and acted as the main lead in his movie.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nMft5QDOHek\r\n<h3><b>Awards and Nominations:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">This movie got the nomination in a total of 10 Oscar categories and won in 5 of them. The winning categories are— Best Picture, Best Director, Best Cinematography, Best Effects, Sound Effects Editing, Best Makeup.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>Conclusion:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">So, this was our list of 20 movies in the direction of actors and actresses. If you think we have left out any names, don’t forget to let us know in the comment box below. In the next article, we will try to add your movie with your name as well. Also if you want any kind of list then you can let us know.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Happy Watching!!!</span>','Movies directed by Hollywood Actor or Actress','','publish','open','open','','movies-directed-by-hollywood-actor-or-actress','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/top-7-porn-star-turned-actor-actress/','2021-10-05 15:01:37','2021-10-05 09:31:37','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=6654',0,'post','',0),(6656,15,'2021-07-31 20:00:14','2021-07-31 14:30:14','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6657 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/750x600-5-1.jpg\" alt=\"july movies\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The first half of 2021 has really been </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">good as Bollywood kept us entertained with its major releases like </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Nail Polish, Ramprasad Ki Tehrvi, Ajeeb Dastans, Sherni</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and many more. As we are entering July, the Hindi film industry is once again ready with its box of surprises. So, </span><b>what films came out in July 2021?</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Today, tvfreak.com presents to you a list of </span><b>movies releasing in July 2021 in India</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Read to know more.</span>\r\n<h2><b>9. Haseen Dilruba:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Release date:</strong> 2</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">nd</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> July</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Releasing platform:</strong> Netflix</span></li>\r\n <li><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Cast</strong>: Vikrant Massey, Har