 movie theatres accordingly.</span>\r\n<h2><b>1. Boss Baby: Family Business</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Director: </b>Tom McGrath</li>\r\n <li><b>Cast: </b>Alek Baldwin, Jimmy Kimmel</li>\r\n <li><b>Release Date: </b>1st July 2021</li>\r\n <li><b>Genre: </b>Comedy, Family</li>\r\n <li><b>Production Company: </b>DreamWorks</li>\r\n <li><b>Releasing on Netflix</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This cute and funny animated story by Michael McCullers and narrated by our one and only Tobey Maguire released its first part in 2017 and won the hearts of everyone in no time. You can say that this one is the cutest Hollywood Movies Released In July 2021.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong> DreamWorks Production</strong> along with its excellent team is bringing you the <strong>third franchise</strong> this summer. After the Boss Baby and Boss Baby: Back in Business, this time it revolves around Templeton and his brother who try to create a secret formula that helps them turn into babies for 48 hours. They must by any chance prevent the wicked mastermind who turns the cute little toddler into monsters.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://youtu.be/QPzy8Ckza08\r\n<h2><b>2. Escape Room : Tournament of Champions</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Director: </b>Adam Robitel</li>\r\n <li><b>Cast:</b> Logan Miller, Holland Roden, Taylor Russell</li>\r\n <li><b>Release Date: </b>1st July, 2021</li>\r\n <li><b>Genre: </b>Horror, Psychological</li>\r\n <li><b>Releasing on Theatres</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Following the enormous success of its first franchising escape room Which was released in 2019, the director Adam Robitel along with Maria Melnikhas again come up with its previous team to release another part to the franchise The Escape Room Tournament Of The Champions.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In this sequel, the plot follows the survivors of the first sequel of the lethal game designed by the mysterious charac