/span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Munnabhai MBBS</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> where he has been given very little screen timing. But he portrayed even those characters in ways brilliant enough to leave a mark.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6722 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/2-2.jpg\" alt=\"jimmy Shergill\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Don’t know if we should call it a tragedy for Shergill, but whenever it comes to big-budget movies, in most cases, he has not received the deserved space and time on screen.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Speaking more frankly, he is more of a non-commercial star rather than a commercial one. And this may be one of the reasons why after 2010, he transitioned himself in mostly medium budget films </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fugly, Mukkabaz, Tanu weds Manu</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> which offered him more significant roles and helped him diversify his horizon in the industry. </span>\r\n<h3><b>Career till 2000:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now coming to the beginning of his career, Shergill made his debut in 1996 with the Bollywood movie </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Maachis</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, a film on terrorism. With the movie getting critical acclamation, Shergill’s performance was also noticed. And this got him his first biggest project </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mohabbatein</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> which starred stars like SRK and Big B and Aishwariya Rai.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://youtu.be/bojkkruE6eM\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>(Shergill in a scene from Mohabbatein)</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><b>2000-2010:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the 2000s, he acted in many numerous films - </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">M