e=\"font-weight: 400;\">His latest appearance in Punjabi films is in 2018 in the movie </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Daana Paani</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in which he was seen in the lead role.</span>\r\n<h2><b>The entry in OTTs – Jimmy Shergill web series – Jimmy Shergill TV shows</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Firstly, OTT platforms these days are equivalent to movie theatres and many actors have made comebacks in these platforms. Jimmy Shergill is also one of them. He made his web series debut in 2019 with the ZEE5 original series </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rangbaaz Phirse</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and played the lead role in it.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dgnhX3fyAkM\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Secondly, In 2020, he was seen in Sony liv’s </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Your Honour</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. And finally, as mentioned, in 2021 he played the lead role in </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Collar Bomb</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, a film that is streaming now on Disney+Hotstar. OTTs are giving him the deserved fame and as an audience, we also wish to see him on these digital platforms more often in the future.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Other works</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Besides acting, he also started his film-producing career in 2011. He has produced around 4 Punjabi films including </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dharti, Taur Mittran Di, Saadi Love Story, Rangeelay.</span></i>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Besides this, he has also appeared in many commercials including those of Aliva, Verito, etc.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YideH8OrdYk\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0zR3AjOodho\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em><strong>(watch Jimmy Shergill in these commercials) </strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><b>Awards received</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Being underrated, he had been appreciated for his works at a much lesser rate than he should have been.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Finally, Shergill has been the recipient of a Best Actor award for his performance in Saheb, Biwi Aur Gangster Returns. He won 2 other Best Actor Awards for Punjabi films - </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Melkarade Rabba</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dharti. </span></i>\r\n<h2><b>How much does the actor earn? - Jimmy Shergill net worth</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The earnings of any individual keep on changing with time. Jimmy’s main income comes from films, web series, and commercials. If we believed in the sources then, his net worth as of 2020 is $10 million.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/highest-paid-actors-and-actress-in-bollywood/\"><em><strong>Check out the celebrity earning list here</strong></em></a>\r\n<h2><b>Jimmy, an active social media user? - Jimmy Shergill Instagram</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The actor has a follower base of about 534k on his Instagram account and whenever uploads a post, receives loving comments from fans and admirers. He either posts frequently or takes a break for a long time. His account is full of snaps and videos of his personal as well as professional lives.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jimmy Shergill is indeed one of the gems Bollywood has but sadly the film industry has not been able to understand his worth and utilize him fully. With every passing year, he is evolving himself as an artist. We really wish to see more of his success in the upcoming years.</span>\r\n\r\nSo now you can tell us in the comment box about the Biography of Jimmy Shergill Movies, careers and Other interesting facts if you liked it or looking for more information.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Lastly, this is the content for today. Hope you had a happy reading. See you in the next article. </span>','Biography of Jimmy Shergill Movies, Career and Other interesting facts','','publish','open','open','','biography-of-jimmy-shergill-movies-career-and-other-interesting-facts','','','2021-07-24 01:02:34','2021-07-23 19:32:34','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=6694',0,'post','',0),(6709,13,'2021-08-08 13:36:46','2021-08-08 08:06:46','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6781 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/1.jpg\" alt=\"Viola Davis\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Viola Davis is one of the most <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/top-10-most-beautiful-hollywood-actresses-of-all-time/\">high-profile actresses</a> and the most popular black actress at the present time. In most of Viola Davis movies and tv shows, she has proved her worth by playing many challenging roles in both. She is also the first African American woman to earn the prestigious <strong>Triple Crown of Acting</strong>. So let’s take a look at her personal life, acting career, and some interesting facts.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Early Life and Career</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Viola Davis was born at her grandparent’s farm in the month of August. She is the fifth among six siblings. Just after a few months of her birth, her parents moved to Long Island. Her childhood life was not a bed of roses. She has to deal with serious poverty growing up. She got her high school graduation from <strong>Central Falls High School</strong> which played a very important role to find her passion for acting. In her teenage years, she was attached to the TRIO Foundation. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Viola Davis earned her college degree from <strong>Rhode Island College</strong> in Theatrical Studies. Later she also got admitted to <strong>Juilliard School</strong> in 1989 which contributed to her acting skills a lot.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After graduation, from the year 1992 to early 2000, Viola Davis was involved with various Broadway theaters. In these years, she had the opportunity to take part in some famous stage plays. She also got to work alongside many theater legends.</span>\r\n<h2><b>First Movie</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It was in <strong>1996</strong> when Viola Davis worked on her debut film. The character was very minor. She played the role of a nurse.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6782 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/2.jpg\" alt=\"Viola davis in The Substance of Fire (1996)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h3><b>The Substance of Fire (1996)</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 6.0</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Director:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Daniel J. Sullivan</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sarah Jessica Parker, Timothy Hutton</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After the debut film, Viola played guest stars in some TV shows. She also worked in theater in the meantime alongside seeking a career opportunity in the on-screen industry. She got her first notable role in a <strong>Steven Soderberg</strong> movie called <strong>Out of Sight (1998)</strong>. </span>\r\n<h2><b>Some Basic Information</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6783 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/3.jpg\" alt=\"Viola Davis\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Full Name: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Viola Davis (Yup, this is her actual name)</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Date of Birth: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">August 11, 1965 (Age 55)</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Birthplace: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">St. Matthews, South Carolina, USA</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Zodiac Sign: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Leo</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Height: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">5 feet 5 inches (165 cm)</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Eye Color: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Black</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Hair Color: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Black</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>Her Family</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6784 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/4.jpg\" alt=\"Viola davis family\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6786 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/5.jpg\" alt=\"Viola davis family\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h3><b>Parents:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The name of Viola Davis’s mother is <strong>Mary Alice.</strong> She was a factory worker. Viola’s father’s name is <strong>Dan Davis</strong> who was a horse trainer. </span>\r\n<h3><b>Spouse:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Viola Davis is married to <strong>Julius Tennon</strong>. They got married in June 2003.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Children:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In 2011, the Davis and Tennon couple adopted a daughter from South Carolina. Her name is <strong>Genesis Tennon</strong>.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Viola Davis Movies and TV Shows</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Here are some notable Viola Davis movies and tv shows from her career:</span>\r\n<h3><b>Most of Viola Davis\'s Movies:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Pentagon Wars (1998)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Out of Sight (1998)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Traffic (2000)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Far from Heaven (2002)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Antwone Fisher (2002)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Solaris (2002)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Architect (2006)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Doubt (2008)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Eat Pray Love (2010)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Help (2011)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Won\'t Back Down (2012)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Prisoners (2013)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Get on Up (2014)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Suicide Squad (2016)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fences (2016)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Widows (2018)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ma Rainey\'s Black Bottom (2020)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Most of Viola Davis\'s TV Shows</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">City of Angels (2000)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Century City (2004)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Traveler (2007)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">United States of Tara (2009-2011)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How to Get Away with Murder (2014-2020)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>Notable Characters</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Viola Davis’s most iconic role is probably <strong>Annalise Keating</strong> from the TV series <strong>How to Get Away from Murder</strong>. In this series, she plays the role of a head-strong defense law professor.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Another important role in her career is <strong>Aibileen Clark</strong> from <strong>The Help</strong>. In this movie, she plays a heartbroken mother who is crushed and humiliated day by day due to the acute racism of society. But when an opportunity arises to be a part of an anonymous protest, she takes part in it for the sake of her dead son. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You will see true acting when you Viola Davis in <strong>Fences</strong>. Many people complained she should\'ve won the Oscar as the leading actress. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Viola Davis Fences:</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=e_ZoA_2ZEdM\r\n<h2><b>Awards and Achievements based for </b><b>Viola Davis Movies and TV shows</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As I have mentioned before, Viola Davis is the first Black American woman to win the Triple Crown of Acting. If you don’t know what The <strong>Triple Crown of Acting</strong> is, it is the term used to honor actors and actresses who have proved their excellence in acting in <strong>Theater, TV, and film</strong> by winning competitive Awards in<strong> Tony, Emmy, and Oscar.</strong> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Viola Davis won her first Tony in 2001 in the category of Best Featured Actress in a Play for <strong>King Hedley II.</strong> She again won 9 years later in the category of Best Actress in a Play for <strong>Fences</strong>.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She won her Emmy in the category of <strong>Outstanding Lead Actress in a Drama Series</strong> in 2015 for <strong>How to Get Away with Murder</strong>.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Viola Davis’s first Oscar nomination was in 2009 in the category of Best Performance by an Actress in a Supporting Role for the movie <strong>Doubt (2008)</strong>. She lost the award to <strong>Penélope Cruz</strong> (Vicky Cristina Barcelona).</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The second time she got nominated in the same category was in 2012, for the movie <strong>The Help (2011)</strong>. She lost the award to a co-star of the film <strong>Octavia Spencer</strong>.  </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">They say the third time is the charm. In 2017, Viola got nominated at the Oscar for the third time, again in the same category, and took the award home. This time, it was for the movie <strong>Fences (2016)</strong>.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In 2021, Viola Davis got nominated in the category of Best Performance by an Actress in a Leading Role for <strong>Ma Rainey\'s Black Bottom (2020)</strong>. This time she lost the award to another Triple Crown Of Acting winning actress <strong>Frances McDormand</strong> (<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6sxCFZ8_d84\">Nomadland</a>).</span>\r\n<h2><b>Social Media</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Viola Davis is very active on almost all social platforms. Here are her social media account links—</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Facebook: </b><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/viola.davis\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https://www.facebook.com/viola.davis</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (2.7M followers)</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Twitter: </b><a href=\"https://twitter.com/violadavis?s=20\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https://twitter.com/violadavis?s=20</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (1.7M Followers)</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Instagram: </b><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/violadavis/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https://www.instagram.com/violadavis/</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (8M Followers)</span>\r\n<h2><b>Some Interesting Facts</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><spa