n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Because of Frances McDormand’s father’s job, they had to move a lot. In 1975, she graduated from Monessen High School. She went to Bethany College, West Virginia, and earned her B.A. in Theatrical study. She also has a Master’s degree which she got from the Yale School of Drama. Then she moved to New York where she was roommates with another Oscar-winning actress </span><b>Holly Hunter</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Frances-McDormand—-Biography-Career-and-Some-Interesting-Facts2.webp\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-6864 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Frances-McDormand—-Biography-Career-and-Some-Interesting-Facts2.webp\" alt=\"Frances McDormand— Biography, Career and Some Interesting Facts\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">McDormand’s first job as a professional actor was in the early 80s. It was a play written by </span><b>Derek Walcott</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> called </span><b>In a Fine Castle</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (also known as </span><b>The Last Carnival</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">). Like many famous movie stars, the beginning of her career also started by working as a theater artist. But it wasn’t long before she landed her first-ever movie role. This opportunity came from the famous director duo </span><b>the Coen Brothers</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (Well, they weren’t that famous at that time.). The movie was called</span><b> Blood Simple (1984)</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Frances McDormand First Movie</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Blood Simple (1984)</b></li>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 7.6</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Directors:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Ether Coen and Joel Coen</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Frances McDormand, Dan Hedaya, John Getz</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Genre:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Crime Thriller</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Platform:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> HBO Max</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>Some Basic Information about Frances McDormand</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Full Name: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Frances Louise McDormand</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Date of Birth: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">June 23, 1957 </span></li>\r\n <li><b>Birthplace: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Gibson City, Illinois, USA</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Zodiac Sign: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cancer</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Height: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">5 feet 5 inches (1.65 m)</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Eye Color: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Blue</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Hair Color: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Blonde</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>Family</b></h2>\r\n<h3><b>Frances McDormand\'s Parents: </b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There is not much information about Frances McDormand’s real parents. The McDormand couple that adopted her has no biological child of their own. Her adoptive father Vernon McDormand is a Reverend and her mother Noreen Eloise McDormand was a nurse. Both of them were born in Canada. And this couple adopted 3 children including Frances.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Siblings:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Frances is the youngest of three siblings. Her elder sister Dorothy McDormand is an ordained disciple of Crist Minister (just like their father). And her elder brother’s name is Kenneth McDormand.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Spouse:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Frances McDormand is married to the </span><b>elder Coen Brother, Joel Coen</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. They got married on the first day of April in 1984 and the marriage is still growing strong. They are now undoubtedly one of the power couples in Hollywood.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Frances McDormand\'s Children:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Like her parents, the Coen-McDormand couple has no biological children of their own. In 2004, they adopted a son and named him </span><b>Pedro McDormand Coen.</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Pedro was only a half year old when he was adopted and he is originally from </span><b>Paraguay</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. </span>\r\n<h2><b>Notable Movies and TV Shows</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Frances McDormand has a total of </span><b>64 acting credits</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> according to IMDb in the span of </span><b>36 years of an acting career</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, till now. Let’s look at some of the notable movies and TV shows that she has worked on.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Frances McDormand Movies:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Blood Simple (1984)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Raising Arizona (1987)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mississippi Burning (1988)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Miller\'s Crossing (1990)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fargo (1996)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Primal Fear (1996)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Wonder Boys (2000)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Almost Famous (2000)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Man Who Wasn\'t There (2000)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Something\'s Gotta Give (2003)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">North Country (2005)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Æon Flux (2005)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Burn After Reading (2008)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Three Billboards Outside Ebbing, Missouri (2017)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Nomadland (2020)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>Frances McDormand\'s TV Shows :</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hill Street Blues (1981-1987)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">State of Grace (2001-2004)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Olive Kitteridge (2014)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Good Omens (2019)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>Notable Characters</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The most notable character of Frances McDormand’s career would be her part in </span><b>Fargo</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> where she played the role of a pregnant police officer, desperate to solve a murder case in the frozen Fargo.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The trademark of Frances McDormand is she always played strong female leads or characters with great inner complexity. In </span><a href=\"https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5027774/\"><b>Three Billboards Outside Ebbing, Missouri</b></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, she played the role of a mother who lost her daughter in a murder. In Nomadland, we see a character who is coping with a great loss and not ready to move forward.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Award and Achievements</b></h2>\r\n<h3><b>Frances McDormand - Academy Award:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When it comes to awards, Frances McDormand has plenty. She is a Triple Crown of Acting winner which means she has won Tony, Emmy, and Oscars.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Frances McDormand has a total of </span><b>4 Oscars</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, 3 of them are in the category of Best Leading actress and one as a producer of a Best Pictures. She won her first Oscar in 1997 for the movie Fargo (1996). The second Oscar win was in 2018 for the movie Three Billboards Outside Ebbing, Missouri (2017). The last two Oscar wins are from the movie Nomadland (2020).</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She was nominated three other times all in the category of the Best leading actress for the movies—</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Mississippi Burning </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">(1988)— lost to </span><b>Geena Davis</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (The Accidental Tourist)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>Almost Famous</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (2000)— lost to </span><b>Marcia Gay Harden</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (Pollock)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><b>North Country</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (2005)— lost to </span><b>Rachel Weisz</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (The Constant Gardener)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><b>Prime Time Emmy:</b></h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Frances McDormand has two Emmy wins (Outstanding Lead Actress in a Limited Series or a Movie, and Outstanding Limited Series). Both of them are for </span><b>Olive Kitteridge</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (2014).</span>\r\n<h2><b>Tony:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Frances McDormand got her first Tony nomination for playing the role of </span><b>Stella Kowalski</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in the play </span><b>A Streetcar Named Desire</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in 1988. She lost to Joan Allen.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She won her Tony finally in 2011 for playing the role of </span><b>Margie Walsh</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> in </span><b>Good People</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span>\r\n<h2><b>Frances McDormand on Social Media</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Frances McDormand has no accounts on Facebook, Twitter, or Instagram. So if you are following someone thinking it’s her, you are following a fan page.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Some Interesting Facts</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Every time she was nominated for an Oscar in a supporting role, she lost. But she won every time she was nominated in a leading role.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She gave voice in an episode of </span><b>The Simpsons</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> as a guest star.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">She is the <b style=\"font-style: inherit;\">23rd Thespian</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> to win the Triple Crown of Acting.</span></li>\r\n</ul>','Frances McDormand — Biography, Career and Some Interesting Facts','','publish','open','open','','frances-mcdormand-biography-career-and-some-interesting-facts','','','2021-10-02 17:25:05','2021-10-02 11:55:05','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=6853',0,'post','',0),(982,11,'2020-06-22 12:49:58','2020-06-22 07:19:58','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-985\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/pankaj-tripathi.jpg\" alt=\"Biograpgy\" width=\"679\" height=\"382\" />\r\n<div align=\"justify\"><strong>Pankaj Tripathi</strong> is an Indian film actor. His biography is not simple as it looks like, every big actor has done so much for this position and so he did.</div>\r\n<div align=\"justify\"></div>\r\n<div align=\"justify\">He appeared in <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/\">Bollywood Movie, web series &amp; Tv Shows</a>. He has done mostly Hindi movies and some English movies and He is well known for his acting talent.</div>\r\n<div align=\"justify\">Despite being a big name in the Bollywood industry and having over 50 films and more than 60 television shows to his credit, actor Pankaj Tripathi is a very humble person.</div>\r\n<div align=\"justify\"></div>\r\n<div align=\"justify\">He debuted in Bollywood in 2004 with Abhishek Bachchan in the movie Run and became famous as an actor with the role of a supporting character in Gangs of Wasseypur. If we tell you about his latest film update then it is <a title=\"Extraction (2020 film)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extraction_(2020_film)\" rel=\"nofollow\">Extraction</a> with Chris Hemsworth, Rudhraksh Jaiswal, and Randeep Hooda.</div>\r\n<div align=\"justify\"></div>\r\n<div align=\"justify\">Instagram Account: @pankajTripathi\r\nTwitter Account: @tripathiipankaj\r\n<strong>Full Name</strong>: Pankaj Tripathi\r\n<strong>Date of birth</strong>: 5th September 1976\r\n<strong>Age:</strong> 44 (as in 2020)\r\n<strong>Height</strong>: 5’10”\r\n<strong>Wife: </strong>Mridula\r\n<strong>Colour:</strong> Brownish</div>\r\n<div align=\"justify\">\r\n\r\nAs everyone knows he is a very down to earth person and loves his family very much. Therefore he regularly visits his family. Even on his twitter, there is a picture of him with his family.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-990 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/pankaj-tripathi-family-1.jpg\" alt=\"Family and loved ones\" width=\"640\" height=\"359\" />\r\n<h2>The early life of Pankaj Tripathi:</h2>\r\nHe was born in Beland Barauli Gopalganj Bihar. His father is a farmer and a religious person. In childhood, he joined RSS. Besides that, he did not know much about the film and acting as if in his house of no television. And he was also married on 15 January 2004, Now he has a daughter.\r\n\r\nPankaj Tripathi started acting at the age of 12 to 14. He performed as a girl artist in the <strong>“Chhath Festival”</strong> in his village. In other words, he was so passionate about acting from starting. He wan to the <strong>National School of Drama Magadh University</strong> for Acting. When he was in Patna studying he joined ABVP and started participating in the youth student\'s movements.\r\n\r\nHe was a leader and speaker too in his college days. He was also good at sports. Mr. Tripathi represented his college in sports competitions like <strong>100-meter spirit</strong> and <strong>High jump</strong>. He has a degree in <strong>Hotel Management</strong> and he worked as a cook for two years in Maurya in Patna. It was there in Patna that he became more attracted to acting and joined the theatres and became fascinated with acting.\r\n<h2>Career beginning - Pankaj Tripathi:</h2>\r\nIn 1995, he first appeared in a role in a play of Brims Sahni\'s story of <strong>Leela Nandlal</strong> directed by Vijay Kumar. After 1996, Pankaj Tripathi became a theatre artist and acted for theatre for more than 4 years.\r\n\r\nHe appeared in the National School of Drama for acting and got selected there. In 2004 he moved to Mumbai to fulfill his dreams in the film industry.\r\n\r\nFrom 2004 to 2010 he appeared in many roles in television as well as movies also. He also did some commercial ads like <strong>Tata Tea</strong>. In 2010 he got a role in <em><strong>Gulal</strong></em> in Star Plus.\r\n\r\nWhile he was shooting for Gulal the tv serial he received a call from Mukesh Chhabra for an audition for <strong>Anurag Kashyap</strong>\'s film <em><strong>Gangs of Wasseypur</strong></em>. Initially, Anurag Kashyap was not happy with Pankaj\'s audition but after convincing Mukhesh he gave the role of Sultan to Pankaj Tripathi.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-991 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/gangs-of-wasseypur.jpg\" alt=\"gangs of wasseypur movie\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" />\r\n\r\nThough he started his career in Bollywood in the year 2004 he got recognition as an actor and took the attention of the audience from the movie Gangs of Wasseypur where his acting talent appreciated by both critics and audience. After that Pankaj Tripathi gave an outstanding performance in his various movies. He won the <strong>National Film Award</strong> for special mention for his role in Newton that was India\'s official entry to the Oscar.\r\n<h2>Film Career- Pankaj Tripathi:</h2>\r\n<h3>Pankaj Tripathi during (2004-2010):</h3>\r\nAs he debuted his first film in Bollywood in the year 2004 in the movie Run. From 2004 to 2010 he played many roles in television as well as in films also like Apaharan (2005), Omkara (2006), Dharm (2007), Mithiya (2008), Shaurya(2008), Chintu (2009)  Aakrosh and Raavan in 2010.\r\n<h4>Dharm(2007) movie:</h4>\r\nIn this film, Pankaj Tripathi was starred with <strong>Supriya Pathak</strong>. In this film, he played a supporting role in Surya Prakash. This film won the National award for the best feature film on National integration. The director of the film was Bhavna Talwar. It was her first movie. This film is based on the true meaning of religion.\r\n<h3>Pankaj Tripathi during (2011-2020):</h3>\r\nHe did his next movie <em><strong>Chillar Party</strong></em> in 2011. In 2012 after <i>Agneepath</i> he did his most famous movie <em><strong>Gangs of Wasseypur. </strong></em>This year made him recognition as a quality actor in Bollywood.\r\n<h4>Movies in 2013:</h4>\r\nIn the year 2013, he came back to the screen with many characters in several movies. Fukrey was a Comedy movie that hit the Cinema very well. The box office collection was also good.  Pankaj Tripathi gave a huge contribution to these movies. He is a peon in this movie. He also has some huge connections to any problems. Pankaj was able to leak the papers as well. He is having a big role in these movies.\r\n<table class=\"wikitable sortable jquery-tablesorter\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><i>ABCD: Any Body Can Dance</i></td>\r\n<td>Vardha Bhai</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><i>Rangrezz</i></td>\r\n<td>Brijbihari Pande</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><i>Fukrey</i></td>\r\n<td>Pandit</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><i>Anwar Ka Ajab Kissa</i></td>\r\n<td>Amol</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><i>Maazii</i></td>\r\n<td>Rathiji</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><i>Janta v/s Janardan – Bechara Aam Aadmi</i></td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><i>Doosukeltha</i></td>\r\n<td>Dilleeswara Rao</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h4>2014:</h4>\r\nPankaj Tripathi appeared in one movie <em><strong>Gundey</strong></em> starred with <strong>Arjun Kapoor, Ranveer Singh,</strong> and <strong>Priyanka Chopra.</strong>\r\n<h4>2015:</h4>\r\nThis year he also came back with several films. The audience has seen him in Sharukh Khan and Kajol\'s comeback movie <em><strong>Dilwale. </strong></em>He also appeared in Manjhi – The Mountain Man, Masaan, Life Biryani.\r\n\r\nBut even after playing so many different roles in many <strong>movies and TV</strong> &amp; Web series his favorite movies as an actor remains ‘Masaan’.\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AptEenO0Yho[/embedyt]\r\n<h4>2016:</h4>\r\nIn 2016 he appeared in only two movies Nil Battery Sannate &amp; Global Baba and Mango Dreams. Mango Dreams was an English Movie.\r\n<h4>2017:</h4>\r\nThis year we saw him in different films like Fukrey Returns, Julie 2 Newton Bareilly ki Barfi Gurgaon Munna Michael Anaarkali of Aarah Coffee with D. His character was becoming big and interesting. Check out these movies with an interesting character. In these big movies, he did an outstanding performance. When an actor is provided sufficient time then he can not be neglected and he has gone very far away from that situation.\r\n<table class=\"wikitable sortable jquery-tablesorter\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><i>Coffee with D</i></td>\r\n<td>Girdhari</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><i>Anaarkali of Aarah</i></