ck Colombian accent. She earned $500,000 per episode in <strong>Modern Family</strong>. Sofia also has her own entertainment business which is now a multi-million company.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Conclusion</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If I make a combined list of all the <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/bollywood-actors-ranking-as-per-their-net-worth/\">Highest Paid</a> Hollywood Actresses, the highest-paid actress Sofia Vergara on this list will be the only woman on that list and that also in the 9th position. For the past decade, women have been raising their voices about the sexism they are facing in the industry.</span>\r\n\r\n[irp posts=\"1485\" name=\"Bollywood Actors Ranking as per their Net Worth\"]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">How, in interviews, the actresses are asked about their makeup and diet and their male co-stars are asked about all the serious stuff. At first, many authority figures even laughed at the women who broke the silence about this important issue. Especially after the Harvey Weinstein incident, things are starting to change but at a very slow pace. Hopefully, in the future, we will be able to achieve absolute equality between men and women in the film industry. </span>','Top 10 Highest Paid Hollywood Actresses of 2020 | English Actresses','','publish','open','open','','top-10-highest-paid-hollywood-actresses-of-2020-english-actresses','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/bollywood-actors-ranking-as-per-their-net-worth/','2021-03-24 13:42:54','2021-03-24 08:12:54','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5531',0,'post','',0),(5550,13,'2021-03-13 21:31:19','2021-03-13 16:01:19','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5553 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lee-Pace—-Biography-Movies-and-TV-Shows-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Lee Pace is an American actor mostly known for playing the iconic Middle Earth Elven King </span><strong><i>Thranduil</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">the <strong>Guardian of the Galaxy</strong></span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> villain Ronan. Yes, most of his characters require heavy makeup and wigs. So, you may have seen his movies without realizing it was him. He is an outstanding actor and has the power to make the most unknown bizarre characters relatable.</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> </span>\r\n<h2><b>Early Life</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Lee Pace and his family had to move quite a lot because his father used to work in an oil company. A great part of his childhood was spent in the Middle East country, Saudia Arabia. He attended high school in Houston, Texas. There he first discovered his love for acting.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">He was involved working at the local theatre so much that he quit high school. But he did finish high school later, and then he got admitted to The Juilliard School in the department of Fine Arts (Drama). So Lee entered college in 1997. There he participated in various plays, playing the leading roles, and made his acting skills even better. Lee graduated in 2001 with a BFA degree. </span>\r\n<h2><b>Some Basic Information About Lee Pace - Biography</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>Full Name: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Lee Grinner Pace</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Date of Birth: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">March 25, 1979 (42)</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Birth Place: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Chickasha, Oklahoma, USA</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Zodiac Sign: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Aries</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Hair Color: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Dark brown</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Eye Color: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Brown</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Height: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">6 feet 5 inch (196 cm)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>Family:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"><strong>Mother:</strong> Charlotte Pace, A high school teacher</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"><strong>Father:</strong> James Roy Pace, An engineer</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Siblings: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Sally Pace (Sister), William Pace (Younger Brother)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5556 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lee-Pace—-Biography-Movies-and-TV-Shows-4.jpg\" alt=\"parents\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h2><b>Beginning of Acting Career</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Lee Pace has been involved in theatre acting from a very young age. His first TV appearance was in an episode of the TV show called</span><strong><i> Law &amp; Order: Special Victims Unit</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> (season 3, episode 18), where he played an episodic character named <strong>Benjamin Tucker.</strong> Lee was 22 years old then.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">His first breakthrough was in a TV movie called </span><strong><i>Soldier\'s Girl</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> where he played the role of a transgender woman who fell in love with a military solder. The movie is <strong>based on the real-life story</strong> of Barry Winchell (the soldier) who lost his life because of falling in love with a transgender woman.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">After this movie, Lee worked full time in a TV show called <strong>Wonderfalls (2004)</strong>, though the character he played was secondary. After that, he played some secondary and minor characters in many famous movies like The White Countess, Infamous, The Good Shepherd, etc.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Lee Pace Debut film: Soldier’s Girl (2003)</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li><b>IMDb Rating:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> 7.9 (4611 votes)</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Director: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Frank Pierson (Also directed A Star Is Born (1976))</span></li>\r\n <li><b>Star Cast:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> Lee Pace, Troy Garity, Andre Braugher (You may know him as Captain Raymond Holt in Brooklyn Nine-Nine)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Lee Pace in Soldier’s Girl</strong></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5555 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lee-Pace—-Biography-Movies-and-TV-Shows-3.jpg\" alt=\"Soldoer’s Girl\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">A/N: I have watched the movie. And I recommend everyone to watch this movie. Lee Pace’s acting was a piece of art in this film.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Lee Pace Movies and TV Shows</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Let’s look at the movies and TV shows Lee pace has participated in his career till now:</span>\r\n<h2><b>Lee Pace Movie List:</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Soldier’s Girl (2003)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The White Countess (2005)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Infamous (2006)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Fall (2006)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Good Shepherd (2006) (This movie is directed by Robert De Niro, you know.)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Miss Pettigrew Lives for a Day (2008)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Possession (2009)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">A Single Man (2009)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">When in Rome (2010)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Ceremony (2010)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Resident (2011)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Lincoln (2012)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Twilight Saga: Breaking Dawn - Part 2 (2012)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Hobbit: The Desolation of Smaug (2013)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Hobbit: The Battle of the Five Armies (2014)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Guardians of the Galaxy (2014)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Program (2015)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">The Book of Henry (2017)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Driven (2018)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Captain Marvel (2019)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>The Fall, Lee Pace Movie trailer:</strong></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rEi-v6aJD7Q[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<strong>Lee Pace Guardian of the Galaxy (Ronan the Accuser)</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5557 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lee-Pace—-Biography-Movies-and-TV-Shows-5.jpg\" alt=\"Lee Pace Guardian of the Galaxy (Ronan the Accuser)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n<h3><strong>Possession Lee Pace Movie trailer:</strong></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XyRL4FKwrxw[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<strong>Lee Pace as Thranduil in The Hobbit: The Desolation of Smaug</strong>\r\n<h3><b>TV Shows Lee Pace actively played roles:</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Wonderfalls (2004)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Pushing Daisies (2007-2009)</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Halt and Catch Fire (2014-2017)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Lee Pace also appeared as a guest star in an episode of </span><strong><i>The Mindy Project</i></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> (season 3, episode 13, San Francisco Bae).</span>\r\n<h2><b>Lee Pace New Movie and Upcoming TV shows:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">There is no news about Lee starring in a new movie, but he is currently working on the TV series </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Foundation</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, <strong>based on the classic Sci-Fi novel</strong> franchisee of Issac Asimov. </span>\r\n<h2><b>Awards and Achievements</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Lee Pace got the nomination in the <strong>Golden Globes two times</strong>. The first one was in 2004 in the category of</span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> Best Performance by an Actor in a Supporting Role in a Series, Mini-series, or Motion Picture Made for Television</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> for Soldier’s Girl. And the second time was in 2008 for Pushing Daisies in the category of</span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> Best Performance by an Actor in a Television Series - Comedy or Musical. </span></i>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">He also got an<strong> Emmy</strong> <strong>nomination</strong> for Pushing Daisies in the category of Outstanding Lead Actor in a Comedy Series.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Personal life</b></h2>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5554 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lee-Pace—-Biography-Movies-and-TV-Shows-2.jpg\" alt=\"Lee Pace— Biography, Movies, and TV Shows (2)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Lee is a very private person. He does not like to talk about his personal life to the media. But it has been confirmed that he is <strong>bisexual</strong> by an interview where he confessed to date both men and women.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">He is good friends with Sarah Michelle Gellar, Matt Bomer, and Evangeline Lilly.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Lee Pace Net Worth - $5 Million</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Lee Pace has a net worth of $5 Million. He also has a farm in the upstate of New York, where he raises chicken and other farm animals.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://twitter.com/Rachael_Conrad/status/1230930181352718342?s=20\r\n<h2><b>Some Fun Facts</b></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">His hobby is <strong>travelling</strong> and <strong>skydiving</strong>.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">He is a <strong>teetotaller</strong>. He does not smoke or drink in real life.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Though he played Thranduil, Legolas’s father in The Hobbit, Lee is actually two years younger than Orlando Bloom. </span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Lee received an approach to play the role of Will Graham in the TV series Hannibal. He declined the offer because he was at that time doing a Broadway play.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Director Bharat Nalluri had to kick him out of the set of <strong>Miss Pettigrew Lives for a Day (2008)</strong> because Ammy Adams found him to be <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/most-handsome-indian-actors-in-bollywood-updated-list-2021/\">too handsome</a> and was very distracted. </span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">He was roommates with Anthony Mackie in college.</span></li>\r\n <li style=\"font-weight: 400\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Despite being very tall and handsome, Lee is quite shy in front of the media.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><b>Social media accounts of Lee Pace:</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Twitter:</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://twitter.com/leepace\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/Lee-Pace-739375939459344\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Click here for Official Facebook Page</span></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Lee Pace Biography, Tweets, Net Worth, Movies and TV Shows','','publish','open','open','','lee-pace-biography-tweets-net-worth-movies-and-tv-shows','','\nhttps://www.thetvfreak.com/most-handsome-indian-actors-in-bollywood-updated-list-2021/','2021-08-12 07:37:52','2021-08-12 02:07:52','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5550',0,'post','',0),(5559,12,'2021-03-14 11:59:43','2021-03-14 06:29:43','<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5561 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Mohammad-Zeeshan-Aayub-biography-1.jpg\" alt=\"Mohammad Zeeshan Aayub biography (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Being underrated in the competitive <a href=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/category/bollywood/\">world of Bollywood</a> has its own advantages. You never typecast as a hero or villain and get to play challenging character roles that make people notice you prove your worth as an artist. Mohammed Zeeshan Ayyub is one such name who has entertained us with versatile roles in numerous movies in all these years. Today let’s get to know a little more about the inspiring journey of the talented actor.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Early life - Biography</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ayyub’s birth and growing up was in the capital city of Delhi. From the nationally reputed educational institution, Kendriya Vidyalaya he completed his school education.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He was good in the field of academics which made him get admission to one of the best colleges of Delhi University, the Kirori Mal College. He graduated with flying colours with a Bachelor’s degree in Science. It was during those college days when the love for acting gradually increased in Ayyub.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In KMC he was an active part of the college’s theatre society and participated in countless plays in 3 years. In an interview, the actor jokingly said that thou</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">gh he wanted to pursue a B.Sc degree, by the end of college he had been a theatre graduate instead.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5562 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Mohammad-Zeeshan-Aayub-biography-2.jpg\" alt=\"Mohammed Zeeshan Ayyub\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His passion took him to the glamorous filmy world with Mumbai post his graduation days. However, reality struck soon when he realized that there was more need to sharpen his acting skills and that he needed to work hard. Ayyub was losing hope but still joined the National School of Drama (NSD) for an acting course. The year was 2006.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Mohammad Zeeshan Ayyub age and physique</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Born in 1984, Zeeshan is currently about 37 years old. With a height of about 5’10” and a camera-friendly face, he has the perfect features of an actor.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Mohammad Zeeshan Ayyub family and friends</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The actor is from a Muslim family, though reportedly his mom has been a devotee of Hinduism. Ayyub is not the single child of his parents. He has a brother as well as a sister.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Though the family had no connections with the biggies of the silver screen, both his parents had been reputed theatre artists and had performed in many plays.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Regarding his friends, the actor is very close to actresses like Swara Bhaskar and Sonam Kapoor and even tagg them as ‘best friends’; at least Mohammad Zeeshan Ayyub Instagram gave us such glimpses.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5563 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Mohammad-Zeeshan-Aayub-biography-3.jpg\" alt=\"Mohammed Zeeshan Ayyub friends\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He had also often been seen spending quality time with his co-actors.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5564 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Mohammad-Zeeshan-Aayub-biography-4.jpg\" alt=\"Mohammad Zeeshan Aayub biography (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5565 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Mohammad-Zeeshan-Aayub-biography-5.jpg\" alt=\"Mohammad Zeeshan Aayub biography (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-5566 size-full\" src=\"https://www.thetvfreak.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Mohammad-Zeeshan-Aayub-biography-6.jpg\" alt=\"Mohammad Zeeshan Aayub biography (1)\" width=\"750\" height=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><b>Beginning of the journey</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Even after completing the acting course at NSD, Aayub didn’t become limelight overnight. That was just the beginning of his struggle. Firstly, as a director in an acting school and then he also worked as an acting teacher in an institute in New York. Finally, it was the year 2011 when stars came in favour of the actor and he got cast in a highly appreciated Hindi film.</span>\r\n<h2><b>Mohammad Zeeshan Ayyub TV shows</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Okay…so before moving to his Bollywood career, let’s know about his struggling days a little more. As an actor, Ayyub’s journey started with a small screen. In 2008, we saw him in a Doordarshan serial </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Kiuki Jeena Isika Naam Haai.</span></i>\r\n<h3><strong>Watch Ayyub in an episode from Kyuki Jeena Iska Naam Haai</strong></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uLCZXwG5WeE[/embedyt]\r\n<h2>Mohammed Zeeshan Ayyub<b> Movies and Reviews</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ayyub’s debut on the big screen was with the ‘inspired from true events’ thriller </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Noone Killed Jessica,</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> where his mind-blowing performance in a negative role had been the show stealer despite the presence of senior actors like Vidya Balan and Rani Mukherjee.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Ayyub’s intense scene from Noone killed Jessica</strong></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=peZ7eeMariM[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Over the years, he somewhat got the tag of ‘hero’s best friend or brother’ for getting type cast in such roles in many films including </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Jannat 2 Mere Brother Ki Dulhan, Zero, Raess, Ranjhaana, Shahid, Tubelight</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. However, he didn’t pay heed to such stuff and continued to explore various roles in different films. It was his dedicated performances that made him gain appreciation from the audience as well as critics.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Ayyub’s best dialogues from Ranjhaana</strong></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Pfj3geVE2gs[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, in recent years, the actor has been successful in breaking his stereotypical image by grabbing some significant roles in some movies. These include the antagonistic role of Sadashiv in the historical drama </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Manikarnika: The Queen of Jhansi</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">; the anti-hero, Nishad of </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Article 15</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">; the ex-army officer of </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mission Mangal</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">; the biased PTI teacher of the sports drama </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Chaalang</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. These are, in fact, fall in the category of his most loved performances.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As a lead character, Ayyub appeared in the 2017 film </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sameer</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> which failed to gain popularity and since then we had no more seen him portraying the main character in Hindi movies.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>watch Ayyub’s full movie Sameer</strong></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jF40WOp-98A[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">His other works in Bollywood include </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Maazi, Raja Natwarlal, Dolly Ki Doli, Phantom, Tanu weds Manu and its sequel, All is Well.</span></i>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">watch what Zeeshan said regarding working with the 3 Khans of Bollywood</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=h7A9ToTEKQA[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Now fans are waiting to see him in the upcoming film </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Atrangi Re</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> along with actors like Akshay Kumar and Dhanush.</span>\r\n<h2>Mohammed Zeeshan Ayyub<b> web series</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">OTTs proved to be the safest place, giving this extremely talented actor his deserved recognition as a protagonist. He made his web series debut last year with the SonyLiv original, </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A Simple Murder</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. He played the character of a struggling entrepreneur trying to rise in the eyes of his wife whom he loves a lot.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">watch how a well-known YouTube channel praised Ayyub’s A Simple Murder</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J-4xhf0y_Xw[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In the same year, he rose to more fame by playing the controversial character of Shiva Shekhar in the Amazon Prime political thriller series, </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Taandav.</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Haters tried to point out how the actor tried to show Hindu Gods in a bad light. Ignoring all of that, if we focus on the portrayal of his character, as viewers we will understand how multifaceted Ayyub is as an actor.</span>\r\n<h3><strong>Watch Ayyub as Shiva from Tandav</strong></h3>\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=e1Ae5xUZATo[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Other works</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We saw Zeeshan in a very heart-touching advertisement for OYO rooms. Every one of you must see it to move to tears.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ayyub’s OYO commercial</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LZf3sekxQio[/embedyt]\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">He had also been part of a short film – </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Guess Pyar Se</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ayyub’s short film – Guess Pyar Se</span>\r\n\r\n[embedyt] https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XWZIAE7mWoU[/embedyt]\r\n<h2><b>Achievements</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">All through his career, Ayyub had been successful in becoming one of the most appreciated actors. But it’s really sad that a talented gem like him had not received a single award for any of his memorable performances. For </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">No One Killed Jessica</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, he gained 2 nominations. For his comic role in </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ranjhaana</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> also he was nominated twice but won none, unfortunately.</span>\r\n<h2>Mohammed Zeeshan Ayyub <b>Relationship status</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Heartbreaking to know that this handsome talented actor is not at all single! Okay, jokes apart, he fell in love with TV actress Rasika Agashe in 2006-07. They both were enrolled in NSD to learn acting and most probably it is where their story began. Soon, in 2007, even before Ayyub made his Bollywood debut, the couple tied the knot. For the last almost 14 years they are leading a successful, happy married life. They are often together, spending time with each other despite their busy schedules.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> In 2015 they were blessed with a sweet daughter whom they named Raahi.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Last year when #BoycottTanishq became trending and was accused of promoting love Jihad in an advertisement, Agashe was one of those who bravely raised her voice against the wrong. She shared her baby shower pictures on her social media handle and expressed her opinions regarding how the public should be aware of the Special Marriage Act. After all, it’s all about love when it comes to marriage and the Zeeshan-Agashe duo has proved it. They look really adorable with each other.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rashika Agashe shared her Baby Shower picture to voice against #BoycottTanishq</span>\r\n<h2>Mohammed Zeeshan Ayyub net worth - $1-$5 Million</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As of 2020, the actor had a net worth of $1-$5 Million.</span>\r\n<h2><b>The Political is personal!</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Zeeshan had always been one of those actors involving himself and voicing strong opinions against any political wrong or such scenarios – be it CAA protests, the arrest of JNU activist Umar Khalid or even the most recent farmers’ protest. He had even joined the farmers in their protest at the Singhu border and supported them.</span>\r\n\r\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/CIqM374JF-1/?igshid=12yvpenq70zii\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nhttps://www.instagram.com/tv/B791qdXJEEW/?igshid=1vfuw3fcjhe7y\r\n<h2><b>Conclusion</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It is high time when talents like Mohammad Zeeshan Ayyub must not get wasted in Bollywood. He has proved his capability many times and deserves to be a lot more than what he is today. Ayyub has the potential of being a leading Bollywood actor and hence we wish him all the luck for his future endeavors.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Finally, this is our content for today. Hope you liked it. See you in the next article. For regular updates of our website, don’t forget to follow us on social media.</span>','Mohammed Zeeshan Ayyub Bio, Relationships, Movies and Tv Shows','','publish','open','open','','mohammed-zeeshan-ayyub-bio-relationships-movies-and-tv-shows','','','2021-03-24 13:41:36','2021-03-24 08:11:36','',0,'https://www.thetvfreak.com/?p=5559',0,'post','',0);
